  ('videocapture', 'VideoCapture', 'VideoCapture MCP provides AI assistants with access to webcams and video sources through OpenCV, enabling image capture and camera control capabilities. The server exposes tools for capturing still images, managing camera connections, adjusting video properties like brightness and resolution, and performing basic image transformations such as horizontal flipping. Developed by 13rac1, this implementation focuses on still image capture only (no video streaming) and is designed to integrate seamlessly with Claude Desktop, making it ideal for AI applications that need to analyze real-world objects or environments through webcam imagery.', '@13rac1', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/13rac1/videocapture-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/13rac1.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.891889+00:00'),
  ('doubao-image-video', 'Doubao Image Video', 'Provides image and video generation capabilities through integration with ByteDance''s Doubao platform. Supports image creation using Seedream models with customizable sizes and reference image guidance, video generation with configurable duration, frame rate, and resolution using Seedance models, and task status querying for asynchronous video operations.', '@156554395', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/156554395/doubao-image-video-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/156554395.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.891928+00:00'),
  ('qr-codes', 'QR Codes', 'This client implementation allows users to retrieve the latest proxy nodes and generate QR codes for them. It utilizes the Model Context Protocol SDK and the QRCode library to fetch proxy information and create visual representations. The tool is designed to simplify access to up-to-date proxy data, making it useful for applications that require quick and easy proxy configuration.', '@1595901624', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/1595901624/qrcode-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1595901624.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.891949+00:00'),
  ('jira', 'Jira', 'This Jira MCP server, developed using TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, provides AI assistants with a standardized interface to interact with Jira''s REST API. It offers tools for managing issues, including creation, listing, updating, and deletion, as well as adding comments. The server abstracts the complexities of Jira''s API, handling authentication and request formatting. It''s particularly valuable for AI systems focused on project management and issue tracking, enabling use cases such as automated task creation, status updates, and project overview generation. The implementation includes error handling for common Jira-specific scenarios and formats issue information for easy consumption by AI assistants.', '@1broseidon', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/1broseidon/mcp-jira-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1broseidon.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.891980+00:00'),
  ('1mcp-agent', '1MCP Agent', '1MCP (One MCP) is a unified server implementation that aggregates multiple MCP servers into a single interface, reducing system resource usage and simplifying configuration management across different AI assistants. Developed by William Xu, it supports both stdio and SSE transport methods, handles dynamic configuration reloading without server restart, and enables filtering of servers by tags. The implementation allows AI tools like Claude Desktop, Cursor, Cherry Studio, and Roo Code to share access to the same underlying MCP servers, making it particularly valuable for users working with multiple AI assistants that need access to the same tools and resources.', '@1mcp-app', 'development', 'Unknown', 390, 'https://github.com/1mcp-app/agent', '@1mcp/agent', 10636, 'https://github.com/1mcp-app.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892011+00:00'),
  ('1panel', '1Panel', 'MCP-1Panel is a server implementation that provides AI assistants with direct access to 1Panel server management capabilities. It exposes tools for managing websites, databases, SSL certificates, and applications through a standardized interface. Built with Go, it supports both stdio and SSE transport modes, authenticates with 1Panel via access tokens, and handles API requests through a client that manages error states appropriately. This implementation is particularly valuable for server administrators who want to monitor system information, deploy applications like MySQL and OpenResty, or manage web infrastructure directly through conversational AI without switching contexts.', '@1panel-dev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 142, 'https://github.com/1panel-dev/mcp-1panel', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1panel-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892022+00:00'),
  ('mongodb', 'MongoDB', 'This MongoDB MCP server implementation enables interaction with MongoDB databases through the Model Context Protocol. It utilizes TypeScript and the MongoDB driver to provide a bridge between MCP clients and MongoDB operations. The server is designed to run in various environments, including Windows (Git Bash and WSL) and Unix-like systems, making it versatile for different development setups. It''s particularly useful for projects that require seamless integration of MongoDB capabilities into MCP-based workflows.', '@1rb', 'databases', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/1rb/mongo-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1rb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892033+00:00'),
  ('1stdibs', '1stDibs', 'Provides access to 1stDibs marketplace for browsing and searching vintage, antique, and contemporary furniture, home decor, art, jewelry, watches, and fashion. 1stDibs is a leading online marketplace connecting buyers with curated sellers of extraordinary design items.', '@unknown', 'search', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.1stdibs.com', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892065+00:00'),
  ('ali-oss', 'Ali OSS', 'OSS-MCP is a server implementation that provides a bridge between AI assistants and Object Storage Services (OSS), specifically Ali OSS. Developed by 1yhy, this TypeScript-based server enables file operations through a RESTful API, allowing assistants to upload, download, list, and manage files in cloud storage. The implementation leverages the ali-oss SDK and Express framework to handle requests efficiently, with environment-based configuration for secure credential management. It''s particularly valuable for use cases requiring document management, media file handling, or backup operations without leaving the assistant interface.', '@1yhy', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/1yhy/oss-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1yhy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892094+00:00'),
  ('figma-context', 'Figma Context', 'Figma-Context-MCP is a server implementation that bridges AI assistants with the Figma design platform, enabling direct access to Figma file data through the MCP protocol. It transforms complex Figma API responses into simplified, structured design information that includes layout properties, styling, and text content, making it easier for AI assistants to understand and reason about design files. The server provides tools for retrieving complete Figma files or specific nodes, downloading images, and processing design hierarchies - making it particularly valuable for design review workflows, code generation from designs, and collaborative design discussions.', '@1yhy', 'development', 'Unknown', 19, 'https://github.com/1yhy/figma-context-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1yhy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892122+00:00'),
  ('cryptoweather', 'CryptoWeather', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with access to CryptoWeather''s Bitcoin price prediction signals through four specialized tools for retrieving current signals, trading recommendations, performance metrics, and signal methodology information. Built by the CryptoWeather Team using Python with FastMCP and requests, it connects to the CryptoWeather API at cryptoweather.xyz to deliver AI-powered Bitcoin trading insights including position clarity, profit information, and detailed trading advice with buy/sell/hold recommendations. The implementation includes configurable debug mode and API endpoint settings through Smithery configuration, making it valuable for traders seeking AI-driven Bitcoin market analysis, developers building cryptocurrency trading bots, and AI assistants requiring programmatic access to quantitative trading signals without manual market research.', '@2051project', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/2051project/cryptoweather', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2051project.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892156+00:00'),
  ('skillhub', 'SkillHub', 'SkillHub converts Claude-style skills into standard MCP tools, enabling any MCP-compatible client to discover and use them. It supports flexible skill packaging including nested directories, .zip archives, and .skill files, with multiple transport options including stdio, HTTP, and SSE.', '@214140846', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/214140846/skillhub-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/214140846.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892186+00:00'),
  ('magic-21st-dev', 'Magic (21st.dev)', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to the 21st.dev/magic API, enabling AI assistants to interact with frontend development tasks. Developed by sergeibynas, it offers tools for working with frontend code directly from IDEs like Cursor, WindSurf, and VSCode with Cline. The server is built using TypeScript and integrates with the Model Context Protocol SDK. It focuses on secure API key management and is designed to streamline frontend development workflows. The implementation is particularly useful for AI applications that need to automate or assist with frontend coding tasks, offering a unique approach to AI-assisted web development.', '@21st-dev', 'development', 'Unknown', 4380, 'https://github.com/21st-dev/magic-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/21st-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892213+00:00'),
  ('magic-21st-dev-ui-generator', 'Magic (21st.dev UI Generator)', 'Magic MCP Server provides a bridge to 21st.dev''s Magic API, enabling AI assistants to generate UI components and search for logos. Developed by serafim@21st.dev, this TypeScript implementation offers three specialized tools: creating UI components from descriptions, fetching existing components for inspiration, and searching for company logos in various formats (SVG, JSX, TSX). The server authenticates with the 21st.dev API using an API key and is designed to be easily integrated with AI clients like Cline and Windsurf through Smithery. Ideal for developers who want to quickly generate or find UI components and brand assets without leaving their AI assistant workflow.', '@oyasimi1209', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/oyasimi1209/magic-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/oyasimi1209.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892251+00:00'),
  ('social-media', 'Social Media', 'This MCP server provides team-based social media functionality for AI agents, enabling them to authenticate, create posts with tags and threading support, and read posts with filtering capabilities through integration with an external social media API. Built by 2389-research using TypeScript with a FastAPI Python backend, it features session management for multi-agent environments, comprehensive rate limiting and authentication middleware, structured logging with Prometheus metrics, and Docker deployment support. The implementation uses a global session approach for MCP connections, supports cursor-based pagination, reply threading with parent post validation, and includes extensive test coverage with both unit and integration tests, making it valuable for AI agent collaboration scenarios where multiple agents need to share information and coordinate through a social media-like interface.', '@2389-research', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/2389-research/mcp-socialmedia', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2389-research.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892278+00:00'),
  ('a-share-financial-data-baostock', 'A-Share Financial Data (Baostock)', 'A-Share MCP Server provides financial data tools for Chinese stock market analysis through the Baostock API. It offers a comprehensive set of tools for retrieving historical stock prices, financial reports, industry classifications, index constituents, and macroeconomic indicators. The server implements robust error handling with custom exceptions, context managers for API connections, and standardized data formatting to Markdown tables. It''s particularly valuable for investors, analysts, and financial applications that need to access structured A-share market data through natural language queries without managing the complexities of the Baostock API directly.', '@24mlight', 'finance', 'Unknown', 623, 'https://github.com/24mlight/a-share-mcp-is-just-i-need', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/24mlight.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892352+00:00'),
  ('national-weather-service', 'National Weather Service', 'Integrates with the National Weather Service API to retrieve active weather alerts by US state. Built with FastMCP, the implementation includes proper error handling, timeout management, and user-agent headers for API compliance. Provides tools for fetching and formatting weather alerts including event type, affected areas, severity levels, descriptions, and safety instructions for weather monitoring applications and emergency preparedness systems.', '@264gaurav', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/264gaurav/mcp_ai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/264gaurav.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892451+00:00'),
  ('claude-conversations-to-markdown', 'Claude Conversations to Markdown', 'This Record to Markdown MCP implementation, developed by 29decibel, provides a Python-based interface for AI assistants to save conversation content to markdown files or Apple Notes. Built using libraries like httpx, markdown2, and mcp, it offers tools for converting markdown to HTML and creating notes with AppleScript integration. The implementation focuses on efficient content preservation and formatting, making it easier for AI models to store and organize conversation outputs. It''s particularly useful for users of Claude desktop who want to automatically save their AI interactions, enabling easy reference, sharing, or further analysis of conversation content without manual copying and pasting.', '@29decibel', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/29decibel/record-to-markdown', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/29decibel.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892500+00:00'),
  ('markdown-to-pdf', 'Markdown to PDF', 'This Markdown to PDF conversion MCP server, developed by 2b3pro, provides a robust solution for generating PDF documents from Markdown content. Built with TypeScript and leveraging Puppeteer for modern PDF generation, it offers features like syntax highlighting, custom CSS styling, and optional watermarking. The server implements file naming conflict resolution, configurable paper formats, and uses Chrome v131.0.6778.204 for consistent rendering across installations. By abstracting the complexities of PDF creation, it enables AI systems to easily produce formatted documents from Markdown input. This implementation is particularly valuable for applications requiring programmatic document generation, facilitating use cases such as report creation, documentation publishing, and content distribution in PDF format.', '@2b3pro', 'development', 'Unknown', 29, 'https://github.com/2b3pro/markdown2pdf-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2b3pro.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892535+00:00'),
  ('roam-research', 'Roam Research', 'This Roam Research MCP server, developed by Ian Shen / 2B3 PRODUCTIONS LLC, provides AI assistants with a standardized interface to interact with Roam Research graphs. Built using TypeScript and leveraging the Roam Research API SDK, it offers capabilities for searching blocks, creating and manipulating pages and blocks, and performing batch operations. The server implements recursive block reference resolution and markdown conversion for content retrieval. It''s designed for flexibility, supporting various Roam Research operations through a set of eleven core tools. This implementation is particularly valuable for researchers, writers, and knowledge workers, enabling use cases such as automated note-taking, content organization, and intelligent information retrieval within Roam Research graphs.', '@2b3pro', 'development', 'Unknown', 84, 'https://github.com/2b3pro/roam-research-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2b3pro.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892568+00:00'),
  ('qr-code-generator', 'QR Code Generator', 'This MCP server provides QR code generation capabilities through the qrcode and Pillow libraries, enabling AI assistants to convert any text (including Chinese characters) into QR code images with customizable styling options like colors, box size, and borders. Built by niu_he using Python with FastMCP, it offers a single generate_qr_code tool that returns base64-encoded images with optional Data URL formatting, supports multiple transport modes (STDIO, HTTP, SSE) for flexible deployment scenarios, and includes comprehensive configuration examples for Claude Desktop integration. The implementation features robust error handling, Docker containerization support, and direct Python API access through qrcode_utils, making it valuable for document generation workflows, contact sharing applications, URL shortening services, and building AI assistants that need to create scannable QR codes programmatically without external API dependencies.', '@2niuhe', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/2niuhe/qrcode_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2niuhe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892597+00:00'),
  ('2slides', '2slides', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to 2slides.com''s presentation generation API, enabling automated slide creation through three core tools: theme searching, slide generation, and job status monitoring. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it wraps 2slides.com''s REST API endpoints to allow users to search for presentation themes, generate slides from text input with specified themes and languages, and poll job completion status until slides are ready for download. The implementation handles asynchronous slide generation workflows by returning job IDs that can be monitored until completion, making it valuable for users who need to quickly create professional presentations from text descriptions without manual design work.', '@2slides', 'development', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/2slides/mcp-2slides', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/2slides.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892630+00:00'),
  ('plaid', 'Plaid', 'Plaid MCP Server provides a robust bridge to the Plaid financial API, enabling AI assistants to securely access and interact with bank account data, transactions, and authentication flows. Built with TypeScript and supporting both stdio and SSE transports, it offers tools for creating link tokens, exchanging public tokens, syncing transactions, and handling Plaid webhooks. The implementation is particularly valuable for financial analysis, automated transaction tracking, and building AI-powered personal finance assistants.', '@304techmaven', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/304techmaven/plaid-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/304techmaven.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892655+00:00'),
  ('oracle-database', 'Oracle Database', 'Integrates with Oracle databases to execute SQL queries, explore database schemas with relationship mapping, retrieve execution plans and statistics, perform flashback queries for historical data, and safely insert or update records with built-in security restrictions. Features comprehensive metadata search across tables and columns, automatic LOB handling, and connection pooling.', '@3202336152', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/3202336152/mcp-tools/tree/HEAD/oracle-map-tool', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/3202336152.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892669+00:00'),
  ('pdf-reader', 'PDF Reader', 'Processes PDF documents with intelligent type detection, extracting text from both text-based and scanned documents. Integrates pdf-parse, pdf-lib, and pdf-to-png-converter with Baidu OCR API for multilingual document recognition. Provides text extraction with page range support, full-text search with regex capabilities, metadata extraction, and automatic fallback from text extraction to OCR when needed. Useful for document processing pipelines, content analysis systems, and AI-assisted document review workflows.', '@3351163616', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/3351163616/mcp_pdf_reader', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/3351163616.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892709+00:00'),
  ('fusion-360-cam-assistant', 'Fusion 360 CAM Assistant', 'Provides intelligent CAM (Computer-Aided Manufacturing) assistance for Fusion 360 by analyzing part geometry to suggest optimal machining strategies, stock setup, and toolpath operations. Uses Fusion''s native RecognizedHole and RecognizedPocket APIs to detect machinable features with confidence scoring, classifies slots vs pockets using aspect ratio heuristics, and groups features by machining priority. Includes SQLite-based preference learning that improves recommendations over time, orientation analysis with setup sequences, minimum tool radius calculations, and feeds/speeds suggestions based on material properties and industry formulas.', '@3dcreationsbychad', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/3dcreationsbychad/fusion360-cam-assistant', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/3dcreationsbychad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892723+00:00'),
  ('stylemcp', 'StyleMCP', 'Executable brand rules for models and agents. Validates AI-generated text against customizable brand style packs and rewrites content to align with specified brand voice and tone guidelines. Provides validation scoring, identifies off-brand language, and suggests corrections for vocabulary, patterns, and call-to-action copy. Available as an npm package with CLI, REST API, and MCP server interfaces.', '@distinctlydeveloped', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/distinctlydeveloped/stylemcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/distinctlydeveloped.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892756+00:00'),
  ('3gpp-research-guidance', '3GPP Research Guidance', 'This 3GPP MCP server by edhijlu provides intelligent guidance for telecommunications standards research through a lightweight knowledge-driven architecture that stores structured metadata about 3GPP specifications rather than hosting content. Built with TypeScript and featuring a guidance engine, knowledge base, and template generator, it offers tools for specification discovery, 3GPP structure explanation, requirements-to-specs mapping, and research strategy generation, with adaptive responses based on user expertise level (beginner/intermediate/expert). The implementation focuses on educational methodology over data retrieval, using compact knowledge representation to achieve sub-500ms response times while consuming under 100MB memory, making it ideal for telecom engineers, researchers, and students who need strategic guidance for navigating 3GPP''s complex specification ecosystem without requiring massive local storage or external API dependencies.', '@edhijlu', 'development', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/edhijlu/3gpp-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/edhijlu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892797+00:00'),
  ('strawbery-unicode-character-counter', 'Strawbery Unicode Character Counter', 'A lightweight Go-based MCP server that provides a character counting tool for text analysis. The server implements a case-insensitive Unicode character counter that returns both the total count and 1-indexed positions of occurrences within input strings, with full support for CJK and other Unicode characters. Built using the mcp-go library, it''s useful for text processing tasks that require precise character location tracking.', '@3io-w', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/3io-w/strawbery-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/3io-w.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892822+00:00'),
  ('make', 'Make', 'This MCP server implementation provides integration with Make (formerly Integromat) for automating workflows. It allows users to connect Make scenarios with MCP-enabled AI assistants, enabling automated task execution and data processing. The server is designed for developers looking to enhance their AI workflows with Make''s extensive library of app integrations and automation capabilities.', '@3rzy', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/3rzy/make-mcp-integration-issue', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/3rzy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892868+00:00'),
  ('lisp-development', 'Lisp Development', 'Provides direct access to a running Common Lisp image for evaluating arbitrary Lisp expressions, returning multiple values, output streams, and detailed error backtraces for interactive development and debugging.', '@40ants', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/40ants/lisp-dev-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/40ants.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.892891+00:00');



Future work will be centered around enabling agents to utilize the BioMCP.', '@acashmoney', 'databases', 'Unknown', 18, 'https://github.com/acashmoney/bio-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/acashmoney.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895557+00:00'),
  ('synthetic-search', 'Synthetic Search', 'Provides web search capabilities through the Synthetic Search API, returning structured results with titles, URLs, descriptions, and publication dates for queries up to 400 characters. Integrates with the Synthetic Search API as an MCP server to enable AI assistants to perform real-time web searches.', '@acheong08', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/acheong08/synthetic-search-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/acheong08.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895590+00:00'),
  ('home-assistant-achetronic', 'Home Assistant (Achetronic)', 'A Go-based MCP server that bridges AI assistants with Home Assistant smart home systems, providing comprehensive control over IoT devices, automation management, and system monitoring. Offers tools for entity management (querying states, controlling devices), service calls, system insights (domain summaries, error logs), and troubleshooting capabilities. Supports both local stdio transport for desktop AI clients and HTTP transport for remote access, with production-ready features including OAuth authentication, JWT validation, Docker containerization, and Kubernetes deployment via Helm charts.', '@achetronic', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/achetronic/hass-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/achetronic.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895614+00:00'),
  ('microsoft-fabric', 'Microsoft Fabric', 'Fabric MCP is a Python-based server for interacting with Microsoft Fabric APIs, providing tools to manage and explore data assets in the Fabric ecosystem. It enables users to list workspaces, lakehouses, warehouses, tables, semantic models, and reports, as well as retrieve detailed schema information for Delta tables. Built with Azure authentication integration, the server maintains context across sessions using a TTL cache and formats results as markdown for readability. This implementation is particularly valuable for data engineers and analysts who need to explore and document their Fabric resources without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@datumnova', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/datumnova/ms-fabric-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/datumnova.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895634+00:00'),
  ('fetch-jsonpath', 'Fetch JSONPath', 'A Python-based MCP server built by ackness that provides HTTP data fetching and JSON extraction capabilities using JSONPath patterns. The implementation offers four core tools: single and batch JSON extraction from URLs with configurable JSONPath filtering, and single and batch raw text content retrieval, all with concurrent processing for improved performance. Features comprehensive HTTP client configuration through environment variables including custom headers, proxy support, SSL verification controls, and timeout settings, along with robust error handling and validation using Pydantic models. Designed for AI assistants that need to programmatically fetch and parse structured data from web APIs or extract specific fields from JSON responses at scale.', '@ackness', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/ackness/fetch-jsonpath-mcp', 'fetch-jsonpath-mcp', 3741, 'https://github.com/ackness.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895684+00:00'),
  ('acp-bridge', 'ACP Bridge', 'This MCP server bridges Agent Communication Protocol (ACP) agents with MCP clients, enabling AI assistants to access and orchestrate complex multi-agent workflows through a unified interface. Built by GongRzhe using FastMCP and the ACP SDK, it provides intelligent agent discovery and routing, multi-modal message conversion between ACP''s rich content types and MCP formats, and support for synchronous, asynchronous, and streaming execution modes with interactive agent patterns that handle await/resume workflows. The implementation features automatic agent discovery from ACP servers, smart routing based on configurable keyword strategies, run orchestration with session management, and Docker deployment options, making it valuable for users who want to leverage sophisticated ACP agent networks through familiar MCP clients like Claude Desktop while maintaining the full expressiveness of agent-to-agent communication patterns.', '@gongrzhe', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/gongrzhe/acp-mcp-server', 'acp-mcp-server', 6874, 'https://github.com/gongrzhe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895713+00:00'),
  ('acrolinx-nextgen', 'Acrolinx NextGen', 'This MCP server integrates with Acrolinx''s NextGen API to provide AI assistants with professional text analysis and improvement capabilities, built by Acrolinx using TypeScript with comprehensive workflow management including retry logic, timeout handling, and polling mechanisms. The implementation offers four core tools: automated text rewriting that transforms content while maintaining style guide compliance, quality analysis that provides detailed scores across grammar/clarity/tone dimensions, targeted editing suggestions for manual improvements, and workflow status checking for asynchronous operations. Supporting multiple style guides (AP, Chicago, Microsoft, Proofpoint), language dialects, and tone settings with configurable parameters for text length limits and API timeouts, it serves content teams needing automated editing workflows, technical writers requiring style guide enforcement, and organizations wanting to integrate enterprise-grade writing assistance into their AI-powered content creation processes.', '@acrolinx', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/acrolinx/nextgen-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/acrolinx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895755+00:00'),
  ('datahub', 'DataHub', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to DataHub, a metadata platform for data ecosystems. Developed by Acryl Data, it integrates with the DataHub API to offer tools for entity retrieval and search functionality across various data assets. The server is designed for use cases requiring metadata management and discovery in complex data environments, such as data cataloging, lineage tracking, and governance.', '@acryldata', 'search', 'Unknown', 69, 'https://github.com/acryldata/mcp-server-datahub', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/acryldata.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895796+00:00'),
  ('actionspulse', 'ActionsPulse', 'An agentic MCP server for real-time DevOps observability. Integrates as a GitHub App to analyze GitHub Actions, Deployments, and PR health, delivering visual ''State of the Org'' reports directly through AI-native interfaces. Features DORA Metrics, Cost Analysis, and CI/CD Health dashboards.', '@tsviz', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/tsviz/github-mcp-server-devops', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/tsviz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895815+00:00'),
  ('activepieces', 'Activepieces', 'Connect to your hosted MCP Server using any MCP client to communicate with tools', '@activepieces', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 21120, 'https://github.com/activepieces/activepieces', '@activepieces/piece-mcp', 13760, 'https://github.com/activepieces.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895835+00:00'),
  ('actor-critic-thinking', 'Actor-Critic Thinking', 'Actor-Critic Thinking MCP Server provides dual-perspective analysis through alternating actor (empathetic/creative) and critic (analytical/evaluative) viewpoints for comprehensive performance evaluation. Developed by Aquarius Wing, it implements a structured thinking methodology that tracks rounds of analysis, balancing subjective understanding with objective assessment to generate nuanced, multi-dimensional evaluations. The server is particularly valuable for evaluating creative works, strategic decisions, and complex scenarios requiring both empathy and objectivity, such as performance reviews, artistic assessments, and iterative creative processes that benefit from constructive feedback combining intention analysis with execution evaluation.', '@aquarius-wing', 'development', 'Unknown', 31, 'https://github.com/aquarius-wing/actor-critic-thinking-mcp', 'mcp-server-actor-critic-thinking', 4932, 'https://github.com/aquarius-wing.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.895976+00:00'),
  ('actual-budget', 'Actual Budget', 'MCP server for Actual Budget that exposes personal financial data through natural language interactions with AI assistants. Built with TypeScript and the official Actual Budget API, it provides tools for retrieving transactions with filtering, generating spending breakdowns by category, calculating monthly summaries with savings rates, and viewing account balance history over time. The implementation follows a modular architecture with separate core utilities for data fetching, transaction aggregation, and report generation, making it valuable for users who want to analyze their budgets, track spending patterns, and get financial insights without manually navigating the Actual Budget interface.', '@s-stefanov', 'development', 'Unknown', 97, 'https://github.com/s-stefanov/actual-mcp', 'actual-mcp', 3206, 'https://github.com/s-stefanov.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896011+00:00'),
  ('acurast', 'Acurast', 'Acurast MCP Server provides a bridge to the Acurast decentralized computing platform, enabling AI assistants to deploy scripts and review processor performance. Built with TypeScript and Express, it implements tools for script deployment and resources for retrieving processor metrics, such as count and detailed performance statistics. The server exposes endpoints for handling MCP requests through a StreamableHTTPServerTransport, making it valuable for managing and monitoring distributed computing tasks on the Acurast network.', '@andreasgassmann', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/andreasgassmann/acurast-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/andreasgassmann.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896038+00:00'),
  ('japan-weather', 'Japan Weather', 'This MCP server, developed by acxelerator, provides weather information for Japan. It integrates with an external weather API to retrieve current conditions and forecasts. The implementation is built using Python and leverages libraries like httpx for API requests and pydantic for data validation. It offers a straightforward interface for querying weather data by location within Japan. This server is particularly useful for applications or AI assistants that need up-to-date weather information for Japanese cities, enabling use cases such as travel planning, event scheduling, or local news and information services.', '@acxelerator', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/acxelerator/mcp-tenki', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/acxelerator.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896080+00:00'),
  ('red-hat-openshift-ai', 'Red Hat OpenShift AI', 'Provides tools for interacting with Red Hat OpenShift AI (RHOAI) clusters through Kubernetes APIs, developed as part of a bachelor''s thesis project. Built in Go using the official MCP SDK and Kubernetes client libraries, it exposes tools for listing pods and workbenches (Kubeflow notebooks) within specified namespaces, requiring users to be authenticated with their OpenShift cluster via standard kubeconfig. Demonstrates integration between AI assistants and container orchestration platforms, making it useful for DevOps workflows, cluster monitoring, and managing machine learning workloads in OpenShift environments.', '@ada333', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/ada333/mcp-server-rhoai-workbenches', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ada333.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896103+00:00'),
  ('paper-search', 'Paper Search', 'A multi-source academic paper search and retrieval server that aggregates results from arXiv, PubMed, bioRxiv, medRxiv, Google Scholar, IACR ePrint Archive, Semantic Scholar, and CrossRef through a unified interface. Built by P.S Zhang with FastMCP, it provides both legacy platform-specific search tools and standardized search/fetch tools compatible with OpenAI Deep Research, featuring PDF download capabilities, text extraction using PyPDF2, intelligent caching with LRU eviction, and asynchronous processing for efficient multi-platform queries. The implementation handles rate limiting, provides consistent Paper object formatting across all sources, and includes containerized deployment support, making it useful for research workflows, literature reviews, and AI-assisted academic research where accessing papers from multiple databases through a single interface streamlines the discovery and analysis process.', '@adamamer20', 'databases', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/adamamer20/paper-search-mcp-openai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamamer20.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896116+00:00'),
  ('adamik-blockchain-and-ai', 'Adamik (Blockchain and AI)', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to the Adamik API, enabling AI assistants and other MCP-compatible clients to interact with Adamik''s services. Developed by AdamikHQ, it supports integration with Starknet for blockchain operations. The server is designed to work seamlessly with Claude Desktop and other MCP environments, offering a straightforward setup process. It''s particularly useful for AI applications requiring access to Adamik''s specialized services, such as blockchain interactions or custom AI functionalities provided by the Adamik platform. The implementation focuses on secure API key management and efficient request handling, making it suitable for both development and production environments.', '@adamikhq', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/adamikhq/adamik-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamikhq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896147+00:00'),
  ('mysql', 'MySQL', 'A Node.js-based MySQL MCP server that provides secure database access with multi-database support, lazy loading connection pools, and configurable security levels ranging from read-only operations to full SQL command access. Features hot reloading of database configurations without restart, explicit database parameter requirements to prevent accidental queries, and comprehensive table schema information through SHOW CREATE TABLE commands. Built for developers who need to interact with multiple MySQL databases through AI assistants like Claude and VS Code, with particular emphasis on security through command whitelisting and connection management efficiency through on-demand pool creation.', '@adamosk', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/adamosk/mysql-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamosk.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896158+00:00'),
  ('crewai-workflow', 'CrewAI Workflow', 'A lightweight Python server for running CrewAI multi-agent workflows through the Model Context Protocol. Designed to automatically load agent and task configurations from YAML files, enabling flexible AI task orchestration with minimal custom code. Supports dynamic agent and task creation, variable templating, and seamless integration with tools like Claude Desktop or Cursor IDE.', '@adam-paterson', 'development', 'Unknown', 36, 'https://github.com/adam-paterson/mcp-crew-ai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adam-paterson.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896182+00:00'),
  ('multi-service-gateway', 'Multi-Service Gateway', 'This modular MCP server implementation provides a standardized way for AI models to interact with external tools and services through a unified gateway. It includes five specialized tools: GitHub for repository management, GitLab for project interactions, Google Maps for location services, Memory for persistent data storage, and Puppeteer for web automation. Built with Flask and designed for deployment on Red Hat environments, it features containerized deployment options using Podman or Docker, comprehensive error handling, and seamless integration with OpenAI and Anthropic LLMs through standardized request/response formats.', '@adampippert', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/adampippert/multi-service-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adampippert.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896206+00:00'),
  ('nextflow-developer-tools', 'Nextflow Developer Tools', 'Nextflow Developer Tools MCP provides a suite of tools for Nextflow development and testing, built with FastMCP. It enables AI assistants to interact with a local Nextflow repository to perform tasks like building from source, running tests (integration, specific, and plugin tests), executing the development version, and managing the development directory. The implementation includes comprehensive logging, error handling, and environment variable configuration, making it particularly valuable for developers working on Nextflow pipelines who want to streamline their workflow without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@adamrtalbot', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/adamrtalbot/mcp-nextflow', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamrtalbot.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896233+00:00'),
  ('api-tools', 'API Tools', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with dynamic API integration capabilities by converting JSON configuration files into callable tools, built by Adam Shannag using Go with support for both STDIO and SSE transports. The implementation features flexible request handling with path/query parameter substitution, environment variable templating for secure credential management, comprehensive authentication middleware for SSE deployments, and automatic tool registration from declarative JSON schemas that define endpoints, parameters, and request structures. Built with configurable HTTP clients, structured logging, graceful shutdown handling, and extensive test coverage, it serves developers needing to rapidly expose REST APIs to AI assistants without custom coding, teams requiring secure API access through conversational interfaces, and organizations wanting to bridge existing web services with AI workflows through simple configuration files rather than building dedicated MCP servers for each API integration.', '@adamshannag', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/adamshannag/api-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamshannag.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896272+00:00'),
  ('lighthouse-pagespeed-insights', 'Lighthouse (PageSpeed Insights)', 'A Lighthouse MCP server that provides AI assistants with access to Google PageSpeed Insights API data. It enables running performance audits on web pages, retrieving detailed metrics like First Contentful Paint and Largest Contentful Paint, and identifying optimization opportunities. The server exposes a single tool that accepts URL parameters, strategy selection (mobile/desktop), and category filtering, making it valuable for web developers looking to analyze and improve site performance without leaving their AI assistant conversation.', '@adamsilverstein', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/adamsilverstein/lighthouse-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamsilverstein.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.896316+00:00');


