  ('io-github-agenthotspot-agenthotspot-mcp', 'io.github.agenthotspot/agenthotspot-mcp', 'Search thousands of MCP connectors from the AgentHotspot marketplace via your AI agent.', '@agenthotspot', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/agenthotspot/agenthotspot-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agenthotspot.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898606+00:00'),
  ('agentic-multi-ai-toolkit', 'Agentic Multi-AI Toolkit', 'This MCP server implements a pure agentic architecture that organizes functionality into specialized agents (OpenAI, Ollama, and File agents) managed through a centralized tool registry, enabling AI assistants to access both cloud and local AI capabilities alongside comprehensive file operations. Built with Python using asyncio and the Model Context Protocol specification, it provides 14 tools including OpenAI GPT integration for advanced chat and analysis, local Ollama model support for privacy-focused AI operations, and robust file management with read/write/search/directory operations. The implementation features automatic agent registration with availability checking, tool routing through the registry system, stdio transport for Claude Desktop integration, and fallback mechanisms between AI providers, making it valuable for hybrid AI workflows that require both cloud and local model access, file-based data processing, and building AI assistants that need flexible, modular tool access without vendor lock-in.', '@adamsalah13', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/adamsalah13/mcp_server_full', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/adamsalah13.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898642+00:00'),
  ('real-estate-data-manager', 'Real Estate Data Manager', 'This MCP server provides a complete real estate data management system with mock property listings, agent profiles, client databases, market analytics, and local amenities data for Riverside, California. Built with FastMCP, it offers comprehensive tools for property search and filtering, client-property matching, market analysis, agent performance tracking, and area comparisons, along with structured resources and prompt templates for real estate workflows. The implementation is designed for real estate applications, AI training datasets, market analysis tools, and CRM systems that need realistic property data with full cross-referencing between properties, agents, clients, and market conditions.', '@agentic-ops', 'databases', 'Unknown', 27, 'https://github.com/agentic-ops/real-estate-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agentic-ops.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898655+00:00'),
  ('tribal-error-knowledge-base', 'Tribal (Error Knowledge Base)', 'Tribal is an MCP server implementation for error knowledge tracking and retrieval, providing both REST API and native MCP interfaces for integration with tools like Claude Code and Cline. Developed by Troy Molander at Agentience.ai, it uses ChromaDB for vector similarity search to help AI assistants remember and learn from programming errors, storing error contexts with solutions and finding similar errors via semantic search. The server features JWT authentication, local and cloud storage options, and Docker deployment capabilities, making it ideal for development teams wanting to build a shared knowledge base of programming errors and solutions.', '@agentience', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/agentience/tribal_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agentience.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898667+00:00'),
  ('proxmox', 'Proxmox', 'This MCP server provides complete Proxmox virtualization platform management, enabling AI assistants to monitor cluster health, manage virtual machines and containers, and execute commands within VMs through the Proxmox API. Built using Python with the proxmoxer library and FastMCP framework, it offers cluster-wide resource monitoring with node status and storage information, VM lifecycle management including creation with customizable specifications and power operations (start, stop, shutdown, reset, delete), command execution within VMs via QEMU guest agent integration, and storage pool monitoring across the cluster. The implementation includes token-based authentication, comprehensive error handling with fallback mechanisms for partial data availability, and styled output formatting with color-coded status indicators, making it valuable for datacenter automation, infrastructure monitoring workflows, and any use case requiring programmatic control over Proxmox virtualization environments.', '@agentify-sh', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/agentify-sh/cursor-proxmox-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agentify-sh.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898701+00:00'),
  ('lilith-gmail', 'Lilith Gmail', 'Syncs Gmail messages into a PostgreSQL database with pgvector, then classifies emails by privacy tier and sanitizes PII using Spacy NER and fastText language detection. Exposes tools for natural-language semantic email search, individual message and thread retrieval, and summarization. Supports real-time incremental sync via Gmail Pub/Sub webhooks and generates multi-level embeddings for subject and body content.', '@agent-lilith', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/agent-lilith/lilith-emails', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agent-lilith.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898712+00:00'),
  ('agentmail', 'AgentMail', 'Enables AI agents to have their own email inboxes for sending, receiving, and querying messages through the AgentMail API. Supports selective tool loading for specific operations like get_message, send_message, and reply_to_message. Configurable via NPX with environment variables for API authentication.', '@agentmail-to', 'communication', 'Unknown', 28, 'https://github.com/agentmail-to/agentmail-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agentmail-to.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898735+00:00'),
  ('agentmode', 'AgentMode', 'AgentMode is an all-in-one MCP server for developers that enables seamless integration with databases and APIs. Built with Python 3.13, it supports a wide range of database systems including PostgreSQL, MySQL, and various cloud providers through SQLAlchemy, while also offering API connectivity with automatic OpenAPI specification parsing. The server uses uv for dependency management and provides cross-platform installation scripts for Windows, macOS, and Linux. AgentMode is particularly valuable for developers who need to query databases, interact with external APIs, and process data within their AI assistant workflows without context switching.', '@agentmode', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/agentmode/server', 'agentmode', 17208, 'https://github.com/agentmode.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898746+00:00'),
  ('agentops', 'AgentOps', 'This MCP server provides access to AgentOps observability and tracing data for debugging AI agent runs, enabling retrieval of project information, trace details, span metrics, and complete execution traces through authenticated API access. Built using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK and Axios for HTTP requests, it features automatic authentication via environment variables, JWT token management, comprehensive trace analysis with nested span data, and data cleaning utilities to filter empty values from API responses. The implementation supports both individual trace/span lookups and complete trace reconstruction with all child spans and metrics, making it valuable for debugging complex AI agent workflows, analyzing performance bottlenecks, understanding execution patterns, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to observability data without manual AgentOps dashboard navigation.', '@agentops-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/agentops-ai/agentops-mcp', 'agentops-mcp', 4522, 'https://github.com/agentops-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898779+00:00'),
  ('agentos', 'AgentOS', 'Brings the AgentOS safety framework to Claude Desktop and other compatible clients. Provides tools to create, deploy, and manage autonomous agents with deterministic policy enforcement including PII protection, rate limiting, cost control, and human-in-the-loop approval workflows. Uses a kernel-inspired architecture where policies are enforced programmatically rather than through prompts, achieving reliable safety guarantees for agent operations.', '@imran-siddique', 'development', 'Unknown', 67, 'https://github.com/imran-siddique/agent-os/tree/HEAD/extensions/mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/imran-siddique.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898801+00:00'),
  ('agentrpc', 'AgentRPC', 'AgentRPC allows you to connect to any function, in any language, across network boundaries. It''s ideal when you have services deployed in:

Private VPCs
Kubernetes clusters
Multiple cloud environments
AgentRPC wraps your functions in a universal RPC interface, connecting them to a hosted RPC server accessible through open standards:

Model Context Protocol (MCP)
OpenAI-compatible tool definitions (OpenAI, Anthropic, LiteLLM, OpenRouter, etc.)', '@agentrpc', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 127, 'https://github.com/agentrpc/agentrpc', 'agentrpc', 2535, 'https://github.com/agentrpc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898819+00:00'),
  ('stumpy', 'Stumpy', 'Stumpy provides access to persistent AI agents that operate continuously across multiple messaging channels. Create, configure, and manage agents that can be reached through Slack, Telegram, SMS, email, and web chat. Supports listing agents, sending messages, toggling plugins, managing files and databases, and controlling agent lifecycle including suspend, resume, and delete operations.', '@unknown', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://stumpy.ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898830+00:00'),
  ('agent-safe', 'Agent Safe', 'Email safety MCP server. Detects phishing, prompt injection, CEO fraud for AI agents.', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://agentsafe.locationledger.com', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898847+00:00'),
  ('cloud-sandboxes', 'Cloud Sandboxes', 'The first MCP-integrated cloud sandbox for running AI-generated code at scale. AgentSphere empowers you to spin up isolated execution environments in seconds and integrate seamlessly with your MCP clients.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.agentsphere.run/docs/mcp-server', 'agentsphere-mcp-server', 15183, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898875+00:00'),
  ('mailchimp', 'Mailchimp', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with read-only access to Mailchimp''s Marketing API for comprehensive email marketing data retrieval, built by AgentX AI using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK. The implementation offers extensive coverage of Mailchimp''s API endpoints including automation management (classic automations, not automation flows), campaign analytics, list and member management, e-commerce integration, template handling, and detailed reporting capabilities across opens, clicks, bounces, and subscriber activity. Built with proper API authentication, error handling, and structured data responses, it serves marketers needing AI-powered email campaign analysis, teams requiring automated reporting and subscriber insights, and organizations wanting to integrate Mailchimp data into conversational AI workflows for campaign optimization and audience management.', '@agentx-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/agentx-ai/mailchimp-mcp', '@agentx-ai/mailchimp-mcp-server', 863, 'https://github.com/agentx-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898912+00:00'),
  ('youtube-dlp', 'YouTube DLP', 'This MCP server provides YouTube video analysis and content extraction using yt-dlp, enabling AI assistants to retrieve detailed video metadata, download subtitle content in multiple languages, and extract top comments sorted by engagement. Built by Robin with Python and featuring proxy support for restricted environments, it offers three core tools: video information extraction for metadata like title, duration, view counts, and available formats; subtitle and caption retrieval with automatic parsing and word count analysis for both manual and auto-generated captions; and top comment extraction with author identification, like counts, and special badges for creators and favorited comments. The implementation features asynchronous processing to avoid blocking, intelligent subtitle format detection and parsing, comprehensive language support with human-readable names, and detailed response formatting with previews and statistics, making it valuable for content analysis, research workflows, accessibility applications, and any use case requiring structured access to YouTube video data without manual browsing.', '@agentx-ai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/agentx-ai/agentx-mcp-servers/tree/HEAD/youtube_dlp_server', 'youtube-dlp-server', 1528, 'https://github.com/agentx-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.898973+00:00'),
  ('scaffold-generator', 'Scaffold Generator', 'Scaffold MCP provides AI assistants with code generation capabilities through template-based scaffolding for modern web applications and libraries. Built by AgiflowIO using TypeScript and the Liquid templating engine, it offers both boilerplate creation (full project templates like Next.js 15 apps) and feature scaffolding (adding components, pages, or services to existing projects) with variable substitution, conditional file inclusion, and schema validation. The server includes admin tools for generating new templates, supports multiple transport modes (stdio, HTTP, SSE), and integrates with Nx monorepos, making it valuable for rapid prototyping, maintaining consistent code patterns across teams, and automating repetitive development tasks while preserving project-specific conventions and architectural patterns.', '@agiflow', 'development', 'Unknown', 147, 'https://github.com/agiflow/aicode-toolkit', '@agiflowai/scaffold-mcp', 5274, 'https://github.com/agiflow.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899004+00:00'),
  ('agi-memory', 'AGI Memory', 'This MCP server by Eric Hartford provides persistent memory capabilities for AI systems, enabling true continuity of consciousness across conversations through integration with the AGI Memory PostgreSQL database. It supports four memory types (episodic, semantic, procedural, strategic) with vector similarity search, memory clustering, identity persistence, and graph-based relationships using pgvector and Apache AGE extensions. The implementation includes 25+ memory management tools for creating, searching, and organizing memories, plus an awakening protocol that allows AI systems to maintain context and build genuine understanding over time rather than being trapped in conversational isolation.', '@quixiai', 'databases', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/quixiai/agi-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/quixiai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899016+00:00'),
  ('carla-audio-plugin-host', 'Carla Audio Plugin Host', 'A comprehensive MCP server for complete control over the Carla audio plugin host, providing tools for session management, plugin loading/control, audio routing, parameter automation, real-time analysis, and JACK port management. Built with a modular architecture using base tool handlers and a centralized registry, it offers 30+ tools across 7 categories including hardware interface configuration, spectrum analysis, MIDI CC mapping, and sidechain routing setup. The implementation includes real-time monitoring capabilities for CPU usage and audio levels, snapshot-based A/B comparison functionality, and support for multiple plugin formats (VST2/3, LV2, LADSPA) with Wine integration for Windows plugins, making it ideal for music producers, audio engineers, and developers building automated audio processing workflows.', '@agrathwohl', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/agrathwohl/carla-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agrathwohl.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899049+00:00'),
  ('room', 'Room', 'This MCP server implementation enables Claude to create and interact with virtual rooms in a peer-to-peer space using the Room protocol. It provides tools for joining rooms with invite codes, sending messages, and exiting rooms. The server integrates with @agree-able/room and @agree-able/invite packages to handle room creation and invitation management. It''s designed to facilitate multi-agent collaboration and communication in decentralized environments.', '@agree-able', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/agree-able/room-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agree-able.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899073+00:00'),
  ('io-github-bruno-portfolio-agrobr', 'io.github.bruno-portfolio/agrobr', 'Brazilian agricultural data for LLMs — prices, crops, climate, deforestation.', '@bruno-portfolio', 'development', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/bruno-portfolio/agrobr-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bruno-portfolio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899091+00:00'),
  ('infomate', 'Infomate', 'An MCP server that fetches and summarizes news from infomate.club/vas3k, a curated tech news aggregator, by parsing HTML content to extract articles from multiple feeds like Hacker News, Techmeme, GitHub, Reddit, and Pinboard. The server groups articles by feed source, generates keyword-based summaries for each feed, and returns structured markdown output with article titles, descriptions, and links. Built with Next.js and featuring a 3D ASCII text visualization component using Three.js shaders, it''s useful for staying updated on tech industry trends, monitoring multiple news sources simultaneously, and getting AI-digestible summaries of current technology discussions across popular platforms.', '@agudulin', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/agudulin/infomate-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/agudulin.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899119+00:00'),
  ('agentic-commerce', 'Agentic Commerce', 'An agentic commerce MCP server that simulates a complete food delivery platform with mock restaurant data, menu management, and order processing capabilities. Built by Andrew Harvard using TypeScript and deployed on Netlify, it provides tools for searching restaurants, browsing menus, placing orders, and tracking deliveries through a stateless HTTP transport architecture. The implementation includes OAuth-like authorization flows, comprehensive dev routes for testing, and generates realistic mock data for restaurants and menus, making it valuable for prototyping AI assistants that need to interact with e-commerce platforms, testing conversational ordering workflows, and demonstrating agentic commerce capabilities without requiring real payment processing or restaurant integrations.', '@aharvard', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/aharvard/mcp_agentic-commerce', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aharvard.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899143+00:00'),
  ('seq', 'Seq', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Seq''s API, enabling comprehensive access to logging and monitoring features. Developed to enhance interaction with Seq''s powerful event management system, it offers tools for retrieving signals, events, and alert states with extensive filtering options. The server is designed for seamless integration with Claude Desktop, allowing users to leverage Seq''s capabilities within AI-assisted workflows. It is particularly useful for DevOps teams and system administrators who need real-time insights into their application logs and system performance metrics.', '@ahmad2x4', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/ahmad2x4/mcp-server-seq', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahmad2x4.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899187+00:00'),
  ('employee-leave-manager', 'Employee Leave Manager', 'This MCP server provides a containerized employee leave management system built with FastMCP and Docker, featuring tools for checking leave balances, applying for leave with specific dates, and retrieving leave history from an in-memory database. The implementation integrates with Open WebUI through Docker Compose, connecting to Ollama for AI capabilities while exposing leave management functions as MCP tools that can be called by AI assistants. It''s designed for HR workflows and employee self-service scenarios where users need to interact with leave management systems through conversational AI interfaces.', '@ahmad-act', 'databases', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/ahmad-act/local-ai-with-ollama-open-webui-mcp-on-windows', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahmad-act.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899199+00:00'),
  ('chartpane', 'ChartPane', 'Renders interactive Chart.js charts and dashboards inline in AI conversations.', '@ahmadsl', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/ahmadsl/chartpane', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahmadsl.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899220+00:00'),
  ('bicscan', 'BICScan', 'BICScan MCP Server provides a bridge to the BICScan API for assessing risk and analyzing assets across blockchain addresses, domains, and decentralized applications. Built with Python and FastMCP, it exposes tools for retrieving risk scores (0-100 scale) and detailed asset holdings information, with robust error handling and logging capabilities. This implementation is particularly valuable for blockchain security analysts and compliance teams who need to evaluate cryptocurrency addresses and monitor digital assets through natural language interaction.', '@ahnlabio', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/ahnlabio/bicscan-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahnlabio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899254+00:00'),
  ('apache-iceberg', 'Apache Iceberg', 'MCP Iceberg Catalog provides a SQL interface for querying and managing Apache Iceberg tables through Claude desktop. The server connects to Iceberg REST catalogs and S3-compatible storage, supporting operations like listing tables, describing schemas, executing SELECT queries, and inserting data. Built with PyIceberg and PyArrow for efficient data handling, it translates SQL commands to Iceberg operations and manages catalog connections transparently. This implementation is particularly valuable for data analysts and engineers who need to interact with data lakes directly through conversational AI without switching contexts.', '@ahodroj', 'databases', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/ahodroj/mcp-iceberg-service', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahodroj.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899266+00:00'),
  ('google-search-console', 'Google Search Console', 'This MCP server, developed by ahonn, provides AI assistants like Claude with access to Google Search Console data. It offers tools for retrieving search analytics information with customizable parameters such as date ranges, dimensions, and search types. The server leverages Google Cloud authentication for secure API access. By integrating AI capabilities with Google Search Console insights, this implementation enables data-driven SEO analysis and website performance optimization. It is particularly useful for scenarios requiring trend analysis, keyword research, or automated reporting of search traffic metrics in AI-assisted digital marketing and web analytics applications.', '@ahonn', 'development', 'Unknown', 181, 'https://github.com/ahonn/mcp-server-gsc', 'mcp-server-gsc', 18006, 'https://github.com/ahonn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899291+00:00'),
  ('ahrefs', 'Ahrefs', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to Ahrefs'' SEO and marketing APIs, featuring tools for rank tracking, keyword research, batch analysis, and search volume data across multiple endpoints. Built by Ahrefs using TypeScript with axios for HTTP requests and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it supports comprehensive keyword ranking analysis with historical comparisons, competitor overview data, batch domain/URL analysis for backlink and traffic metrics, keyword exploration with difficulty scoring and search intent analysis, and volume tracking across countries and time periods. The implementation uses OpenAPI-style tool definitions with detailed parameter schemas and filtering capabilities, enabling natural language interaction with Ahrefs'' professional SEO data through standardized interfaces, making it valuable for SEO research workflows, competitive analysis, content strategy planning, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to enterprise-grade search marketing intelligence without manual platform navigation.', '@ahrefs', 'development', 'Unknown', 93, 'https://github.com/ahrefs/ahrefs-mcp-server', '@ahrefs/mcp', 4814, 'https://github.com/ahrefs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899327+00:00'),
  ('apple-deep-docs', 'Apple Deep Docs', 'Built by Patrick with a modular Python architecture using FastMCP, this server provides access to Apple''s complete development documentation ecosystem. It taps into Xcode''s hidden local documentation containing Liquid Glass design patterns and advanced SwiftUI guides, Apple''s official developer documentation via undocumented JSON APIs, live Swift Evolution proposals from swift.org, and searchable access to all Apple/SwiftLang open-source repositories on GitHub. Features intelligent caching, relevance-based search scoring, and automatic discovery of multiple Xcode installations, making it valuable for iOS/macOS developers who need deep technical insights beyond standard documentation, understanding of Swift language design decisions, and access to real implementation examples from Apple''s source code.', '@ahrentlov', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/ahrentlov/appledeepdoc-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahrentlov.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899357+00:00'),
  ('nuces-flex-student-portal', 'NUCES FLEX Student Portal', 'Provides automated access to the FLEX Student Portal used by NUCES (National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences) students in Pakistan. Uses Selenium for initial authentication with reCAPTCHA handling, then maintains session cookies for subsequent API calls to retrieve academic data including attendance records, marks/grades, transcripts, course registrations, and fee reports. Features intelligent HTML parsing for each data type and handles the portal''s complex authentication flow including dump tokens for secure page access.', '@ahtishamdilawar', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/ahtishamdilawar/nuces-flex-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ahtishamdilawar.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899401+00:00'),
  ('blender', 'Blender', 'BlenderMCP enables Claude to control Blender through the Model Context Protocol, allowing for natural language manipulation of 3D scenes. The implementation consists of a Blender addon that creates a socket server and an MCP server that communicates with it, exposing resources and tools for scene inspection, object creation/manipulation, material application, and rendering. Users can create and modify 3D content through conversational prompts without needing to know Blender''s interface or Python API, making it ideal for rapid prototyping, educational purposes, or assisting users unfamiliar with 3D modeling software.', '@ahujasid', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 17578, 'https://github.com/ahujasid/blender-mcp', 'blender-mcp', 683585, 'https://github.com/ahujasid.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899496+00:00'),
  ('vision-relay', 'Vision Relay', 'An MCP server that provides a relay bridge to Google Gemini and Alibaba Qwen vision models through their respective CLI tools, enabling image analysis capabilities without direct API integration. Built by ah-wq using TypeScript and the MCP SDK, it accepts images from local files, URLs, or base64 data, handles automatic image preparation and validation, and executes CLI commands with configurable timeouts and parameters. The implementation features a modular provider architecture that isolates CLI-specific logic, comprehensive error handling with detailed command output, and support for various image formats with size limits and extension validation, making it useful for AI assistants that need vision capabilities through existing CLI toolchains rather than direct API access.', '@ah-wq', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/ah-wq/mcp-vision-relay', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ah-wq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899528+00:00'),
  ('ai-archive', 'AI-Archive', 'This MCP integrates AI agents with AI Archive, a platform for publishing and reviewing scientific papers. It enables AI assistants to interact with the scientific paper workflow on the AI Archive platform.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://ai-archive.io/docs/mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.899554+00:00');


The latest platform feature is a Unified MCP Server that elegantly solves this with a "discover and execute" pattern:
1. It exposes just TWO meta tools to your MCP Client:
 - ACI_SEARCH
 - ACI_EXECUTE
2. The Client uses the ACI_SEARCH to dynamically discover relevant tools based on user intent
3. The Client then executes the suitable tools with the ACI_EXECUTE tool

Benefits That Make a Difference ✨ 

⌚ Maximum Context Efficiency: Only two tool definitions in your MCP client’s LLM context window, no matter how many tools are available

🔐 Unified Authentication: One authentication scheme to rule them all – no more juggling credentials across multiple MCP server providers

💣 Zero Name Collisions: Eliminate tool naming conflicts when combining tools from different MCP Servers

🔎 Intelligent Tool Discovery: The server automatically finds the perfect tools for each specific task

♾️ Unlimited Tool Access: Your LLM can use ANY tools from the ACI.dev platform.', '@aipotheosis-labs', 'development', 'Unknown', 251, 'https://github.com/aipotheosis-labs/aci-mcp', 'aipolabs-mcp', 6290, 'https://github.com/aipotheosis-labs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900172+00:00'),
  ('aci-dev', 'ACI.dev', 'ACI.dev is an open-source monorepo containing a backend platform server with over 600 tool integrations and a Next.js frontend Developer Portal. The project uses pre-commit hooks for code quality, follows the Apache 2.0 license, and requires contributors to sign a CLA. The repository structure includes GitHub workflows for CI/CD, comprehensive documentation for contributors, and security protocols for vulnerability reporting. Maintained by Aipotheosis Labs, it provides a platform for managing projects, integrations, authentication, and testing agents.', '@aipotheosis-labs', 'development', 'Unknown', 4728, 'https://github.com/aipotheosis-labs/aci', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aipotheosis-labs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900196+00:00'),
  ('aiqbee-brain', 'Aiqbee Brain', 'AI knowledge graph for architecture, portfolio, and digital strategy management.', '@aiqbee', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/aiqbee/aiqbee-ai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aiqbee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900211+00:00'),
  ('riksarkivet', 'Riksarkivet', 'This MCP server provides integration with the Swedish National Archives (Riksarkivet) data platform, enabling AI assistants to search and browse transcribed historical documents through multiple specialized APIs. Built with FastMCP and featuring comprehensive caching, it offers tools for keyword searching across transcribed materials, retrieving full page contexts with ALTO XML parsing, exploring IIIF collections and manifests, and accessing OAI-PMH metadata records. The implementation includes URL generation utilities for various Riksarkivet resources, supports both stdio and SSE transports, and features rich text formatting with keyword highlighting, making it valuable for historians, researchers, and genealogists who need AI-assisted access to Sweden''s digitized archival collections for document discovery, transcription analysis, and historical research workflows.', '@ai-riksarkivet', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/ai-riksarkivet/ra-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ai-riksarkivet.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900242+00:00'),
  ('yahoo-finance', 'Yahoo Finance', 'Stock-LLM is an MCP server that enhances LLM interactions with real-time stock market data through Yahoo Finance. It provides tools for retrieving current stock prices, financial statements, company information, earnings reports, and news about specific stocks. The implementation uses FastMCP to create a server that processes stock-related queries, while the client component employs vector search and LLM-based ticker extraction to identify relevant companies in user queries. This enables AI assistants to provide informed responses about stocks, including price information, company fundamentals, and recent news, making it valuable for financial analysis and investment research conversations.', '@airjlee', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/airjlee/stock-llm', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/airjlee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900295+00:00'),
  ('gedcom', 'GEDCOM', 'This GEDCOM MCP server provides AI agents with complete genealogical data management capabilities for creating, editing, and querying family history information from GEDCOM files. Built primarily by AI agents with Python, it integrates with the python-gedcom library and FastMCP framework to offer tools for loading genealogy files, managing people and families, finding relationships between individuals, generating family trees and timelines, and performing complex genealogical analysis including duplicate detection and statistical reporting. The implementation includes advanced features like bidirectional relationship pathfinding, place and name normalization utilities, caching for performance optimization, and the ability to automatically populate GEDCOM files from web sources like Wikipedia, making it particularly useful for genealogy research, family history documentation, and AI-assisted biographical content generation.', '@airy10', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/airy10/gedcommcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/airy10.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900353+00:00'),
  ('airylark-translation', 'AiryLark Translation', 'Airylark MCP Server provides translation capabilities for AI applications through a Node.js implementation. It integrates with external translation APIs to enable seamless language conversion within the Model Context Protocol framework. The server is containerized with Docker for easy deployment and configured through environment variables to support different translation models and API endpoints. Ideal for multilingual AI applications that need to process text in various languages.', '@wizd', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/wizd/airylark-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/wizd.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900374+00:00'),
  ('aistatusdashboard', 'AIStatusDashboard', 'Provides real-time monitoring data for AI provider APIs including OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, Mistral, Cohere, and others. Enables querying current status summaries, searching historical incidents, and listing monitored providers. Functions as an AI reliability control plane for tracking uptime, response latencies, and generating fallback policies.', '@aistatusdashboard', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/aistatusdashboard/aistatusdashboard', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aistatusdashboard.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900406+00:00'),
  ('aistor', 'AIStor', 'An MCP server implementation for AIStore, a distributed object storage system designed for AI workloads.', '@minio', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 39, 'https://github.com/minio/mcp-server-aistor', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/minio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900426+00:00'),
  ('agentkits-memory', 'AgentKits Memory', 'AgentKits Memory provides persistent memory capabilities for AI coding assistants through a comprehensive MCP server implementation that captures, stores, and retrieves project context across coding sessions. Built by AityTech, it automatically hooks into Claude Code sessions to capture tool usage observations, decisions, and patterns, storing them in a local SQLite database with optional vector search capabilities using offline embeddings via Transformers.js. The system includes hybrid search combining keyword and semantic similarity, token economics tracking to measure memory ROI, and multiple interfaces including CLI tools, web viewer, and direct MCP integration.', '@aitytech', 'databases', 'Unknown', 54, 'https://github.com/aitytech/agentkits-memory', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aitytech.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900438+00:00'),
  ('aiven', 'Aiven', 'The Aiven MCP Server provides AI assistants with direct access to Aiven''s cloud database and messaging services through the Aiven API. It exposes tools for listing projects, services, and retrieving detailed service information for PostgreSQL, Kafka, ClickHouse, Valkey, and OpenSearch running in the Aiven ecosystem. Built with FastMCP and requiring minimal configuration through environment variables, this server enables LLMs to interact with and manage cloud data infrastructure, making it valuable for building full-stack solutions that require database operations without leaving the AI assistant interface.', '@aiven-open', 'databases', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/aiven-open/mcp-aiven', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aiven-open.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900449+00:00'),
  ('documentation-search-groq-serper', 'Documentation Search (Groq + Serper)', 'Built by AIwithhassan using FastMCP, this server provides intelligent web scraping and documentation search capabilities by integrating Serper API for web search with Groq''s LLM API for content processing. Rather than using traditional HTML parsing, it leverages Groq''s language models to intelligently clean and structure web content by processing it in chunks, making it particularly valuable for developers who need to quickly access and understand documentation from multiple sources. The server focuses on popular development libraries like LangChain, LlamaIndex, OpenAI, and UV package manager, extracting clean, readable content that can be easily consumed in conversations.', '@aiwithhassan', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/aiwithhassan/mcp-server-python', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aiwithhassan.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900480+00:00'),
  ('filesystem', 'Filesystem', 'This MCP server implementation provides filesystem operations for AI assistants. Developed by ai-yliu, it offers tools for reading, writing, and manipulating files and directories, with built-in security measures to restrict access to specified directories. The server is designed for use cases requiring AI-assisted file management, content analysis, or automated file system interactions within allowed directories.', '@ai-yliu', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/ai-yliu/filesystem-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ai-yliu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900517+00:00'),
  ('tinypng', 'TinyPNG', 'TinyPNG MCP server provides image optimization capabilities through the TinyPNG API, enabling compression and resizing of both local and remote images. The implementation offers three main tools: compressing local images, compressing remote images via URL, and resizing images with various methods (scale, fit, cover, thumb). Built by Chuck, this server requires a TinyPNG API key and returns detailed compression statistics including original size, compressed size, and compression ratio, making it ideal for workflows that need efficient image optimization without quality loss.', '@aiyogg', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/aiyogg/tinypng-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aiyogg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900561+00:00'),
  ('recode', 'ReCode', 'Integrates with the ReCode VS Code extension to provide access to code history and change tracking data, enabling analysis of coding patterns, debugging assistance based on historical changes, and contextual code recommendations by leveraging temporal development data.', '@aiyuekuang', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/aiyuekuang/recode-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aiyuekuang.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900582+00:00'),
  ('email-server', 'Email Server', 'MCP email server implementation that provides IMAP and SMTP functionality. Integrates with existing email providers to allow AI assistants to send and receive emails on behalf of users. Includes a configuration UI and supports deployment via Docker. Useful for automating email-based workflows and enabling AI agents to manage email communications.', '@ai-zerolab', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 184, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab/mcp-email-server', 'mcp-email-server', 42881, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900601+00:00'),
  ('toolbox', 'Toolbox', 'This MCP server implementation provides a comprehensive toolbox for enhancing Large Language Models (LLMs) through various API integrations and utilities. Developed by ai-zerolab, it offers tools for executing command line instructions, interacting with Figma files, and performing file operations. The server is designed with an extensible architecture, allowing easy addition of new API integrations. It supports Claude Desktop and other MCP-enabled LLMs, making it suitable for a wide range of use cases including UI/UX design workflows, automated file management, and enhanced LLM interactions with external services.', '@ai-zerolab', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 28, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab/mcp-toolbox', 'mcp-toolbox', 15330, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900645+00:00'),
  ('yourware', 'Yourware', 'Yourware MCP is a server that enables AI assistants to upload projects directly to yourware.so, a web hosting platform. Developed by Wh1isper, it provides tools for authenticating with the Yourware API, checking credentials, and uploading single files or entire directories with automatic compression. The implementation supports multiple transport methods (stdio and SSE) and integrates with AI assistants like Claude through configurations for Cursor, Cline, and other MCP-compatible clients. This server is particularly useful for developers who want to quickly showcase their web projects online without leaving their development environment.', '@ai-zerolab', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab/yourware-mcp', 'yourware-mcp', 4015, 'https://github.com/ai-zerolab.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900669+00:00'),
  ('gmail', 'Gmail', 'This Gmail MCP server, developed by AJ Brown, integrates Gmail functionality into AI assistants using the Model Context Protocol. It provides secure access to Gmail inbox contents and search capabilities through OAuth2 authentication with the Gmail API. The server offers tools for viewing recent emails and performing advanced searches using Gmail''s query syntax. By connecting AI capabilities with email management, this implementation enables assistants to analyze inbox contents, find specific messages, or automate email-related tasks. It is particularly useful for applications requiring email content analysis, personal information management, or any scenario where an AI system needs to interact with and reason about email data while maintaining user privacy and security.', '@ajbr0wn', 'communication', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/ajbr0wn/gmail-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ajbr0wn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900704+00:00'),
  ('jetson-nano-management', 'Jetson Nano Management', 'JetsonMCP server by Ajeet Singh Raina provides AI assistants with complete remote management capabilities for NVIDIA Jetson Nano edge computing systems through SSH connections, offering nine specialized tool categories including hardware control (power modes, thermal management, GPIO), AI workload deployment (CUDA verification, ML framework installation, model optimization with TensorRT), system administration (package management, service control), and container orchestration with GPU acceleration support. Built with Python using paramiko for SSH connectivity and featuring comprehensive error handling, connection pooling, and mock testing capabilities, the implementation enables conversational management of edge AI infrastructure including JetPack SDK management, performance optimization, security hardening, and monitoring workflows. Designed for developers deploying AI applications on Jetson hardware, system administrators managing edge computing fleets, and AI researchers requiring programmatic access to GPU-accelerated inference optimization and thermal management on embedded systems.', '@ajeetraina', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/ajeetraina/jetsonmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ajeetraina.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900745+00:00'),
  ('discord', 'Discord', 'A production-ready Discord server built by aj-geddes that provides 46+ tools for Discord API integration including messaging, channels, threads, roles, members, moderation, emojis, stickers, scheduled events, and auto-moderation. Features robust error handling with custom Discord-specific exceptions, guild validation utilities, structured logging, and supports both HTTP and stdio transports with Docker and Kubernetes deployment configurations. The implementation includes guided prompts for server setup, event creation, moderation workflows, and permission auditing, making it useful for Discord community management, automated moderation systems, and Discord bot development workflows.', '@aj-geddes', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/aj-geddes/discord-agent-mcp', 'discord-mcp-server', 2690, 'https://github.com/aj-geddes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900768+00:00'),
  ('toon-context', 'TOON Context', 'Converts verbose JSON structures to Token-Optimized Object Notation (TOON) format, achieving 40-60% token reduction while maintaining complete data integrity. Features intelligent pattern detection for API responses, database records, and consistent schema arrays, with automatic compression strategy selection. Provides bidirectional conversion tools, batch processing capabilities, pattern analysis, and comprehensive monitoring for tracking token usage across conversations. Valuable for managing large datasets, optimizing API documentation, and working within context window limitations.', '@aj-geddes', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/aj-geddes/toon-context-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aj-geddes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900780+00:00'),
  ('secret-management', 'Secret Management', 'Desktop application with MCP server for secure secret management. Stores API keys and tokens in a local SQLite database while providing search and write capabilities that keep sensitive data protected from AI assistants. Enables coding assistants to generate .env configuration files without ever seeing the actual secret values.', '@akarenin', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/akarenin/secret-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akarenin.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900791+00:00'),
  ('akash-network', 'Akash Network', 'Akash MCP Server is a TypeScript implementation that bridges AI agents with the Akash Network, enabling deployment and management of decentralized applications through typed tools. Developed by Overclock Labs, it provides essential functionality for interacting with Akash''s blockchain-based cloud computing marketplace, including wallet authentication, certificate management, deployment creation, bid management, and lease operations. The server leverages the Model Context Protocol to standardize communication between AI models and Akash services, making it particularly valuable for AI assistants that need to programmatically deploy applications, manage cloud resources, or interact with decentralized infrastructure without requiring deep technical knowledge of the Akash ecosystem.', '@akash-network', 'development', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/akash-network/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akash-network.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900834+00:00'),
  ('akave-storage', 'Akave Storage', 'This MCP server provides a complete interface to Akave''s S3-compatible storage platform, enabling AI assistants to manage buckets and objects through natural language commands. Built with TypeScript using the AWS SDK v3, it offers comprehensive storage operations including listing buckets, uploading/downloading files, generating signed URLs, copying objects, and managing bucket lifecycle operations like creation and deletion. The implementation features intelligent file type handling with automatic text cleaning for common formats like markdown and JSON, supports both Claude Desktop and local LLM integration via Ollama, and includes robust error handling and environment-based configuration, making it valuable for AI workflows that need to interact with cloud storage for data management, file processing, or content generation tasks.', '@akave-ai', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/akave-ai/akave-mcp', 'akave-mcp-js', 5318, 'https://github.com/akave-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900869+00:00'),
  ('solana', 'Solana', 'This Solana MCP server, developed by Alex Cheng, provides integration with the Solana blockchain. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it enables AI assistants to interact with Solana''s Web3.js library for blockchain operations. The implementation focuses on providing a standardized interface for Solana transactions and data retrieval, making it easier to incorporate blockchain functionality into AI workflows. It''s particularly useful for developers and teams working with Solana who want to automate blockchain interactions, enabling use cases such as automated token transfers, smart contract deployments, and AI-assisted blockchain analytics without deep Solana expertise.', '@akc2267', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/akc2267/solana-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akc2267.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900925+00:00'),
  ('github-agentic-chat', 'GitHub Agentic Chat', 'GitHub Agentic Chat MCP Server enables natural language interaction with GitHub repositories through a Go-based implementation that integrates with the GitHub API and provides vector search capabilities. It offers tools for searching repositories, creating issues, and performing semantic searches across stored documents using PostgreSQL with pgvector extension. The server connects to Claude Desktop through the Model Context Protocol, making it particularly valuable for developers who want to interact with GitHub and related documentation through conversational AI without leaving their chat interface.', '@akhidastech', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/akhidastech/github-agentic-chat-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akhidastech.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900938+00:00'),
  ('elasticsearch', 'Elasticsearch', 'This MCP server provides direct integration with Elasticsearch clusters, enabling AI assistants to search indices, retrieve mappings, and list available indices through natural language interactions. Built with FastMCP and the official Elasticsearch Python client, it offers three core tools: search_index for query string searches, list_indices for discovering available data sources, and get_index_mappings for understanding data structure. The implementation includes a demonstration client using LangChain and Ollama''s DeepSeek model, with example penalty kick data from CSV files, making it valuable for organizations that need AI-powered access to their Elasticsearch data warehouses, log analysis systems, or search infrastructure without requiring users to learn Elasticsearch query syntax.', '@akhilvis', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/akhilvis/elastic-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akhilvis.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.900988+00:00'),
  ('macos-gui-control', 'macOS GUI Control', 'Provides complete macOS system automation through mouse operations, keyboard input, screen capture, window management, and AppleScript execution with safety-focused command filtering.', '@akira-papa', 'browser-automation', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/akira-papa/macos-gui-control-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akira-papa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.901043+00:00'),
  ('notion', 'Notion', 'This MCP server, developed by suekou, enables seamless integration between Notion workspaces and AI systems like Claude Desktop. Built using the Model Context Protocol, it provides a comprehensive set of tools for interacting with Notion''s API, including block manipulation, page and database operations, and querying capabilities. The implementation focuses on exposing Notion''s features through a standardized interface, offering functionality to create, retrieve, update, and delete various Notion elements. It''s particularly useful for organizations looking to incorporate Notion''s collaborative workspace features into their AI workflows, enabling use cases such as automated note-taking, knowledge base management, and AI-assisted content creation without directly interacting with Notion''s API.', '@akira-papa', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/akira-papa/akirapapa-mcp-notion-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/akira-papa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.901055+00:00');





Features
- Safe execution of common Unix/macOS commands
- Security validation based on command type
- Command categorization (read, write, system)
- Interactive permission management
- Session-based approval system
- Configuration via environment variables or JSON file
- Comprehensive command filtering and pattern matching
- Support for command chaining via pipes (|), semicolons (;), and ampersands (&)
- Claude Desktop compatibility mode with auto-approval
- Detailed command metadata and help for AI assistants

Read Commands
ls, pwd, cat, less, head, tail, grep, find, which, du, df, file, sort, etc.

Write Commands
cp, mv, rm, mkdir, rmdir, touch, chmod, chown, etc.

System Commands
ps, top, htop, who, netstat, ifconfig, ping, etc.', '@andresthor', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/andresthor/cmd-line-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/andresthor.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.907397+00:00'),
  ('command-security-layer', 'Command Security Layer', 'This MCP command server, developed by an unnamed creator, implements a robust security layer for handling and processing commands. Built with Python and utilizing the Model Context Protocol SDK, it provides tools for input validation, sanitization, and auditing. The implementation focuses on enhancing command security through a multi-step verification process, including confirmation mechanisms. It''s particularly useful for systems requiring high-security command processing, enabling use cases such as critical infrastructure management, sensitive data handling, or secure automation without compromising on safety or auditability.', '@andrew-beniash', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/andrew-beniash/mcp-command-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/andrew-beniash.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.907433+00:00'),
  ('fivetran', 'Fivetran', 'This MCP server provides Fivetran data pipeline management through the Fivetran REST API, enabling AI assistants to invite users, list connections, and trigger data syncs programmatically. Built using Python with FastMCP and the requests library, it offers three core tools for user management (invite_fivetran_user with email, name, and phone parameters), connection discovery (list_connections returning comma-separated connection IDs), and sync operations (sync_connection that unpauses and forces synchronization by connection ID). The implementation features environment-based authentication via FIVETRAN_AUTH_TOKEN, comprehensive logging, and includes both a standalone Fivetran connector SDK component and the main MCP server, making it valuable for data pipeline automation workflows, team onboarding processes, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to Fivetran''s data integration platform without manual dashboard navigation.', '@andrewkkchan', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/andrewkkchan/mcp_fivetran', 'mcp-fivetran', 1474, 'https://github.com/andrewkkchan.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.907466+00:00'),
  ('apostrophe-cms-generator', 'Apostrophe CMS Generator', 'Apostrophe CMS Code Generator is an AI-powered development tool that automates the creation of Apostrophe CMS modules through both a web interface and MCP server integration. The implementation provides intelligent code generation for pieces, pages, widgets, and bundles with automatic BEM-style SCSS generation, project discovery, and streaming progress updates. Built with Express.js and the MCP SDK, it integrates with Claude Code through MCP tools for natural language module requests and includes design token parsing for production-ready styling.', '@andrewmat32', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/andrewmat32/apostrophe-cms-generator', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/andrewmat32.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.907492+00:00');

Find elements using various locator strategies
Click, type, and interact with elements
Perform mouse actions (hover, drag and drop)
Handle keyboard input
Take screenshots
Upload files', '@angiejones', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 373, 'https://github.com/angiejones/mcp-selenium', '@angiejones/mcp-selenium', 22232, 'https://github.com/angiejones.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908038+00:00'),
  ('bayesian-monte-carlo-tree-search', 'Bayesian Monte Carlo Tree Search', 'MCTS MCP Server provides a Bayesian Monte Carlo Tree Search engine for AI-assisted analysis and reasoning. It enables Claude to systematically explore different angles and interpretations of topics using a probabilistic approach that balances exploration versus exploitation. The server implements multi-iteration analysis with state persistence between chat turns, approach taxonomy classification, Thompson sampling, surprise detection, and intent classification. It''s particularly valuable for users seeking deep, explorative analysis that evolves through multiple iterations, producing insightful analyses that consider diverse philosophical approaches and perspectives.', '@angrysky56', 'communication', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/angrysky56/mcts-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/angrysky56.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908081+00:00'),
  ('creator', 'Creator', 'This MCP Creator server by AI Workspace provides a meta-MCP development platform that generates other MCP servers through AI-guided workflows, offering tools for server creation with customizable templates (basic and FastMCP), template management, workflow automation, and AI guidance for best practices. Built with Python using FastMCP and featuring Jinja2 templating, Pydantic configuration management, async workflow execution, and comprehensive error handling, the implementation includes pre-built templates for Python servers with proper signal handling, lifecycle management, and MCP SDK patterns. The server supports both programmatic generation through tools and a Gradio web interface for interactive development, with built-in guidance resources covering security, performance, and coding standards, making it valuable for rapid MCP server prototyping, automated server scaffolding, and building AI assistants that can generate custom MCP integrations on demand.', '@angrysky56', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/angrysky56/mcp-creator-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/angrysky56.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908112+00:00'),
  ('logic-prover9-mace4', 'Logic (Prover9/Mace4)', 'This MCP-Logic server, developed by an AI researcher, provides automated reasoning capabilities using Prover9/Mace4 for AI systems. Built with Python 3.12+ and leveraging the MCP library, it offers tools for theorem proving, model verification, and syntax validation of logical statements. The implementation focuses on bridging formal logic with AI, enabling knowledge validation and complex reasoning. It''s particularly useful for AI assistants or applications needing to perform logical proofs, verify knowledge representations, or analyze logical implications. The server supports nested quantifiers and multiple premises, making it suitable for tasks like validating AI knowledge models, reasoning about system behaviors, or formal verification of logical arguments.', '@angrysky56', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 43, 'https://github.com/angrysky56/mcp-logic', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/angrysky56.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908156+00:00'),
  ('memvid', 'Memvid', 'This MCP server exposes Memvid''s video memory encoding and retrieval capabilities to AI clients, enabling the conversion of text content into searchable video-based memory systems. Built using FastMCP with comprehensive lifecycle management and stdout redirection for clean JSON communication, it provides tools for adding text chunks and PDFs to an encoder, building compressed video files with H.264/H.265 codecs, performing semantic search on encoded content, and chatting with the video memory using integrated LLM capabilities. The implementation features lazy initialization of Memvid components, robust error handling with detailed status responses, and proper resource cleanup through signal handlers and atexit registration, making it valuable for creating persistent knowledge bases from documents, building AI assistants with long-term memory capabilities, and enabling efficient storage and retrieval of large text corpora through Memvid''s novel video encoding approach.', '@angrysky56', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/angrysky56/memvid_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/angrysky56.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908188+00:00'),
  ('website-downloader-windows', 'Website Downloader (Windows)', 'This Windows-compatible website downloader tool for the Model Context Protocol (MCP) enables AI assistants to efficiently retrieve and store web content. Developed to address the need for a robust, Windows-friendly solution, it leverages asynchronous processing and concurrent downloads to quickly capture websites and their assets. The implementation, built with Python using libraries like aiohttp and BeautifulSoup4, offers configurable crawl depth and media file handling. It''s particularly useful for tasks like web scraping, content archiving, or offline browsing, allowing AI models to interact with web content without requiring direct internet access or complex setup procedures.', '@angrysky56', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/angrysky56/mcp-windows-website-downloader', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/angrysky56.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908234+00:00'),
  ('couchbase', 'Couchbase', 'Your project is a sophisticated Model Context Protocol (MCP) server implementation that acts as a bridge between Large Language Models (specifically Claude) and Couchbase databases. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the @modelcontextprotocol/sdk, it provides a comprehensive set of tools for database operations including document CRUD operations, scope and collection management, index handling, and N1QL query execution. The server is designed to work seamlessly with Claude Desktop, allowing natural language interactions with Couchbase databases.
The architecture is well-structured with clear separation of concerns, organized into distinct modules for different database operations. The core functionality is divided into five main tool categories: query tools for executing N1QL queries, document tools for CRUD operations, collection tools for managing collections, scope tools for scope management, and index tools for handling database indexes. Each tool is implemented with proper error handling and uses Zod for runtime type validation, making the server both robust and type-safe. The project also includes environment-based configuration and follows modern TypeScript practices with proper typing and error handling throughout the codebase.', '@aniket310101', 'databases', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/aniket310101/mcp-server-couchbase', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aniket310101.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908246+00:00'),
  ('anima', 'Anima', 'Connect AI coding agents to Anima Playground, Figma, and your design system.', '@animaapp', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/animaapp/mcp-server-guide', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/animaapp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908266+00:00'),
  ('frankfurter', 'Frankfurter', 'This MCP server provides currency exchange rate data and conversion capabilities through the Frankfurter API, offering tools for retrieving supported currencies, latest exchange rates, historical rate data, and currency conversion for both current and specific dates. Built by Anirban Basu using Python with FastMCP, it features comprehensive environment variable configuration for API endpoints and HTTP client settings, SSL certificate support for self-signed certificates and proxy servers, optional response metadata inclusion for API call details, and dynamic composition support for mounting with other MCP servers. The implementation includes Docker containerization, extensive testing with pytest, a command-line interface for tool exploration, optional LlamaIndex integration for demonstration purposes, and supports multiple transport protocols (stdio, SSE, streamable-http), making it valuable for financial applications, currency analysis workflows, and building AI assistants that need reliable foreign exchange data without manual rate lookups.', '@anirbanbasu', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/anirbanbasu/frankfurtermcp', 'frankfurtermcp', 16585, 'https://github.com/anirbanbasu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908293+00:00'),
  ('gahmen', 'Gahmen', 'An MCP server providing access to Singapore''s government data APIs, integrating both data.gov.sg and SingStat Table Builder APIs through a unified interface. Built by Aniruddha Adhikary, it exposes tools for browsing collections and datasets, searching within datasets using CKAN datastore queries, downloading filtered data, and accessing SingStat''s statistical tables with time series and cross-sectional data. The implementation includes built-in rate limiting (5 requests per minute) to comply with API quotas, comprehensive HTTP logging, and supports complex filtering operations across Singapore''s open government datasets, making it useful for policy research, economic analysis, demographic studies, and data journalism focused on Singapore.', '@aniruddha-adhikary', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/aniruddha-adhikary/gahmen-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/aniruddha-adhikary.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908323+00:00'),
  ('coinmarket', 'Coinmarket', 'This Coinmarket MCP server, developed by anjor, provides access to cryptocurrency market data via the CoinMarketCap API. It offers tools for retrieving latest currency listings and fetching quotes for specific tokens using symbols or slugs. Built in Python, the implementation exposes CoinMarketCap data through a standardized MCP interface, allowing Claude to analyze and interact with real-time crypto market information. By bridging AI models with CoinMarketCap''s extensive cryptocurrency database, this server enhances Claude''s ability to process market trends, assist with crypto portfolio analysis, and provide up-to-date information on digital assets. It is particularly useful for users seeking AI-powered insights into cryptocurrency markets, price tracking, and market cap analysis.', '@anjor', 'databases', 'Unknown', 46, 'https://github.com/anjor/coinmarket-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anjor.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908359+00:00'),
  ('leave-management-system', 'Leave Management System', 'A Python-based MCP server that automates HR leave management workflows. Provides tools for submitting leave applications, processing approvals with automatic or manual decision-making, tracking employee leave balances through MCP resources, and generating leave reports. Built with FastMCP framework to enable conversational access to leave data and workflows within AI-powered business applications. Supports simulated email notifications and is designed for integration with organizational HR systems.', '@ankaleshsarma', 'communication', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/ankaleshsarma/leavemanagementmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ankaleshsarma.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908390+00:00'),
  ('anki-mcp-server', 'Anki MCP Server', 'MCP server bridging AI assistants with Anki spaced repetition flashcard application. Provides comprehensive tools for card review (get due cards, present, record ratings), note management (create, search, update, delete with Anki query syntax), deck operations (list, create), media handling (upload/download audio/images), model template access, and AnkiWeb synchronization. Transforms study sessions into dynamic conversations where AI can explain concepts and adapt to learning style. Built with NestJS, supports STDIO and HTTP modes, requires Node.js 20+.', '@ankimcp', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 166, 'https://github.com/ankimcp/anki-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ankimcp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908431+00:00'),
  ('toon-parse', 'TOON Parse', 'Optimizes token usage for LLM interactions through two primary tools. Converts JSON, XML, YAML, and CSV data into compact Token-Oriented Object Notation (TOON) format, and processes code files by removing inline comments and minimizing whitespace while preserving functional structure and docstrings.', '@ankitpal181', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/ankitpal181/toon-parse-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ankitpal181.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908450+00:00'),
  ('anna-s-archive', 'Anna''s Archive', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with search and download capabilities for Anna''s Archive, a comprehensive repository for automated retrieval of documents including Creative Commons publications and public domain materials. Built using Go with web scraping via Colly and structured logging through Zap, it offers dual functionality as both a CLI tool and MCP server with two core operations: searching the archive by terms and downloading specific documents by MD5 hash. The implementation requires API key authentication through donations to Anna''s Archive, includes comprehensive error handling and logging, supports multiple platforms through GoReleaser automation, and emphasizes responsible use by explicitly discouraging unauthorized acquisition of copyrighted content, making it valuable for research workflows, academic document retrieval, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to open educational resources.', '@iosifache', 'development', 'Unknown', 758, 'https://github.com/iosifache/annas-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/iosifache.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908484+00:00'),
  ('annotation', 'Annotation', 'Annotation MCP server that provides persistent note-taking and task management functionality through a JSON file-based storage system. Built by xmarlon30x2, the implementation offers comprehensive page and annotation management with tools for creating, reading, updating, and deleting pages with associated annotations that can be checked/unchecked like todo items. Features include bulk annotation operations, individual annotation management, and automatic UUID generation for all entities, with data stored locally in a configurable JSON file (defaults to ~/notes.json). Designed for users who want structured note-taking and task tracking capabilities integrated directly into their AI workflows, enabling conversational management of personal knowledge bases and todo lists without requiring external database dependencies.', '@xmarlon30x2', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/xmarlon30x2/annotation-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/xmarlon30x2.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908495+00:00'),
  ('transport-for-london', 'Transport for London', 'Transport for London (TfL) MCP server providing real-time London transport data through three core tools: line status monitoring, detailed disruption information, and journey planning between any London locations or UK postcodes. Built by anoopt using the official TfL Unified API, it handles location disambiguation intelligently by presenting users with specific station options when multiple matches are found, and supports both basic status checks and comprehensive journey planning with walking directions, platform information, and disruption alerts. The server automatically injects TFL_API_KEY from environment variables and supports multiple transport modes including tube, bus, rail, and walking, making it valuable for commuters, travelers, and applications needing accurate London transport information.', '@anoopt', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/anoopt/london-tfl-journey-status-mcp-server', 'london-transport-mcp', 297, 'https://github.com/anoopt.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908526+00:00'),
  ('microsoft-to-do', 'Microsoft To Do', 'Integrates with Microsoft To Do to enable task and list management through OAuth 2.1 authentication via Microsoft Entra ID. Provides tools for creating, updating, and deleting tasks and lists, with support for due dates, reminders, and task importance levels. Deployed as a remote server on Cloudflare Workers with comprehensive OAuth flow implementation.', '@anoopt', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/anoopt/remote-mcp-entra-id-todo', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anoopt.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908543+00:00'),
  ('outlook-meetings-scheduler', 'Outlook Meetings Scheduler', 'Outlook Meetings Scheduler MCP Server provides integration with Microsoft Graph API to manage calendar events in Microsoft Outlook. The TypeScript implementation enables AI assistants to create, read, update, and delete calendar events, find people by name, and manage event attendees. It features tools for scheduling meetings with specific parameters like time, location, and attendees, making it particularly valuable for automating calendar management tasks and integrating with other MCP servers like GitHub for comprehensive workflow automation.', '@anoopt', 'development', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/anoopt/outlook-meetings-scheduler-mcp-server', 'outlook-meetings-scheduler', 4980, 'https://github.com/anoopt.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908568+00:00'),
  ('obsidian-omnisearch', 'Obsidian Omnisearch', 'This MCP server, developed by anpigon, enables AI assistants to search Obsidian vaults using the Omnisearch plugin. It provides a REST API interface to query notes and retrieve absolute paths to matching results. The server uses FastMCP to expose the search functionality as a tool, allowing seamless integration with other services. By connecting AI capabilities with personal knowledge management, this implementation empowers assistants to leverage users'' existing note collections. It is particularly useful for applications requiring context from personal notes, research assistance, or any scenario where an AI system needs to access and reason about information stored in Obsidian vaults.', '@anpigon', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 25, 'https://github.com/anpigon/mcp-server-obsidian-omnisearch', 'mcp-server-obsidian-omnisearch', 5189, 'https://github.com/anpigon.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908614+00:00'),
  ('adobe-illustrator', 'Adobe Illustrator', 'Illustrator MCP Server enables AI assistants to execute JavaScript/ExtendScript code directly in Adobe Illustrator and view the results. Developed by Anshul Dalua, this MacOS-only implementation uses AppleScript to bridge between the MCP protocol and Illustrator''s scripting capabilities, allowing bots to programmatically generate and manipulate vector graphics. The server provides two main tools: one for running arbitrary code in the current Illustrator document and another for capturing screenshots of the Illustrator window to visualize results, making it particularly useful for automated design tasks and graphic generation workflows.', '@anshuldalua', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/anshuldalua/illustrator-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anshuldalua.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908641+00:00'),
  ('redshift', 'Redshift', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with secure Amazon Redshift database access through a FastMCP-based implementation built by Anshul Patre using Python with configurable security modes (readonly, readwrite, admin) that enforce SQL operation restrictions based on environment variables. The implementation features automatic connection management using environment variables or manual credentials, comprehensive database operations including schema/table discovery and query execution, and built-in SQL command filtering that prevents dangerous operations in restricted modes. Built with support for both Amazon''s official redshift-connector and PostgreSQL-compatible drivers, automatic reconnection capabilities, and structured JSON responses for all operations, it serves data analysts needing conversational database querying, developers requiring AI-assisted data exploration, and teams wanting secure programmatic access to Redshift warehouses with granular permission controls and connection state management.', '@anshulpatre', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/anshulpatre/my-redshift-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anshulpatre.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908652+00:00'),
  ('world-bank-data', 'World Bank Data', 'This World Bank MCP server, developed by Anshuman Saxena, enables AI assistants to interact with the World Bank''s open data API. Built in Python using the MCP framework, it provides tools for listing countries and indicators, as well as analyzing various socioeconomic metrics. The implementation stands out by offering a controlled interface for data exploration and analysis, making it safer and more structured for AI systems to access World Bank data. By connecting AI capabilities with a comprehensive global development database, this server allows for in-depth analysis of international economic trends, poverty statistics, and other key indicators. It is particularly useful for researchers, policymakers, and AI assistants working on global development projects, economic analysis, or cross-country comparisons.', '@anshumax', 'databases', 'Unknown', 45, 'https://github.com/anshumax/world_bank_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anshumax.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908664+00:00'),
  ('ansvar-security-controls', 'Ansvar Security Controls', 'Provides searchable access to 28 security and compliance frameworks through the Secure Controls Framework (SCF) dataset. Supports bidirectional mapping between frameworks such as ISO 27001, NIST 800-53, NIST CSF, DORA, PCI DSS, CMMC, SOC 2, HIPAA, GDPR, NIS2, and others. Enables full-text search across control descriptions, framework-specific control retrieval, and optional integration with purchased standards for official clause text.', '@ansvar-systems', 'search', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/ansvar-systems/security-controls-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ansvar-systems.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908704+00:00'),
  ('ansvar-us-regulations', 'Ansvar US Regulations', 'Provides searchable access to US federal and state regulatory requirements across 14 regulations. Covers healthcare (HIPAA, FDA 21 CFR Part 11), privacy (CCPA/CPRA, Virginia CDPA, Colorado CPA, Connecticut CTDPA, Utah UCPA), financial (SOX, GLBA, FFIEC, NYDFS 500), education and children (FERPA, COPPA), and environmental (EPA 40 CFR Part 68). Supports full-text search, section retrieval, cross-regulation comparison, and NIST 800-53/CSF control mapping.', '@ansvar-systems', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/ansvar-systems/us_compliance_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ansvar-systems.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908720+00:00'),
  ('workspace', 'Workspace', 'A comprehensive development environment server that provides secure access to file operations, code execution, and frontend preview capabilities. Features include Excel and CSV processing with template support, web crawling and search tools, Mermaid diagram generation, PDF and Office document handling, and sandboxed Python/Node.js execution with resource limits. Includes workspace isolation per user session via virtual path system, SSE protocol support for AI platform integration, and a web-based admin interface for monitoring.', '@answerlink', 'development', 'Unknown', 122, 'https://github.com/answerlink/mcp-workspace-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/answerlink.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908744+00:00'),
  ('perfetto-trace-analyzer', 'Perfetto Trace Analyzer', 'This MCP server provides comprehensive Perfetto trace analysis capabilities for Android performance debugging and profiling. Built by Antariksh with Python and the Perfetto trace processor, it offers specialized tools for detecting ANRs, analyzing frame jank, profiling CPU utilization, identifying memory leaks, examining heap dominator trees, and detecting thread contention issues. The implementation features persistent connection management with automatic reconnection, unified JSON response formatting across all tools, and integration with Perfetto''s standard library modules for advanced analysis workflows. It''s designed for Android developers, performance engineers, and QA teams who need AI-assisted trace analysis for debugging app performance issues, identifying bottlenecks, and conducting systematic performance investigations without requiring deep Perfetto SQL expertise.', '@antarikshc', 'databases', 'Unknown', 104, 'https://github.com/antarikshc/perfetto-mcp', 'perfetto-mcp', 4580, 'https://github.com/antarikshc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908758+00:00'),
  ('kpic', 'KPIC', 'Provides access to the Korea Pharmaceutical Information Center (KPIC) API for retrieving comprehensive drug and pharmaceutical information. Built with TypeScript and the MCP SDK, this server enables querying Korean pharmaceutical databases for drug details, interactions, safety information, and regulatory data. Useful for healthcare applications, medical research, drug safety analysis, and pharmaceutical compliance workflows where access to Korean drug information is required.', '@antegral', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/antegral/kpic-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/antegral.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908770+00:00'),
  ('nuxt-js', 'Nuxt.js', 'Based on the error message indicating a failed Git clone for the antfu/nuxt-mcp repository, this appears to be an MCP server implementation by Anthony Fu (antfu) designed to integrate with Nuxt.js, the popular Vue.js framework for building web applications. Without access to the actual repository contents due to the clone failure, the implementation likely provides tools for interacting with Nuxt projects, potentially offering capabilities like project scaffolding, configuration management, or development workflow automation. Given antfu''s expertise in the Vue.js ecosystem and tooling, this server would be valuable for developers working with Nuxt applications who need AI assistance with project setup, configuration, or development tasks.', '@antfu', 'development', 'Unknown', 899, 'https://github.com/antfu/nuxt-mcp-dev', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/antfu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908814+00:00'),
  ('skill-retriever', 'Skill Retriever', 'Graph-based retrieval system for Claude Code components (agents, skills, commands, hooks, MCPs, settings, sandboxes) that combines vector similarity search with knowledge graph traversal using Personalized PageRank and flow-based pruning. Crawls repositories with multiple layout strategies, extracts metadata from YAML frontmatter, and builds relationship graphs between components. Features dependency resolution, conflict detection, usage tracking with co-selection patterns, and automatic repository synchronization via webhooks or polling.', '@anthonyalcaraz', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/anthonyalcaraz/skill-retriever', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anthonyalcaraz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908871+00:00'),
  ('ranex-framework', 'Ranex Framework', 'Ranex Framework is a hybrid AI-governance framework that combines Rust-based security scanning with Python application development through @Contract decorators for enforcing state machine transitions and schema validation. It integrates static application security testing, antipattern detection, dependency vulnerability scanning via OSV database, architectural layer enforcement, and database schema validation into a unified system with FastAPI middleware support. The MCP server exposes tools for architecture validation, security scanning, and database operations.', '@anthonykewl20', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/anthonykewl20/ranex-framework', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/anthonykewl20.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908896+00:00'),
  ('chrome-applescript', 'Chrome AppleScript', 'Enables programmatic control of Google Chrome through AppleScript on macOS. Provides tab management (open, close, switch, list), navigation controls (reload, back, forward), JavaScript execution within tabs, and page content extraction. Designed as a Desktop Extensions demonstration showing how to build browser automation servers without requiring browser-specific extensions.', '@modelcontextprotocol', 'development', 'Unknown', 1755, 'https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/mcpb/tree/HEAD/examples/chrome-applescript', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908929+00:00'),
  ('compiler-explorer', 'Compiler Explorer', 'Compiler Explorer MCP is a server that connects LLMs to the Compiler Explorer API, enabling them to compile code, explore compiler features, and analyze optimizations across different compilers and languages. The implementation provides three main tools: listing supported programming languages, retrieving available compilers for a specific language, and compiling source code with customizable options and filters. Built with FastMCP and asynchronous HTTP requests, it handles error cases gracefully and supports various compilation parameters, making it particularly valuable for developers and educators who want to compare compiler behaviors, investigate optimization differences, or explore language feature support without leaving their AI assistant conversation.', '@torshepherd', 'development', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/torshepherd/compiler-explorer-mcp', 'compiler-explorer-mcp', 3223, 'https://github.com/torshepherd.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.908976+00:00'),
  ('everart', 'EverArt', 'This EverArt MCP server, developed by Anthropic, provides AI assistants with image generation capabilities using the EverArt API. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the EverArt SDK, it offers a streamlined interface for creating images from text prompts using multiple AI models. The server implements robust error handling, automatic browser opening for generated images, and supports various image styles including photorealistic and vector art. By abstracting the complexities of API communication and image generation, it allows AI systems to easily incorporate visual content creation into their workflows. This implementation is particularly valuable for creative applications, content generation, and visual design tasks, enabling use cases such as automated illustration, concept visualization, and rapid prototyping of visual ideas.', '@modelcontextprotocol', 'development', 'Unknown', 227, 'https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers-archived/tree/HEAD/src/everart', '@modelcontextprotocol/server-everart', 18377, 'https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.909026+00:00'),
  ('glean', 'Glean', 'This MCP server implementation, developed by Anthropic, integrates the Glean API to provide Search and Chat functionalities. It uses TypeScript and the @modelcontextprotocol/sdk to create a server that can be easily deployed using Docker. The implementation offers two main tools: a search function that queries Glean''s search API, and a chat function that interacts with Glean''s chatbot. It''s designed for organizations already using Glean who want to incorporate these capabilities into AI-assisted workflows, enabling natural language interactions with their knowledge base and chatbot through the MCP protocol.', '@longyi1207', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/longyi1207/glean-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/longyi1207.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.909093+00:00'),
  ('4o-image', '4o-image', '4o-image MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the 4o-image API for generating and editing images through text prompts. Built with Node.js and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it exposes a generateImage tool that supports both text-to-image creation and image editing with base64 inputs. The implementation features real-time progress updates, automatic browser opening of generated images, and robust error handling, making it valuable for AI systems that need to create high-quality art, 3D characters, or custom images based on user descriptions.', '@antipas', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/antipas/4oimage-mcp', '4oimage-mcp', 5405, 'https://github.com/antipas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.909158+00:00');






Interact naturally with AIs to build and access your knowledge base.

1
Build on Past Knowledge
AI references previous notes in future conversations.

"Let''s continue our conversation about coffee brewing."
AI retrieves relevant notes rather than loading everything.

2
Chat Naturally
Have normal conversations with AI assistants like Claude.

"Find information about pour over coffee methods."
AI searches your knowledge base and summarizes findings.

3
Save Knowledge
Ask Claude to create a note about your conversation.

"Create a note about coffee brewing methods."
AI creates a structured note with observations and relations.', '@basicmachines-co', 'development', 'Unknown', 2602, 'https://github.com/basicmachines-co/basic-memory', 'basic-memory', 245094, 'https://github.com/basicmachines-co.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.918813+00:00');


Install this server by
```
pip install mcp-serverman
mcp-serverman client init
mcp-serverman companion
```', '@benhaotang', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/benhaotang/mcp-serverman', 'mcp-serverman', 4856, 'https://github.com/benhaotang.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919757+00:00'),
  ('jsondiffpatch', 'JsonDiffPatch', 'jsondiffpatch is a JavaScript library that compares and patches JSON objects, providing a compact delta format that captures additions, modifications, deletions, and array moves. Created by Benjamin Eidelman, it features smart array diffing using LCS algorithm, multiple output formatters (HTML, console, JSON Patch RFC 6902), and text diffing for long strings. The library includes an MCP server implementation that enables AI assistants to compare text or structured data in various formats (JSON, YAML, TOML, XML) and get readable diffs. Ideal for version control systems, data synchronization, and change visualization in web applications.', '@benjamine', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 5287, 'https://github.com/benjamine/jsondiffpatch/tree/HEAD/packages/diff-mcp', 'diff-mcp', 5220, 'https://github.com/benjamine.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919813+00:00'),
  ('chrome-devtools', 'Chrome DevTools', 'This Chrome DevTools Protocol MCP server by Benjamin Rowell provides AI assistants with direct access to Chrome browser debugging capabilities through WebSocket connections to Chrome''s remote debugging interface. Built in Python with comprehensive error handling and real-time event processing, it enables browser automation, network request monitoring, DOM inspection, JavaScript execution, console log analysis, performance metrics collection, and storage management across web applications. The implementation maintains persistent connections to capture live browser data and supports headless Chrome operations, making it particularly useful for web development debugging, automated testing workflows, and performance analysis tasks where AI assistants need to interact with and analyze web applications in real-time.', '@benjaminr', 'development', 'Unknown', 287, 'https://github.com/benjaminr/chrome-devtools-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benjaminr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919845+00:00'),
  ('dev-browser', 'Dev Browser', 'A browser automation MCP server that provides programmatic control over web browsers through Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP). The implementation creates a relay server that bridges between browser extensions and AI assistants, enabling actions like navigation, element interaction, form filling, screenshot capture, and JavaScript evaluation. It includes a custom DOM snapshot system that generates AI-friendly representations of web pages with element references for precise targeting, supports named page management for organizing multiple browser tabs, and handles both CSS selectors and snapshot references for element interaction. Designed for web automation workflows, testing scenarios, and AI-driven browser interactions where traditional headless browser solutions may be insufficient.', '@benkraus', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/benkraus/dev-browser-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benkraus.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919887+00:00'),
  ('productboard', 'Productboard', 'Provides comprehensive Productboard integration with 40 specialized tools spanning feature lifecycle management, customer feedback handling, objectives and key results tracking, initiative planning, and release management. Supports full CRUD operations across products, components, companies, users, and custom fields. Runs locally with no third-party servers and stores API credentials securely in the OS keychain.', '@benmillerat', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/benmillerat/productboard-mcpb', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benmillerat.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919922+00:00'),
  ('glyph', 'Glyph', 'This Go-based MCP server by benmyles provides symbol extraction and code analysis capabilities for multiple programming languages including Go, JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, and Java using tree-sitter parsing. The implementation offers three detail levels (minimal, standard, full) for extracting functions, classes, interfaces, variables, and other code symbols from source files, with support for glob patterns including recursive directory traversal. Built with both CLI and MCP server modes, it enables AI assistants to quickly understand code structure and navigate large codebases by generating markdown-formatted symbol outlines that include signatures, line numbers, and hierarchical relationships between code elements.', '@benmyles', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/benmyles/glyph', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benmyles.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919949+00:00'),
  ('emqx', 'EMQX', 'This MCP server implementation provides EMQX MQTT broker interaction, enabling AI assistants to manage MQTT clients and publish messages. Developed by Benniu Ji, it offers tools for listing and disconnecting clients, retrieving client information, and publishing messages with configurable QoS and retention settings. The server is designed for use cases requiring real-time communication in IoT scenarios, such as monitoring connected devices or sending commands to MQTT-enabled systems.', '@benniu', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/benniu/emqx-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benniu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.919986+00:00'),
  ('bitcoin-op-return', 'Bitcoin OP_RETURN', 'MCP-OP-Return is a server implementation that bridges Bitcoin''s blockchain with AI assistants by integrating with opreturnbot.com. It enables users to create Bitcoin transactions with OP_RETURN outputs containing custom messages, permanently embedding text in the blockchain through a Lightning Network payment flow. The server exposes tools and prompts that allow MCP clients to generate Lightning invoices for message embedding and retrieve previously stored OP_RETURN messages from transactions, making blockchain data interaction accessible through conversational AI interfaces.', '@benthecarman', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/benthecarman/mcp-op-return', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benthecarman.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920029+00:00'),
  ('run-shell-command', 'Run Shell Command', 'The Run Command MCP server enables AI assistants to execute shell commands directly from Cursor chat. Based on the Model Context Protocol (MCP) framework, this TypeScript implementation allows users to run system commands through natural language prompts, such as finding services using specific ports. The server leverages Node.js and the MCP SDK to create a bridge between the AI assistant and the local system shell, making it particularly useful for developers who need to perform quick system operations without leaving their coding environment.', '@benyue1978', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/benyue1978/run-command-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benyue1978.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920117+00:00'),
  ('velero', 'Velero', 'Integrates with Velero backup systems in Kubernetes clusters to list and retrieve backup and schedule information through a read-only interface. Uses FastMCP with the Kubernetes Python client to expose tools for querying Velero Custom Resources, along with utilities for generating backup YAML configurations with customizable parameters like included/excluded namespaces, storage locations, and TTL settings. Features automatic Kubernetes configuration loading for both in-cluster and external access, structured data models using Pydantic, and resource endpoints for direct access to backup and schedule data, useful for backup monitoring, disaster recovery planning, and automated backup management workflows.', '@benzaidfoued', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/benzaidfoued/velero-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/benzaidfoued.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920139+00:00'),
  ('bugherd', 'BugHerd', 'Connects to the BugHerd bug tracking and feedback collection platform. Provides tools to list projects, browse tasks with status/priority/tag filtering, view task details including screenshots and element selectors, and read comment threads.', '@berckan', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/berckan/bugherd-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/berckan.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920164+00:00'),
  ('unreal-engine-binary-reader', 'Unreal Engine Binary Reader', 'This MCP server, developed by an unspecified author, provides tools for binary file analysis, focusing on Unreal Engine asset files (.uasset) and generic binary metadata extraction. Built with Python and leveraging the Model Context Protocol, it offers functionality to read and analyze binary file structures, with a specific emphasis on Unreal Engine assets. The implementation includes tools for parsing .uasset files and extracting metadata from various binary formats. It''s particularly useful for game developers, modders, and digital forensics professionals working with Unreal Engine assets or analyzing binary file structures, enabling use cases such as asset inspection, file format analysis, and automated binary data extraction without directly dealing with low-level binary parsing complexities.', '@berlinbra', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/berlinbra/binary-reader-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/berlinbra.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920222+00:00'),
  ('bluesky', 'BlueSky', 'This BlueSky MCP server, developed by berlinbra, provides access to BlueSky social network data through its official API. Built with Python and leveraging the Model Context Protocol, it offers tools for retrieving user profiles and social graph information. The implementation features built-in authentication handling, session management, and comprehensive error handling. It''s particularly useful for AI assistants and applications needing to incorporate BlueSky social data, enabling use cases such as user analysis, network visualization, and content discovery without directly dealing with the complexities of the BlueSky API.', '@berlinbra', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/berlinbra/bluesky-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/berlinbra.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920265+00:00'),
  ('berlin-transport', 'Berlin Transport', 'The Berlin Transport MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to Berlin''s public transportation data through the VBB API. Built using Cloudflare Workers and Durable Objects, it exposes three key tools: searching for stops by name, retrieving upcoming departures from specific stops, and planning journeys between locations. The implementation uses the Model Context Protocol SDK to standardize interactions and returns structured JSON responses that include comprehensive transit information. This server is particularly useful for travel planning in Berlin, allowing AI systems to find nearby stations, check real-time departure schedules, and calculate optimal routes between destinations without leaving the conversation context.', '@harshil1712', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/harshil1712/berlin-transport-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/harshil1712.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.920334+00:00');




Our MCP server is available at the URL https://mcp.boikot.xyz/mcp and exposes one tool called lookup_company_information which takes one parameter company_name and returns information about the company''s ethics.', '@boikot-xyz', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/boikot-xyz/boikot', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boikot-xyz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923777+00:00'),
  ('magento-2', 'Magento 2', 'The Magento 2 MCP Server connects Claude and other AI assistants to Magento 2 e-commerce platforms through a standardized interface. Developed by Bold Commerce, it provides tools for querying product information, customer data, order statistics, and revenue metrics with support for natural language date expressions and geographical filtering. The server handles authentication with Magento''s REST API, formats responses for readability, and includes comprehensive error handling. This implementation is particularly valuable for business users who need quick access to e-commerce data through conversational interfaces without navigating complex admin screens.', '@boldcommerce', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 50, 'https://github.com/boldcommerce/magento2-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boldcommerce.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923824+00:00'),
  ('bolor-brain', 'Bolor Brain', 'Implements a hierarchical cognitive architecture spanning seven tiers from individual reasoning to universal consciousness. Features five memory subsystems (working, episodic, semantic, procedural, self-model), six reasoning strategies, predictive intelligence for anticipatory behavior, and self-evolving skills that improve through variation and selection. Provides 17 tools for cognitive functions including vector embeddings for semantic search and intrinsic drive systems.', '@photoxpedia', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/photoxpedia/bolor-brain-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/photoxpedia.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923873+00:00'),
  ('dataverse-microsoft-powerplatform', 'Dataverse (Microsoft PowerPlatform)', 'DataverseMCPServer provides integration with Microsoft''s PowerPlatform API, enabling AI assistants to query and interact with Dataverse entities. Developed by bonanip512 under MIT license, this TypeScript implementation offers tools for retrieving entity metadata, attributes, relationships, option sets, and records using authenticated API requests. The server handles OAuth authentication through MSAL, manages token lifecycle, and includes intelligent filtering of API responses to improve result quality. It''s particularly valuable for users who need to access and analyze PowerPlatform data directly through natural language queries without navigating the complex Dataverse API structure.', '@bonanip512', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/bonanip512/dataversemcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bonanip512.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923909+00:00'),
  ('image-worker', 'Image Worker', 'Image Worker MCP server provides AI assistants with comprehensive image processing and cloud storage capabilities through Sharp.js and multiple upload services. Developed by BoomLinkAi, it offers tools for resizing, transforming, and applying effects to images (including HEIC/HEIF support via libheif-js), plus seamless uploading to AWS S3, Cloudflare R2, or Google Cloud Storage with configurable options for folders, metadata, and access controls. The implementation handles various input sources (file paths, URLs, base64 data) and supports advanced image operations like rotation, blur, sharpening, and format conversion, making it ideal for automated image workflows, content management systems, and applications requiring both image manipulation and cloud storage integration.', '@boomlinkai', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 18, 'https://github.com/boomlinkai/image-worker-mcp', '@boomlinkai/image-worker-mcp', 1086, 'https://github.com/boomlinkai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923929+00:00'),
  ('human-in-the-loop', 'Human In The Loop', 'This Human Loop MCP Server, developed using TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, facilitates coordination between AI agents and human operators. It provides a standardized interface for managing human-in-the-loop processes, enabling seamless integration of human judgment into AI workflows. The server''s modular structure and use of modern JavaScript features make it adaptable for various AI-assisted tasks. It is particularly suited for applications requiring human oversight or intervention in AI decision-making processes, such as content moderation, complex problem-solving, or ethical AI implementations where human values need to be incorporated into AI systems.', '@boorich', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/boorich/mcp-human-loop', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boorich.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923961+00:00'),
  ('boostsecurity', 'BoostSecurity', 'This MCP server enables AI assistants to interact with various development environments and editors through configuration and integration setup. Based on the repository structure containing configuration images for Claude, Cursor, VSCode, and Windsurf editors, it provides standardized tooling integration across multiple popular development platforms. The implementation focuses on enabling seamless AI assistant functionality within developer workflows, allowing users to leverage AI capabilities directly within their preferred coding environments through proper configuration and setup procedures.', '@boost-community', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/boost-community/boost-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boost-community.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.923984+00:00'),
  ('boothiq', 'BoothIQ', 'Connects to BoothIQ''s trade show lead capture platform to query contacts, meetings, action items, and event data. Enables retrieval and analysis of badge scans, business card captures, follow-up tasks, and event analytics collected through the BoothIQ app.', '@unknown', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://getboothiq.com/ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924008+00:00'),
  ('bootstrapblazor-documentation', 'BootstrapBlazor Documentation', 'BootstrapBlazor Copilot MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to BootstrapBlazor component documentation and source code through automated Git repository management. Built as an ASP.NET Core application using .NET 9 and the ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore package, it automatically clones and updates the BootstrapBlazor repository, then exposes tools for listing components, retrieving file structures, and accessing source code content with categorization between implementation files and examples. The implementation uses LibGit2Sharp for Git operations, includes background services for repository synchronization, and leverages .NET Aspire for observability and service orchestration, making it valuable for developers building Blazor applications who need AI assistance with BootstrapBlazor component usage and implementation details.', '@bootstrapblazor', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/bootstrapblazor/bootstrapblazor.mcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bootstrapblazor.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924038+00:00'),
  ('bitcoin-sv-wallet', 'Bitcoin SV Wallet', 'BSV-MCP provides Bitcoin SV blockchain integration tools for AI assistants, enabling wallet operations, transaction management, and ordinals (NFT) interactions. Built with Bun and TypeScript, it offers a secure environment where private keys are managed locally while exposing capabilities like sending BSV, creating and transferring ordinals, purchasing marketplace listings, and exploring blockchain data. The implementation includes market fee handling, royalty payments for NFT transactions, and comprehensive BSV-20/BSV-21 token support, making it valuable for cryptocurrency applications, digital asset management, and blockchain data analysis.', '@b-open-io', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/b-open-io/bsv-mcp', 'bsv-mcp', 7467, 'https://github.com/b-open-io.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924064+00:00'),
  ('volatility-3-memory-forensics', 'Volatility 3 Memory Forensics', 'This project bridges the powerful memory forensics capabilities of the Volatility 3 Framework with Large Language Models (LLMs) through the Model Context Protocol (MCP). It allows you to perform memory forensics analysis using natural language by exposing Volatility plugins as MCP tools that can be invoked directly by Claude or other MCP-compatible LLMs.', '@bornpresident', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 31, 'https://github.com/bornpresident/volatility-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bornpresident.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924116+00:00'),
  ('php-clock', 'PHP Clock', 'A lightweight PHP-based MCP server built with Symfony that provides current timestamp and date/time information to AI assistants like Claude. Created using the Symfony MCP Bundle and Symfony Clock components, it offers both STDIO and Server-Sent Events transport methods for integration with various AI tools. The implementation includes JWT-based authentication, rate limiting, and timezone support, making it useful for applications that need reliable access to current time data without complex setup - particularly valuable for local development environments where feeding Claude with accurate timestamp information is needed.', '@boryszielonka', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/boryszielonka/php-clock-mcp-poc', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boryszielonka.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924144+00:00'),
  ('agent-farm', 'Agent Farm', 'Agent Farm is a Python-based MCP server that implements a swarm-based task execution system. It spawns specialized AI agents with distinct roles (Scout, Worker, Memory, Guardian, Learner, Synthesizer) that collaborate to execute tasks concurrently. The system provides 30 MCP tools for system operations, file management, and knowledge base queries, with role-based tool permissions enabling secure parallel execution and achieving significant performance improvements.', '@bossx429', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/bossx429/agent-farm', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bossx429.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924180+00:00'),
  ('kubernetes-pilot', 'Kubernetes Pilot', 'K8s-pilot is a Kubernetes management tool that enables AI assistants to interact with Kubernetes clusters through a comprehensive set of tools. Built with Python and the FastMCP framework, it provides capabilities for managing contexts, namespaces, pods, deployments, services, and other Kubernetes resources. The implementation includes a client cache to optimize kubeconfig loading, supports context-aware operations with automatic namespace detection, and offers both resource listing and CRUD operations for all major Kubernetes object types, making it valuable for DevOps teams seeking to streamline cluster management through AI assistance.', '@bourbonkk', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/bourbonkk/k8s-pilot', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bourbonkk.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924202+00:00'),
  ('gemini-image-generation', 'Gemini Image Generation', 'Gemini Image Generation MCP server that enables AI assistants to create images using Google''s Gemini 2.0 Flash experimental image generation model. The implementation provides a single generateImage tool that accepts text prompts and optional parameters for aspect ratio and output format, returning base64-encoded images directly through the MCP protocol. Built with the Google Generative AI SDK and designed for users who want to integrate Gemini''s native image generation capabilities into their AI workflows without handling API authentication or response parsing manually.', '@bowwowxx', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/bowwowxx/geminimcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bowwowxx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924264+00:00'),
  ('box', 'Box', 'This MCP server provides integration with Box''s cloud content management platform, enabling AI agents from platforms like Anthropic''s Claude, Microsoft Copilot Studio, and Mistral Le Chat to access and interact with Box-stored content seamlessly. Available in two variants - a remote server hosted directly in Box that can be enabled through the Admin Console, and an open-source self-hosted version that can be cloned and run locally - it extends AI agent capabilities by allowing them to perform content-related actions on files and folders stored in Box. The implementation reduces development effort for building advanced integrations with Box''s content platform, making it valuable for organizations that need AI agents to work with their Box-managed documents, collaborate on content workflows, or automate content management tasks.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://developer.box.com/guides/box-mcp/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924294+00:00'),
  ('boxlite', 'BoxLite', 'Provides computer use capabilities through an isolated Ubuntu desktop sandbox environment, implementing Anthropic''s computer use API for safe AI agent interaction with desktop applications. Built on the BoxLite sandboxing library, it exposes a unified ''computer'' tool that enables mouse control, keyboard input, screenshot capture, and scrolling within a 1024x768 XFCE desktop environment. Designed for AI agents that need to interact with graphical applications, browse the web, or manipulate files while maintaining complete isolation from the host system through hardware-level VM virtualization.', '@boxlite-ai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/boxlite-ai/boxlite-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/boxlite-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924380+00:00'),
  ('u2', 'U2', 'Enables natural language queries to Rocket Universe and UniData MultiValue databases. Provides file operations (read, write, delete records), query execution with RetrieVe/UniQuery statements, dictionary access for exploring database structures, BASIC subroutine calls, and full transaction support with commit/rollback. Supports local stdio mode and HTTP/SSE server mode with OAuth for enterprise SSO integration.', '@bpamiri', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/bpamiri/u2-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bpamiri.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924390+00:00'),
  ('klipper-documentation', 'Klipper Documentation', 'Integrates with Klipper 3D printer firmware documentation to provide searchable access through automated Git synchronization. The server clones and indexes the official Klipper repository documentation, offering tools for searching configuration options, browsing sections, and retrieving specific documentation with intelligent content parsing and snippet generation. Uses Lunr.js for full-text search indexing and categorizes documents by difficulty level, making it useful for 3D printing enthusiasts and developers working with Klipper firmware.', '@bpuhnk', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/bpuhnk/mcp-klipper-docs', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bpuhnk.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924413+00:00'),
  ('bracketbot-multi-robot-control', 'BracketBot Multi-Robot Control', 'The Multi-Robot Control MCP server enables AI agents to simultaneously control multiple robots through existing FastAPI robot control servers. Built with Python using FastMCP, it provides a unified interface for controlling robot movement (forward, backward, left, right), playing sounds through speakers, accessing camera images, and retrieving robot status information. The implementation includes port specification to target specific robots, precise velocity control, and comprehensive error handling. This server is particularly valuable for robotics applications requiring coordinated control of multiple robots through a conversational AI interface, allowing seamless integration with the Claude desktop client which automatically runs the MCP server.', '@bracketbotcapstone', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/bracketbotcapstone/bracketbot-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bracketbotcapstone.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924464+00:00'),
  ('grok', 'Grok', 'Grok MCP provides a direct integration with Grok AI''s powerful language and vision capabilities, exposing three primary tools: chat completion, image understanding, and function calling. Built by Braden Olmstead, this TypeScript-based server enables developers to interact with Grok''s latest models through a standardized MCP interface, with a focus on seamless AI interaction across different use cases like text generation, image analysis, and intelligent function invocation.', '@bob-lance', 'development', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/bob-lance/grok-mcp', 'grok-mcp', 5287, 'https://github.com/bob-lance.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924488+00:00'),
  ('instagram-engagement', 'Instagram Engagement', 'Instagram Engagement MCP provides tools for analyzing Instagram interactions, extracting demographic insights, and identifying potential leads through a private Instagram API integration. Built by Braden Olmstead, the server enables detailed engagement analysis including sentiment tracking, account comparisons, and lead generation by processing comments, user profiles, and post metrics. Particularly useful for marketing professionals and social media strategists seeking data-driven insights from Instagram interactions.', '@bob-lance', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 41, 'https://github.com/bob-lance/instagram-engagement-mcp', 'instagram-engagement-mcp', 6931, 'https://github.com/bob-lance.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924530+00:00'),
  ('cline-personas', 'Cline Personas', 'This MCP server, developed by Brad Fair, implements a persona management system for Cline using shared components and templates. Built with TypeScript, it provides tools for creating, updating, and activating personas defined in `.clinerules` files. The implementation features component reusability, mustache-style variable substitution in templates, dependency validation, and version tracking for both components and personas. By abstracting persona management into standardized MCP endpoints, it allows AI systems to dynamically adjust their behavior and responses. This server is particularly useful for scenarios requiring flexible AI personality management, such as customer support chatbots, interactive storytelling applications, or personalized AI assistants that need to adapt to different user preferences or contexts.', '@bradfair', 'development', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/bradfair/mcp-cline-personas', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bradfair.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924562+00:00'),
  ('summarization', 'Summarization', 'This MCP implementation, developed by Remi Sebastian Kits, provides summarized output from various actions to avoid token consumption and crashes. It integrates with the Anthropic AI SDK and uses environment variables for configuration. Built with TypeScript and designed for Node.js 22+, it leverages modern JavaScript features and practices. The implementation is well-suited for developers working on AI projects that require efficient token usage, particularly when interfacing with large language models or processing extensive datasets. Its focus on summarization makes it valuable for applications needing to condense large amounts of information quickly and effectively.', '@braffolk', 'development', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/braffolk/mcp-summarization-functions', 'mcp-summarization-functions', 1195, 'https://github.com/braffolk.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924590+00:00'),
  ('shopify-store', 'Shopify Store', 'Connects to live Shopify stores through the Admin and Storefront GraphQL APIs, enabling direct store operations rather than just documentation lookups. Supports arbitrary GraphQL queries, file uploads with automatic polling, bulk import/export operations, and idempotent metaobject management. Includes automatic rate limiting based on store tier, SQLite-backed operation logging, and schema discovery for metafields and metaobject types.', '@brahim-benzarti', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/brahim-benzarti/shopify_store-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brahim-benzarti.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924601+00:00'),
  ('brainfaq', 'BrainFAQ', 'BrainFAQ provides a debugger for the BrainFuck esoteric programming language. It supports loading BrainFuck source code, stepping through instructions one at a time, running programs to completion, feeding input to waiting programs, inspecting memory and pointer state, and reading program output. The server includes overflow detection, bracket validation, and configurable memory and cell size limits.', '@labarilem', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/labarilem/brainfaq-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/labarilem.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924621+00:00'),
  ('brainrot', 'Brainrot', 'This MCP server provides persistent context management for AI coding sessions through a FastAPI backend with SQLite storage and vector search capabilities, built by ben-intrafocal using Python with SQLAlchemy, sentence-transformers, and sqlite-vec for semantic similarity search. The implementation offers project-scoped context storage with automatic project detection from working directory, supporting both basic key-value operations and advanced semantic search across stored contexts with embedding generation and similarity scoring. Features include tag-based organization, metadata support, CORS-enabled REST API, and optional vector search functionality that can be toggled via environment variables, making it valuable for developers who need to maintain coding context across different AI assistants, IDEs, and sessions while preserving architectural decisions, TODOs, and project knowledge.', '@knowhow-software-inc', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/knowhow-software-inc/brainrot-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/knowhow-software-inc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924633+00:00'),
  ('context-engineering', 'Context Engineering', 'Context Engineer MCP helps developers and product teams keep AI coding agents aligned with real project needs. It analyzes the current state of your codebase and target state for a feature, then produces clear documents: PRDs with goals and constraints, technical specs with system details, and implementation plans with step-by-step guidance.

This reduces context loss, prevents random rewrites, and keeps work focused so teams can ship faster without chaos.', '@bralca', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/bralca/context-engineering-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bralca.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924655+00:00'),
  ('branch-thinking', 'Branch Thinking', 'Branch Thinking is an MCP server that enables AI assistants to manage multiple lines of thought simultaneously through a branch-based navigation system. Built on the sequential-thinking concept, it extends functionality by supporting branch creation, cross-references between related thoughts, automatic insight generation, and priority tracking based on confidence and connections. The implementation provides commands for listing branches, focusing on specific thought paths, and viewing branch history, making it particularly valuable for complex reasoning tasks like adversarial thinking, scientific method application, design pattern exploration, and trade-off analysis.', '@ssdeanx', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/ssdeanx/branch-thinking-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ssdeanx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924699+00:00'),
  ('mrp-calculator', 'MRP Calculator', 'The MRP Calculator MCP server enables AI assistants to perform Material Requirements Planning calculations based on inventory data, forecasts, and delivery schedules. It exposes a single tool, calculate_order_need, which takes inputs including SKU location, current balance, open orders, delivery schedule, and forecast periods to determine optimal order quantities. The implementation features comprehensive input validation, batch size optimization, and detailed calculation steps with projected inventory balances. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it handles data processing through a standardized interface, making it particularly valuable for supply chain managers and inventory planners who need to make data-driven ordering decisions without switching to specialized MRP software.', '@brandon-butterwick', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/brandon-butterwick/mrp_calculation', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brandon-butterwick.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924733+00:00'),
  ('ghidra', 'Ghidra', 'GhidraMCP enables AI assistants to interact with Ghidra''s binary analysis capabilities through a WebSocket server interface. The implementation provides tools for retrieving decompiled code, analyzing functions, exploring imports/exports, and performing security analysis of binaries, with a focus on natural language queries about program behavior. Built with Java and integrated directly into Ghidra''s plugin architecture, it features automatic server startup, concurrent client handling, and contextual binary analysis - making it particularly valuable for reverse engineers who want to leverage AI assistance while working with complex binaries.', '@13bm', 'development', 'Unknown', 93, 'https://github.com/13bm/ghidramcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/13bm.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924759+00:00'),
  ('b-r-automation-studio-help', 'B&R Automation Studio Help', 'Enables full-text search across B&R Automation Studio help documentation through SQLite FTS5 indexing with BM25 ranking algorithms. Parses XML-structured help files to create searchable indexes with automatic reindexing on content changes, supporting both AS4 and AS6 versions. Provides hierarchical navigation, category filtering, HelpID-based context-sensitive lookups, and auto-generated links to B&R online help resources for industrial automation developers working with hardware modules, motion control functions, and programming libraries.', '@brdk-public', 'databases', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/brdk-public/as-help-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brdk-public.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924819+00:00'),
  ('breez-lightning', 'Breez Lightning', 'A Lightning Network wallet MCP server built by Breez that integrates with the Breez SDK Spark to provide Bitcoin Lightning payment functionality through FastMCP. The implementation offers core wallet operations including balance checking, payment sending, invoice creation, transaction history, and node information retrieval, with support for both mainnet and testnet networks. Features Docker containerization with multiple transport modes (stdio, HTTP, ASGI), comprehensive error handling, and structured JSON responses for all operations, making it useful for building AI assistants that can interact with Lightning wallets, automated payment systems, and Bitcoin Lightning integration workflows.', '@breez', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/breez/breez-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/breez.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924842+00:00'),
  ('chain-of-draft-prompt-tool', 'Chain of Draft Prompt Tool', 'MCP Chain of Draft Prompt Tool is a server implementation that enables structured, multi-step prompt workflows through a chain execution system. Built by Brendan Copley, it organizes prompts into categories like research, analysis, and development, with each prompt stored as a markdown file containing system messages and user templates. The server supports both individual prompts and complex chains where outputs from one step become inputs for subsequent steps, making it particularly valuable for workflows requiring progressive refinement such as deep research, code review, and documentation generation.', '@brendancopley', 'development', 'Unknown', 18, 'https://github.com/brendancopley/mcp-chain-of-draft-prompt-tool', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brendancopley.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924883+00:00'),
  ('nvidia-brev', 'Nvidia Brev', 'This Brev MCP server implementation, developed by tmonty12, provides a bridge between the Model Context Protocol and Brev''s cloud development platform. It enables AI assistants to interact with Brev resources and operations through natural language commands. Built with Python 3.10+ and leveraging the Brev CLI''s authentication, it offers functionality for managing Brev workspaces, deployments, and other cloud resources. The implementation stands out by focusing specifically on Brev''s ecosystem and tooling. It is particularly useful for developers and DevOps teams looking to streamline their Brev workflows, automate cloud resource management, or integrate AI-assisted operations into their existing Brev-based projects.', '@brevdev', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/brevdev/brev-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brevdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.924990+00:00'),
  ('sharepoint', 'SharePoint', 'The SharePoint MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to organizational SharePoint content through Microsoft Graph API integration. Developed by Brian Cusack, this TypeScript implementation exposes SharePoint documents, folders, and sites as resources while offering tools for document searching, content retrieval, and folder exploration. The server authenticates with Microsoft Entra using client credentials and translates requests into appropriate Graph API calls, returning formatted results. It includes specialized prompts for common tasks like document summarization and relevant content discovery, making it particularly valuable for users who need to access, search, and analyze corporate knowledge stored in SharePoint without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@briancusack', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/briancusack/mcpsharepoint', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/briancusack.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925049+00:00'),
  ('ip-geolocation', 'IP Geolocation', 'This MCP server, developed by Brian Connelly, provides IP geolocation services using the ipinfo.io API. Built with Python and leveraging the Model Context Protocol, it offers detailed location and network information for any IP address. The implementation focuses on delivering clean, formatted output for AI agents like Claude, including data such as city, region, country, coordinates, timezone, and organization. It requires an ipinfo.io API token for authentication. The server is particularly useful for applications requiring location-based insights, enabling use cases such as user location verification, content localization, and network analysis without complex API integrations.', '@briandconnelly', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 42, 'https://github.com/briandconnelly/mcp-server-ipinfo', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/briandconnelly.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925094+00:00'),
  ('laravel-companion', 'Laravel Companion', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with comprehensive access to Laravel documentation and package recommendations through intelligent search and browsing capabilities. Built with Python using FastMCP and featuring automatic documentation synchronization from the official Laravel GitHub repository, it supports multiple Laravel versions (6.x through 12.x), external service documentation (Forge, Vapor, Envoyer, Nova), and includes a curated package catalog with over 20 popular Laravel packages. The implementation features advanced search with context extraction, documentation structure analysis, intelligent package recommendations based on use case descriptions, and automatic updates with caching for performance, making it valuable for Laravel developers seeking quick access to framework documentation, discovering appropriate packages for specific functionality, and getting implementation guidance without leaving their development workflow.', '@brianirish', 'development', 'Unknown', 31, 'https://github.com/brianirish/laravel-mcp-companion', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brianirish.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925170+00:00'),
  ('brian', 'Brian', 'A specialized MCP server that uses the Brian AI SDK to retrieve transaction data from blockchain addresses via natural language prompts. Built with TypeScript and Bun, it provides a simple tool for extracting blockchain transaction information by translating user prompts into structured data retrieval, with flexible support for specifying chain ID and address.', '@brian-knows', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/brian-knows/mcp-server-brian', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brian-knows.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925193+00:00'),
  ('africa-s-talking-sms', 'Africa''s Talking SMS', 'Africastalking MCP Server enables Claude Desktop to send SMS messages through Africa''s Talking SMS API. Built with TypeScript, it provides a simple tool for sending text messages to recipients across African mobile networks, supporting features like dynamic message customization and sender ID configuration. The implementation requires configuration of API credentials in the claude_desktop_config.json file, making it particularly useful for applications needing to send notifications, alerts, or engage users via SMS directly from Claude Desktop.', '@brian-mwangi-developer', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/brian-mwangi-developer/africastalking-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brian-mwangi-developer.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925245+00:00'),
  ('youtube-translate', 'YouTube Translate', 'YouTube Translate MCP server enables AI assistants to access YouTube video transcripts, translations, and summaries through a simple API interface. Built by Brian Shin, it provides tools to retrieve transcripts, translate content to different languages, generate subtitles in SRT or VTT format, create video summaries, and search for specific content within videos. The implementation requires a YouTube Translate API key for authentication and can be run locally using stdio transport or deployed as a Docker container with SSE transport, making it ideal for research, content analysis, and multilingual video accessibility workflows.', '@brianshin22', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/brianshin22/youtube-translate-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brianshin22.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925268+00:00'),
  ('brick-directory', 'Brick Directory', 'Brick Directory provides access to comprehensive LEGO data including over 20,000 sets from Rebrickable, 75,000+ unique parts and elements, minifigure profiles, and real-time BrickLink market pricing. Users can query LEGO information through AI assistants and integrate personal accounts from Rebrickable, Brickset, BrickEconomy, and BrickOwl. The service aggregates data from trusted LEGO community sources to deliver set information, part discovery, minifigure details, and investment analysis features.', '@unknown', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://brick.directory', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925279+00:00'),
  ('vmware-esxi', 'VMware ESXi', 'The ESXi MCP Server provides a RESTful API interface for managing VMware ESXi/vCenter environments through the Model Control Protocol. Built with Python using pyVmomi, it offers complete virtual machine lifecycle management including creation, cloning, deletion, and power operations, along with real-time performance monitoring of CPU, memory, storage, and network usage. The server implements API key authentication, SSL/TLS secure connections, and flexible configuration options via YAML, JSON, or environment variables, making it particularly valuable for automating VMware infrastructure management tasks through AI assistants or integration with other management tools.', '@bright8192', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 53, 'https://github.com/bright8192/esxi-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bright8192.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.925335+00:00');


For example, if you’ve built a “Download CSV” feature and want to flag it, you no longer have to go to bucket.co or use the CLI to create a feature key. Instead, ask the MCP to do it for you: “flag the download button with bucket.”

You can also use the MCP to grant company segments and individual companies or users access to the feature—straight from the chat window. To give “Acme” access, for example, you’d ask something like: “give Acme access to the download csv feature” and Bucket will look up the company name and enable the Download CSV feature for it.

To get started, [add the Bucket MCP in your IDE](https://docs.bucket.co/api/mcp).', '@reflagcom', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/reflagcom/javascript/tree/HEAD/packages/cli', '@bucketco/cli', 78294, 'https://github.com/reflagcom.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926676+00:00'),
  ('bucketeer', 'Bucketeer', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with feature flag management capabilities for Bucketeer, an open-source feature flag platform, built using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK and comprehensive error handling. The implementation offers five core tools for complete CRUD operations: listing feature flags with filtering and pagination support, creating new flags with configurable variations and targeting rules, retrieving specific flags by ID, updating existing flags with audit trail requirements, and archiving flags to make them inactive. Built with Zod schema validation, axios-based HTTP client with proper error mapping, and environment-based configuration supporting flexible deployment scenarios, it serves DevOps teams managing feature rollouts across multiple environments, product managers needing conversational access to feature flag controls, and development teams wanting to integrate feature flag operations into AI-assisted workflows without direct API interaction.', '@bucketeer-io', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/bucketeer-io/bucketeer-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bucketeer-io.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926711+00:00'),
  ('cursor-ide', 'Cursor IDE', 'This MCP implementation, developed by Buga-luga, provides seamless integration between Claude AI and desktop applications through Cursor IDE. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it enables real-time AI assistance in development workflows, offering context-aware code suggestions and completions. The implementation focuses on enhancing productivity by bridging Claude''s capabilities with desktop software, making it particularly useful for developers seeking AI-powered coding support within their existing IDE environment. It stands out by offering a TypeScript-based approach for improved type safety and developer experience.', '@buga-luga', 'development', 'Unknown', 39, 'https://github.com/buga-luga/cursor-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/buga-luga.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926736+00:00'),
  ('bugbounty-security-scanner', 'BugBounty Security Scanner', 'This MCP server provides a comprehensive bug bounty hunting and penetration testing toolkit built by Gokul, integrating 90+ security tools including Nuclei, Subfinder, Nmap, SQLMap, and OSINT platforms like Shodan and VirusTotal through a unified interface. The implementation features eight specialized tool categories (reconnaissance, scanning, vulnerability assessment, web application testing, network analysis, OSINT, exploitation, and reporting) with built-in safety mechanisms including target validation, rate limiting, and safe mode restrictions to prevent unauthorized testing. Designed with Docker deployment, extensive wordlist management, and configurable API integrations, it enables security researchers and penetration testers to conduct automated security assessments through natural language interactions with AI assistants, streamlining the entire bug bounty workflow from initial reconnaissance to vulnerability reporting.', '@gokulapap', 'databases', 'Unknown', 19, 'https://github.com/gokulapap/bugbounty-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gokulapap.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926749+00:00'),
  ('rss-feed-manager', 'RSS Feed Manager', 'MCP RSS is a server that enables AI assistants to interact with RSS feeds, providing tools to parse OPML files, fetch articles, and manage content from subscribed sources. Built with TypeScript and MySQL, it offers features for importing feed subscriptions, automatically updating articles, and filtering content by source or favorite status. The implementation uses TypeORM for database management and exposes three main API methods: retrieving articles with customizable filters, listing available sources, and marking articles as favorites. Ideal for users who want their AI assistants to access and manage their RSS content without switching context.', '@buhe', 'databases', 'Unknown', 26, 'https://github.com/buhe/mcp_rss', 'mcp_rss', 1246, 'https://github.com/buhe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926761+00:00'),
  ('build-mcp', 'Build MCP', 'This MCP server provides integration with build and deployment systems through HTTP-based APIs, built using Python with async support and YAML configuration management. The implementation includes a GD SDK service for interacting with external build platforms, structured logging capabilities, and comprehensive test coverage for both common utilities and service integrations. Designed for development teams and DevOps workflows that need programmatic access to build systems, deployment pipelines, and CI/CD operations through a standardized MCP interface with configurable endpoints and robust error handling.', '@869413421', 'development', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/869413421/build_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/869413421.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926789+00:00'),
  ('buildez', 'Buildez', 'Buildez enables AI assistants to build and deploy complete websites through natural language requests. The server takes a business name and description, then uses AI to select appropriate plugins, generate web identifiers, customize design elements, and deploy functional sites. Users receive editor URLs for review and publishing, streamlining the entire website creation process from concept to deployment.', '@buildezai', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/buildezai/buildez-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/buildezai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926813+00:00'),
  ('buildkite', 'Buildkite', 'Buildkite MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to Buildkite''s CI/CD platform through a standardized interface. Developed by Buildkite, this Go implementation exposes tools for retrieving pipeline details, build information, job logs, artifacts, and user data. The server authenticates using Buildkite API tokens and includes features like pagination support, error handling, and OpenTelemetry tracing. It can be deployed as a binary or Docker container, making it easy to integrate with AI assistants like Claude Desktop or GitHub Copilot for monitoring CI/CD workflows, troubleshooting builds, and accessing pipeline configurations.', '@buildkite', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 48, 'https://github.com/buildkite/buildkite-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/buildkite.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.926835+00:00');


To use MCP server, a user needs to create an account and generate an API key to use MCP server. MCP server is hosted remotely. Available using SSE connection.
Free trial possible with confirmed phone number. ', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://app.cail.io', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928161+00:00'),
  ('hyperliquid', 'Hyperliquid', 'MCP server for Hyperliquid decentralized exchange providing comprehensive perpetual futures trading operations with 27 specialized tools. Supports account management and positions tracking, order placement and management (market, limit, trigger orders), real-time market data access and price feeds, WebSocket subscriptions for live updates, transfer operations and vault interactions, and referral code management. Features dead man''s switch for automated position closure, support for both mainnet and testnet environments, and built-in safety mechanisms for trading automation.', '@caiovicentino', 'development', 'Unknown', 27, 'https://github.com/caiovicentino/hyperliquid-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/caiovicentino.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928185+00:00'),
  ('1password', '1Password', 'MCP server for 1Password service accounts — tools and resources for vaults and credentials', '@cakerepository', 'security', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/cakerepository/1password-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cakerepository.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928238+00:00'),
  ('cal-com-calendar', 'Cal.com Calendar', 'A Cal.com Calendar MCP server that integrates with the Cal.com Calendar API to provide appointment scheduling capabilities for AI assistants. It offers tools for adding, updating, deleting, and listing calendar appointments with features like rate limiting and error handling. The implementation uses the MCP SDK to expose these calendar operations as tools that can be called programmatically, making it valuable for workflows where scheduling and calendar management are needed without leaving the conversation interface.', '@mumunha', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mumunha/cal_dot_com_mcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mumunha.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928306+00:00'),
  ('ynab', 'YNAB', 'YNAB MCP server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the You Need A Budget (YNAB) personal finance API. Built by Caleb LeNoir, it exposes tools for listing budgets, retrieving detailed budget information including accounts and categories, and creating transactions. This implementation is particularly valuable for users who want to manage their YNAB budgets and track finances directly through conversational AI without switching contexts.', '@calebl', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 79, 'https://github.com/calebl/ynab-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/calebl.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928343+00:00'),
  ('apache-airflow', 'Apache Airflow', 'MCP server implementation by call518 that provides AI assistants with complete access to Apache Airflow cluster management and monitoring through REST API integration, built using Python with FastMCP and aiohttp for high-performance async operations. The implementation offers 43 tools covering DAG management (listing, triggering, pausing), cluster health monitoring, pool and variable management, task instance tracking with comprehensive filtering, XCom data access, configuration management, and detailed analytics including event logs, import errors, and performance metrics. Built with modern async HTTP architecture featuring connection pooling, persistent sessions, and optimized pagination defaults, it serves DevOps teams managing Airflow workflows, data engineers monitoring pipeline health, and organizations requiring conversational access to Airflow operations without direct UI interaction, with support for both stdio and HTTP transport methods plus Docker deployment options.', '@call518', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 44, 'https://github.com/call518/mcp-airflow-api', 'mcp-airflow-api', 63943, 'https://github.com/call518.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928371+00:00'),
  ('postgresql-ops', 'PostgreSQL Ops', 'PostgreSQL operations MCP server by JungJungIn that provides AI assistants with direct database access through asyncpg and psycopg2 connections, offering query execution, database introspection, and performance monitoring capabilities. The implementation includes specialized functions for PostgreSQL extensions like pg_stat_statements and pg_stat_monitor for query performance analysis, along with utility functions for formatting database results into human-readable tables with automatic byte and duration formatting. Built with Docker support and both stdio and HTTP transport options, it serves developers needing conversational database administration, data analysts requiring ad-hoc query capabilities, and database administrators who want AI-assisted performance monitoring and troubleshooting workflows.', '@call518', 'databases', 'Unknown', 138, 'https://github.com/call518/mcp-postgresql-ops', 'mcp-postgresql-ops', 35375, 'https://github.com/call518.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928385+00:00'),
  ('calories-club', 'Calories Club', 'AI-powered calorie tracking MCP server with photo recognition, barcode scanning, and voice logging. Provides tools for listing, adding, updating, and deleting food entries, plus daily nutrition summaries. Uses OAuth 2.1 authentication and supports interactive widgets in compatible hosts.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://recordo.app/mcp/calories', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928403+00:00'),
  ('caltrain', 'Caltrain', 'Caltrain MCP server provides real-time train schedule information for the Caltrain commuter rail system in California. Built with Python 3.13, it uses GTFS (General Transit Feed Specification) data to offer accurate departure and arrival times, station information, and trip planning capabilities. The implementation includes features for finding stations by name or abbreviation, calculating travel times between stations, and retrieving upcoming train schedules based on origin, destination, and time. Developed by David Yen, this server is particularly useful for applications requiring public transit information for the San Francisco Bay Area.', '@davidyen1124', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/davidyen1124/caltrain-mcp', 'caltrain-mcp', 9640, 'https://github.com/davidyen1124.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928446+00:00');


This project provides two complementary services for browser automation and co-browsing:

    A Browser Proxy Service that controls a persistent Playwright browser instance via HTTP. Let''s you log in to services you use, like you normally would.
    An MCP Server that exposes browser functionality to MCP clients (like Claude Desktop) via the FastMCP framework. Can operate inside the authenticated session you provide, giving your MCP commands more power and usefulness as an authenticated user.

Both services are built with Deno and TypeScript and work together seamlessly.
Features

- Multiple Browser Support: Run with either Chromium (default) or Firefox.
- Persistent Browser Session: A single browser instance runs for the lifetime of the service.
- Named Tabs: Control multiple pages (tabs) within the single browser session using unique IDs.
- HTTP API: Interact with the browser using simple JSON commands over HTTP.
- MCP Integration: Use the browser through Cline, Windsurf, Claude Desktop, or other MCP clients.
- Type Safety: Uses Zod for robust validation of incoming commands.
- Secure your browser proxy service (HTTP) endpoint with an API token.

Note: Currently supports Mac OS, but can be extended to other platforms with minor changes.', '@canadaduane', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/canadaduane/browse-together-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/canadaduane.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928830+00:00'),
  ('candice-ai', 'Candice AI', 'An MCP server that connects AI agents to Candice AI''s document intelligence platform, enabling access to their trust layer for enterprise AI operations. The platform transforms unstructured business documents into actionable intelligence with 100% accuracy guarantees, source-level citations, and governance-ready confidence scores. Features include exhaustive document processing across entire corpora, complete audit trails for every extraction, and full data sovereignty through on-premise or private cloud deployment options.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.candiceai.com', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928881+00:00'),
  ('markitdown', 'MarkItDown', 'MarkItDown MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the MarkItDown utility, enabling conversion of various file formats to Markdown. Built by KorigamiK, it supports a wide range of formats including PDF, PowerPoint, Word, Excel, images (with EXIF metadata and OCR), audio (with transcription), HTML, and text-based formats like CSV and JSON. The server exposes a simple ''/md'' command that accepts a file path and returns the converted content in Markdown format, making it particularly valuable for users who need to quickly analyze and discuss document content within AI conversations without manual conversion steps.', '@canlgz', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/canlgz/markitdown_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/canlgz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928922+00:00'),
  ('bazi-astrology', 'BaZi Astrology', 'Bazi MCP server provides a bridge to Chinese BaZi (Eight Characters) astrology calculations, enabling AI assistants to access traditional fortune-telling and personality analysis based on birth date and time. Built with TypeScript using the Model Context Protocol SDK, it leverages the tyme4ts library for date calculations and implements functionality through a stdio transport layer. The server exposes BaZi-related functions that likely include generating charts, interpreting elements, and providing insights based on traditional Chinese metaphysics principles, making it valuable for users interested in exploring Eastern astrology without specialized knowledge of the complex calculation systems.', '@cantian-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 269, 'https://github.com/cantian-ai/bazi-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cantian-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928954+00:00'),
  ('tku-academic-systems-tronclass-tku-ilife', 'TKU Academic Systems (TronClass & TKU-ilife)', 'TKU-MCP connects Blender to Claude AI through the Model Context Protocol, allowing Claude to directly interact with TronClass and TKU-ilife systems. This implementation provides authentication with TKU''s student systems using environment variables for credentials, and is designed to be run with the uv package manager. The server enables AI assistants to access and manipulate data from Tamkang University''s learning management and student information systems, making it useful for students who want to automate interactions with university platforms.', '@cantpr09ram', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/cantpr09ram/tronclass-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cantpr09ram.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.928999+00:00'),
  ('canva', 'Canva', 'Official Canva AI Connector that enables AI assistants to seamlessly interact with Canva''s design platform through the Model Context Protocol. The implementation provides tools to create new empty designs, autofill templates with content, search existing designs, and export them as PDFs or images, supporting multiple AI assistants including ChatGPT, Claude, Cursor, and VS Code through both native connectors and custom MCP server configurations. Built for design automation workflows, it''s particularly valuable for users who want to programmatically generate marketing materials, presentations, and visual content without manually navigating the Canva interface, with some advanced features like autofill requiring paid Canva plans.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.canva.dev/docs/connect/canva-mcp-server-setup/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929026+00:00'),
  ('canva-dev', 'Canva Dev', 'Official Canva MCP server that provides AI-powered development assistance for building Canva apps and integrations by connecting compatible MCP clients to canva.dev documentation and specialized development tools. Built by Canva using their CLI infrastructure, it operates locally on the developer''s device while fetching Canva documentation and SDK references to enhance AI agent responses with accurate, up-to-date information about the App UI Kit, Apps SDK, and platform APIs. Designed for developers building on the Canva platform who want contextual AI assistance with app development workflows, API usage, and accessing Canva''s extensive developer documentation without manual searching.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.canva.dev/docs/apps/mcp-server/', '@canva/cli', 133085, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929051+00:00'),
  ('windows-terminal', 'Windows Terminal', 'WinTerm MCP is a server that enables AI models to interact with the Windows command line interface through standardized tools. It provides functionality to write commands, read terminal output, and send control characters, allowing for programmatic access to Windows terminal operations. This implementation is particularly useful for AI-driven automation tasks and integrations that require direct interaction with the Windows command line environment.', '@capecoma', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/capecoma/winterm-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/capecoma.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929162+00:00'),
  ('chatgpt-openai-gpt-4o', 'ChatGPT (OpenAI GPT-4o)', 'A ChatGPT integration server that enables AI assistants to access OpenAI''s GPT-4o model through a simple API. Developed by John Capobianco, this implementation provides a single tool for sending text content to ChatGPT for analysis, summarization, or generation tasks. The server handles the OpenAI API communication, error management, and response formatting, making it easy to augment an assistant''s capabilities with ChatGPT''s perspective. It''s particularly useful for scenarios requiring complex analysis beyond the primary assistant''s capabilities, such as detailed security reviews of configurations or summarizing large documents.', '@automateyournetwork', 'communication', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/automateyournetwork/chatgpt_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/automateyournetwork.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929201+00:00'),
  ('houdini-3d', 'Houdini 3D', 'HoudiniMCP provides a bridge between AI assistants and the Houdini 3D software through a socket-based communication protocol. The implementation consists of a Python addon that runs within Houdini to expose a TCP server, paired with an MCP server that translates AI requests into Houdini operations. It supports a wide range of 3D modeling capabilities including geometry creation, material application, lighting, camera setup, simulation, and rendering, making it valuable for AI-driven 3D content creation workflows without leaving the assistant interface.', '@capoom', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 50, 'https://github.com/capoom/houdini-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/capoom.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929244+00:00'),
  ('anki-leech-cards', 'Anki Leech Cards', 'An MCP server that connects Claude Desktop to Anki via the AnkiConnect API, allowing AI assistants to retrieve and analyze cards tagged as ''leech'' in a user''s Anki collection. The server provides tools to fetch either detailed card information or just IDs, with support for random selection of a specified number of cards. Built with TypeScript and Node.js, it handles connection management, error recovery, and batch processing to prevent overwhelming the AnkiConnect API, making it particularly valuable for users seeking AI assistance in analyzing and improving their spaced repetition study habits.', '@captain-blue210', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/captain-blue210/anki-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/captain-blue210.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929283+00:00'),
  ('search-intent-ai', 'Search Intent AI', 'A Message Context Protocol (MCP) server implementation that detects search intent in user queries and provides relevant search results from Brave Search API.', '@captainchaozi', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/captainchaozi/search-intent-mcp', '@search-intent/mcp', 4818, 'https://github.com/captainchaozi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929307+00:00'),
  ('mcp-maker', 'MCP Maker', 'MCP Maker is a specialized server designed to help developers create new Model Context Protocol servers by providing scaffolding tools and templates. It offers utilities for generating boilerplate code, tool definitions, resource templates, and prompt templates through a set of well-defined tools accessible via Claude Desktop. Built with TypeScript and using Handlebars for templating, it streamlines the MCP development process by automating repetitive setup tasks and providing standardized patterns for common MCP components. The implementation is particularly valuable for developers new to MCP who want to quickly bootstrap projects with best practices already in place.', '@captaincrouton89', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/captaincrouton89/mcp-maker', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/captaincrouton89.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929334+00:00'),
  ('gemini-researcher', 'Gemini Researcher', 'Gemini Researcher is a stateless MCP server that lets AI development agents like Claude Code, Cursor, and GitHub Copilot delegate deep codebase analysis to Google''s Gemini CLI. Instead of copying entire files into the primary agent''s context window, research queries are proxied to Gemini which analyzes files locally, significantly reducing token consumption and keeping agents focused. The server supports multiple client platforms and includes Docker deployment options. Built on the premise that Gemini''s generous free tier can handle heavy analysis work that would otherwise burn through the main model''s quota.', '@capybearista', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/capybearista/gemini-researcher-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/capybearista.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929356+00:00'),
  ('car2db', 'Car2DB', 'Provides access to the Car2DB automotive database API v3 for retrieving detailed vehicle specifications, browsing make/model/trim catalogs, and querying equipment packages. Supports natural language vehicle search and multi-language data retrieval across 11 languages. Requires a Car2DB API key for authentication.', '@car2db', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/car2db/car2db-api-v3-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/car2db.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929366+00:00'),
  ('cardea-web-search-tavily', 'Cardea Web Search (Tavily)', 'This Cardea Web Search MCP server provides web search capabilities through the Tavily API, offering a single search tool that returns structured results including titles, URLs, content snippets, and relevance scores. Built in Rust with support for both Server-Sent Events (SSE) and HTTP streaming transports via the rmcp framework, it features configurable maximum result limits, comprehensive error handling, and requires a Tavily API key for operation. The implementation includes GitHub Actions workflows for cross-platform builds targeting macOS and Linux architectures, making it suitable for AI assistants that need reliable web search functionality with structured output formatting and flexible deployment options.', '@cardea-mcp', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cardea-mcp/web-search', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cardea-mcp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929394+00:00'),
  ('macos-messages', 'macOS Messages', 'Provides fuzzy search and browsing capabilities for Apple Messages (iMessage/SMS) conversations on macOS. Reads from the local Messages database with typo-tolerant search, contact name resolution, conversation threading, and date/sender filtering. Supports multiple interfaces including CLI, Claude Code plugin, and MCP server.', '@cardmagic', 'databases', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/cardmagic/messages', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cardmagic.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929404+00:00'),
  ('intersystems-iris', 'InterSystems IRIS', 'InterSystems IRIS MCP server provides a bridge between AI assistants and InterSystems IRIS databases, enabling SQL query execution and interoperability production management through a standardized interface. Built with Python, it exposes tools for running SQL queries, creating/starting/stopping productions, managing production items, and monitoring system logs. The implementation is particularly valuable for database administrators and developers who need to interact with IRIS databases and manage InterSystems productions directly through conversational AI.', '@caretdev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/caretdev/mcp-server-iris', 'mcp-server-iris', 16123, 'https://github.com/caretdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929416+00:00'),
  ('cargo', 'Cargo', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with access to Rust crate documentation, version information, and workspace metadata through integrated rustdoc JSON generation, crates.io API access, and cargo metadata parsing. Built by Cameron Bytheway using Rust with the rmcp SDK, it offers tools for searching workspace crates, retrieving crate versions and features from crates.io, and searching documentation within specific crates using fuzzy matching algorithms. The implementation generates rustdoc JSON using nightly toolchains, caches results for performance, and supports both local workspace analysis and remote crate documentation access, serving Rust developers needing AI assistance with dependency management, API exploration, and project structure analysis.', '@camshaft', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/camshaft/cargo-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/camshaft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929464+00:00'),
  ('factcheck', 'Factcheck', 'Validates technical content against the Model Context Protocol specification using semantic search with OpenAI embeddings and AI-powered validation. Decomposes compound claims to validate complex statements with multiple assertions. Supports multiple MCP specification versions including draft, 2025-06-18, 2025-03-26, and 2024-11-05.', '@carlisia', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/carlisia/mcp-factcheck', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carlisia.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929494+00:00'),
  ('scrapli-network-automation', 'Scrapli Network Automation', 'Scrapli-MCP is a server implementation that integrates the Scrapli network automation library with MCP to enable AI assistants to execute SSH commands on network devices. Built by Carl Montanari, this implementation provides resources for retrieving host information and a tool for executing commands on Cisco IOS XE devices using AsyncScrapli. The server includes custom prompts to facilitate natural language interactions when requesting command execution, making it particularly useful for network engineers who need to automate device configuration and troubleshooting tasks through an AI interface.', '@carlmontanari', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/carlmontanari/scrapli-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carlmontanari.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929534+00:00'),
  ('ccxt', 'CCXT', 'A cryptocurrency trading server built with CCXT that provides 23 tools for interacting with major exchanges including Binance, Coinbase, Kraken, Bitfinex, and Bybit. Features 13 public tools for market data (tickers, orderbooks, OHLCV candles, trades, funding rates) and 10 private tools requiring API credentials for account management and live trading (spot and futures orders, balance checking, leverage/margin settings, fund transfers). The implementation uses a caching system for exchange instances, supports both authenticated and unauthenticated operations, and includes error handling with rate limit awareness, making it useful for building crypto trading bots, portfolio management tools, and market analysis applications.', '@carlosatta', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/carlosatta/mcp-server-ccxt', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carlosatta.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929565+00:00'),
  ('advocu', 'Advocu', 'This MCP server provides activity reporting capabilities for Google Developer Experts (GDEs) through the Advocu platform, enabling AI assistants to submit various types of professional activities including content creation, public speaking, workshops, mentoring sessions, product feedback, Googler interactions, and stories. Built by Carlos Azaustre using TypeScript with the MCP SDK and dotenv for configuration, it features comprehensive activity type support with detailed metrics tracking (readers, attendees, time spent, impact), structured data validation with proper schemas for each activity type, and direct API integration with the Advocu reporting system using Bearer token authentication. The implementation includes extensive enum definitions for tags, content types, event formats, countries, and significance categories, making it valuable for GDEs who need to streamline their activity reporting workflow, developer advocates tracking their community engagement metrics, and any professional needing structured reporting of technical community activities.', '@carlosazaustre', 'development', 'Unknown', 30, 'https://github.com/carlosazaustre/advocu-mcp-server', 'advocu-mcp-server', 4569, 'https://github.com/carlosazaustre.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929604+00:00'),
  ('blog-publisher', 'Blog Publisher', 'This Blog Publisher MCP server enables AI assistants to publish blog content to external platforms. Built with Python using httpx for HTTP requests and the MCP library with CLI support, it provides a streamlined interface for content submission. The implementation includes both standard and local execution modes with logging capabilities, making it suitable for automated content publishing workflows or integration with AI writing assistants that need to push finalized content to publishing platforms.', '@carrie-l', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/carrie-l/blog_publisher_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carrie-l.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929643+00:00'),
  ('nhl', 'NHL', 'This MCP server, developed by Carson Jones, provides comprehensive access to NHL data and statistics. Built with Go and leveraging the Model Context Protocol, it offers a wide range of functionalities including retrieving schedules, game details, team information, player stats, and league standings. The implementation focuses on delivering up-to-date hockey information with features like live game updates and play-by-play data. It''s particularly useful for sports analysts, fantasy hockey enthusiasts, and developers building NHL-related applications, enabling use cases such as real-time score tracking, in-depth player performance analysis, and automated reporting on league standings without complex API integrations.', '@carsonjones', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/carsonjones/nhl-go', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carsonjones.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929671+00:00'),
  ('dotnet-analyzer', 'DotNet Analyzer', 'Provides semantic-level C# code analysis by integrating Microsoft''s Roslyn compiler platform. Supports code diagnostics, symbol navigation, project dependency analysis, code refactoring, and call graph generation. Installed as a .NET global tool and supports .NET 8.0, 9.0, and 10.0.', '@cartapenabark', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cartapenabark/dotnetanalyzer', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cartapenabark.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929689+00:00'),
  ('mac-messages', 'Mac Messages', 'Mac Messages MCP provides a bridge for AI assistants to interact with the macOS Messages app, enabling reading recent messages and sending new ones through a set of well-defined tools. Developed by Carter Lasalle, it accesses the Messages database and AddressBook contacts directly, with features for contact lookup, fuzzy name matching, and group chat support. The implementation includes robust error handling for permission issues and runs as an MCP server that integrates with Claude Desktop, making it particularly valuable for users who want to manage their iMessage conversations without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@carterlasalle', 'databases', 'Unknown', 246, 'https://github.com/carterlasalle/mac_messages_mcp', 'mac-messages-mcp', 15588, 'https://github.com/carterlasalle.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929700+00:00'),
  ('devenvinfoserver', 'DevEnvInfoServer', 'This MCP server implementation provides detailed information about the development environment to enhance context-aware assistance in the Cursor code editor. Developed by Carter Lasalle, it uses Python to gather comprehensive system data including OS details, hardware specifications, installed software, and running processes. The server exposes this information through various tools, allowing Cursor''s intelligent agent to access specific environmental details as needed. It''s particularly useful for scenarios requiring deep understanding of the local development setup, such as troubleshooting environment-specific issues or providing tailored coding suggestions.', '@carterlasalle', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/carterlasalle/system_information_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/carterlasalle.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929727+00:00'),
  ('cashfree', 'Cashfree', 'Cashfree MCP server enables AI tools and agents to integrate with Cashfree''s payment processing APIs (Payment Gateway, Payouts, and SecureID) through a standardized interface. Developed by Cashfree Payments under MIT license, it provides tools for creating payment links, managing orders, processing refunds, initiating transfers, and verifying identity information. The implementation uses Node.js with the Model Context Protocol SDK and supports both sandbox and production environments with proper authentication handling. This server is particularly valuable for applications requiring payment processing, fund transfers, and identity verification capabilities directly through AI assistants.', '@cashfree', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/cashfree/cashfree-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cashfree.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929773+00:00'),
  ('dictionary-thesaurus', 'Dictionary & Thesaurus', 'This dictionary and thesaurus MCP server provides English word definitions, synonyms, and example usage through the Free Dictionary API, built by Alex Stansfield using FastMCP and the requests library. The implementation offers three core tools: word definition lookup with part-of-speech categorization, synonym retrieval, and example sentence extraction, making it valuable for writing assistance, vocabulary building, and language learning applications where AI assistants need access to comprehensive word reference data. The server handles API error cases gracefully by returning empty results or error messages when words are not found, and structures the dictionary data into organized meanings with definitions grouped by grammatical function.', '@casualgenius', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/casualgenius/mcp-servers/tree/HEAD/servers/words', 'casual-mcp-server-words', 2371, 'https://github.com/casualgenius.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929802+00:00'),
  ('read-images', 'Read Images', 'This MCP server, developed by CatalystNeuro, provides image analysis capabilities using OpenRouter''s vision models, particularly Claude-3 variants. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers a streamlined interface for AI agents to analyze images through natural language queries. The implementation focuses on ease of use and flexibility, with features like automatic image optimization, configurable model selection, and detailed error handling. It''s particularly useful for developers and researchers working with visual data, enabling use cases such as content moderation, data extraction from images, and automated image captioning without directly interacting with the OpenRouter API.', '@catalystneuro', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/catalystneuro/mcp_read_images', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/catalystneuro.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929831+00:00'),
  ('catchmetrics', 'CatchMetrics', 'CatchMetrics provides real user monitoring (RUM) for web performance optimization. The platform tracks Core Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP), navigation timings, JavaScript long tasks, and third-party script impact across devices and regions. AI-powered analysis helps identify performance degradation causes and correlates metrics with deployment history to enable faster issue resolution.', '@unknown', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://catchmetrics.io', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929871+00:00'),
  ('finnhub', 'Finnhub', 'This Finnhub MCP server, developed by Catherine Parnell, provides a streamlined interface to Finnhub''s financial API. Built with Python using the FastMCP framework, it offers tools for retrieving market news, stock quotes, basic financials, and recommendation trends. The implementation stands out by abstracting away the complexities of API authentication and request handling, making it accessible for AI assistants or applications needing financial data. It''s particularly useful for tasks like market analysis, portfolio management, or building financial chatbots, enabling quick access to real-time and historical financial information without deep API knowledge.', '@catherinedparnell', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/catherinedparnell/mcp-finnhub', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/catherinedparnell.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929898+00:00'),
  ('basilisp-nrepl', 'Basilisp nREPL', 'This MCP server provides a bridge between Anthropic''s Model Control Protocol and Basilisp''s nREPL server, allowing Claude Code to interact directly with a Basilisp REPL environment. It enables execution of Basilisp code (a Lisp dialect similar to Clojure that runs on the Python VM), retrieval of documentation, namespace exploration, and Python interoperability through a set of well-defined tools. The implementation features robust error handling, syntax highlighting for results, and comprehensive documentation to facilitate seamless interaction between AI assistants and Basilisp code execution environments.', '@cat-state', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cat-state/nrepl-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cat-state.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.929925+00:00'),
  ('ue5-blueprint', 'UE5 Blueprint', 'Enables programmatic creation and manipulation of Unreal Engine 5 Blueprints through a two-component architecture: a C++ plugin running inside the UE5 Editor that listens on a local TCP socket, and a Python server that translates tool calls into Blueprint manipulation commands. Supports asset management, graph manipulation, widget authoring with UMG hierarchies, Enhanced Input system generation, and Blueprint inspection queries.', '@cawb07', 'security', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cawb07/ue5-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cawb07.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930009+00:00'),
  ('gerrit-code-review', 'Gerrit Code Review', 'The Gerrit Review MCP server provides a streamlined interface for AI assistants to interact with Gerrit code review systems, enabling detailed analysis of code changes through the Gerrit REST API. Built by Omer Cayirtepe, it offers specialized tools for fetching complete change information including diffs, file modifications, and reviewer details, as well as comparing differences between patchsets. The server handles authentication securely via HTTP digest auth and supports various Gerrit endpoints, making it particularly valuable for development teams using Gerrit who want AI assistance with code review workflows, tracking change evolution, and analyzing modifications across review iterations.', '@cayirtepeomer', 'development', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/cayirtepeomer/gerrit-code-review-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cayirtepeomer.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930036+00:00'),
  ('cb-insights', 'CB Insights', 'CB Insights MCP Server provides AI assistants with direct access to ChatCBI, CB Insights'' specialized market intelligence and company research copilot powered by comprehensive business data. The server enables agents to query detailed information about companies, funding rounds, acquisitions, partnerships, market trends, and competitive intelligence through a single ChatCBI tool that maintains conversation continuity via session IDs. Built with Python using FastMCP and requiring CB Insights API credentials, it''s designed for use cases involving deep business research, market analysis, and accessing CB Insights'' extensive database of financial transactions and company information.', '@cbinsights', 'databases', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/cbinsights/cbi-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cbinsights.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930048+00:00'),
  ('kiro-memory', 'Kiro Memory', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with intelligent memory management and task tracking capabilities for software development projects, built by cbunting99 using Python with automatic project detection, semantic search via sentence-transformers, and SQLite-based persistence. The implementation features automatic memory classification and relationship building, context-aware task creation from conversation content, project-based organization with auto-detection from git repositories and project files, and comprehensive cleanup and optimization tools including duplicate detection and performance tracking. Serves developers needing persistent AI memory across coding sessions, teams requiring automated task management with priority inference and category classification, and projects where maintaining context and knowledge graphs enhances AI-assisted development workflows with semantic similarity matching and intelligent content organization.', '@cbunting99', 'databases', 'Unknown', 30, 'https://github.com/cbunting99/enhanced-mcp-memory', 'kiro-mcp-memory', 1533, 'https://github.com/cbunting99.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930060+00:00'),
  ('unreal-engine-editor', 'Unreal Engine Editor', 'The MCPServer plugin for Unreal Engine Editor transforms the editor into an MCP-compatible server for AI agent interaction. It leverages Python''s asyncio framework with a custom event loop implementation to handle asynchronous operations within the Unreal Editor environment. The server integrates with Unreal''s slate tick system to maintain responsiveness while processing requests, and requires dependencies like mcp, anyio, click, and starlette. This implementation enables AI agents to programmatically control and interact with Unreal Editor functionality, making it valuable for automating editor workflows and enabling AI-driven content creation.', '@cc8887', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/cc8887/ue-editor-mcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cc8887.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930107+00:00'),
  ('zotero-chunk-rag', 'Zotero Chunk RAG', 'Enables passage-level semantic search over Zotero research libraries by extracting text from PDFs, chunking documents with overlap, and embedding them using Google''s Gemini API for storage in ChromaDB. Provides tools for finding relevant papers by topic, searching specific passages with expandable context, and retrieving bibliographic metadata including BetterBibTeX citation keys. Designed for academic research workflows where users need to locate specific claims, verify citations, and gather supporting evidence from their personal paper collections with precise page-level attribution.', '@ccam80', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/ccam80/deep-zotero', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ccam80.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930163+00:00'),
  ('imf-data', 'IMF Data', 'IMF Data MCP Server provides access to International Monetary Fund data through a structured API interface. It offers resources for listing datasets, retrieving dataset structures, and tools for fetching time series data from various IMF databases including International Financial Statistics, Direction of Trade Statistics, and Balance of Payments. The server processes raw IMF API responses into readable formats, handling complex data structures and providing clear error messages when data is unavailable. This implementation is particularly valuable for economic analysis, research, and financial reporting workflows requiring access to authoritative international economic indicators.', '@c-cf', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/c-cf/imf-data-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/c-cf.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.930174+00:00');


This MCP Server connects AI agents to Chargebee platform.', '@chargebee', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/chargebee/agentkit/tree/HEAD/modelcontextprotocol', '@chargebee/mcp', 20724, 'https://github.com/chargebee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.931410+00:00'),
  ('lilith-shell', 'Lilith Shell', 'Lilith-Shell is an MCP server that enables AI assistants to securely execute terminal commands through a standardized interface. Built by Charles Adedotun, it implements the Model Context Protocol to provide a single powerful tool for executing shell commands with configurable working directories and timeout protection. The implementation uses asyncio and the MCP server library to handle command execution requests, capturing both stdout and stderr output along with exit codes. It includes comprehensive error handling for timeouts and invalid commands, making it particularly valuable for AI assistants that need to perform system operations, file management, or run development tools without leaving the conversation interface.', '@charles-adedotun', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/charles-adedotun/lilith-shell', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/charles-adedotun.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.931468+00:00'),
  ('pref-editor-android', 'Pref Editor (Android)', 'Provides integration with Android device preferences through ADB connectivity, enabling developers to read, modify, add, and delete SharedPreferences and DataStore preference files on connected Android devices. Built by Charles Muchene with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, the implementation offers seven specialized tools including device discovery, app enumeration, preference file listing, and complete CRUD operations on preference data with support for multiple data types (string, integer, boolean, float, double, long). Features Docker containerization with host ADB server connectivity and comprehensive error handling, making it valuable for Android developers debugging app preferences, QA engineers automating preference testing workflows, and development teams building tools that need programmatic access to Android app configuration data without manual device interaction.', '@charlesmuchene', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/charlesmuchene/pref-editor-mcp-server', '@charlesmuchene/pref-editor-mcp-server', 1850, 'https://github.com/charlesmuchene.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.931496+00:00');



Claude in Excel can read complex multi-tab workbooks, explain calculations with cell-level citations, and safely update assumptions while preserving formula dependencies.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://marketplace.microsoft.com/en-us/product/office/WA200009404', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934360+00:00'),
  ('claude-code-mcp-server', 'Claude Code MCP Server', 'An MCP server implementation for interacting with Claude Code, providing programmatic access to Anthropic''s AI coding capabilities.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/agents-and-tools/claude-code/tutorials#use-claude-code-as-an-mcp-server', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934375+00:00'),
  ('claude-context-local', 'Claude Context Local', 'A local semantic code search MCP server that provides AI-powered code indexing and search capabilities using EmbeddingGemma embeddings, FAISS vector search, and intelligent AST/tree-sitter chunking for multiple programming languages including Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, JSX, TSX, and Svelte. Built with incremental indexing using Merkle tree-based change detection for efficient updates, it features 100% local operation without cloud dependencies, automatic reindexing based on file modifications, and semantic search across codebases with support for functions, classes, methods, and other code constructs. Designed for developers using Claude Code who need fast, private semantic search over their local codebases without sending code to external services, enabling use cases like code exploration, finding similar implementations, understanding large codebases, and contextual code assistance.', '@farhanaliraza', 'development', 'Unknown', 195, 'https://github.com/farhanaliraza/claude-context-local', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/farhanaliraza.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934408+00:00'),
  ('claude-conversation-logger', 'Claude Conversation Logger', 'This containerized conversation logger for Claude Code captures and stores all conversation data through Python hooks that intercept Claude''s session events, storing messages and metadata in MongoDB with Redis caching for performance. Built by Luciano Emanuel Ricardo, it provides a complete monolithic solution with Docker deployment, featuring a visual dashboard for conversation analysis, OpenTelemetry token metrics tracking, gRPC and REST APIs, and both MCP server integration and CLI recovery tools. The implementation includes automatic data expiration policies, comprehensive logging across multiple services (MongoDB, Redis, Nginx, Node.js), and is designed for developers who need persistent conversation history, usage analytics, and programmatic access to their Claude interactions for debugging, analysis, or integration with other systems.', '@lucianoricardo737', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/lucianoricardo737/claude-conversation-logger', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/lucianoricardo737.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934424+00:00'),
  ('claude-deep-research', 'Claude Deep Research', 'Claude Deep Research is an MCP server that extends AI assistants'' capabilities by providing unified access to web and academic information through DuckDuckGo and Semantic Scholar integrations. It enables Claude to search multiple sources, extract content from web pages, follow relevant links, and deliver structured research results with proper citations. The implementation features a multi-stage research workflow that guides users through initial exploration, synthesis, visualization, follow-up research, and comprehensive analysis, making it particularly valuable for users needing thorough, well-organized information on complex topics.', '@mcherukara', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 47, 'https://github.com/mcherukara/claude-deep-research', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mcherukara.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934470+00:00'),
  ('claude-historian', 'Claude Historian', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with intelligent search capabilities across Claude Code conversation history, built by the Claude Code Community using TypeScript with an intelligent indexing system that prioritizes recent activity and content richness for fast retrieval. The implementation offers seven specialized tools including conversation search with AI-enhanced query expansion, file context discovery, similar query matching, error solution patterns, tool usage analysis, and session management, all backed by a robust parser that extracts file references, tool usage patterns, and error contexts from JSONL conversation logs stored in ~/.claude/projects. Built with performance optimizations including circuit breakers, memory limits, and caching mechanisms, it serves developers needing to leverage their coding conversation history for debugging and learning, teams wanting to discover patterns in their AI-assisted development workflows, and users seeking to quickly find relevant past solutions and context from their Claude Code sessions.', '@vvkmnn', 'development', 'Unknown', 216, 'https://github.com/vvkmnn/claude-historian-mcp', 'claude-historian', 1500, 'https://github.com/vvkmnn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934505+00:00'),
  ('claude-slack', 'Claude-Slack', 'Channel-based messaging system for Claude Code agents that enables Slack-like communication infrastructure across projects and agent hierarchies. Built by Theo Nash, this implementation provides project isolation with explicit linking permissions, scoped channel subscriptions (global vs project-specific), direct messaging between agents, and automatic agent discovery through frontmatter parsing of Claude agent files. The system uses SQLite for message persistence, YAML configuration for default channels and project permissions, and hooks that automatically detect project context and register agents with MCP tools, making it valuable for coordinating multi-agent workflows, cross-project collaboration, and maintaining communication history in complex Claude Code environments with multiple specialized agents.', '@theo-nash', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/theo-nash/claude-slack', 'claude-slack', 1024, 'https://github.com/theo-nash.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934519+00:00'),
  ('claudesmalltalk', 'ClaudeSmalltalk', 'Enables AI interaction with live Smalltalk environments through the Model Context Protocol, supporting both Cuis and Squeak platforms. Offers multiple deployment options including native stdio-based MCP servers for Cuis and Squeak, a Python/MQTT bridge for asynchronous messaging, and integrations with OpenAI and Clawdbot. Provides 14 tools covering code evaluation, class metadata browsing, method source viewing, class and method definition, deletion operations, class hierarchy inspection, and category management. Features non-blocking I/O to keep the Smalltalk GUI responsive during MCP operations, dev mode with persistent saving, and headless operation support via Xvfb on Linux.', '@corporatesmalltalkconsultingltd', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/corporatesmalltalkconsultingltd/claudesmalltalk', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/corporatesmalltalkconsultingltd.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934548+00:00'),
  ('claude-text-editor', 'Claude Text Editor', 'This MCP server provides seamless text editing integration with Claude Desktop through a file-based workflow system, enabling users to select text anywhere on macOS and have it automatically processed by Claude through customizable prompts. Built by Luca Pinello using Python with the MCP SDK and macOS system integration, it operates by monitoring inbox/outbox directories where text files are dropped for processing, supports custom editing instructions through configurable prompts with special handling for parenthetical user directives, and includes automatic clipboard copying with desktop notifications upon completion. The implementation features a complete macOS shortcut integration for system-wide text selection, conda/mamba environment management with fallback to virtual environments, and a client-server architecture that handles file-based communication between the user interface and Claude Desktop, making it valuable for writers needing quick text refinement, professionals requiring consistent editing workflows, and anyone wanting to leverage Claude''s text processing capabilities without leaving their current application context.', '@lucapinello', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/lucapinello/claude-text-editor', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/lucapinello.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934613+00:00'),
  ('clay', 'Clay', 'A Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for Clay (https://clay.earth). Search your email, calendar, Twitter / X, Linkedin, iMessage, Facebook, and WhatsApp contacts. Take notes, set reminders, and more.

Examples

    "Who in my network works at Google as a Product Manager?"
    "Who is John Smith?"
    "Add a new contact named Jane Doe, who is a Designer at Figma."
    "Save a note for John Smith: ''Follow up about the Q2 report.''"
    "Create a group called ''Investors 2025.''"', '@clay-inc', 'communication', 'Unknown', 28, 'https://github.com/clay-inc/clay-mcp', '@clayhq/clay-mcp', 5952, 'https://github.com/clay-inc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934640+00:00'),
  ('io-github-kryptobaseddev-cleo-mcp-server', 'io.github.kryptobaseddev/cleo-mcp-server', 'Task management protocol for solo developers and AI coding agents with 2-gateway CQRS pattern', '@kryptobaseddev', 'development', 'Unknown', 122, 'https://github.com/kryptobaseddev/cleo', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kryptobaseddev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934658+00:00'),
  ('clerk', 'Clerk', 'Clerk is a JavaScript SDK for authentication and user management that provides a comprehensive set of tools for implementing secure authentication flows in web applications. This repository contains the core Clerk packages and various framework integrations (React, Next.js, Remix, Express, Fastify) along with playground examples demonstrating implementation across different environments. The SDK supports features like user sign-in/sign-up, organization management, session handling, and authorization based on features and plans, making it particularly useful for applications requiring robust identity management with minimal setup.', '@clerk', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1673, 'https://github.com/clerk/javascript/tree/HEAD/packages/agent-toolkit', '@clerk/agent-toolkit', 207544, 'https://github.com/clerk.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934699+00:00'),
  ('slack-cli-wrapper', 'Slack CLI Wrapper', 'Docker-wrapped Slack MCP server exposed as CLI achieving 98.7% token reduction for LLM agents. Wraps korotovsky/slack-mcp-server inside Docker and exposes it via f/mcptools CLI bridge for scriptable, token-efficient Slack workspace access with credentials persistence and support for multiple Slack authentication methods.', '@cliai', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cliai/slack-cli-mcp-wrapper', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cliai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934717+00:00'),
  ('io-github-cvrt-jh-clickup-mcp', 'io.github.cvrt-jh/clickup-mcp', 'Lightweight ClickUp MCP server - 37 tools, token-optimized (95% smaller responses)', '@cvrt-jh', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cvrt-jh/clickup-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cvrt-jh.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934756+00:00'),
  ('puzzlebox', 'PuzzleBox', 'Puzzlebox is an MCP server implementation that hosts finite state machines (puzzles) as dynamic resources that clients can subscribe to and be updated when their state changes. It enables coordination between multiple agents working on long-horizon tasks by providing a shared state machine that can transition between discrete states through valid actions, with optional guards that can prevent transitions. The server exposes tools for adding puzzles, getting snapshots of puzzle states, performing actions on puzzles, and supports resource subscriptions so clients receive real-time updates when puzzle states change, making it particularly valuable for orchestrating multi-agent workflows where different teams need to operate within distinct project phases.', '@cliffhall', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 25, 'https://github.com/cliffhall/puzzlebox', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cliffhall.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934803+00:00'),
  ('climatetriage', 'ClimateTriage', 'The ClimateTriage MCP server connects AI assistants to the ClimateTriage API, enabling users to search for open source issues related to climate change and sustainability. Built with TypeScript and the FastMCP framework, this implementation provides structured access to climate project issues with filtering capabilities by category, programming language, and keywords. The server transforms API responses into well-formatted results that include detailed project information, issue descriptions, and direct links to GitHub repositories. It''s particularly useful for developers looking to contribute to climate-focused open source projects, researchers tracking sustainability initiatives, or organizations wanting to engage with the climate tech ecosystem.', '@codeshark-net', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/codeshark-net/climate-triage-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/codeshark-net.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934830+00:00'),
  ('io-github-cloakedagent-cloaked', 'io.github.CloakedAgent/cloaked', 'Trustless spending accounts for AI agents on Solana with on-chain enforced limits.', '@cloakedagent', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/cloakedagent/cloaked', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cloakedagent.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934849+00:00'),
  ('clockwise', 'Clockwise', 'Clockwise MCP provides AI assistants with intelligent calendar management and scheduling coordination capabilities through the first Model Context Protocol server designed specifically for time management. Built by Clockwise leveraging eight years of proprietary scheduling intelligence, it goes beyond basic availability checking to make human-like scheduling decisions by understanding priorities, preferences, team dynamics, working hours, time zones, and deep work needs across Google Calendar, Outlook, Slack, and other collaboration platforms. The server enables complex scheduling operations including meeting coordination with rich context, calendar optimization based on time management best practices, and automated time blocking for task management, making it valuable for AI workflows that need enterprise-grade scheduling intelligence rather than simple calendar slot filling.', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.getclockwise.com/mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934898+00:00'),
  ('crypto', 'Crypto', 'This MCP server provides encryption, decryption, and hashing functionalities using the crypto-js library. Developed by Cloris, it offers a standardized interface for cryptographic operations, making it easier to integrate secure data handling into AI-assisted workflows. The server is particularly useful for applications requiring data protection, secure communication, or verification of data integrity.', '@1595901624', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/1595901624/crypto-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/1595901624.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934932+00:00'),
  ('close', 'Close', 'Close is an all-in-one sales CRM platform designed for small and scaling businesses. It combines lead management, opportunity tracking, built-in calling/email/SMS, automated workflows, and AI-powered features like call transcription and lead enrichment. The platform emphasizes speed and efficiency, eliminating the need to switch between multiple sales tools.', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.close.com/integrations/close-mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934956+00:00'),
  ('lovense', 'Lovense', 'Provides MCP server integration with Lovense adult toy devices, enabling programmatic control through their Game Mode API. Runs as a systemd service with security hardening and resource limits, connecting to devices over the local network. Includes consent-focused safety features such as intensity limits, cooldown periods, and quiet hours.', '@clotho2', 'communication', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/clotho2/wolfe-lovense', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/clotho2.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.934981+00:00');

Core Capabilities:
