▷ Browser Behavior Simulation: Precisely execute interactions such as web page access, element-level screenshots, dynamic data scraping, and intelligent form filling.
▷ Exclusive Adaptation for LLM: Browser behavior trajectory simulation, DOM tree parsing optimization, and structured data output.
▷ Elastic Resource Scheduling: From single-session debugging to concurrent collection at the scale of tens of thousands, automatically matching computing power requirements.', '@clpublic', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/clpublic/mcp-server-cloudbrowser', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/clpublic.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935737+00:00'),
  ('dataiku', 'Dataiku', 'MCP server for Dataiku DSS project, flow, and operations APIs.', '@clssck', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/clssck/dataiku_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/clssck.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935757+00:00'),
  ('aave-liquidation', 'Aave Liquidation', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with tools to analyze Aave V3 liquidation opportunities on Ethereum mainnet. Created by clumsynonono, it exposes 8 tools for monitoring DeFi positions including user health factor checking, position analysis, reserve data retrieval, asset pricing from Aave oracles, and batch address monitoring with risk level classification. The server connects directly to Ethereum RPC endpoints to fetch real-time data from Aave''s pool, data provider, and oracle contracts using ethers.js. It''s designed for DeFi liquidation bots, risk management systems, and automated position monitoring workflows, providing read-only analysis without executing transactions.', '@clumsynonono', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/clumsynonono/aave-liquidation-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/clumsynonono.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935805+00:00'),
  ('google-search-via-chrome', 'Google Search (via Chrome)', 'This MCP tool, developed by Chris Mann, enables Google search and webpage content extraction using the Chrome browser. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it provides a bridge between AI models like Claude and web-based information sources. The implementation focuses on automating browser interactions to perform searches and extract content, making it easier for AI systems to access up-to-date web information. It''s particularly useful for enhancing AI capabilities with real-time web data, enabling use cases like fact-checking, research assistance, and content generation that requires current online information.', '@cmann50', 'development', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/cmann50/mcp-chrome-google-search', '@cmann50/mcp-chrome-google-search', 4909, 'https://github.com/cmann50.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935836+00:00'),
  ('excalidraw', 'Excalidraw', 'Enables programmatic creation and manipulation of Excalidraw diagram files through tools for adding nodes, creating edges between elements, deleting diagram components, and exporting complete diagram state. Works with local .excalidraw files to support AI-assisted diagramming workflows.', '@cmd8', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/cmd8/excalidraw-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cmd8.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935878+00:00'),
  ('reddit-extractor', 'Reddit Extractor', 'MCP Reddit is a server that enables AI assistants to extract content from Reddit discussions without requiring an API key. Developed by Andi Ellison, this Python implementation uses both API and HTML parsing methods to retrieve post metadata and comments from Reddit threads. The server exposes a single tool called ''reddit_extract'' that accepts a Reddit URL and returns formatted discussion data including the post content, author information, and comments. It''s particularly useful for research, content analysis, and staying updated on Reddit discussions while avoiding API rate limits and authentication requirements.', '@cmpxchg16', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/cmpxchg16/mcp-ethical-hacking/tree/HEAD/reddit-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cmpxchg16.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.935955+00:00'),
  ('command-executor', 'Command Executor', 'MCP Command Executor is a secure server that enables safe remote command execution via the MCP protocol, with robust security controls like command allowlisting, direct command execution without shell invocation, and strict environment variable management. Created by cnosuke, it provides a controlled mechanism for executing predefined system commands with granular configuration options, making it useful for scenarios requiring restricted, auditable command execution across different environments.', '@cnosuke', 'security', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cnosuke/mcp-command-exec', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cnosuke.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936019+00:00'),
  ('meilisearch', 'Meilisearch', 'This MCP server implementation provides a Go-based wrapper for Meilisearch, enabling large language models to access Meilisearch''s search capabilities through the Model Context Protocol. Developed by cnosuke, it offers tools for index management, document operations, and search functionality, allowing AI assistants like Claude to perform powerful search operations against Meilisearch indexes. The lightweight server supports features such as health checks, creating indexes, adding documents, and executing complex searches with filtering and sorting options, making it ideal for applications requiring AI-assisted information retrieval from structured data.', '@cnosuke', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/cnosuke/mcp-meilisearch', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cnosuke.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936068+00:00'),
  ('backlinks-ahrefs', 'Backlinks (Ahrefs)', 'Backlinks MCP is a FastMCP service that retrieves backlink information for any domain using Ahrefs'' data. Developed by cnych, it solves CAPTCHA challenges automatically using CapSolver''s API to access Ahrefs'' backlink checker, then caches signature tokens to minimize redundant requests. The server exposes a tool that returns detailed backlink data including anchor text, domain rating, and URL information. This implementation is particularly useful for SEO analysis, competitive research, and link building strategies where understanding a website''s backlink profile is essential.', '@cnych', 'development', 'Unknown', 223, 'https://github.com/cnych/seo-mcp', 'backlinks-mcp', 2204, 'https://github.com/cnych.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936094+00:00'),
  ('sqlite-tool', 'SQLite Tool', 'A Python-based SQLite database management server that provides tools for executing queries, managing schemas, and performing row deletion operations with specialized safety features. The implementation includes a delete_rows tool that supports conditional filtering using equality conditions on specific columns, with a safety toggle to prevent accidental full-table deletions. Built with comprehensive testing infrastructure and clear documentation, it enables AI-assisted database maintenance workflows, data cleanup operations, and precise record management within SQLite databases.', '@cnzhangxy51', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/cnzhangxy51/sqlite-tool', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cnzhangxy51.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936108+00:00'),
  ('eclass-uoa', 'eClass (UoA)', 'eClass MCP Server provides integration with the Open eClass platform, specifically tailored for UoA''s SSO authentication system. Built with Python and the MCP protocol, it handles authentication, session management, and course access through a modular architecture that separates concerns like HTML parsing and course management. The server exposes tools for logging in, retrieving course lists, and managing authentication state, making it valuable for students and faculty who need to access eClass resources through AI assistants.', '@sdi2200262', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/sdi2200262/eclass-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/sdi2200262.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936180+00:00'),
  ('tractatus-thinking', 'Tractatus Thinking', 'MCP server for logical concept analysis that applies Wittgenstein''s Tractatus method to break through confused thinking with structured decomposition. Created by Alexander Warth, it focuses on revealing WHAT something is rather than HOW to do it by exposing hidden dependencies and multiplicative requirements that sequential thinking typically misses. Designed for AI reasoning workflows, cognitive problem-solving, and knowledge base construction where clear conceptual boundaries and logical structure are essential for understanding complex domains.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://gitlab.com/CochainComplex/tractatus-thinking', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936224+00:00'),
  ('codacy', 'Codacy', 'This MCP server provides integration with Codacy''s code quality platform, enabling AI assistants to interact with automated code review and quality analysis tools. The implementation allows access to Codacy''s static analysis capabilities, code coverage metrics, and quality gate configurations, making it valuable for developers who need AI assistance with code quality workflows, automated review processes, and maintaining coding standards across projects.', '@codacy', 'development', 'Unknown', 56, 'https://github.com/codacy/codacy-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/codacy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936257+00:00'),
  ('cloud-services', 'Cloud Services', 'Multi-cloud management server built by code-alchemist01 that provides unified access to AWS, Azure, and GCP resources through a single interface. Features cloud-agnostic adapters for each provider, comprehensive resource management tools for instances, storage, databases, and functions, plus specialized capabilities for cost analysis, monitoring, security scanning, and compliance checking. Built with TypeScript and official cloud SDKs, it handles credential management through environment variables, supports cross-cloud resource operations like starting and stopping instances, and includes formatters for consistent output across providers. Useful for DevOps teams managing multi-cloud infrastructure, cost optimization workflows, security auditing across cloud environments, and workflows requiring unified visibility and control across AWS, Azure, and GCP.', '@code-alchemist01', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/code-alchemist01/cloud-mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/code-alchemist01.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936269+00:00'),
  ('development-tools', 'Development Tools', 'A comprehensive development toolkit that integrates code quality analysis and web scraping into AI-assisted workflows. Provides code analysis features including cyclomatic complexity calculation, security vulnerability scanning, dependency analysis, ESLint integration, and code smell detection. Also includes static and dynamic web scraping tools using Cheerio and Playwright for extracting content, discovering API endpoints, and monitoring network requests. Supports automated code reviews, security audits, dependency management, and data extraction through natural language commands in AI assistants like Claude Desktop and Cursor.', '@code-alchemist01', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/code-alchemist01/development-tools-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/code-alchemist01.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936296+00:00'),
  ('codealive', 'CodeAlive', 'CodeAlive MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the CodeAlive platform, enabling deep code understanding for large codebases. It offers tools for semantic code search, repository exploration, and context-aware chat completions that leverage CodeAlive''s ability to analyze entire codebases including documentation and dependencies. The server integrates with popular AI clients like Claude Desktop, Cursor, and VS Code (GitHub Copilot), making it particularly valuable for developers who need to quickly find relevant code snippets, understand project structure, and get precise answers about implementation details without extensive manual searching.', '@codealive-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 75, 'https://github.com/codealive-ai/codealive-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/codealive-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936321+00:00'),
  ('code-audit-ollama', 'Code Audit (Ollama)', 'This MCP server provides AI-powered code auditing capabilities using local Ollama models to analyze code for security vulnerabilities, performance bottlenecks, quality issues, architectural problems, testing gaps, documentation deficiencies, and implementation completeness. Built by Warren Gates using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK, it features specialized auditors for each analysis type, configurable model selection strategies, complexity analysis utilities, and a comprehensive CLI tool for setup, health checking, and server management. The implementation supports multiple audit modes (fast/thorough), language-specific analysis patterns, severity-based issue classification, and both stdio and HTTP transport modes, making it valuable for code review workflows, continuous integration pipelines, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to detailed code quality analysis without relying on external services.', '@moikas-code', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/moikas-code/code-audit-mcp', '@moikas/code-audit-mcp', 793, 'https://github.com/moikas-code.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936355+00:00'),
  ('gitlab-mr-confluence-linker', 'GitLab MR Confluence Linker', 'MRConfluenceLinker-mcp-server provides a bridge between GitLab merge requests and Confluence documentation, enabling AI assistants to fetch, analyze, and document code changes. The server offers tools to retrieve merge request details, perform code analysis (including file type breakdowns and change statistics), and automatically generate structured documentation in Confluence pages. Built with comprehensive error handling and detailed logging, it''s particularly valuable for development teams who want to maintain up-to-date documentation of their code changes without leaving their conversation interface.', '@codebywaqas', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/codebywaqas/mrconfluencelinker-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/codebywaqas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936381+00:00'),
  ('code-context-semantic-code-search', 'Code Context (Semantic Code Search)', 'Code Context MCP server that provides semantic code search and understanding capabilities by cloning git repositories, splitting code into semantic chunks, and generating embeddings using HuggingFace transformers. Built with TypeScript and SQLite, it features intelligent code splitting based on file types, vector similarity search, and keyword filtering. Particularly valuable for developers who want to search and understand large codebases through natural language queries without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@fkesheh', 'databases', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/fkesheh/code-context-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/fkesheh.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936398+00:00'),
  ('local-voice', 'Local Voice', 'Provides text-to-speech capabilities using local Chatterbox TTS and Kokoro neural models. Supports voice cloning via reference audio, prosody controls for expressiveness, and multi-language synthesis with 40+ voices. Runs entirely locally with cross-platform audio playback and automatic dependency management.', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.pulsemcp.com/servers/codecraftersllc-local-voice', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936422+00:00'),
  ('io-github-egoughnour-code-firewall-mcp', 'io.github.egoughnour/code-firewall-mcp', 'Structural similarity-based code filter. Stops malicious code pattern reaching execution tools.', '@egoughnour', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/egoughnour/code-firewall-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/egoughnour.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.936437+00:00');



list_auction: Scan ebay for auctions. This tool is helpful for finding auctions on ebay.
Required "query" argument for the search query
Optional "ammount" argument for ammount of results
defaults to 0
Returns result from Ebay''s REST API', '@cookey-monster', 'search', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/cookey-monster/ebaymcpserver', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cookey-monster.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939161+00:00'),
  ('cookie-jar', 'Cookie Jar', 'This MCP Cookie Server by Bhargav Nookala provides AI assistants with cookie management capabilities for web automation and testing workflows. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, the implementation enables programmatic cookie storage, retrieval, and manipulation operations that can be integrated into browser automation scripts or API testing scenarios. The server is designed for developers who need to manage session state and authentication cookies across different web services, making it valuable for testing authenticated endpoints, maintaining login sessions, or debugging cookie-related issues in web applications.', '@bnookala', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/bnookala/mcp-cookiejar', 'mcp-cookie-server', 3832, 'https://github.com/bnookala.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939189+00:00'),
  ('zotero', 'Zotero', 'This MCP server provides integration with Zotero reference management software through a dual-component architecture: a Zotero plugin that runs an HTTP server within Zotero, and a standalone MCP server that communicates with it. Built using TypeScript with the Zotero Plugin Toolkit and MCP SDK, it exposes four core tools for pinging the server, searching the Zotero library, retrieving detailed item information by key, and finding items by DOI/ISBN identifiers. The implementation allows AI assistants to access bibliographic data, abstracts, tags, notes, and attachments from Zotero libraries, making it valuable for academic research workflows, literature reviews, and citation management tasks where programmatic access to reference data is needed.', '@cookjohn', 'development', 'Unknown', 419, 'https://github.com/cookjohn/zotero-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cookjohn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939221+00:00'),
  ('cookwith-recipe', 'Cookwith Recipe', 'Provides AI-powered recipe generation from natural language descriptions and recipe transformation capabilities. Supports dietary restrictions, allergies, and nutritional targeting including calorie and protein goals. Integrates with the cookwith.co platform to deliver personalized cooking assistance.', '@valetdotdev', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/valetdotdev/recipe-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/valetdotdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939252+00:00'),
  ('coolify', 'Coolify', 'Provides complete integration with Coolify''s self-hosted PaaS platform through its REST API, enabling management of applications, databases, services, servers, and deployments via natural language commands. Built by Pavel Sukhachev with TypeScript and comprehensive test coverage, this server exposes over 40 tools for operations like creating Git-based applications, setting up databases (PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis), managing environment variables, executing commands in containers, and monitoring deployment logs. Includes pre-built prompts for common workflows like deploying applications from repositories, setting up SSL certificates, scaling resources, and troubleshooting failed deployments, making it valuable for developers who want to manage their Coolify infrastructure through AI assistants without switching to the web interface.', '@pavelsukhachev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/pavelsukhachev/mcp-server-coolify', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/pavelsukhachev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939263+00:00'),
  ('home-assistant-vibecode', 'Home Assistant (Vibecode)', 'Connects MCP-enabled IDEs like Cursor, VS Code, and Claude Code to Home Assistant for configuration development and management. Provides tools for creating automations, designing dashboards, modifying themes and configs, analyzing existing setups, and deploying changes with automatic Git versioning through an on-board Home Assistant add-on that exposes a safe REST API.', '@coolver', 'development', 'Unknown', 39, 'https://github.com/coolver/home-assistant-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/coolver.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939301+00:00'),
  ('second-opinion-gemini', 'Second Opinion (Gemini)', 'Second Opinion is a code review and analysis tool that provides AI-powered second opinions on challenging coding issues using Google Gemini models. It features streaming responses with automatic fallback between Gemini models, context caching for cost reduction, multi-turn session management with budget controls, and agentic capabilities through web search and URL fetching tools with SSRF protection. The server includes secret scanning, structured prompting with XML delimiters to prevent injection, and supports both brief and detailed analysis modes with cost estimation and token tracking.', '@cooneycw', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/cooneycw/claude-power-pack/tree/HEAD/mcp-second-opinion', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cooneycw.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939327+00:00'),
  ('lifelogger', 'Lifelogger', 'Personal knowledge system that captures information entries, automatically generates flashcards, and schedules spaced repetition reviews using the SM-2 algorithm for optimal long-term retention.', '@coopermayne', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/coopermayne/mcp-personal', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/coopermayne.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939390+00:00'),
  ('copus', 'Copus', 'Copus MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to Copus''s human-curated content discovery platform. Unlike SEO-driven search results, Copus surfaces recommendations from real people who explain why content is valuable. The server offers two tools: search_curations for finding expert-vetted content recommendations by keyword, and get_curation for retrieving detailed information including curator notes, credentials, key takeaways, and engagement metrics. Available via npm for use with Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Cline, Continue, and other MCP-compatible clients.', '@copus-io', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/copus-io/copus-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/copus-io.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939414+00:00'),
  ('fabric-atelier', 'Fabric Atelier', 'Fabric Atelier is a high-performance server built in Rust that exposes all 226+ expert-crafted Fabric patterns as tools for content processing. Created by copyleftdev, it features sub-millisecond semantic search using Apache Arrow and Parquet for columnar data operations, with advanced performance optimizations including SIMD acceleration, parallel processing with rayon, and memory-mapped I/O for enterprise-scale deployments. The implementation automatically loads patterns from Daniel Miessler''s Fabric repository via git submodules and integrates with multiple LLM providers (Ollama, OpenAI, Anthropic), providing specialized tools for writing assistance, security analysis, code generation, threat assessment, and content analysis for developers and teams who want to leverage Fabric''s battle-tested prompt engineering patterns through a fast, production-ready interface.', '@copyleftdev', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/copyleftdev/fabric-atelier', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/copyleftdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939445+00:00'),
  ('toon-format', 'TOON Format', 'Provides TOON format encoding and decoding for LLM cost optimization, achieving token savings over standard JSON. Exposes tools for converting JSON to the compact TOON format and back, validating TOON syntax, and computing comparative statistics between formats. Built with both MCP stdio transport for Claude Desktop integration and HTTP REST API support with Swagger documentation.', '@copyleftdev', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/copyleftdev/toon-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/copyleftdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939480+00:00'),
  ('coreflux-mqtt', 'Coreflux MQTT', 'Coreflux MQTT MCP Server provides AI assistants with direct access to Coreflux IoT platform capabilities through MQTT broker integration. Developed by the CorefluxCommunity, it enables dynamic discovery and execution of Coreflux actions, comprehensive management of LOT language models and rules, and real-time MQTT message handling with TLS support. The implementation automatically registers discovered actions as callable tools, includes an interactive setup assistant for configuration, and provides specialized tools for LOT code generation through integration with Coreflux''s API, making it valuable for IoT automation, device management, and industrial control systems.', '@corefluxcommunity', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/corefluxcommunity/coreflux-mqtt-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/corefluxcommunity.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939508+00:00'),
  ('marlo', 'Marlo', 'A Python client for interacting with the Marlo MCP (Model Context Protocol) server. This package provides an async client for making authenticated requests to the MCP API and includes example tools for vessel data retrieval.', '@core-marlo', 'search', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/core-marlo/marlo-mcp', 'marlo-mcp', 11088, 'https://github.com/core-marlo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.939541+00:00');


', '@crisschan', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/crisschan/mcp-repo2llm', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/crisschan.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941000+00:00'),
  ('mobile-development-tools', 'Mobile Development Tools', 'A native MCP server for mobile development that provides 36 tools across Android, iOS, and Flutter platforms, including automated SDK setup and 10 intelligent super-tools that combine multiple operations into complete workflows. Built by cristianoaredes, it features security-validated command execution, fallback systems (like using native-run when ADB is unavailable), and comprehensive tooling for device management, building, testing, and deployment across mobile platforms. The implementation includes smart device selection, automated environment fixes, complete development session setup, and multi-platform release building, making it useful for Flutter development workflows, mobile CI/CD pipelines, and AI-assisted mobile app development where you need reliable cross-platform tooling with intelligent fallbacks.', '@cristianoaredes', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/cristianoaredes/mcp-mobile-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cristianoaredes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941034+00:00'),
  ('android-debug-bridge-adb', 'Android Debug Bridge (ADB)', 'This MCP server provides Android Debug Bridge (ADB) integration, enabling AI assistants to interact with Android devices and emulators through standard ADB commands. The implementation wraps ADB functionality as MCP tools, allowing for device management, app installation, file operations, and debugging tasks directly from AI conversations. It''s particularly useful for Android developers and testers who want to automate device interactions, troubleshoot applications, or perform bulk operations across multiple devices without manually executing ADB commands.', '@cristianoritta', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/cristianoritta/mcp_adb', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cristianoritta.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941062+00:00'),
  ('lean-mathlib-4-documentation', 'Lean Mathlib 4 Documentation', 'Enables searching through Lean Mathlib 4 documentation by downloading and parsing declaration data from the official Lean community documentation site. Provides regex-based search functionality to find theorems, definitions, and other mathematical constructs by name, returning formatted results with documentation links and type information. Designed for mathematicians and formal verification practitioners working with Lean who need quick access to Mathlib''s extensive library of mathematical formalization.', '@criticalline', 'search', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/criticalline/lean-mathlib-docs-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/criticalline.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941156+00:00'),
  ('jina-supabase-rag', 'Jina Supabase RAG', 'A documentation crawling and indexing server by Marty Martin that combines Jina AI''s Reader API with Crawl4AI for intelligent content extraction and stores processed documents in Supabase with pgvector for semantic search. The implementation features multi-strategy URL discovery (sitemap parsing, recursive crawling), dual extraction methods with automatic fallback, intelligent text chunking by headers and paragraphs, OpenAI embedding generation, and vector similarity search with project-based filtering.', '@croakingtoad', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/croakingtoad/mcp-jina-supabase-rag', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/croakingtoad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941172+00:00'),
  ('croit-ceph', 'Croit Ceph', 'This MCP server by Croit provides dynamic access to Ceph cluster management through the Croit platform''s OpenAPI specification. Built with Python and aiohttp, it automatically fetches the swagger.json from a Croit cluster and dynamically generates MCP tools for each API endpoint, supporting both individual endpoint-as-tool mapping and generic API calling approaches with configurable reference resolution for OpenAPI schemas. The implementation includes comprehensive request handling with path parameters, query parameters, and request bodies, plus Docker containerization with GitLab CI/CD pipeline for automated publishing to Docker Hub and the MCP registry, making it valuable for storage administrators managing Ceph clusters through AI assistants, DevOps teams automating storage operations, and organizations integrating Ceph management into their AI-powered infrastructure workflows.', '@croit', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/croit/mcp-croit-ceph', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/croit.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941197+00:00'),
  ('hippycampus-openapi-tools', 'Hippycampus (OpenAPI Tools)', 'Hippycampus is a LangChain-based MCP server that dynamically loads OpenAPI specifications to expose external APIs as tools for AI agents. Developed by Ray Cromwell, it bridges the gap between LangChain''s structured agent capabilities and the MCP protocol, enabling seamless integration with Langflow for visual workflow creation. The server supports both CLI and SSE transport modes, automatically converts OpenAPI endpoints into structured tools, and handles authentication tokens for secure API access. Particularly useful for developers who want to quickly enable AI assistants to interact with existing REST APIs without writing custom tool implementations.', '@cromwellian', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/cromwellian/hippycampus', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cromwellian.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941242+00:00'),
  ('crowdstrike-falcon', 'CrowdStrike Falcon', 'CrowdStrike Falcon MCP server that provides AI assistants with direct access to CrowdStrike''s cybersecurity platform through comprehensive modules covering detections, incidents, threat intelligence, host management, vulnerability scanning, cloud security, identity protection, and sensor usage analytics. Built by CrowdStrike''s cloud integrations team, the implementation uses the FalconPy SDK with proper API scope management and error handling, supporting multiple transport methods (stdio, SSE, streamable-http) and featuring modular architecture with FQL query guides, retry logic for E2E testing, and Docker deployment options. Designed for security operations teams, threat hunters, and incident responders who need conversational access to their CrowdStrike environment for tasks like investigating security alerts, analyzing threat intelligence, managing endpoints, and generating security reports without switching between multiple interfaces.', '@crowdstrike', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 115, 'https://github.com/crowdstrike/falcon-mcp', 'falcon-mcp', 24120, 'https://github.com/crowdstrike.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941273+00:00'),
  ('teamtailor', 'Teamtailor', 'MCP Teamtailor provides a server implementation that enables AI assistants to interact with the Teamtailor recruitment platform API. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it exposes tools for listing candidates with filtering options and retrieving detailed candidate information. The server requires API key authentication through environment variables and supports deployment via npm, making it valuable for teams that want to integrate AI assistants with their recruitment workflows for candidate discovery and evaluation.', '@crunchloop', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/crunchloop/mcp-teamtailor', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/crunchloop.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941300+00:00'),
  ('scryfall', 'Scryfall', 'This MCP server, developed by cryppadotta, provides a standardized interface for interacting with the Scryfall Magic: The Gathering API. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for card searches, retrieving card details, rulings, and pricing information. The implementation focuses on exposing Scryfall''s comprehensive database through a consistent MCP interface, enabling AI models to perform complex card queries and game-related operations. By connecting AI assistants with Scryfall''s extensive MTG data, this server facilitates sophisticated scenarios like deck building assistance, card market analysis, and rules clarification. It''s particularly valuable for applications and AI systems aimed at enhancing Magic: The Gathering gameplay, collection management, and strategic analysis.', '@cryppadotta', 'databases', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/cryppadotta/scryfall-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cryppadotta.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941311+00:00'),
  ('solana-blockchain', 'Solana Blockchain', 'Solana Agent Kit MCP Server provides a standardized interface for Claude AI to interact with the Solana blockchain through custom actions. Built by cryptoleek, it extends the Solana Agent Kit with specialized tools for retrieving validator information, estimating priority fees, fetching transaction histories, and extracting security contact information from Solana programs. The implementation integrates with Helius API for blockchain data access and includes core Solana functionality for asset management, token operations, and network information, making it particularly valuable for users who need to perform blockchain operations within AI conversations.', '@cryptoleek-team', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/cryptoleek-team/awesome-solana-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cryptoleek-team.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941337+00:00'),
  ('solana-rugcheck-transaction-helper', 'Solana RugCheck & Transaction Helper', 'GOAT-MCP is a Solana blockchain integration that enables AI assistants to interact with on-chain data and execute transactions through a Model Context Protocol server. It implements two key plugins: RugCheck for token security analysis (detecting potential scams and generating token reports) and TransactionHelper for retrieving transaction history using the Helius API. The implementation uses a standardized configuration approach with environment variables for wallet private keys and RPC provider URLs, making it particularly valuable for AI agents that need to perform secure Solana blockchain operations or analyze token safety.', '@cryptoleek-team', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/cryptoleek-team/goat-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cryptoleek-team.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.941384+00:00');

