  ('scrapling-fetch', 'Scrapling Fetch', 'Scrapling Fetch MCP enables AI assistants to access text content from websites protected by bot detection mechanisms, bridging the gap between what humans can view in browsers and what AIs can access. Built by cyberchitta, it provides two main tools: s-fetch-page for retrieving complete web pages with pagination support, and s-fetch-pattern for extracting specific content using regex patterns with surrounding context. The server offers three protection levels (basic, stealth, and max-stealth) to handle various degrees of bot detection, making it particularly valuable for retrieving documentation and reference materials from protected sites without requiring users to manually copy and paste content.', '@cyberchitta', 'communication', 'Unknown', 65, 'https://github.com/cyberchitta/scrapling-fetch-mcp', 'scrapling-fetch-mcp', 9411, 'https://github.com/cyberchitta.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942769+00:00'),
  ('tcl-udf', 'TCL UDF', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with a complete TCL scripting environment and dynamic tool management system, built by Cyberdione Labs using Rust with the Molt TCL interpreter. The implementation offers both direct TCL script execution and a sophisticated tool framework where users can create, persist, and execute custom tools with parameter validation, namespace organization (bin/sbin/user), and filesystem-based tool discovery. Built with privileged/restricted execution modes, file-based persistence, and support for both inline TCL scripts and executable .tcl files with metadata annotations, it serves developers needing programmable automation capabilities, system administrators requiring scriptable tools with proper isolation, and teams building custom workflow automation where TCL''s text processing and system integration capabilities can be leveraged through conversational AI interfaces.', '@cyberdione', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/cyberdione/mcp-tcl-udf-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cyberdione.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942805+00:00'),
  ('cyberedu', 'CyberEdu', 'Official MCP server for the CyberEdu CTF platform that provides access to cybersecurity challenges, contests, file downloads, service deployment, flag submission, and leaderboard tracking. Includes dynamic tool discovery that automatically exposes all CyberEduClient methods as MCP tools, enabling comprehensive interaction with CyberEdu''s hands-on labs, realistic simulations, and competitive environments.', '@cyberedu-cyber-range', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/cyberedu-cyber-range/cyberedu-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cyberedu-cyber-range.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942831+00:00'),
  ('exploit-db', 'Exploit-DB', 'Integrates the Exploit-DB vulnerability database with searchsploit command-line functionality. Enables searching for exploits by keyword, CVE identifier, or software version, retrieving exploit code and metadata, and managing local database updates. Designed for security researchers and penetration testers who need to quickly identify relevant exploits during vulnerability assessments without manually navigating the Exploit-DB interface.', '@cyberroute', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/cyberroute/mcp_exploitdb', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cyberroute.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942841+00:00'),
  ('offensive-security-toolkit', 'Offensive Security Toolkit', 'Offensive-MCP-AI is a cybersecurity toolkit that provides AI assistants with access to penetration testing and security analysis capabilities. The implementation consists of four specialized servers: a payload generator for creating various attack payloads using tools like msfvenom and Sliver, a reconnaissance server for domain enumeration and DNS analysis, a shellcode builder for compiling and extracting code from binaries, and a Wazuh integration for security monitoring and response. Each server exposes its functionality through the MCP protocol, enabling AI systems to execute security testing commands, analyze alerts, and generate offensive security artifacts in a structured manner, making it particularly useful for red team operations, vulnerability assessment, and security education.', '@joasasantos', 'development', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/joasasantos/offensive-mcp-ai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/joasasantos.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942883+00:00'),
  ('cyber-sentinel', 'Cyber Sentinel', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with threat intelligence aggregation capabilities across multiple security sources including VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, URLhaus, Shodan, ThreatFox, and MalwareBazaar, built by Zeng Junxiang using Python with FastMCP and asyncio for concurrent processing. The implementation offers seven core tools for analyzing security indicators (IPs, domains, hashes, URLs) with automatic type detection and confidence scoring, checking API status across configured sources, performing code security analysis with vulnerability detection, scanning project dependencies for known security issues, analyzing Docker configurations for security best practices, scanning Kubernetes manifests for security risks, and generating visual security reports with Mermaid charts. Built with intelligent caching, rate limiting, error recovery mechanisms, and zero data storage for privacy protection, it serves security analysts needing unified threat intelligence queries across multiple sources, incident response teams requiring rapid IOC analysis, and DevOps teams wanting to integrate security scanning into AI-assisted workflows with automated vulnerability detection and reporting.', '@jx888-max', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/jx888-max/cyber-sentinel-mcp', 'cyber-sentinel-mcp', 539, 'https://github.com/jx888-max.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942915+00:00'),
  ('cybersim-pro', 'CyberSim Pro', 'Provides comprehensive cybersecurity training and incident response simulation capabilities. Generates adaptive adversary scenarios based on real APT profiles and CVEs, simulates multi-phase attacks, and produces detection artifacts including Sigma, Splunk, and KQL rules. Supports incident timeline reconstruction, digital forensics analysis, and integrates with MITRE ATT&CK framework. Includes governance features like RBAC, audit logging, and compliance reporting for professional security teams.', '@kayembahamid', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/kayembahamid/cybersim-pro', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kayembahamid.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942938+00:00'),
  ('scaleway-functions', 'Scaleway Functions', 'This MCP server provides integration with Scaleway''s serverless Functions platform, enabling AI assistants to create, deploy, update, and manage serverless functions directly from code directories. Built in Go with comprehensive testing and CI/CD workflows, it offers tools for namespace management, function deployment with automatic code archiving and upload, runtime configuration, and function lifecycle operations including downloading existing function code. The implementation includes safety features that prevent deletion of resources not created by the tool through tagging, supports both SSE and stdio transports, and features progress reporting during deployment operations, making it valuable for developers building serverless applications on Scaleway who need AI-assisted function management and deployment automation.', '@cyclimse', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/cyclimse/mcp-scaleway-functions', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cyclimse.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.942969+00:00');



