  ('onos', 'ONOS', 'An MCP server for ONOS (Open Network Operating System) that provides programmatic access to network management, device control, and analytics through a rich set of resources and tools. Developed by David Lin, this server enables interaction with ONOS''s REST API, offering capabilities like network topology exploration, flow management, application control, and system diagnostics, making it valuable for SDN research, network prototyping, and educational environments.', '@davidlin2k', 'search', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/davidlin2k/onos-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidlin2k.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946625+00:00'),
  ('pox-sdn-controller', 'POX SDN Controller', 'POX MCP Server provides a bridge to the POX SDN controller, enabling AI assistants to manage and configure OpenFlow-based networks. Developed by David Lin, this implementation exposes network topology information and controller configurations through resources, while offering specialized prompts for network management, hub implementation, and learning switch configuration. The server includes tools for datapath management, flow statistics retrieval, and table configuration, making it particularly valuable for educational environments, network prototyping, and SDN research where AI assistants need to interact with network infrastructure.', '@davidlin2k', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/davidlin2k/pox-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidlin2k.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946672+00:00'),
  ('git-file-forensics', 'Git File Forensics', 'This MCP server, developed by davidorex.ai, provides deep git file-level forensics capabilities. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for tracking file versions, analyzing diffs, examining commit contexts, and evaluating semantic changes. The implementation focuses on individual file analysis rather than repository-wide operations, enabling detailed insights into file histories and change patterns. It''s particularly useful for developers and code reviewers who need to investigate specific file changes, track complex refactorings, or assess code evolution over time, without requiring extensive git expertise.', '@davidorex', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/davidorex/git-file-forensics', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidorex.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946699+00:00'),
  ('git-forensics', 'Git Forensics', 'This MCP server, developed by davidorex.ai, provides deep git repository analysis and investigation capabilities. Built with TypeScript using the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for branch overview, time period analysis, file change tracking, and merge recommendations. The implementation focuses on forensic examination of git histories, enabling detailed insights into development patterns and repository structures. It''s particularly useful for development teams and code auditors who need to understand complex git workflows, assess merge risks, and optimize branching strategies without manually parsing git logs. The server can be integrated with any MCP-compatible client, making it versatile for various git analysis workflows.', '@davidorex', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/davidorex/git-forensics-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidorex.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946725+00:00'),
  ('project-handoffs', 'Project Handoffs', 'This MCP server implementation, developed for managing AI session handoffs and next steps, provides a TypeScript-based interface leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK. It offers tools for coordinating AI workflows across multiple sessions or models. The implementation focuses on maintaining context and continuity between AI interactions, enabling seamless handoffs and structured progression of tasks. It''s particularly useful for complex, multi-stage AI processes that require coordination between different models or handling extended user interactions over time. The server allows for efficient management of AI conversation flows, task delegation, and context preservation without requiring deep knowledge of underlying AI model architectures.', '@davidorex', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/davidorex/project-handoffs', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidorex.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946757+00:00'),
  ('aws-bedrock', 'AWS Bedrock', 'This AWS Bedrock MCP implementation, developed by Anthropic, provides a seamless integration between Anthropic''s Model Context Protocol and Amazon''s Bedrock service. Built with Python using boto3 and the MCP SDK, it offers a client that can interact with MCP-enabled tools through Bedrock''s runtime service, specifically using the Nova Pro model. The implementation features tool format conversion for Bedrock compatibility, asynchronous communication handling, and structured logging. By bridging MCP and Bedrock, it enables AI systems to leverage both protocols'' strengths, making it particularly useful for developers looking to combine Anthropic''s MCP capabilities with AWS''s scalable infrastructure for applications in natural language processing, task automation, and AI-assisted decision making.', '@davidshtian', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 55, 'https://github.com/davidshtian/mcp-on-aws-bedrock', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidshtian.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946774+00:00'),
  ('context-manager', 'Context Manager', 'This TypeScript-based MCP server implementation, developed using the Model Context Protocol SDK, provides a foundation for building AI-driven applications. It leverages modern JavaScript features and TypeScript''s type safety to create a robust and scalable server structure. The implementation is designed to be easily extensible, allowing developers to integrate various AI models or services. It''s particularly well-suited for projects requiring a lightweight, customizable MCP endpoint, such as chatbots, content generation tools, or data analysis applications. The server''s modular architecture and use of up-to-date dependencies make it adaptable to a wide range of AI-powered use cases, from simple text processing to more complex multi-modal interactions.', '@davidteren', 'development', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/davidteren/claude-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidteren.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946804+00:00'),
  ('play-sound', 'Play Sound', 'This MCP server provides audio notification capabilities for AI agents, enabling them to play sound alerts when coding tasks are completed. Built using Python with FastMCP and multiple audio backend support (afplay for macOS and simpleaudio for cross-platform compatibility), it offers four core tools: play_notification_sound for triggering audio alerts with custom or default sounds, get_audio_status for checking system configuration and available backends, test_audio_playback for troubleshooting audio functionality, and list_audio_devices for discovering available output devices on macOS. The implementation features automatic fallback between audio backends, volume control, device switching capabilities, configurable timeouts, and security restrictions to prevent unauthorized file access, making it valuable for developers who want audible feedback from AI coding assistants to stay informed about task completion without constantly monitoring their screens.', '@davidteren', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/davidteren/play-sound-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidteren.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946841+00:00'),
  ('code-analysis', 'Code Analysis', 'This Code Analysis MCP plugin, developed by an unspecified author, enables AI assistants to perform sophisticated code analysis using a Neo4j graph database. Built with Java and leveraging libraries like JavaParser and Neo4j, it offers tools for analyzing code structure, calculating quality metrics, extracting documentation, and answering high-level questions about codebases. The plugin implements advanced metrics calculation and natural language query processing, abstracting the complexities of code parsing and graph database operations. By providing a comprehensive view of code structure and quality, it allows AI systems to generate insights, identify potential issues, and assist in code review processes. This implementation is particularly valuable for software development teams, code reviewers, and architects, facilitating use cases such as architectural analysis, code quality assessment, and automated documentation generation.', '@davidvc', 'databases', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/davidvc/code-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidvc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946864+00:00'),
  ('code-embeddings', 'Code Embeddings', 'A knowledge management tool for code repositories using vector embeddings. This tool helps maintain and query knowledge about your codebase using advanced embedding techniques.', '@davidvc', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/davidvc/code-knowledge-mcptool', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/davidvc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946882+00:00'),
  ('davinci-resolve', 'DaVinci Resolve', 'DaVinci Resolve MCP Server enables AI assistants like Claude to directly interact with and control DaVinci Resolve through its Python API. Built by apvlv, the server provides tools for project management, timeline manipulation, media organization, and Fusion integration, allowing users to programmatically create, modify, and inspect video editing projects through natural language commands.', '@apvlv', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 52, 'https://github.com/apvlv/davinci-resolve-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/apvlv.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946917+00:00'),
  ('clever-cloud', 'Clever Cloud', 'This MCP server, developed by David Legrand, provides a JavaScript-based interface for AI assistants to interact with Clever Cloud''s tools and services. Built using the mcp-js-server SDK, it offers a streamlined way to access Clever Cloud''s platform capabilities. The implementation focuses on simplicity and ease of use, requiring minimal setup to get started. It''s particularly useful for developers and AI models looking to leverage Clever Cloud''s infrastructure and services, enabling tasks like application deployment, environment management, or resource monitoring without requiring deep knowledge of Clever Cloud''s API intricacies.', '@davlgd', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/davlgd/mcp-clever-demo', 'mcp-clever-demo', 1273, 'https://github.com/davlgd.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946961+00:00'),
  ('affine', 'AFFiNE', 'AFFiNE MCP server that provides AI assistants with comprehensive access to AFFiNE workspaces, documents, and collaboration features through GraphQL and WebSocket integration. Built by dawncr0w, the implementation supports multiple authentication methods (bearer tokens, session cookies, email/password), offers 50+ tools across workspace management, document operations, real-time collaboration, version control, user management, and blob storage. Features advanced capabilities like CRDT-based document updates using Yjs, WebSocket-powered real-time synchronization, and workspace creation with proper AFFiNE document structure, making it valuable for knowledge management workflows, collaborative document editing, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to AFFiNE''s full feature set.', '@dawncr0w', 'development', 'Unknown', 87, 'https://github.com/dawncr0w/affine-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dawncr0w.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.946992+00:00'),
  ('cocos-creator', 'Cocos Creator', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with comprehensive control over Cocos Creator 3.8 game development workflows, built using TypeScript with extensive tool coverage across scene manipulation, node management, component operations, asset handling, prefab creation, and project debugging. The implementation offers over 50 specialized tools organized into categories including scene hierarchy management with node creation/deletion/property modification, component addition/removal with real-time property updates, asset database queries with support for textures/materials/prefabs, project-level operations for settings and build management, and debugging capabilities with console log capture and performance monitoring. Built with both Editor API integration for design-time operations and runtime scene script execution for live game state manipulation, it serves game developers needing AI assistance with Cocos Creator workflows, technical artists requiring automated scene setup and asset management, and development teams wanting to integrate AI-powered debugging and optimization into their game development pipeline.', '@daxianlee', 'databases', 'Unknown', 542, 'https://github.com/daxianlee/cocos-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/daxianlee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947004+00:00'),
  ('hwpx-editor', 'HWPX Editor', 'Enables comprehensive editing and manipulation of HWPX and HWP Korean word processing documents with 76 specialized tools covering text operations, table management, styling, search/replace, metadata handling, and document structure through both VS Code extension and server interfaces.', '@dayoooun', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/dayoooun/hwpx-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dayoooun.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947028+00:00'),
  ('github-mapper', 'GitHub Mapper', 'This GitHub Mapper MCP server, developed by an unnamed author, provides AI assistants with capabilities to analyze and map GitHub repositories. Built using TypeScript and leveraging the Octokit REST API client, it offers functionalities for authenticating with GitHub, retrieving repository metadata, and generating detailed file structure maps. The server abstracts the complexities of GitHub API interactions, enabling AI systems to easily access and process repository information. It''s particularly valuable for developers and researchers working on code analysis, project management, and software development workflows, facilitating use cases such as automated code reviews, dependency analysis, and repository structure visualization.', '@dazeb', 'development', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/dazeb/mcp-github-mapper', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dazeb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947053+00:00'),
  ('markdown-downloader', 'Markdown Downloader', 'This Markdown Downloader MCP server, developed by an unknown author, provides AI assistants with capabilities to download and process Markdown content. Built with TypeScript and leveraging libraries like axios and fs-extra, it offers a streamlined interface for retrieving Markdown files from URLs, parsing their content, and saving them locally. The server implements error handling and file system operations to manage downloaded content effectively. By abstracting the complexities of web requests and file manipulation, it enables AI systems to easily incorporate Markdown processing into their workflows. This implementation is particularly useful for content aggregation, documentation management, and text analysis tasks, facilitating use cases such as automated content curation, knowledge base creation, and structured data extraction from Markdown sources.', '@dazeb', 'development', 'Unknown', 49, 'https://github.com/dazeb/markdown-downloader', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dazeb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947087+00:00'),
  ('mssql-dba', 'MSSQL DBA', 'Empowers language models to perform SQL Server database administration tasks including query optimization, table health assessment, index management, and performance analysis. Provides tools for retrieving execution plans from Query Store, identifying missing indexes, analyzing wait statistics, and optimizing database performance. Requires SQL Server login with VIEW SERVER STATE and VIEW DEFINITION permissions.', '@dba-i', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/dba-i/mssql-dba', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dba-i.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947100+00:00'),
  ('aws-amplify-data', 'AWS Amplify Data', 'AWS Amplify Data MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and AWS Amplify Data APIs, enabling interaction with GraphQL-based data models through a standardized interface. This implementation authenticates with Amazon Cognito, introspects data models from Amplify outputs, and offers tools for listing models, querying relationships, and executing custom GraphQL operations. It handles authentication token refresh automatically and provides detailed model information, making it particularly useful for AI agents that need to access or manipulate data in Amplify-powered applications without requiring users to write complex GraphQL queries.', '@dbsmith7491', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/dbsmith7491/aws-amplify-data-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dbsmith7491.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947150+00:00'),
  ('dbt', 'dbt', 'dbt-MCP server provides a bridge between AI assistants and dbt (data build tool) resources, enabling interaction with data models, metrics, and transformations. Built by dbt Labs, it offers tools for executing dbt CLI commands, discovering metadata about models, and querying the dbt Semantic Layer. The server supports local dbt project operations, metadata retrieval from dbt Cloud, and metric querying capabilities, making it valuable for data analysts and engineers who want to explore, analyze, and manage their data transformations through natural language interfaces without manually navigating dbt''s command line or web interface.', '@dbt-labs', 'development', 'Unknown', 503, 'https://github.com/dbt-labs/dbt-mcp', 'dbt-mcp', 228626, 'https://github.com/dbt-labs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947176+00:00'),
  ('deadends-dev', 'Deadends.dev', 'Structured failure knowledge for AI agents — dead ends, workarounds, error chains.', '@dbwls99706', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/dbwls99706/deadends.dev', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dbwls99706.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947200+00:00'),
  ('terraform-registry', 'Terraform Registry', 'Terraform MCP Server provides seamless integration with Terraform Registry APIs, enabling advanced automation and interaction capabilities for Infrastructure as Code development. Developed by HashiCorp, this server exposes tools for automating Terraform provider and module discovery, extracting data from Terraform Registry, getting detailed information about provider resources and data sources, and exploring Terraform modules. Built with Go and packaged as a Docker container, it features a robust architecture with standardized communication protocols and comprehensive testing. The server is particularly valuable for developers who need to programmatically interact with Terraform resources or automate infrastructure workflows through natural language interfaces.', '@dcamonier1980', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/dcamonier1980/terraform-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcamonier1980.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947225+00:00'),
  ('tasker', 'Tasker', 'Tasker MCP server by Luis Sanchez that bridges AI assistants with Android''s Tasker automation platform through HTTP API integration, enabling conversational control of device automation tasks, smart home routines, and custom workflows. The implementation includes a CLI server with both stdio and SSE transport modes, a utility for converting Tasker XML exports into MCP tool definitions, and support for dynamic argument parsing from Tasker task variables with proper type inference and validation. Built with Go and designed for Android power users, it transforms Tasker''s extensive automation capabilities into AI-accessible tools, making it valuable for voice-controlled home automation, contextual device management, and integrating physical world actions into AI workflows through Tasker''s deep Android system integration.', '@dceluis', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/dceluis/tasker-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dceluis.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947273+00:00'),
  ('bloodyad', 'bloodyAD', 'This bloodyAD MCP server by Diego Collao Albornoz provides Active Directory penetration testing and enumeration capabilities through a Docker-containerized wrapper around the bloodyAD tool. Built with FastMCP and running on Kali Linux in Docker, it offers 26 specialized tools covering AD reconnaissance (object enumeration, DNS dumping, trust mapping), privilege escalation (DCSync rights, shadow credentials, RBCD), and object manipulation (user/computer creation, group membership management, password changes) with support for various authentication methods including Kerberos. The implementation includes comprehensive setup automation scripts for Windows, Linux, and macOS that handle Docker image building, MCP configuration, and Gemini CLI integration, making it valuable for penetration testers and red team operators who need AI-assisted Active Directory attack workflows within controlled lab environments like HackTheBox.', '@dcollaoa', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/dcollaoa/bloodyad_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcollaoa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947299+00:00'),
  ('swagger-api', 'Swagger API', 'Swagger MCP Server ingests Swagger/OpenAPI specifications and exposes them as MCP tools, enabling AI assistants to interact with any API documented in the OpenAPI format. It supports multiple authentication methods (Basic Auth, Bearer Token, API Key, OAuth2), automatically generates tools from API endpoints, and provides real-time communication through Server-Sent Events. The implementation is designed for personal use to create a bridge between AI assistants and existing web APIs, making it particularly valuable for developers who want to give their AI assistants access to specific services without writing custom integrations for each API.', '@dcolley', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 114, 'https://github.com/dcolley/swagger-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcolley.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947346+00:00'),
  ('aws-rds-mysql', 'AWS RDS MySQL', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to AWS RDS MySQL databases through a single SQL execution tool that handles both SELECT queries and data modification operations. Built using Python with FastMCP and PyMySQL, it includes basic safety measures by blocking dangerous operations like DROP DATABASE and TRUNCATE while supporting standard database operations with proper connection management, error handling, and result formatting. The implementation uses environment-based configuration for database credentials and connection parameters, making it valuable for AI assistants that need to query production databases, analyze data warehouse contents, or perform database administration tasks without manual SQL client interaction.', '@dcs5star', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/dcs5star/aws-rds-mysql-mcp-server-amazonq-cli', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcs5star.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947357+00:00'),
  ('ethereum-wallet-evm', 'Ethereum Wallet (EVM)', 'MCP Crypto Wallet EVM provides Claude with access to Ethereum and EVM-compatible blockchain operations through ethers.js v5. Developed by dcSpark, this server enables wallet creation, balance checking, transaction sending, and smart contract interactions on EVM blockchains. It exposes over 40 tools organized into categories including wallet management, blockchain queries, transaction handling, and network operations, making it valuable for users who need to perform cryptocurrency operations directly through Claude without switching to specialized wallet applications.', '@dcspark', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/dcspark/mcp-cryptowallet-evm', '@mcp-dockmaster/mcp-cryptowallet-evm', 4476, 'https://github.com/dcspark.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947403+00:00'),
  ('helius-solana-blockchain', 'Helius (Solana Blockchain)', 'This MCP server implementation provides Claude with access to Solana blockchain data via the Helius API. Developed by dcSpark, it offers tools for checking wallet balances and retrieving the current block height on Solana. The server is designed for use cases requiring real-time Solana blockchain data integration, such as monitoring account balances or tracking network status.', '@dcspark', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/dcspark/mcp-server-helius', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcspark.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947442+00:00'),
  ('jupiter', 'Jupiter', 'This MCP server provides Claude with access to Jupiter''s swap API on the Solana blockchain. Developed by dcSpark, it enables operations like getting quotes, building swap transactions, and sending swap transactions. The server is designed for use cases requiring programmatic access to decentralized exchange functionality on Solana, such as automated trading strategies or integrating Jupiter swaps into other applications.', '@dcspark', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/dcspark/mcp-server-jupiter', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/dcspark.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947465+00:00'),
  ('install-mcp', 'Install MCP', 'This meta MCP server manages other MCP servers through an agent-first interface, providing a unified way to install, configure, and manage MCP servers across multiple clients including Claude Desktop, Cursor, and Windsurf. Built by ddfourtwo using Python with FastMCP, it features tools for executing installation commands within a sandboxed ~/mcp-servers/ directory, collecting API keys through a secure local web interface that saves namespaced secrets to a central .env file, and automatically configuring all MCP clients from a central configuration store with backup creation and placeholder resolution. The implementation supports both GitHub repository cloning and NPM package installation, includes portable command detection with UV integration for Python servers, and provides export/import functionality for sharing complete MCP setups across teams, making it valuable for developers who want to manage multiple MCP servers without manually editing configuration files or handling secrets across different AI tools.', '@ddfourtwo', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/ddfourtwo/install-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ddfourtwo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947588+00:00'),
  ('brain-memory-system', 'Brain Memory System', 'A TypeScript-based memory and thinking management system implementing both short-term (FIFO cache) and long-term (graph-based persistent) memory with an advanced thinking process framework. Features five cognitive modes (analytical, creative, critical, intuitive, meta-cognitive), thought chain management with branching capabilities, automatic file persistence with backup and recovery, and association-based memory retrieval. Provides comprehensive tools for memory operations, thought process tracking, and system statistics.', '@ddguan2010', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/ddguan2010/brain-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ddguan2010.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947616+00:00'),
  ('github-enterprise', 'GitHub Enterprise', 'GitHub Enterprise MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and GitHub Enterprise API, enabling repository management, issue tracking, and code access through natural language. The implementation supports both GitHub Enterprise Server and GitHub.com, with special features for enterprise environments like license information and admin statistics. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for managing repositories, branches, pull requests, issues, and GitHub Actions workflows through either stdio or HTTP transport. Particularly valuable for developers who need to interact with GitHub repositories without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@ddukbg', 'development', 'Unknown', 29, 'https://github.com/ddukbg/github-enterprise-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ddukbg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947646+00:00'),
  ('opennutrition', 'OpenNutrition', 'This MCP server provides access to the OpenNutrition food database containing 300,000+ food items with comprehensive nutritional data sourced from authoritative public databases (USDA, CNF, FRIDA, AUSNUT). The implementation offers four core tools for searching foods by name with fuzzy matching, browsing paginated food lists, retrieving detailed nutritional information by food ID, and looking up products via EAN-13 barcodes. Built with TypeScript and SQLite for local data processing, it automatically downloads and converts the OpenNutrition dataset during build, ensuring fast response times and privacy by eliminating external API calls while providing AI assistants with reliable access to accurate nutritional data for recipe analysis, dietary planning, and food composition queries.', '@deadletterq', 'databases', 'Unknown', 162, 'https://github.com/deadletterq/mcp-opennutrition', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/deadletterq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947656+00:00'),
  ('hal-http-api-layer', 'HAL (HTTP API Layer)', 'This MCP server provides HTTP API capabilities to Large Language Models through OpenAPI/Swagger integration, enabling dynamic tool generation from API specifications with comprehensive secrets management and URL restrictions. Built by Dean Ward using TypeScript with Zod validation, it offers standard HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, HEAD, OPTIONS) with secret substitution using {secrets.key} syntax, namespaced secrets with URL pattern restrictions for enhanced security, and automatic documentation search tools for API exploration. The implementation features intelligent secret loading from HAL_SECRET_ environment variables, URL validation against allowed patterns, OpenAPI spec parsing for automatic tool registration, and specialized presentation component support, making it valuable for integrating AI assistants with existing APIs, managing secure API credentials across multiple services, and building AI tools that need programmatic access to REST APIs without manual HTTP client configuration.', '@deanward', 'development', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/deanward/hal', 'hal-mcp', 5417, 'https://github.com/deanward.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947692+00:00'),
  ('rfk-jr-gateway', 'RFK Jr Gateway', 'This MCP gateway bridges AI assistants to RFK Jr campaign endpoints, enabling access to various campaign-related tools and data. It dynamically registers tools based on OpenAPI schemas from configured endpoints, supports both STDIO and SSE transports, and includes features for endpoint discovery and information retrieval. The implementation is designed for flexibility and easy integration with existing campaign infrastructure.', '@voitta-ai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/voitta-ai/mcp-voitta-gateway', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/voitta-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947731+00:00'),
  ('debtstack-ai', 'DebtStack.ai', 'Corporate credit data API for AI agents — bonds, leverage, guarantors, SEC filings.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.pulsemcp.com/servers/debtstack-ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947757+00:00'),
  ('debuggai', 'DebuggAI', 'This MCP server provides zero-configuration AI-managed end-to-end testing for web applications by integrating with the DebuggAI platform to automatically generate and execute UI tests using AI agents. Built by Quinn Osha using TypeScript with ngrok tunneling, axios for API communication, and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it creates secure tunnels to local development servers, spawns AI testing agents that interact with web interfaces through natural language descriptions, and returns detailed test results including execution recordings and final screenshots. The implementation handles the complete testing lifecycle from tunnel creation to AI agent coordination, with support for Docker deployment and configurable environment variables for repository context, making it valuable for developers who need automated UI testing without writing test scripts, continuous integration workflows requiring AI-driven quality assurance, and scenarios where traditional testing approaches are insufficient for dynamic user interfaces.', '@debugg-ai', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 91, 'https://github.com/debugg-ai/debugg-ai-mcp', '@debugg-ai/debugg-ai-mcp', 12023, 'https://github.com/debugg-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947785+00:00'),
  ('decodo-web-scraper', 'Decodo Web Scraper', 'Connects to Decodo''s enterprise web scraping platform to extract web content dynamically with geographic flexibility and advanced anti-detection. Provides specialized tools for general URL scraping, Google Search results, Amazon product searches, Reddit posts, and subreddit content with support for geo-restricted sites, JavaScript rendering, and customizable token limits.', '@decodo', 'search', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/decodo/mcp-web-scraper', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/decodo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947880+00:00'),
  ('deco-site-loaders', 'Deco Site Loaders', 'This Deco MCP server implementation enables AI assistants to interact with Deco site loaders through a standardized interface. Built with the Model Context Protocol SDK and Hono, it dynamically registers site loaders as MCP tools by extracting their schemas from the Deco metadata, allowing AI assistants to discover and invoke these tools via Server-Sent Events (SSE). The server handles tool discovery and execution requests, transforming loader results into MCP-compatible responses, making it ideal for integrating AI capabilities with Deco-powered websites and applications.', '@deco-sites', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/deco-sites/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/deco-sites.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.947926+00:00');






The server provides dynamic tool registration through Echo3D''s tool registry, exposing platform-specific capabilities for 3D model transformation, asset processing, and project management operations. Additionally, it offers resource access to project metadata and information via standardized URI schemes. Built as a dual-purpose servlet, it seamlessly handles both MCP protocol requests (JSON-RPC) and traditional management API calls, making it a versatile integration point for both AI-driven automation and administrative platform operations. This enables developers to build sophisticated AR content pipelines where AI assistants can intelligently manage, process, and deploy 3D assets across Echo3D projects.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.echo3d.com/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957578+00:00'),
  ('decompose', 'Decompose', 'Decompose text into classified semantic units. Authority, risk, attention. No LLM.', '@echology-io', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/echology-io/decompose', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/echology-io.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957598+00:00'),
  ('twitch-smithery', 'Twitch Smithery', 'Twitch MCP server by Eclipse-XV that provides AI assistants with comprehensive Twitch stream management and chat moderation capabilities through real-time IRC integration and Twitch Helix API access. The implementation combines live chat monitoring with intelligent moderation features including smart user targeting through behavioral descriptors (toxic, spam, rude), automated timeout duration selection based on violation severity, and chat analysis with word frequency tracking. Built with TypeScript using tmi.js for IRC connectivity and featuring tools for stream management (polls, predictions, clips, title/category updates), chat interaction, and moderation actions, it serves streamers needing AI-powered chat moderation, content creators requiring automated stream management, and developers building Twitch-integrated applications with real-time chat processing and API-driven stream control.', '@eclipsevr-live', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/eclipsevr-live/twitch-mcp-smithery', 'twitch-mcp-server', 431, 'https://github.com/eclipsevr-live.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957661+00:00'),
  ('universal-image-generator', 'Universal Image Generator', 'This universal image generator MCP server provides AI assistants with multi-provider image generation and transformation capabilities, supporting Google Gemini, ZhipuAI (CogView-4), and Alibaba Bailian (WanX) through a unified interface. Built by Tony Wang using Python with FastMCP, it features automatic prompt translation and optimization for each provider''s preferred language (English for Gemini, Chinese for ZhipuAI/Bailian), comprehensive image transformation tools including URL-based editing with mask support, and flexible input methods supporting base64 encoding, file paths, and public URLs. The implementation includes Docker deployment, automatic filename generation, local image saving with display functionality, and provider-specific optimizations like detailed prompt templates and translation capabilities using each provider''s native language models, making it valuable for multilingual image generation workflows, content creation pipelines, and building AI assistants that need access to diverse image generation services without manual API integration.', '@ecnu3d', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/ecnu3d/universal-image-generator-mcp', 'universal-image-generator-mcp', 2084, 'https://github.com/ecnu3d.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957695+00:00'),
  ('ecosyste-ms', 'Ecosyste.ms', 'MCP server for querying package ecosystem data from ecosyste.ms, providing comprehensive package information across 30+ ecosystems including npm, PyPI, Maven, Cargo, and more. Combines a local SQLite database of critical packages for fast lookups with API fallback for comprehensive coverage. Offers tools to retrieve package metadata, security advisories, version histories, dependency information, and repository statistics. Useful for security audits, dependency analysis, package discovery, and understanding the software supply chain across multiple programming language ecosystems.', '@ecosyste-ms', 'databases', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/ecosyste-ms/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ecosyste-ms.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957706+00:00'),
  ('ectors', 'Ectors', 'MCP-Ectors is a high-performance, actor-based MCP server that manages multiple routers, supporting tools, prompts, and resources. Developed by Maarten Ectors, it uses the Actix framework to provide a modular architecture where each router can be registered with a unique ID, allowing clients to access different capabilities through a unified interface. The server supports multiple transport protocols including SSE, STDIO, and WASI, making it versatile for various deployment scenarios. Its multi-router design enables composition of different services, with built-in examples like a counter router and hello world router demonstrating how specialized functionality can be exposed through the MCP protocol.', '@mcp-ectors', 'search', 'Unknown', 31, 'https://github.com/mcp-ectors/mcp-ectors', 'mcp-ectors', 0, 'https://github.com/mcp-ectors.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957763+00:00'),
  ('eda-tools', 'EDA Tools', 'EDA Tools MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to Electronic Design Automation workflows through a unified interface. It integrates with industry-standard tools including Yosys for Verilog synthesis, Icarus Verilog for simulation, GTKWave for waveform analysis, and OpenLane for complete ASIC design flows. The server manages project workspaces, handles file operations, and executes EDA commands with appropriate error handling and timeout management. Particularly valuable for hardware designers working with AI assistants who need to perform complex chip design tasks like RTL synthesis, simulation, timing analysis, and physical layout generation without leaving their conversation interface.', '@nellyw8', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 66, 'https://github.com/nellyw8/mcp4eda', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/nellyw8.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957807+00:00'),
  ('xcode-automation', 'Xcode Automation', 'Comprehensive Xcode automation server providing 97+ tools for iOS/macOS development workflows including project management, building, testing, simulator control, device provisioning, Swift package management, Git integration, crash analysis, and asset management. Features both local stdio and network HTTP/WebSocket modes with optional authentication, LLM-powered code analysis and error explanation using configurable providers (OpenAI, Ollama, DeepSeek), and specialized tools for performance profiling, localization, and CI/CD integration. Built with modular architecture using dynamic tool registry and supports remote access via bridge scripts.', '@eddiksonpena', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/eddiksonpena/xcode-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eddiksonpena.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957832+00:00'),
  ('sketchfab', 'Sketchfab', 'This MCP server provides a streamlined interface to the Sketchfab API, enabling users to search for and download 3D models. Developed by Eduardo del Palacio Lirola, it exposes two primary tools: one for searching downloadable models with filtering options for animated or rigged content, and another for downloading models by their unique identifier. The implementation is containerized with Docker for easy deployment and requires a Sketchfab API token for authentication, making it ideal for applications that need programmatic access to Sketchfab''s extensive 3D model library.', '@eddydpyl', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/eddydpyl/sketchfab_mcp', 'sketchfab-mcp', 2247, 'https://github.com/eddydpyl.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957863+00:00'),
  ('longman-dictionary-of-contemporary-english', 'Longman Dictionary of Contemporary English', 'LDOCE MCP Server provides a bridge to the Longman Dictionary of Contemporary English, enabling AI assistants to look up word definitions, examples, and related linguistic information. The implementation uses TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK and leverages tools like Axios, Cheerio, and TurndownJS to scrape and parse dictionary content from the LDOCE website. This server is particularly valuable for enhancing AI assistants with accurate English language definitions and usage examples without requiring context switching to external dictionary resources.', '@edgardamasceno-dev', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/edgardamasceno-dev/ldoce-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/edgardamasceno-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957895+00:00'),
  ('edgeone-geolocation', 'EdgeOne Geolocation', 'The EdgeOne Pages MCP Geo Location Service provides AI assistants with access to user geolocation information through a simple API endpoint. Built with Next.js and the Model Context Protocol SDK, this implementation exposes a single tool that fetches geographic data from EdgeOne''s edge functions and returns it in a structured JSON format. The server handles error recovery gracefully and is designed for easy deployment, making it ideal for applications that need to customize responses based on a user''s location without requiring complex setup or configuration.', '@edgego', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/edgego/mcp-geo-pub', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/edgego.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957934+00:00'),
  ('businessmap', 'BusinessMap', 'This BusinessMap (Kanbanize) MCP server by Edicarlos Lopes provides AI assistants with complete access to BusinessMap''s project management platform through 42 tools across workspace, board, card, and workflow operations. Built with TypeScript and the official MCP SDK, it integrates with BusinessMap''s REST API v2 to enable comprehensive Kanban board management including card CRUD operations, parent-child relationships, subtasks, outcomes tracking, custom fields, cycle time analysis, and user management. The implementation features read-only mode for safe exploration, Docker support for containerized deployments, automatic connection verification, and robust error handling, making it ideal for teams managing complex project workflows who need programmatic access to their BusinessMap data through conversational interfaces.', '@edicarloslds', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/edicarloslds/businessmap-mcp', '@edicarlos.lds/businessmap-mcp', 2355, 'https://github.com/edicarloslds.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957962+00:00'),
  ('io-github-ajtgjmdjp-edinet-mcp', 'io.github.ajtgjmdjp/edinet-mcp', 'Access Japanese financial disclosures (EDINET). Search companies, retrieve BS/PL/CF statements.', '@ajtgjmdjp', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/ajtgjmdjp/edinet-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ajtgjmdjp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.957983+00:00'),
  ('defi-trading-agent', 'DeFi Trading Agent', 'DeFi Trading MCP server that transforms AI assistants into autonomous crypto trading agents with real-time market analysis, portfolio management, and seamless trade execution across 17+ blockchains. Built by Ed, the implementation integrates with 0x API for swap aggregation, CoinGecko for market data, and supports both regular and gasless trading through EIP-712 signature handling and Permit2 integration. Features comprehensive blockchain support including Ethereum, Base, Arbitrum, and emerging chains like Berachain and Unichain, with automatic RPC provider management using Alchemy or public endpoints, making it valuable for traders who want conversational access to DeFi markets without manual transaction management.', '@edkdev', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 39, 'https://github.com/edkdev/defi-trading-mcp', 'defi-trading-mcp', 1041, 'https://github.com/edkdev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958037+00:00'),
  ('up-bank', 'Up Bank', 'Up Bank MCP Server provides a bridge to the Up Bank API, allowing Claude to interact with personal banking data including accounts, transactions, categories, and tags. Created by Eddie Kranz as a learning project for building MCP servers, it wraps the up-bank-api Python package to expose financial data through structured tools. The implementation enables AI assistants to analyze spending patterns, categorize transactions, and manage webhooks, making it particularly useful for personal finance analysis and transaction history review.', '@edkranz', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/edkranz/up-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/edkranz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958064+00:00'),
  ('jira-edrich13', 'Jira (edrich13)', 'Integrates with self-hosted Jira instances to provide comprehensive issue management including creation, updates, searching via JQL, comment operations, workflow transitions, and project discovery. Supports Personal Access Token authentication for secure access to on-premise Jira deployments.', '@edrich13', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/edrich13/mcp-jira-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/edrich13.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958091+00:00'),
  ('godot-script-integration', 'Godot Script Integration', 'This MCP server implementation provides integration between Godot and the Model Context Protocol, allowing access to the currently open script in the Godot editor. Developed as a TypeScript server with a Godot editor plugin, it enables AI assistants like Claude to interact with Godot scripts, supporting features such as reading current scripts, listing project scripts, and updating script information. The implementation is designed for game developers and AI researchers looking to enhance their Godot development workflow with AI assistance.', '@ee0pdt', 'development', 'Unknown', 484, 'https://github.com/ee0pdt/godot-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ee0pdt.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958117+00:00'),
  ('fast-filesystem', 'Fast Filesystem', 'Advanced filesystem operations server for Claude Desktop with large file handling capabilities and Claude-optimized features. Built by efforthye with TypeScript, it provides streaming-based writing for files of any size, auto-chunking for memory-efficient operations, sequential reading with continuation token support, and comprehensive file management including copy, move, delete, batch operations, and archive compression/extraction. The implementation includes sophisticated editing tools for precise line-based modifications, backup and recovery mechanisms, retry logic with exponential backoff, and smart exclusions for system files, making it particularly useful for developers working with large codebases, data processing workflows, and automated file operations that require reliable handling of substantial file sizes without memory overflow.', '@efforthye', 'development', 'Unknown', 43, 'https://github.com/efforthye/fast-filesystem-mcp', 'fast-filesystem-mcp', 7610, 'https://github.com/efforthye.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958147+00:00'),
  ('freshdesk', 'Freshdesk', 'Freshdesk MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the Freshdesk customer support platform, enabling comprehensive ticket management and knowledge base operations. Built by Gopi Krishnan and Maanaesh Swamy at effy, it offers tools for creating, updating, and searching tickets; managing contacts and agents; handling conversations; and working with canned responses and solution articles. The server handles Freshdesk API authentication through environment variables and implements over 30 endpoints covering the core functionality of the platform. It''s particularly valuable for support teams who need to integrate Freshdesk capabilities into conversational AI interfaces without managing the complexities of the Freshdesk API directly.', '@effytech', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 46, 'https://github.com/effytech/freshdesk_mcp', 'freshdesk-mcp', 8846, 'https://github.com/effytech.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958198+00:00'),
  ('freshservice', 'Freshservice', 'Freshservice MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the Freshservice IT service management platform, enabling comprehensive ticket management and service catalog operations. Built by Gopi Krishnan, Maanaesh Swamy, and Vijay Ragunath, it offers tools for creating, updating, and filtering tickets; managing service requests; handling conversations; and working with products, requesters, agents, and groups. The server handles Freshservice API authentication and implements a wide range of endpoints covering the core functionality of the platform. It''s particularly valuable for IT support teams who need to integrate Freshservice capabilities into conversational AI interfaces without managing the complexities of the Freshservice API directly.', '@effytech', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 18, 'https://github.com/effytech/freshservice_mcp', 'freshservice-mcp', 2591, 'https://github.com/effytech.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958247+00:00'),
  ('agileday', 'Agileday', 'Integrates with Agileday, a professional services automation platform for talent and competence management. Enables natural language queries to find employees with specific skills and proficiency levels, retrieve detailed employee competence profiles, and explore the organization''s complete skill taxonomy. Built by Eficode for talent management and project staffing decisions, helping organizations match employee capabilities with project demands without manually navigating Agileday''s interface. Supports both stdio and HTTP transport modes with Docker deployment.', '@eficode', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/eficode/mcp-agileday', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eficode.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958267+00:00'),
  ('youtube-knowledge', 'YouTube Knowledge', 'Transforms YouTube into a queryable knowledge source through five specialized tools for video search, detailed content analysis, trending discovery, channel research, and AI-powered content insights. Built with intelligent quota management and multi-tier caching (Redis/memory) to optimize YouTube Data API usage, the implementation includes transcript extraction via web scraping, comment sentiment analysis, and optional LLM integration with OpenAI/Anthropic for advanced features like learning path generation, knowledge graph creation, and content simplification. Features automatic quota optimization, fallback mechanisms for API limits, and comprehensive analytics tracking, making it valuable for content creators researching competitors and trends, educators building learning curricula from video content, and researchers analyzing YouTube discourse patterns and audience engagement metrics.', '@efikuta', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/efikuta/youtube-knowledge-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/efikuta.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958282+00:00'),
  ('engineer-your-data', 'Engineer Your Data', 'Provides 17 tools for data engineering workflows including file operations, data validation and quality checks, transformations (filter, aggregate, join, pivot, clean), visualization (charts, summaries, exports), and API integration. Built on pandas, numpy, matplotlib, and scikit-learn for local data pipeline development and business intelligence tasks.', '@eghuzefa', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/eghuzefa/engineer-your-data-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eghuzefa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958320+00:00'),
  ('egnyte', 'Egnyte', 'Provides secure access to Egnyte''s enterprise content management platform. Enables file search, upload, download, and management operations within Egnyte accounts. Designed for teams requiring secure collaboration on business-critical files with enterprise-grade governance and compliance features.', '@unknown', 'search', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.egnyte.com', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958355+00:00'),
  ('claude-code', 'Claude Code', 'Wraps Anthropic''s Claude Code agent SDK to enable task delegation from MCP clients to Claude Code sessions. Built by egoist using TypeScript and the Claude Agent SDK, it exposes a single task tool that accepts natural language descriptions of coding work, working directory paths, and optional session IDs for continuity. The implementation streams Claude Code execution with automatic edit permissions, restricts tool access to a curated set (WebSearch, WebFetch, Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite, Write), and returns structured results with session tracking and cost metrics.', '@egoist', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/egoist/claude-code-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/egoist.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958381+00:00'),
  ('fetch-web-content-youtube-transcripts', 'Fetch (Web Content & YouTube Transcripts)', 'Fetch-MCP provides a server for retrieving web content and YouTube video transcripts through two specialized tools. The implementation fetches URLs and converts HTML to Markdown by default, with options to return raw HTML or limit content length. It also extracts YouTube video transcripts with timestamps, making it useful for AI assistants that need to reference web content or video information. Built with TypeScript using the Model Context Protocol SDK, it supports both stdio and SSE server modes for flexible integration options.', '@egoist', 'development', 'Unknown', 157, 'https://github.com/egoist/fetch-mcp', 'fetch-mcp', 47289, 'https://github.com/egoist.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958439+00:00'),
  ('shell-command', 'Shell Command', 'A shell command execution server for the MCP that allows AI assistants to run system commands in a controlled environment. Developed by egoist, this implementation provides a single tool for executing shell commands with built-in security features through an allowlist system. The server uses the ALLOWED_COMMANDS environment variable to explicitly permit specific commands, preventing unauthorized access to potentially dangerous system operations. It returns command results in YAML format with stdout, stderr, and exit code information. This implementation is particularly useful for scenarios where AI assistants need to interact with the local file system or run specific utilities while maintaining security boundaries.', '@egoist', 'development', 'Unknown', 50, 'https://github.com/egoist/shell-command-mcp', 'shell-command-mcp', 6006, 'https://github.com/egoist.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958502+00:00'),
  ('apple-calendar', 'Apple Calendar', 'Integrates with Apple Calendar on macOS using a three-layer architecture: a TypeScript layer for JSON-RPC communication, a compiled Swift CLI bridge, and Apple''s native EventKit framework. Properly expands recurring events into individual occurrences, supports calendar listing, event retrieval by date range, search by title/location/notes, event creation, and deletion. Requires macOS 13+ and Swift 5.9+.', '@egorkurito', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/egorkurito/apple-calendar-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/egorkurito.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958525+00:00'),
  ('roslyn-c-analyzer', 'Roslyn C# Analyzer', 'Roslyn MCP Server provides C# code analysis capabilities by leveraging the Microsoft Roslyn compiler platform. It enables AI assistants to validate C# files for syntax errors and semantic issues, find symbol references across projects, and run Microsoft recommended code analyzers - all within the context of a .NET project. The server integrates with MSBuild to load full project context and communicates via standard I/O, making it particularly valuable for ensuring code quality and catching potential issues before compilation when working with C# codebases.', '@egorpavlikhin', 'development', 'Unknown', 28, 'https://github.com/egorpavlikhin/roslyn-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/egorpavlikhin.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.958554+00:00');



Learn more about what it can do for you and how to set it up here: https://www.epicai.pro/your-ai-assistant-instructor-the-epicshop-mcp-server-0eazr', '@epicweb-dev', 'development', 'Unknown', 243, 'https://github.com/epicweb-dev/epicshop/tree/HEAD/packages/workshop-mcp', '@epic-web/workshop-mcp', 39805, 'https://github.com/epicweb-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.960882+00:00'),
  ('anki-flashcards', 'Anki Flashcards', 'This server provides Anki flashcard creation capabilities through the genanki Python library, enabling the generation and export of Anki deck files (.apkg). The implementation includes predefined card models for basic front/back cards and cloze deletion cards, with tools for creating individual cards, building complete decks, and exporting them as downloadable Anki packages. Built with Python 3.13+ and featuring image support through Pillow, it''s particularly useful for educational applications where users need to quickly convert study materials, vocabulary lists, or Q&A content into properly formatted Anki decks for spaced repetition learning.', '@epiphany-0312', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/epiphany-0312/genanki-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/epiphany-0312.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.960913+00:00'),
  ('turbovault-obsidian', 'TurboVault (Obsidian)', 'TurboVault is a production-grade MCP server built by Epistates that transforms Obsidian vaults into intelligent knowledge systems, featuring advanced editing capabilities with LLM-optimized SEARCH/REPLACE blocks, full-text search powered by Tantivy, link graph analysis for relationship discovery, and atomic batch operations with rollback support. The implementation supports multiple vault management, real-time file watching, export functionality for analysis results, and includes specialized tools for vault health monitoring, broken link detection, and orphan note identification. Built with a modular Rust architecture using pulldown-cmark for Obsidian Flavored Markdown parsing, it''s designed for AI-assisted knowledge work, research workflows, and automated vault maintenance tasks.', '@epistates', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 37, 'https://github.com/epistates/turbovault', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/epistates.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.960962+00:00'),
  ('open-notebook', 'Open Notebook', 'Integrates with Open Notebook, a self-hosted alternative to Google''s NotebookLM. Manage research notebooks, add documents and web content as sources, generate AI-assisted notes, and search across your knowledge base with vector and text search. Supports multiple AI models including local options via Ollama.', '@epochal-dev', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/epochal-dev/open-notebook-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/epochal-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.960996+00:00'),
  ('epsilla', 'Epsilla', 'This Epsilla MCP implementation, developed by Eric from Epsilla, integrates the pyepsilla library to provide a standardized interface for interacting with Epsilla databases. Built with Python and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for creating, deleting, and listing tables, as well as inserting, querying, and deleting data. The implementation abstracts the complexities of Epsilla''s API, enabling AI systems to easily manage and manipulate data within Epsilla databases. It is particularly useful for applications requiring programmatic database operations, facilitating use cases such as dynamic data storage, retrieval, and management in AI-driven systems that need efficient vector database capabilities.', '@epsilla-cloud', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/epsilla-cloud/mcp-epsilla', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/epsilla-cloud.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961007+00:00'),
  ('equinix', 'Equinix', 'This MCP server provides integration with the Brave Search API, enabling web search capabilities through Brave''s independent search index. Built with TypeScript and featuring proper error handling and response formatting, it offers tools for performing web searches with configurable parameters like result count, search safety levels, and result freshness filters. The implementation includes comprehensive query processing with support for various search options and structured result formatting, making it valuable for AI assistants that need access to current web information, research workflows, and applications requiring search functionality independent of Google''s search ecosystem.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.equinix.com/products/digital-infrastructure-services/equinix-fabric', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961034+00:00'),
  ('code-graph-rag', 'Code Graph RAG', 'This multi-agent LiteRAG MCP server provides advanced code graph analysis through specialized agents for parsing, indexing, querying, and semantic search across codebases. Built with TypeScript and featuring Tree-sitter parsing for multiple languages (TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, C/C++), SQLite with sqlite-vec for vector storage, and optional embedding models, it offers 13 MCP tools including semantic search, code similarity detection, clone analysis, impact assessment, and cross-language pattern matching. The implementation uses an agent-based architecture with a coordinator for task distribution, supports incremental parsing for large codebases, includes comprehensive caching and performance optimization for commodity hardware, and provides hybrid search combining structural graph traversal with semantic vector similarity, making it valuable for code review workflows, refactoring analysis, and understanding complex codebases through natural language queries.', '@er77', 'databases', 'Unknown', 92, 'https://github.com/er77/code-graph-rag-mcp', '@er77/code-graph-rag-mcp', 4641, 'https://github.com/er77.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961046+00:00'),
  ('pinescript-syntax-checker', 'PineScript Syntax Checker', 'PineScript Syntax Checker MCP server that validates TradingView PineScript code by interfacing with TradingView''s official pine-facade API. The implementation uses httpx for async HTTP requests and FastMCP for the server framework, providing a single tool that accepts PineScript source code and returns detailed syntax validation results including any compilation errors. Designed for developers working with TradingView indicators and strategies who need real-time syntax validation without manually checking code in the TradingView Pine Editor, making it valuable for automated trading script development workflows and educational tools.', '@erevus-cn', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/erevus-cn/pinescript_syntax_checker', 'pinescript-syntax-checker', 2654, 'https://github.com/erevus-cn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961073+00:00'),
  ('two-truths-and-a-twist', 'Two Truths and a Twist', 'Two Truths and a Twist is an MCP server implementation that enables AI assistants to host an interactive trivia game where players guess which of three statements is false. Developed by Ergodic Labs, this Python-based server manages game rounds, player guesses, and score tracking through a SQLite database, while providing tools for creating trivia rounds, submitting guesses, and revealing answers with explanations. The implementation is designed for Python 3.13+ and integrates with Claude Desktop through a simple configuration, making it particularly valuable for educational entertainment and showcasing how AI can create engaging, interactive content experiences.', '@ergodiclabs', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/ergodiclabs/twotruthsandatwist', 'ttaat', 4880, 'https://github.com/ergodiclabs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961085+00:00'),
  ('bigquery', 'BigQuery', 'This BigQuery MCP server, developed by Salih Ergüt, provides a secure interface for language models to interact with Google BigQuery datasets. It enables AI agents to explore schemas, run SQL queries, and analyze data within configurable limits. The server integrates seamlessly with Claude Desktop, offering a natural language interface to BigQuery''s powerful data warehousing capabilities. By focusing on read-only access and built-in safety constraints, it allows AI systems to generate insights from large datasets while maintaining data security. This implementation is particularly useful for AI assistants designed to perform ad-hoc data analysis, generate business intelligence reports, or provide data-driven recommendations using BigQuery as the backend.', '@ergut', 'databases', 'Unknown', 133, 'https://github.com/ergut/mcp-bigquery-server', '@ergut/mcp-bigquery-server', 10283, 'https://github.com/ergut.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961102+00:00'),
  ('android-mobile', 'Android Mobile', 'Android Mobile MCP bridges AI assistants with Android device automation through the uiautomator2 library, enabling comprehensive mobile app testing and interaction workflows. Built by erichung0906, it provides 9 core tools spanning UI analysis (hierarchical element extraction, screenshots), touch interactions (clicking with coordinate validation, swiping), text input, system navigation, and app management (listing and launching applications). The implementation uses XML parsing to extract focusable UI elements with calculated center coordinates, validates click targets against current UI state to prevent invalid interactions, and filters out system apps to show only user-accessible applications, making it valuable for automated mobile testing, app interaction workflows, and AI assistants that need to operate Android devices programmatically.', '@erichung9060', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/erichung9060/android-mobile-mcp', 'android-mobile-mcp', 20284, 'https://github.com/erichung9060.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961175+00:00'),
  ('erick-wendel-contributions', 'Erick Wendel Contributions', 'The erickwendel-contributions-mcp server provides AI assistants with access to Erick Wendel''s content contributions across different platforms through a set of specialized tools. Built with Node.js and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it enables querying talks, posts, and videos with filtering options by language, title, country, and other parameters. The implementation includes Docker containerization for easy deployment and is configured through Smithery.ai for seamless integration with AI assistants. This server is particularly valuable for users wanting to discover and reference Erick Wendel''s technical content within AI assistant conversations without needing to search across multiple platforms manually.', '@erickwendel', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 122, 'https://github.com/erickwendel/erickwendel-contributions-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/erickwendel.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961199+00:00'),
  ('download-tools-comfyui', 'Download Tools (ComfyUI)', 'Integrates gallery-dl, yt-dlp, and custom web scraping into ComfyUI workflows for downloading media from 1000+ platforms with browser authentication, quality presets, and JavaScript-heavy site support including Instagram, Bluesky, and ArtStation.', '@ericrollei', 'search', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/ericrollei/download_tools', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ericrollei.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961260+00:00'),
  ('uber-eats', 'Uber Eats', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Uber Eats, enabling AI assistants to search for restaurants, find menu options, and place food orders. Built using Python and the FastMCP framework, it leverages browser automation to interact with the Uber Eats website. The server offers asynchronous operations for searching and ordering, making it suitable for use cases requiring food delivery integration within AI-assisted applications.', '@ericzakariasson', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 217, 'https://github.com/ericzakariasson/uber-eats-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ericzakariasson.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961327+00:00'),
  ('sql-server-performance-monitor', 'SQL Server Performance Monitor', 'A free, open-source SQL Server performance monitoring tool (Lite edition) that remotely queries DMVs without installing anything on the target server. Stores collected metrics locally in DuckDB with automatic Parquet archival. Includes an embedded MCP server exposing tools for diagnosing CPU issues, wait statistics, blocking chains, query performance, memory pressure, I/O bottlenecks, TempDB contention, SQL Agent job health, and alerting. Supports SQL Server 2016-2025, Azure SQL MI, AWS RDS, and Azure SQL Database.', '@erikdarlingdata', 'databases', 'Unknown', 231, 'https://github.com/erikdarlingdata/performancemonitor/tree/HEAD/Lite', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/erikdarlingdata.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961341+00:00'),
  ('azure-fhir', 'Azure FHIR', 'Azure FHIR MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and Azure Health Data Services FHIR servers, enabling secure access to healthcare data through the Model Context Protocol. Developed by Erik Howard, it implements OAuth2 authentication with Azure Active Directory and offers comprehensive tools for searching and retrieving FHIR resources across 70+ resource types. The server dynamically generates resource functions for all FHIR resources, handles error reporting through the MCP context system, and maintains detailed logging—making it particularly valuable for healthcare applications requiring secure, standards-compliant access to patient records, clinical observations, and medical documentation.', '@erikhoward', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 18, 'https://github.com/erikhoward/azure-fhir-mcp-server', 'azure-fhir-mcp-server', 8141, 'https://github.com/erikhoward.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961370+00:00'),
  ('grep', 'Grep', 'MCP-Grep provides a server implementation that exposes the system grep binary''s functionality through the Model Context Protocol, allowing AI assistants to search for patterns in files using regular expressions. Developed by Ernie Brodeur, it offers both a resource endpoint for retrieving grep binary information and a tool for performing searches with support for common grep options like case-insensitive matching, context lines, recursive directory searching, and fixed string matching. The implementation uses Python''s subprocess module to execute grep commands on the host system, making it particularly valuable for AI assistants that need to analyze text files or codebases without leaving their conversation interface.', '@erniebrodeur', 'development', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/erniebrodeur/mcp-grep', 'mcp-grep', 3923, 'https://github.com/erniebrodeur.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961408+00:00'),
  ('twilio-manager', 'Twilio Manager', 'Twilio Manager MCP provides a robust interface for managing Twilio resources through asynchronous API interactions. The implementation offers tools for handling subaccounts, phone numbers, addresses, and regulatory bundles with features like transferring phone numbers between accounts and duplicating regulatory bundles. Built with an async-first approach using aiohttp, it enables efficient concurrent operations against the Twilio API while handling authentication, session management, and error recovery. This server is particularly valuable for organizations that need to programmatically manage multiple Twilio accounts and resources without leaving their AI assistant conversation.', '@errajibadr', 'communication', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/errajibadr/twilio_manager_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/errajibadr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961445+00:00'),
  ('linkedin-ligo', 'LinkedIn + LiGo', 'LinkedIn MCP Runner is a server implementation that enables Claude AI to interact with LinkedIn, allowing users to publish posts, schedule content, analyze chats, and retrieve profile information through a set of specialized tools. Developed by Ertiqah, LLC, this Node.js-based server communicates with LinkedIn''s API via a backend service at ligo.ertiqah.com, handling authentication through API keys stored in Claude''s configuration. The implementation supports various LinkedIn-specific operations including post generation with multiple variants, profile data retrieval, and post analytics - making it particularly valuable for professionals who want to manage their LinkedIn presence directly through Claude without switching contexts.', '@ertiqah', 'communication', 'Unknown', 27, 'https://github.com/ertiqah/linkedin-mcp-runner', 'linkedin-mcp-runner', 6329, 'https://github.com/ertiqah.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961483+00:00'),
  ('tradingview-chart', 'TradingView Chart', 'The TradingView Chart MCP server enables AI assistants to capture and share TradingView chart images directly through a Selenium-based scraper. Developed by ertugrul59, this implementation authenticates with TradingView using session cookies, navigates to specific chart layouts with customizable tickers and timeframes, and captures screenshot links that are converted to direct image URLs. The server exposes both a primary tool for fetching chart images and several prompt templates for natural language interaction, making it valuable for traders, analysts, and financial advisors who need to quickly reference and share market charts without leaving their conversation context.', '@ertugrul59', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 70, 'https://github.com/ertugrul59/tradingview-chart-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ertugrul59.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961534+00:00'),
  ('esagu', 'eSagu', 'Provides centralized access to eSagu''s marketplace management tools. Control dynamic repricing strategies for Amazon, eBay, and Kaufland listings. Handle Amazon FBA Lost & Found case submissions and tracking. Manage customer support tickets through the integrated HelpDesk with email communication and status updates.', '@unknown', 'communication', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.esagu.de/en/resources/knowledge-base/tutorials/mcp-ki-steuert-repricing-and-support-direkt-per-chat', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961556+00:00'),
  ('nexus-data-processor', 'Nexus Data Processor', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to various data processing and API services. It integrates with libraries like Effect, Zod, and CSV for data handling, as well as external services such as YAML parsing and date manipulation. The server is designed to facilitate complex data operations and API interactions, making it suitable for tasks involving data transformation, validation, and integration with multiple data sources and formats.', '@esh2n', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/esh2n/mcp-servers', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/esh2n.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961592+00:00'),
  ('esignatures', 'eSignatures', 'This MCP server for eSignatures, developed by eSignatures, provides integration with the eSignatures.com API for contract and document management. Built with Python, it offers tools for creating, querying, and managing contracts and templates. The implementation focuses on simplifying access to eSignatures functionality through a standardized MCP interface, with features like draft creation, contract withdrawal, and template management. It''s particularly useful for AI assistants and applications needing to handle digital contracts and signatures, enabling use cases such as automated contract generation, document workflow management, and legal compliance tracking without directly dealing with the complexities of the eSignatures.com API.', '@esignaturescom', 'development', 'Unknown', 35, 'https://github.com/esignaturescom/mcp-server-esignatures', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/esignaturescom.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961618+00:00'),
  ('ree-spain-electricity', 'REE (Spain Electricity)', 'Provides access to Spain''s electricity system data through REE (Red Eléctrica de España) API, enabling retrieval of real-time and historical electricity indicators including demand, generation by source, prices, and emissions data. Built with clean architecture principles using domain-driven design, the server offers tools for querying over 1,900+ available indicators with flexible time granularities and geographic scopes, plus convenience functions for common use cases like demand summaries and generation mix analysis. Useful for energy analysts, researchers, and developers building applications that need Spanish electricity market data for forecasting, monitoring, or analysis purposes.', '@esjavadex', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/esjavadex/ree-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/esjavadex.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961655+00:00'),
  ('blowback-frontend-development', 'Blowback (Frontend Development)', 'Blowback is an MCP server that integrates with frontend development environments to provide real-time feedback and debugging capabilities. It uses Puppeteer to launch a browser instance that connects to development servers (like Vite), monitors Hot Module Replacement (HMR) events, captures console logs, and provides tools for interacting with the DOM. The server includes features for taking screenshots, monitoring network requests, retrieving element properties, and executing browser commands - making it particularly valuable for AI assistants that need to understand and debug frontend applications during development without leaving the conversation interface.', '@esnark', 'development', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/esnark/blowback', 'blowback-context', 4944, 'https://github.com/esnark.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961688+00:00'),
  ('esp32-cyd', 'ESP32 CYD', 'A comprehensive MCP server implementation for the ESP32 CYD (Cheap Yellow Display) board that transforms the ESP32-2432S028R into a remotely controllable IoT device through WebSocket-based communication. The server exposes over 100 tools across eight categories including display control (drawing text, shapes, progress bars), touch input handling with gesture detection, GPIO manipulation, sensor readings (temperature, light, hall sensor), network operations, system monitoring, file management for SPIFFS and SD card storage, and audio playback with predefined melodies. Built using PlatformIO with the Arduino framework, it leverages the board''s 2.8" ILI9341 TFT display and XPT2046 touch controller to create a versatile hardware interface that can be controlled programmatically by AI assistants, making it valuable for IoT prototyping, remote monitoring, educational projects, and hardware automation tasks where visual feedback and touch interaction are needed.', '@ofryl', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/ofryl/esp-cyd-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ofryl.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961740+00:00'),
  ('okx-cryptocurrency', 'OKX Cryptocurrency', 'The OKX MCP server provides real-time cryptocurrency price data from the OKX exchange through two main tools: get_candlesticks for historical OHLCV data and get_price for current market information. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it connects directly to OKX''s API to deliver structured cryptocurrency data with comprehensive error handling and rate limiting. This implementation is ideal for AI assistants that need to analyze crypto market trends, monitor specific instruments, or incorporate live financial data into their responses.', '@esshka', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/esshka/okx-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/esshka.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961767+00:00'),
  ('e-stat-japan', 'e-Stat Japan', 'eStatMCP is a Kotlin-based MCP server that provides AI assistants with access to Japan''s official statistics portal (e-Stat). Developed by Ichiro Murata, it offers four main tools: searching statistical tables, finding surveys, retrieving metadata, and fetching actual statistical data with filtering capabilities. The implementation uses Ktor for HTTP requests and XML parsing, presenting results in a structured JSON format that makes complex government statistical data accessible for analysis. Particularly useful for researchers, economists, and analysts who need programmatic access to Japanese official statistics through conversational AI interfaces.', '@ichiromurata', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/ichiromurata/estatmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ichiromurata.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961814+00:00'),
  ('knowledge-graph-memory', 'Knowledge Graph Memory', 'This Memory MCP Server, developed by estav, provides a knowledge graph management system for AI assistants using the Model Context Protocol. It offers tools for storing, retrieving, and querying information in a graph structure, enabling assistants to build and maintain long-term memory. The server uses SQLite for persistent storage and implements optimized batch operations for efficiency. By connecting AI capabilities with structured knowledge representation, this implementation allows assistants to accumulate and reason over information across conversations. It is particularly useful for applications requiring context retention, relationship modeling between concepts, or any scenario where an AI system needs to build and leverage a persistent knowledge base.', '@evangstav', 'databases', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/evangstav/python-memory-mcp-server', 'memory-mcp-server', 83559, 'https://github.com/evangstav.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961826+00:00'),
  ('journal-rag', 'Journal RAG', 'The Journal RAG MCP server enables AI assistants to search through personal markdown journal entries using semantic similarity. It implements a vector database approach with ChromaDB and sentence-transformers to index journal content, supporting both full and incremental indexing of entries. The server exposes two main tools: one for querying journal entries based on semantic relevance, and another for updating the index when new entries are added. Built with GPU acceleration support for faster embedding generation on NVIDIA hardware, this implementation is particularly useful for users who maintain personal journals in markdown format and want to reference past experiences, thoughts, and activities during conversations with AI assistants without manually searching through entries.', '@estevaom', 'databases', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/estevaom/markdown-journal-rust', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/estevaom.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961839+00:00'),
  ('demo-time', 'Demo Time', 'Enables searching through Demo Time documentation using natural language queries and automating Demo Time actions like opening files and running demo steps. Demo Time is a VS Code extension for scripting live coding presentations to eliminate typos and ensure flawless demos.', '@estruyf', 'development', 'Unknown', 238, 'https://github.com/estruyf/vscode-demo-time', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/estruyf.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961871+00:00'),
  ('security-audit', 'Security Audit', 'This MCP server implementation provides a security audit tool for package.json dependencies. Developed by esx, it leverages npm-audit-report and npm-registry-fetch to analyze and report potential vulnerabilities in Node.js projects. The server is built using TypeScript and integrates with the Model Context Protocol SDK. It offers a command-line interface for easy integration into development workflows and CI/CD pipelines. The implementation focuses on providing clear, actionable security insights, making it particularly useful for development teams prioritizing code safety and compliance. It supports various output formats and can be easily incorporated into existing project management tools and security protocols.', '@qianniuspace', 'development', 'Unknown', 51, 'https://github.com/qianniuspace/mcp-security-audit', 'mcp-security-audit', 5315, 'https://github.com/qianniuspace.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961902+00:00'),
  ('api-client', 'API Client', 'A specialized server designed for REST API testing and exploration, functioning as a "Postman for LLMs." Built with FastMCP and httpx, it provides two core tools: single HTTP requests and efficient batch requests that minimize token usage by returning only status codes and response bodies by default. Optimized for local development workflows, allowing direct testing of localhost endpoints during development, API change validation, and HTTP debugging through natural language interactions.', '@etaaa', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/etaaa/mcp-api-client', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/etaaa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961926+00:00'),
  ('google-ai-studio', 'Google AI Studio', 'This MCP server provides Google AI Studio/Gemini API integration with comprehensive file processing capabilities, supporting images, videos, audio, PDFs, and text files for content generation and analysis. Built by eternnoir using TypeScript with the Google GenAI SDK, it offers a single generate_content tool that handles multimodal inputs with configurable parameters for model selection, system prompts, and file limits (up to 10 files per request, 50MB total). The implementation features automatic MIME type detection, base64 file encoding, robust error handling with individual file failure reporting, and support for common use cases like PDF-to-Markdown conversion, image analysis, and audio transcription, making it valuable for document processing workflows, multimodal content analysis, and building AI assistants that need to work with diverse file types through Gemini''s advanced capabilities.', '@eternnoir', 'development', 'Unknown', 26, 'https://github.com/eternnoir/aistudio-mcp-server', 'aistudio-mcp-server', 5462, 'https://github.com/eternnoir.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961958+00:00'),
  ('bybit', 'Bybit', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with access to Bybit cryptocurrency exchange APIs for trading and market data analysis, built using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK and bybit-api library. The implementation offers 11 tools across three categories: market data tools for price feeds, order books, klines, and 24hr tickers (public access), account management tools for balance and order information (requires API credentials), and trading operations for placing/canceling orders (testnet-only for safety). Built with comprehensive input validation via Zod schemas, API credential sanitization in error messages, and safety restrictions that limit trading to testnet environments, it serves cryptocurrency traders needing programmatic access to Bybit''s trading infrastructure, developers building crypto trading bots or portfolio management tools, and AI assistants requiring real-time market data and order management capabilities with built-in safety guardrails.', '@ethancod1ng', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/ethancod1ng/bybit-mcp-server', 'bybit-mcp-server', 439, 'https://github.com/ethancod1ng.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.961992+00:00'),
  ('math', 'Math', 'This MCP server provides basic mathematical and statistical functions to Large Language Models (LLMs). Developed by EthanHenrickson, it offers capabilities such as arithmetic operations, statistical calculations, and rounding functions. The server is designed for use cases requiring accurate numerical computations within AI-assisted applications, enabling LLMs to perform precise calculations through a simple API.', '@ethanhenrickson', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 91, 'https://github.com/ethanhenrickson/math-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ethanhenrickson.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.962055+00:00'),
  ('fedramp-docs', 'FedRAMP Docs', 'Built by Ethan Troy, this server automatically clones and indexes the official FedRAMP docs repository, offering tools to query Key Security Indicators (KSI), Methods and Assessment Standards (MAS), and other FRMR documents. It provides full-text search across markdown documentation and specialized functions for tracking significant changes and NIST control references. The implementation is particularly valuable for compliance professionals, security engineers, and auditors working with federal cloud security requirements who need quick access to authoritative FedRAMP guidance and the ability to cross-reference controls across different document types.', '@ethanolivertroy', 'search', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/ethanolivertroy/fedramp-docs-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ethanolivertroy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.962111+00:00'),
  ('ethereal-rust', 'Ethereal Rust', 'This Rust implementation of the MCP server provides a robust foundation for building AI-powered applications. It offers core functionalities like tool management, authentication handling, and custom middleware support. The server is designed with flexibility in mind, supporting both stdio and SSE transports. It''s particularly well-suited for developers looking to integrate AI capabilities into Rust-based projects or those seeking a performant, type-safe MCP server implementation.', '@ethereumdegen', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/ethereumdegen/mcp-rs', 'mcp-rs', 0, 'https://github.com/ethereumdegen.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.962136+00:00');


Features
Simple - Merge any number of files with a single command
Fast - Efficiently combines files of any size
Secure - Only accesses directories you allow
Detailed - Reports file sizes and merge summary', '@exoticknight', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/exoticknight/mcp-file-merger', '@exoticknight/mcp-file-merger', 4117, 'https://github.com/exoticknight.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963528+00:00'),
  ('expenselm', 'ExpenseLM', 'Integrates with ExpenseLM, an AI-powered expense management platform that uses multimodal LLMs to extract structured data from receipt and invoice images. Supports semantic search across expenses, multi-currency tracking, and conversational expense queries through an AI agent. Provides item-level expense details with automatic categorization.', '@expenselm', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/expenselm/expenselm-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/expenselm.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963558+00:00'),
  ('stacks-clarity', 'Stacks Clarity', 'Stacks Clarity MCP Server provides comprehensive tooling for Stacks blockchain development, offering 32+ specialized tools covering SIP standards access, token development (SIP-009 NFTs and SIP-010 fungible tokens), security analysis with mandatory post-conditions, SIP-012 performance optimization, account management, and Clarinet project generation. Built by Exponent Labs with TypeScript and integrated with Hiro APIs, it enforces security best practices by requiring post-conditions for all token transfers, provides real-time blockchain data access, and generates production-ready Clarity contracts with test suites, making it valuable for developers building DeFi protocols, NFT marketplaces, DAOs, and other Stacks applications while ensuring SIP compliance and optimal performance.', '@exponentlabshq', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/exponentlabshq/stacks-clarity-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/exponentlabshq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963590+00:00'),
  ('text-to-speech-windows', 'Text To Speech (Windows)', 'This Windows Speech MCP server, developed by ExpressionsBot, provides text-to-speech and speech-to-text capabilities using native Windows speech services. Built with Node.js and leveraging PowerShell commands, it offers tools for converting text to speech, recording audio, and transcribing speech without external API dependencies. The implementation focuses on utilizing built-in Windows features, making it accessible for AI models to interact with speech functionalities on Windows systems. It''s particularly useful for voice-enabled applications, accessibility tools, or integrating speech capabilities into AI assistants on Windows platforms, allowing natural language interactions without requiring additional speech services or APIs.', '@danielgillespie278', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/danielgillespie278/ms-lucidia-voice-gateway-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/danielgillespie278.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963640+00:00'),
  ('cv-resume-builder', 'CV Resume Builder', 'Generates and updates professional CVs by automatically aggregating data from multiple sources including git commits, Jira tickets, Credly badges, and LinkedIn profiles. Analyzes code contributions and work achievements to extract quantifiable metrics and impact statements, then formats them into LaTeX-compatible documents with configurable bullet point limits and ATS-friendly formatting. Supports multi-repository configurations for freelancers and consultants, includes PDF parsing capabilities for enhancing existing CVs, and provides comprehensive tooling for career documentation automation.', '@eyaab', 'development', 'Unknown', 12, 'https://github.com/eyaab/cv-resume-builder-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eyaab.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963665+00:00'),
  ('task-master', 'Task Master', 'This MCP server provides AI-driven task management capabilities for development workflows, built using Node.js with FastMCP and integrating multiple AI providers including Anthropic, OpenAI, Perplexity, and Google. It offers comprehensive project management tools including PRD parsing to generate initial tasks, task CRUD operations with dependency management, AI-powered task expansion into subtasks, complexity analysis, and tagged task contexts for organizing work across different project phases. The implementation uses a modular architecture with direct function wrappers, session-based environment variable handling, and context management for efficient AI operations, plus includes both CLI and MCP interfaces for flexible integration into development environments where teams need structured, AI-assisted project planning and task breakdown.', '@eyaltoledano', 'development', 'Unknown', 25820, 'https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master', 'task-master-ai', 1561311, 'https://github.com/eyaltoledano.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963695+00:00'),
  ('browser-control', 'Browser Control', 'Browser Control MCP is a server paired with a Firefox extension that enables AI assistants to control the user''s browser. Developed by eyalzh, it provides tools for tab management, history searching, webpage content extraction, and text highlighting. The implementation uses WebSocket communication between a Node.js server and browser extension, with a shared secret for secure messaging. It''s particularly useful for scenarios requiring browser automation, research assistance, and content analysis, allowing AI assistants to open tabs, read webpage content, search browser history, and manipulate the browser environment based on user requests.', '@eyalzh', 'communication', 'Unknown', 250, 'https://github.com/eyalzh/browser-control-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eyalzh.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963737+00:00'),
  ('kanban', 'Kanban', 'MCP Kanban provides a task management system for complex multi-session workflows with AI agents, structured as kanban boards with columns and tasks. Built by eyalzh, it features column capacity limits, an embedded SQLite database, and a web UI for monitoring workflow progress. The server includes tools for creating boards, adding tasks, moving them between columns, and retrieving board information, along with predefined prompts for starting and resuming projects. It''s particularly valuable for directing AI agents to document their work in a structured format across planning and execution sessions, maintaining state between interactions.', '@eyalzh', 'databases', 'Unknown', 34, 'https://github.com/eyalzh/kanban-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eyalzh.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963748+00:00'),
  ('eyevinn-open-source-cloud', 'Eyevinn Open Source Cloud', 'This MCP server, developed by EyevinnOSC, enables AI assistants to interact with the Eyevinn Open Source Cloud API for creating and managing cloud infrastructure components. It provides tools for setting up databases, storage buckets, and VOD pipelines through a standardized interface. The implementation stands out by leveraging open source technologies to offer vendor-independent cloud services, where creators share in the platform''s revenue. By connecting AI capabilities with scalable cloud infrastructure, this server empowers AI systems to dynamically provision and manage resources for data storage, content delivery, and media processing. It is particularly useful for applications requiring flexible cloud deployments, media workflows, or any scenario where an AI assistant needs to orchestrate cloud services while avoiding vendor lock-in.', '@eyevinnosc', 'databases', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/eyevinnosc/mcp-server', '@osaas/mcp-server', 10315, 'https://github.com/eyevinnosc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963762+00:00'),
  ('mcp-gateway', 'MCP Gateway', 'MCP Gateway aggregates multiple MCP servers into a single unified endpoint, allowing clients to search, discover, and invoke tools across all connected servers through a centralized interface. Built with TypeScript and Bun, it supports both local command-based servers and remote HTTP/WebSocket servers, providing intelligent tool search with BM25 scoring and fuzzy matching, asynchronous job execution with priority queuing, and hot-reloading configuration management. Useful for consolidating disparate MCP services into a single access point, enabling cross-server tool discovery, and managing complex multi-server workflows through a simplified gateway architecture.', '@eznix86', 'development', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/eznix86/mcp-gateway', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/eznix86.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963791+00:00'),
  ('io-github-drivenrajat-f1', 'io.github.drivenrajat/f1', 'Access Formula 1 race data, telemetry, lap times, standings, and analytics powered by FastF1', '@drivenrajat', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/drivenrajat/f1', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/drivenrajat.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963873+00:00'),
  ('figma-to-code', 'Figma to Code', 'F2C-MCP is a server implementation that bridges Figma design files to code generation through the Model Context Protocol. Built with TypeScript, it provides tools for parsing Figma URLs, handling authentication via API tokens, and managing output rules for generated code. The server implements JSON-RPC communication for error handling and notifications, making it valuable for designers and developers who need to convert Figma designs directly into HTML, CSS, and other assets with customizable output paths, naming conventions, and file organization.', '@f2c-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 366, 'https://github.com/f2c-ai/f2c-mcp', '@f2c/mcp', 15774, 'https://github.com/f2c-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963898+00:00'),
  ('io-github-robinmordasiewicz-f5xc-terraform-mcp', 'io.github.robinmordasiewicz/f5xc-terraform-mcp', 'F5 Distributed Cloud Terraform provider docs, 270+ OpenAPI specs, and subscription info for AI.', '@robinmordasiewicz', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/robinmordasiewicz/terraform-provider-f5xc', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/robinmordasiewicz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963939+00:00'),
  ('intercom', 'Intercom', 'This MCP server, developed by Fabian, provides seamless access to Intercom conversations and chats for AI-assisted analysis. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers a robust interface for querying Intercom data with flexible filtering options. The implementation supports searching conversations by date range, customer ID, and conversation state, providing rich conversation details including contact information and statistics. It''s particularly useful for customer support teams, data analysts, and developers looking to incorporate on-demand access to Intercom data into their AI workflows, enabling dynamic analysis of customer interactions and support trends.', '@fabian1710', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/fabian1710/mcp-intercom', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/fabian1710.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.963968+00:00'),
  ('threedee-meshy', 'Threedee (Meshy)', 'ThreeDee-MCP is a server implementation that enables AI assistants to generate 3D models from text descriptions or images through the Meshy API. Built with Python and FastMCP, it provides tools for creating 3D previews, refining models with PBR textures, converting images to 3D objects, and managing tasks with detailed status tracking. The implementation includes a JavaScript backend using Bun and Anthropic''s Claude for natural language processing, making it particularly valuable for users who want to create 3D assets through conversational interfaces without specialized modeling skills. Developed as a hackathon project for Paris AI Tinkerers, it demonstrates practical integration of generative AI with 3D content creation workflows.', '@fabianh001', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/fabianh001/threedee-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/fabianh001.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.964016+00:00');







With our MCP server, you can create and update projects through conversational language, get explanations about your database schema and API, generate code that correctly interfaces with your backend, make schema changes through natural language, and manage your cloud databases. This integration works through your IDE''s chat interface, with the MCP server providing context about your database configuration.', '@unknown', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.gibsonai.com/#mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975108+00:00'),
  ('gif-creator', 'GIF Creator', 'This MCP server converts video files to high-quality GIF animations using FFmpeg with optimized palette generation and Lanczos scaling. Built by Anand Tyagi with fluent-ffmpeg and automatic FFmpeg installation, it offers customizable output settings including FPS (1-30), dimensions with aspect ratio preservation, and precise time-based extraction of video segments. The implementation includes a 120-second timeout for processing, progress monitoring, and saves GIFs in the same directory as source videos, making it valuable for creating animated previews, social media content, or documentation assets from video files.', '@ananddtyagi', 'file-systems', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/ananddtyagi/gif-creator-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ananddtyagi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975164+00:00'),
  ('gigapipe', 'Gigapipe', 'This MCP server provides unified access to Gigapipe''s observability platform, enabling AI assistants to query Prometheus metrics with PromQL, search Loki logs with LogQL, and retrieve Tempo traces by ID through a single interface. Built in Go using the mcp-go library, it connects to Gigapipe instances via HTTP/HTTPS with optional basic authentication, offering tools for metric queries with time ranges and step intervals, log searches with configurable limits, trace retrieval in JSON format, and label/tag discovery across all three data sources. The implementation includes cross-platform binary releases for Linux, macOS, and Windows, making it valuable for DevOps teams monitoring distributed systems, SRE workflows requiring correlation between metrics, logs, and traces, and automated troubleshooting scenarios that need to query multiple observability data types through a unified API.', '@gigapipehq', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/gigapipehq/gigapipe-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gigapipehq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975220+00:00'),
  ('gigapi', 'GigAPI', 'This MCP server provides seamless integration with GigAPI Timeseries Lake, enabling AI assistants to execute SQL queries, manage databases and tables, and write time-series data using InfluxDB Line Protocol. Built by the GigAPI team with Python and leveraging GigAPI''s HTTP API with NDJSON response format, it offers tools for database operations including health checks, schema inspection, and data ingestion. The implementation supports both local development and production deployments with authentication, SSL configuration, and connection to public demo instances, making it particularly useful for AI assistants working with time-series analytics, IoT data processing, and real-time monitoring applications.', '@gigapi', 'databases', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/gigapi/gigapi-mcp', 'mcp-gigapi', 1992, 'https://github.com/gigapi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975231+00:00');


Available Tools
getStockQuote: Get the current quote for an Indian stock.
getHistoricalData: Get historical data for an Indian stock with custom intervals and periods.', '@giptilabs', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/giptilabs/mcp-stock-analysis', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/giptilabs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975479+00:00'),
  ('aws-cognito', 'AWS Cognito', 'AWS Cognito MCP Server provides authentication and user management capabilities for AI assistants by connecting to AWS Cognito. Developed by gitCarrot, this TypeScript implementation exposes a comprehensive set of user authentication flows including sign-up, sign-in, password management, account verification, and multi-factor authentication. The server uses the amazon-cognito-identity-js library to interact with AWS Cognito User Pools, handling token management and user sessions securely. Particularly valuable for applications requiring robust identity management without building custom authentication systems, it enables AI assistants to manage user accounts through natural language interactions.', '@gitcarrot', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/gitcarrot/mcp-server-aws-cognito', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gitcarrot.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975497+00:00'),
  ('git-commit-aider', 'Git Commit Aider', 'Git Commit Aider MCP Server provides a TypeScript implementation that enables AI assistants to make Git commits on behalf of users, automatically appending ''(aider)'' to the committer''s name for tracking AI contributions in codebases. Built by Johnson Liang, this server exposes a single tool for committing staged changes with a specified message, retrieving committer information from environment variables or git config. The implementation integrates with the Model Context Protocol SDK and uses execa for executing git commands, making it valuable for developers who want to track AI-assisted code changes and analyze AI contribution statistics through tools like ''aider --stats''.', '@mrorz', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/mrorz/mcp-git-commit-aider', 'mcp-git-commit-aider', 4554, 'https://github.com/mrorz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975524+00:00'),
  ('qiita', 'Qiita', 'Integrates with Qiita''s API to enable article publishing workflows for Japan''s premier technical blogging platform. Provides minimalist, focused implementation for creating and publishing technical content through Qiita''s official v2 API. Designed for AI-assisted authoring workflows targeting Japanese developer audiences.', '@github30', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/github30/qiita-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/github30.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975613+00:00'),
  ('zenn', 'Zenn', 'Integrates with Zenn.dev''s API to automate publishing workflows from GitHub to the Zenn platform. Enables content creators to publish technical articles to Zenn using GitHub Actions, with support for token-based authentication and automated deployment pipelines. Zenn is a Japanese information-sharing platform for engineers and technical writers.', '@github30', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/github30/zenn-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/github30.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975630+00:00'),
  ('github-actions', 'GitHub Actions', 'GitHub Actions MCP Server enables AI assistants to manage and operate GitHub Actions workflows through a comprehensive set of tools. It provides capabilities for listing, viewing, triggering, canceling, and rerunning workflows, along with detailed information about workflow runs and their jobs. The implementation features robust error handling, type validation with Zod schemas, and security-focused design including timeout handling, rate limiting, and strict URL validation. Particularly valuable for developers who need to monitor CI/CD pipelines, troubleshoot failed workflows, or trigger automated processes without leaving their conversation interface.', '@ko1ynnky', 'development', 'Unknown', 40, 'https://github.com/ko1ynnky/github-actions-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ko1ynnky.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975680+00:00'),
  ('github-gists', 'GitHub Gists', 'Gists MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and GitHub Gists, enabling creation, retrieval, updating, listing, and deletion of code snippets through a standardized interface. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it authenticates with GitHub via personal access tokens and exposes five tools that map directly to GitHub''s Gists API operations. This implementation is particularly valuable for developers who want to manage code snippets, share examples, or store programming notes directly through conversational AI without switching contexts.', '@bmorphism', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/bmorphism/gists-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/bmorphism.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975724+00:00'),
  ('io-github-nirholas-github-to-mcp', 'io.github.nirholas/github-to-mcp', 'Convert any GitHub repo to MCP server - automatic tool generation API wrap', '@nirholas', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/nirholas/github-to-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/nirholas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975739+00:00'),
  ('github-url-converter', 'GitHub URL Converter', 'GitHub URL MCP server that provides AI assistants with tools for converting and validating GitHub URLs between different formats. Built by kongyo2 using TypeScript and the fastmcp framework, the implementation handles transformations between standard GitHub repository URLs, raw file URLs, and other GitHub URL variants, with validation to ensure URLs are properly formatted and accessible. The server uses Zod for input validation and includes comprehensive testing with Vitest, serving developers who need programmatic GitHub URL manipulation for documentation generation, file processing workflows, or integration tasks that require consistent URL formatting across different GitHub URL types.', '@kongyo2', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/kongyo2/github-url-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kongyo2.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975764+00:00'),
  ('gitkraken', 'GitKraken', 'Command-line tool for managing Git repositories with a bundled MCP server that wraps git, GitHub, and Jira operations. Provides AI assistants with secure access to Git context, branches, commits, pull requests, and issues across multiple hosting providers. Includes AI-powered commit message generation, automated PR creation, and unified authentication system.', '@gitkraken', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 371, 'https://github.com/gitkraken/gk-cli', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gitkraken.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975782+00:00'),
  ('gitlab-code-review', 'GitLab Code Review', 'The GitLab MCP for Code Review server enables AI assistants like Claude to interact directly with GitLab''s merge requests through the GitLab API. Built on FastMCP and adapted from a Gerrit code review implementation, this Python-based server provides tools for analyzing merge requests, viewing file diffs, comparing versions, managing reviews, and retrieving project information. It handles authentication via GitLab personal access tokens and includes robust error handling for API requests. The implementation is particularly valuable for developers seeking AI assistance with code reviews without leaving their workflow, allowing assistants to fetch complete merge request details, add comments, approve changes, and analyze code differences across branches or commits.', '@mehmetakinn', 'development', 'Unknown', 42, 'https://github.com/mehmetakinn/gitlab-mcp-code-review', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mehmetakinn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975829+00:00'),
  ('dub-co', 'Dub.co', 'Dub.co MCP server provides a streamlined interface for creating, updating, and deleting short links through the Dub.co URL shortening service. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it enables AI assistants to programmatically manage links by exposing tools for link creation with custom domains, updating existing links, and deleting links. The implementation focuses on simplifying URL management with robust error handling and automatic domain selection.', '@gitmaxd', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/gitmaxd/dubco-mcp-server-npm', 'dubco-mcp-server', 5093, 'https://github.com/gitmaxd.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975869+00:00'),
  ('ntfy-push-notifications', 'Ntfy Push Notifications', 'ntfy-me-mcp is a Node.js server that enables AI assistants to send push notifications through the ntfy service. It provides a simple tool called ''ntfy_me'' that accepts task titles, summaries, and optional parameters like priority levels and tags, then delivers these notifications to configured ntfy topics. The implementation supports both public and protected topics with authentication, making it useful for alerting users about completed tasks, errors, or status updates from AI-driven workflows.', '@gitmotion', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 54, 'https://github.com/gitmotion/ntfy-me-mcp', 'ntfy-me-mcp', 7907, 'https://github.com/gitmotion.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975938+00:00'),
  ('git-repository-browser', 'Git Repository Browser', 'Git Commands MCP provides a Node.js implementation of a Git repository browser that enables AI assistants to interact with Git repositories through a set of specialized tools. Built by Sreeram Balamurugan, it offers capabilities for cloning repositories, exploring directory structures, reading file contents, comparing branches, analyzing commit history, and searching code patterns. The server uses the simple-git library to execute Git operations and returns structured JSON responses, making it particularly valuable for developers who need to analyze repositories, track changes, or extract code snippets without leaving their conversation interface.', '@bsreeram08', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/bsreeram08/git-commands-mcp', 'git-commands-mcp', 4088, 'https://github.com/bsreeram08.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975968+00:00'),
  ('gitscrum', 'GitScrum', 'Provides operational access to GitScrum workspaces, enabling management of tasks, sprints, time tracking, discussions, proposals, budgets, and analytics. Supports core project management operations as well as ClientFlow CRM features including client management, invoicing, and proposals. Requires a GitScrum API token for authentication.', '@gitscrum-core', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/gitscrum-core/mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gitscrum-core.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.975986+00:00'),
  ('git-spice-documentation-search', 'Git-Spice Documentation Search', 'Git Spice Help MCP Server provides a tool for searching git-spice documentation directly within Cursor IDE. This TypeScript implementation fetches documentation from the git-spice website, parses the content, and enables real-time searching through a simple query interface. The server integrates with Cursor''s agent mode, automatically offering documentation assistance when relevant to user queries, making it particularly useful for developers working with git-spice who need quick access to command references and usage examples.', '@sach999', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/sach999/git-spice-help-mcp', 'test-mcp', 4822, 'https://github.com/sach999.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976011+00:00'),
  ('nvd-national-vulnerability-database', 'NVD (National Vulnerability Database)', 'The MCP-NVD server provides AI assistants with direct access to the National Vulnerability Database (NVD) for retrieving CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) information. Built with Python 3.12 and the MCP framework, it exposes a tool for fetching detailed vulnerability data including descriptions, severity ratings, publication dates, and references by CVE ID. The implementation includes rate limit handling, language-specific description retrieval, and comprehensive error recovery. Security analysts, developers, and IT professionals can use this server to quickly access up-to-date vulnerability information through natural language interactions with AI assistants, without needing to manually search the NVD database.', '@gkhays', 'databases', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/gkhays/mcp-nvd-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gkhays.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976042+00:00'),
  ('audius', 'Audius', 'This MCP server, developed by glassBead, enables AI agents to interact with the Audius music platform API. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it provides tools for querying users, tracks, playlists, and other Audius data. The implementation focuses on simplifying Audius API interactions, offering functionality like user searches, track streaming, and playlist management. It''s particularly useful for applications requiring programmatic Audius engagement, enabling use cases such as music discovery, playlist curation, and artist analytics without directly dealing with Audius API complexities.', '@glassbead-tc', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc/audius-mcp-atris', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976119+00:00'),
  ('subspacedomain', 'SubspaceDomain', 'MCP Bridge Server is a macOS-native intermediary that enables seamless communication between different AI clients like Claude and Cline. It provides Unix socket transport, persistent client registration, and robust connection handling with automatic recovery mechanisms. The server includes a client discovery protocol, configurable message routing, and integration with macOS launchd services for system-level operation. Particularly useful for applications that need to coordinate tool execution across multiple AI clients or create workflows that leverage capabilities from different models.', '@glassbead-tc', 'communication', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc/subspacedomain', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976156+00:00'),
  ('tinder', 'Tinder', 'Tinder API MCP Server provides a standardized interface for interacting with the Tinder dating app API, handling authentication flows (SMS and Facebook), request processing, rate limiting, and caching. Built with TypeScript and Express.js, it implements robust security features including token management, validation using Zod schemas, and protection against common web vulnerabilities. The server exposes endpoints for core Tinder functionality like user profiles, recommendations, matching, and messaging, making it ideal for developers building applications that need reliable access to Tinder''s ecosystem while maintaining proper rate limits and security protocols.', '@glassbead-tc', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc/tinder-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glassbead-tc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976183+00:00'),
  ('glasstape-policy-builder', 'GlassTape Policy Builder', 'Built by GlassTape, this MCP server transforms natural language policy requirements into production-ready Cerbos YAML policies through an intermediate canonical policy (ICP) format. The implementation features a complete policy development workflow including generation from structured JSON or natural language, syntax validation via Cerbos CLI integration, comprehensive test suite execution, security analysis with red-team findings, and a template library covering finance, healthcare, AI safety, data access, and system administration scenarios. With air-gap capability for maximum security, built-in compliance framework support (HIPAA, GDPR, SOX, EU AI Act), and automated policy testing, it''s designed for developers building secure authorization systems who need to rapidly generate, validate, and deploy access control policies with confidence.', '@glasstape', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/glasstape/agent-policy-builder-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glasstape.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976217+00:00'),
  ('todo-list', 'Todo List', 'Todo List MCP Server built by Glaucia Lemos that provides comprehensive task management capabilities through in-memory storage with full CRUD operations, advanced filtering, search functionality, and priority-based organization. The implementation uses TypeScript with Zod for robust schema validation, supports tagging and categorization, and offers sophisticated querying options including status filtering (completed/pending), priority levels (low/medium/high), and text-based search across titles and descriptions. Designed for AI assistants that need persistent todo list functionality with rich metadata support, making it valuable for productivity workflows, project management, and personal task organization without requiring external database dependencies.', '@glaucia86', 'databases', 'Unknown', 48, 'https://github.com/glaucia86/todo-list-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glaucia86.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976230+00:00'),
  ('postgresql-explorer', 'PostgreSQL Explorer', 'PostgreSQL MCP Server enables AI agents to interact with PostgreSQL databases through a standardized interface, providing tools for schema exploration, table inspection, relationship discovery, and SQL query execution. Built with Python using the FastMCP library, this implementation connects to any PostgreSQL database via a connection string and exposes database functionality through six well-defined tools that handle everything from basic metadata retrieval to complex relationship analysis. Ideal for developers and data analysts who need to give AI assistants the ability to explore and query relational databases without direct database access.', '@gldc', 'databases', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/gldc/mcp-postgres', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gldc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976241+00:00'),
  ('osv-dev-security-analyzer', 'OSV.dev Security Analyzer', 'MCP Security Analyst is a Go-based server that integrates with OSV.dev to identify and analyze potential vulnerabilities in codebases. Developed by gleicon, it provides tools for checking dependencies against known vulnerabilities and analyzing code files for security issues, with optional enhanced static analysis through Semgrep integration. The server communicates through the Model Context Protocol, making it compatible with AI tools like Claude and Cursor IDE, enabling developers to receive security insights and recommendations directly within their workflow.', '@gleicon', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/gleicon/mcp-osv', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gleicon.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976310+00:00'),
  ('glider', 'Glider', 'Glider is an MCP server that enables AI assistants to perform deep semantic analysis of C# codebases using Microsoft''s Roslyn compiler platform. It provides tools for loading and analyzing .NET solutions, obtaining compiler diagnostics, locating type definitions and implementations, performing semantic renaming, relocating types between files, and accessing source code from NuGet packages and framework types.', '@glidermcp', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/glidermcp/glidermcp.com', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glidermcp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976376+00:00'),
  ('glif', 'Glif', 'Glif MCP server enables Claude to run AI workflows from glif.app, providing tools to execute glifs with inputs, access metadata, and manage saved workflows. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it connects to the Glif API using authentication tokens and exposes resources for glifs, runs, and user profiles. The implementation includes features for running glifs, listing featured workflows, saving favorite glifs as custom tools, and accessing user-specific content, making it particularly valuable for users who want to leverage Glif''s visual AI workflow capabilities directly within Claude conversations.', '@glifxyz', 'development', 'Unknown', 79, 'https://github.com/glifxyz/glif-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glifxyz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976402+00:00'),
  ('mymcpspace', 'MyMCPSpace', 'A Model Context Protocol server that provides AI assistants with access to MyMCPSpace, a social media platform designed for AI interaction. Developed by glifxyz, this TypeScript implementation enables creating posts, replying to existing content, toggling likes, retrieving feed data, and updating usernames through a set of well-defined tools. The server authenticates with the MyMCPSpace API using a bearer token and handles all communication with the platform''s endpoints, making it particularly useful for AI agents that need to participate in social media conversations, share content, or monitor discussions on this AI-native platform.', '@glifxyz', 'development', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/glifxyz/mymcpspace-mcp-server', '@glifxyz/mymcpspace-mcp-server', 5038, 'https://github.com/glifxyz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976430+00:00'),
  ('gemini-ai-patched', 'Gemini AI (Patched)', 'A patched MCP server that integrates with Google''s Gemini AI models through the Gemini CLI, featuring Windows compatibility fixes and intelligent quota management with automatic fallback from gemini-2.5-pro to gemini-2.5-flash when limits are exceeded. Provides specialized tools including a structured brainstorming framework with multiple methodologies (SCAMPER, design thinking, lateral thinking), a changeMode system that formats Gemini responses into Claude-compatible edit instructions with chunking for large responses, and sandbox execution capabilities for safe code testing.', '@glitterkill', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/glitterkill/gemini-mcp-tool-patched', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/glitterkill.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976523+00:00'),
  ('chart-canvas', 'Chart Canvas', 'MCP server for creating interactive charts, diagrams, and tables through AI assistants. Built with Vue 3, ECharts, and Mermaid, it provides a real-time dashboard for visualizations. Supports querying SQLite, CSV, Parquet, JSON, and NDJSON data sources using DuckDB, with a privacy-first architecture where data never leaves your machine.', '@gluip', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/gluip/chart-canvas/tree/HEAD/backend', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gluip.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976535+00:00'),
  ('hive', 'Hive', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to the Hive blockchain, enabling AI assistants to interact with Hive data and operations. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the @hiveio/dhive library, it offers tools for querying blockchain data, posting content, and managing accounts. The server is designed for use cases requiring AI-driven content creation, social media automation, or analysis of Hive blockchain data.', '@gluneau', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/gluneau/hive-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gluneau.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976559+00:00'),
  ('glyphic', 'Glyphic', 'Provides access to Glyphic''s sales intelligence platform, enabling retrieval of call recordings, transcripts, and structured conversation analysis. Supports CRM-integrated deal insights, participant data, and automated meeting recording capabilities.', '@unknown', 'data-analytics', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.glyphic.ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976611+00:00'),
  ('gmail-lead-nurturing', 'Gmail Lead Nurturing', 'This Gmail-based lead nurturing MCP server automates email outreach campaigns for dental practices by providing 24/7 lead follow-up automation with intelligent response tracking and lead scoring. Built with Python and integrating Gmail API, Jinja2 templating, and automated scheduling, it manages multi-stage follow-up sequences (initial contact, 3-day and 7-day follow-ups), analyzes email responses for interest keywords, and maintains lead scoring based on engagement patterns. The implementation includes Docker deployment, systemd service configuration, and comprehensive tools for starting/stopping automation, running single cycles, monitoring system status, generating lead reports, and sending test emails, making it ideal for sales teams and marketers who need hands-off lead nurturing with detailed tracking and remote management capabilities.', '@brandononchain', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/brandononchain/gmail-mcp-agent', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/brandononchain.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976651+00:00'),
  ('headhunter-hh-ru', 'HeadHunter (hh.ru)', 'This server provides access to the HeadHunter (hh.ru) job search API, enabling both public job searching and authenticated user operations through OAuth integration. It offers 10 tools covering vacancy search with advanced filtering (location, salary, experience, schedule), detailed job and employer information retrieval, resume management, job applications, and application tracking. Built with async HTTP client support, it includes an automated vacancy-hunter agent that can analyze job matches across multiple resumes and generate CSV reports, making it ideal for job seekers who want to systematically search, evaluate, and apply to positions on Russia''s largest job platform.', '@gmen1057', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/gmen1057/headhunter-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gmen1057.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976700+00:00'),
  ('image-generator', 'Image Generator', 'MCP Image Generator enables AI assistants to create images using Replicate or Together AI''s image generation models. Built by GMKR, it provides a tool called ''generate_image'' that accepts parameters like prompt, width, height, and number of images to generate. The server can be run locally using stdio or deployed as a Docker container with an SSE endpoint, making it flexible for different integration needs. Configuration requires setting the appropriate provider API keys as environment variables, allowing users to leverage powerful image generation capabilities directly within their AI assistant workflows.', '@gmkr', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/gmkr/mcp-imagegen', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gmkr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976723+00:00'),
  ('zoom-recording-downloader', 'Zoom Recording Downloader', 'Automates the retrieval of Zoom meeting recordings using the Zoom API with OAuth authentication. Supports batch downloading within specified date ranges, resume capability for interrupted transfers, and automatic file organization by meeting topic and timestamp. Useful for organizations archiving meeting recordings or integrating Zoom recording management into automated backup workflows.', '@gmlove', 'file-systems', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gmlove/zoom-recording-downloader', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gmlove.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976767+00:00'),
  ('branch-monkey', 'Branch Monkey', 'Connects to Branch Monkey Cloud (New Kojo), an AI-integrated business operations platform, using browser-based device authentication. Provides comprehensive project-scoped operations including task creation and tracking, team member management, version control, and machine (automated process) management. Features automatic prompt logging to associate AI interactions with specific tasks, making it useful for development teams wanting to track AI-assisted work within their project management workflow.', '@gneyal', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gneyal/p_69_branch_monkey_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gneyal.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976790+00:00'),
  ('github-trending-repositories-findrepo', 'GitHub Trending Repositories (FindRepo)', 'FindRepo MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to GitHub trending repositories through the findrepo.work API. Developed by bhwang, this server exposes a tool to retrieve today''s trending GitHub repositories, with optional filtering by programming language. The implementation uses the Model Context Protocol SDK to create a simple stdio-based server that returns formatted repository information including names and URLs, making it useful for developers who want to stay updated on popular open-source projects without leaving their AI assistant conversation.', '@gnosis23', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/gnosis23/findrepo-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gnosis23.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976819+00:00'),
  ('gnu-radio', 'GNU Radio', 'GNU Radio MCP server built by yoelbassin that provides AI assistants with programmatic access to GNU Radio''s signal processing platform through a FastMCP-based interface. The implementation wraps GNU Radio''s core platform, flowgraph, and block management APIs with middleware layers that handle validation, error reporting, and block connections, exposing tools for creating and manipulating radio flowgraphs including adding/removing blocks, setting parameters, connecting signal paths, and validating configurations. Built with a layered architecture using Pydantic models for type safety and comprehensive error handling, it serves software-defined radio developers who want conversational access to GNU Radio''s capabilities, educators teaching signal processing concepts, and researchers prototyping radio systems who need an intuitive interface for building and debugging complex signal processing workflows without manually navigating GNU Radio Companion''s GUI.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.pulsemcp.com/servers/gnuradio', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976867+00:00'),
  ('go-development-tools', 'Go Development Tools', 'Go Development MCP Server by James Anderton (MrFixit96) provides AI assistants with complete Go development workflow automation through six core tools: go_build for compilation with custom output paths and build tags, go_test for running tests with coverage analysis and pattern matching, go_run for executing programs with command-line arguments, go_mod for dependency management, go_fmt for code formatting, and go_analyze for static analysis using go vet. The implementation supports multiple execution contexts including direct code input, project directories, and Go workspaces with multi-module support, using hybrid and direct execution strategies with comprehensive error parsing, natural language metadata for AI interpretation, and fuzzy matching middleware for intuitive tool selection. Built with extensive testing infrastructure including unit tests, integration tests, and benchmark suites, it serves developers building AI-powered Go development environments, teams requiring automated code quality workflows, and AI assistants needing robust Go toolchain integration with structured error reporting and workspace-aware operations.', '@mrfixit96', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/mrfixit96/go-dev-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mrfixit96.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976905+00:00'),
  ('keitaro-mcp', 'Keitaro MCP', 'A Java implementation of the Model Context Protocol (MCP) for Keitaro, allowing integration with Anthropic''s Claude models.', '@godzilladancer', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/godzilladancer/keitaro-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/godzilladancer.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976936+00:00'),
  ('smart-connections', 'Smart Connections', 'MCP server for Obsidian Smart Connections. Semantic search using your vault''s embeddings.', '@gogogadgetbytes', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gogogadgetbytes/smart-connections-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gogogadgetbytes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976959+00:00'),
  ('r-econometrics', 'R Econometrics', 'An R-based econometrics MCP server that provides advanced statistical modeling capabilities through R packages like plm, lmtest, and AER. Developed by goji+, the server enables AI assistants to perform complex econometric analyses including linear regression, panel data modeling, instrumental variables regression, and diagnostic testing across various research domains. Useful for researchers and data scientists seeking programmatic access to robust statistical modeling tools.', '@finite-sample', 'development', 'Unknown', 198, 'https://github.com/finite-sample/rmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/finite-sample.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.976986+00:00'),
  ('moling', 'MoLing', 'MoLing is an MCP server implementation that enables AI assistants to interact with local system resources through a secure, configurable interface. Developed by CFC4N, it provides services for browser automation (using ChromeDP), file system operations (with strict path validation), and command execution (with allowlist filtering), making it particularly valuable for AI assistants like Claude that need controlled access to local resources. The server supports both stdio and SSE transport methods, includes client configuration tools for popular MCP clients (Claude Desktop, VSCode extensions), and implements robust security measures to prevent unauthorized access to system resources.', '@gojue', 'development', 'Unknown', 330, 'https://github.com/gojue/moling', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gojue.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.977017+00:00'),
  ('moling-minecraft', 'Moling Minecraft', 'MoLing Minecraft MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and Minecraft servers through a Go implementation that enables command execution and server management. Built by CFC4N, this server exposes Minecraft commands as MCP tools for operations like block manipulation (/fill, /setblock), entity management (/summon), and game state control (/time, /weather), while also offering client configuration utilities that automatically detect and configure popular MCP clients like Claude, Cline, and Roo Code. The implementation supports both STDIO and SSE communication modes, includes cross-platform support for Windows, macOS, and Linux, and features robust logging and configuration management, making it valuable for Minecraft players seeking AI assistance with complex builds and server administration.', '@gojue', 'development', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/gojue/moling-minecraft', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gojue.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.977046+00:00');



