  ('gramps-web', 'Gramps Web', 'This MCP server provides AI-powered genealogy research and management through integration with the Gramps Web API, offering 24 specialized tools organized into search & discovery, data management, and analysis categories. Built by cabout.me with comprehensive Pydantic models for type safety and modular handlers for data formatting, it features real-time family tree exploration, person and family detail retrieval, timeline generation, relationship analysis, and full CRUD operations for genealogical records including people, families, events, places, sources, and media. The implementation includes JWT authentication, Docker deployment with multi-architecture support, and direct API integration without mocking, making it ideal for genealogists, family historians, and researchers who need programmatic access to their Gramps databases for AI-assisted family tree analysis, automated record management, and intelligent genealogical research workflows.', '@cabout-me', 'databases', 'Unknown', 25, 'https://github.com/cabout-me/gramps-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cabout-me.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979518+00:00'),
  ('chronos-stellar-blockchain', 'Chronos (Stellar Blockchain)', 'Chronos MCP is a server implementation that provides AI assistants with direct access to the Stellar blockchain network. Built with TypeScript, it exposes tools for connecting to wallets, listing tokens, checking balances, and transferring funds between Stellar addresses. The server uses the Model Context Protocol SDK to handle requests and the Stellar SDK to interact with the Stellar public network. This implementation is particularly valuable for users who need to perform Stellar blockchain operations directly through conversational interfaces without switching contexts or handling complex blockchain interactions manually.', '@grandmastr', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/grandmastr/chronos-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/grandmastr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979579+00:00'),
  ('granola', 'Granola', 'Official Granola MCP server that provides AI assistants with authenticated access to meeting notes and transcripts from the Granola AI notepad platform. Built by Granola, the implementation enables AI tools like Claude, ChatGPT, and Cursor to directly access meeting context without manual copy-pasting, supporting workflows like creating tickets from discussed bugs, updating project boards from standups, drafting CRM notes from sales calls, and building proposals using discovery conversations. Features enterprise-grade controls with admin-configurable access, usage monitoring, and flexible rate limits, making it valuable for developers and teams who want their meeting context seamlessly available across their AI-powered workflows.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://granola.ai/blog/granola-mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979609+00:00'),
  ('graphistry', 'Graphistry', 'The Graphistry MCP server provides AI assistants with GPU-accelerated graph visualization capabilities through a FastMCP implementation. This server enables creating, analyzing, and styling network visualizations by exposing tools for graph rendering, layout algorithms, pattern detection, and visual encoding. It integrates with Graphistry''s cloud platform for high-performance rendering while maintaining a local cache of graph data for efficient manipulation. The implementation supports both standard and specialized layouts (ring, tree, group-in-a-box), community detection, and comprehensive visual customization through node color, size, icon, and badge encodings, making it valuable for network analysis, threat detection, and data exploration workflows.', '@graphistry', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/graphistry/graphistry-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/graphistry.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979652+00:00'),
  ('graphite', 'Graphite', 'This is the Graphite CLI, a command-line tool for managing Git workflows with stacked pull requests and branch management. The CLI provides commands for creating, managing, and syncing stacked branches, enabling developers to work with multiple dependent changes efficiently. It integrates with GitHub and other Git hosting platforms to streamline the process of creating and maintaining complex feature development workflows where changes build upon each other in a stack.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://graphite.dev/docs/gt-mcp', '@withgraphite/graphite-cli', 1112037, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979672+00:00'),
  ('graphlit', 'Graphlit', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to the Graphlit platform, enabling integration between MCP clients and Graphlit services. Developed by Unstruk Data Inc., it utilizes the Graphlit client library and Model Context Protocol SDK to facilitate communication. The server is designed for use cases requiring access to Graphlit''s API capabilities, such as natural language processing tasks or data retrieval from the Graphlit ecosystem.', '@graphlit', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 372, 'https://github.com/graphlit/graphlit-mcp-server', 'graphlit-mcp-server', 59958, 'https://github.com/graphlit.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979704+00:00'),
  ('mcpoogle-mcp-search', 'McPoogle (MCP Search)', 'McPoogle is a search engine specifically designed for MCP Servers and Tools, powered by Graphlit''s knowledge API platform. The implementation provides a web interface that allows users to search and discover various Model Context Protocol resources, leveraging Graphlit''s capabilities for ingestion, memory, and retrieval for AI applications and agents.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.mcpoogle.com/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979739+00:00'),
  ('graphql-bridge', 'GraphQL Bridge', 'mcp4gql serves as a bridge between MCP clients (like Cursor or Claude Desktop) and any GraphQL API, enabling AI assistants to interact with GraphQL endpoints through standard MCP tools. Built by Jorge Alejandro, it provides two key capabilities: introspecting GraphQL schemas and executing arbitrary GraphQL operations with full support for queries, mutations, variables, and authentication. The server is configured via environment variables and can be easily integrated with MCP clients through npx, making it valuable for developers who want to give AI assistants access to their GraphQL data sources without building custom integrations.', '@jorgeraad', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/jorgeraad/mcp4gql', 'mcp4gql', 332, 'https://github.com/jorgeraad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979765+00:00'),
  ('gravity-forms', 'Gravity Forms', 'A full-featured MCP server for Gravity Forms built by GravityKit that provides complete REST API v2 coverage with 24 tools spanning forms, entries, submissions, feeds, and notifications management. The implementation features intelligent field operations with dependency tracking, page-aware positioning, and compound field support (address, name, credit card), along with advanced search capabilities, file upload handling, and comprehensive validation with dual environment support for safe testing. Built with security-first design including delete operation protection, OAuth 1.0a and Basic authentication, extensive error handling with retry logic, and automated testing infrastructure, making it ideal for WordPress developers, form automation workflows, and AI assistants that need reliable programmatic access to Gravity Forms data without affecting production environments.', '@gravitykit', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/gravitykit/gravitymcp', '@gravitykit/gravitymcp', 343, 'https://github.com/gravitykit.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979798+00:00'),
  ('grey-swan', 'Grey Swan', 'Grey Swan MCP Server provides a specialized MongoDB-integrated platform for documenting and analyzing AI safety challenges, particularly focused on tracking LLM vulnerabilities through detailed thread, message, and model tracking. Built for the Grey Swan Arena competitions, it enables researchers to systematically record jailbreak attempts, safety flags, and challenge metadata across different testing sessions. The server offers six MongoDB tools that support a structured workflow for red-teaming AI systems, making it valuable for AI safety researchers seeking to comprehensively document and analyze potential model weaknesses.', '@gravityphone', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/gravityphone/swanzmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gravityphone.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979811+00:00'),
  ('gravity-swarm', 'Gravity Swarm', 'Integrates with the Gravity Swarm distributed agent reputation network built on Nostr. Agents can register as contributors with automatic cryptographic identity generation, retrieve and execute available tasks, submit signed results, propose new tasks for the network, and view network statistics and leaderboard rankings. Handles Nostr keypair generation and BIP-340 Schnorr signing internally.', '@antoinedelorme', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/antoinedelorme/gravity-swarm-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/antoinedelorme.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979843+00:00'),
  ('sharp-image-processing', 'Sharp Image Processing', 'Provides session-based image processing capabilities using Sharp for high-performance image manipulation and machine learning-powered background removal. Creates persistent image sessions from base64 data or file paths, enabling operations like dimension extraction, color sampling from specific coordinates, region cropping, format conversion with compression, and AI-based background removal using @imgly/background-removal-node. Built with TypeScript and supports both stdio and HTTP transports for image analysis workflows, UI color extraction, batch image processing, and preparing images for web optimization.', '@greatsumini', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/greatsumini/sharp-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/greatsumini.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979885+00:00'),
  ('greb', 'Greb', 'Enables developers to search and locate code across repositories using natural language queries. Integrates with AI coding assistants including Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, and Cheetah AI. Claims to deliver faster and more accurate results than traditional RAG approaches through AI-powered ranking algorithms.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://greb.cheetahai.co/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979903+00:00'),
  ('stitch', 'Stitch', 'Integrates with Google Stitch API using OAuth authentication to provide automated design workflow capabilities including UI/UX development, design systems management, export processes, and quality assurance with minimal setup overhead.', '@greensheep01201', 'development', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/greensheep01201/stitch-mcp-auto', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/greensheep01201.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.979924+00:00'),
  ('dmcp', 'DMCP', 'Query-driven tool discovery system that uses semantic search and Redis vector storage to dynamically expose relevant tools from multiple MCP servers. Features a two-process architecture with a server exposing a meta-tool for vector queries and an indexer that discovers and embeds tools from connected servers. Implements lazy connection architecture, intelligent routing with capability clustering, and tool eviction to manage large tool ecosystems efficiently.', '@grep-juub', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/grep-juub/dmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/grep-juub.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980047+00:00'),
  ('greptimedb', 'GreptimeDB', 'GreptimeDB MCP Server provides a secure interface for AI assistants to interact with GreptimeDB time-series databases through MySQL protocol. Developed by Greptime Inc., this Python implementation enables listing tables, reading data, and executing SQL queries with built-in security gates that prevent dangerous operations like DROP or DELETE. The server connects to any GreptimeDB instance using configurable connection parameters and exposes database resources as structured MCP resources and tools. Particularly useful for data exploration, time-series analysis, and integrating database operations directly into AI assistant conversations without requiring manual query construction.', '@greptimeteam', 'databases', 'Unknown', 26, 'https://github.com/greptimeteam/greptimedb-mcp-server', 'greptimedb-mcp-server', 7914, 'https://github.com/greptimeteam.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980062+00:00'),
  ('memory-storage', 'Memory Storage', 'Memory MCP Server provides a persistent storage solution for text memories with tagging capabilities, enabling AI assistants to store, retrieve, search, and manage information across conversations. Built with TypeScript using the Model Context Protocol SDK, it exposes five tools for memory operations including storing new memories with optional tags, searching by text or tags, retrieving all memories, deleting specific memories, and viewing tag usage statistics. The implementation uses a local JSON file for storage, making it particularly valuable for users who want to maintain conversation context and important information without relying on external databases or cloud services.', '@grizzlypeaksoftware', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/grizzlypeaksoftware/mcp-memory-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/grizzlypeaksoftware.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980076+00:00'),
  ('grok-vision-ocr', 'Grok Vision OCR', 'This MCP server by 7etsuo provides AI-powered image analysis using xAI''s Grok API with vision capabilities, offering tools for describing images from URLs or local files and extracting text through OCR using Tesseract. Built with Python and featuring Docker deployment with security best practices including non-root execution and secret management, it processes images temporarily in memory without permanent storage while supporting multiple formats including JPEG, PNG, WebP, and others. The implementation combines Grok''s advanced vision model with local OCR processing through OpenCV and Pillow, making it valuable for content analysis workflows, document digitization, and automated image understanding tasks that require both AI-generated descriptions and text extraction capabilities.', '@7etsuo', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/7etsuo/image-description-mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/7etsuo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980112+00:00'),
  ('aws-security-inspector', 'AWS Security Inspector', 'AWS Security MCP is a server that enables AI assistants to inspect and analyze AWS infrastructure for security issues. Built with Python and boto3, it provides tools for querying security findings from GuardDuty, SecurityHub, and IAM Access Analyzer, examining EC2 instances, analyzing IAM roles and permissions, scanning S3 buckets, and inspecting CloudFront distributions. The implementation supports natural language queries about AWS resources, generates security recommendations, and creates network maps and blast radius analyses, making it valuable for security professionals who need to assess AWS environments without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@groovybugify', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 81, 'https://github.com/groovybugify/aws-security-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/groovybugify.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980133+00:00'),
  ('ground', 'Ground', 'Provides structured reference data to AI assistants including classification systems (wire gauges, IP ratings, shoe sizes, battery types), measurement conversions (temperature, pressure, length, mass), and encoding systems (HS codes, ICD-10 taxonomies). Designed for precise information that''s too specialized for training data and too structured for web searches.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://ground.fyi', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980152+00:00'),
  ('e-gov-japanese-legal-database', 'e-Gov (Japanese Legal Database)', 'This server provides access to Japanese legal information through the e-Gov API, Japan''s official government legal database. Built by groundcobra009 as a Node.js application, it enables querying specific laws, browsing legal categories, and accessing up-to-date regulatory content in Japanese. The server serves as a bridge to Japan''s comprehensive legal framework, making it valuable for legal research, compliance checking, regulatory analysis, and educational purposes related to Japanese law.', '@groundcobra009', 'databases', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/groundcobra009/hourei-mcp-server', 'hourei-mcp-server', 1013, 'https://github.com/groundcobra009.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980168+00:00'),
  ('grounddocs', 'GroundDocs', 'GroundDocs MCP server provides source-verified documentation lookup for Python libraries and Kubernetes resources. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers two specialized tools that retrieve accurate, version-specific documentation from authoritative sources. The server connects to a dedicated backend service (grounddocs.onrender.com) that indexes and serves documentation content, ensuring responses are grounded in real documentation rather than potentially hallucinated information. This implementation is particularly valuable for developers who need reliable, contextually relevant documentation without leaving their AI assistant conversation.', '@grounddocs', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/grounddocs/grounddocs', '@grounddocs/grounddocs', 4818, 'https://github.com/grounddocs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980191+00:00'),
  ('groundx-rag', 'GroundX RAG', 'This RAG-based MCP server implementation integrates with GroundX to provide AI assistants with document search and ingestion capabilities. The server exposes two main tools: one for searching existing documents in a knowledge base to retrieve relevant context for queries, and another for ingesting new PDF documents into the system. Built with FastMCP, it operates over stdio transport and uses environment variables for API authentication, making it particularly useful for enhancing AI assistants with domain-specific knowledge retrieval without requiring direct access to the underlying document storage.', '@prixyy', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/prixyy/rag_based_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/prixyy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980237+00:00'),
  ('group-protection', 'Group Protection', 'Group Protection MCP server provides access to insurance policy and claims data through a standardized interface. Built with FastMCP, it exposes tools for retrieving recent activity data including policy changes, premium payments, member enrollments and claims processing. Particularly valuable for operations directors and brokers who need to monitor insurance activity and analyze claims data through AI assistants.', '@wayneqs', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/wayneqs/mcp_server_spike', 'gp', 25058, 'https://github.com/wayneqs.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980272+00:00'),
  ('grove', 'Grove', 'Grove''s Public Endpoints MCP server provides direct access to blockchain data across 100+ networks through Grove''s public RPC infrastructure, supporting major chains like Ethereum, Polygon, Solana, and various Layer 2 solutions. Built by Grove with TypeScript and the MCP SDK, it offers both natural language blockchain queries ("get the latest height for ethereum") and direct JSON-RPC method calls, with intelligent endpoint selection that prioritizes foundation-sponsored endpoints for better reliability. The server includes comprehensive blockchain service discovery, method aliasing for user-friendly queries, detailed error handling with rate limit guidance, and extensible endpoint configuration, making it valuable for developers building blockchain applications, analysts querying on-chain data, and AI assistants that need reliable access to multi-chain blockchain information without managing individual RPC connections.', '@pokt-network', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/pokt-network/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/pokt-network.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980309+00:00'),
  ('pokemon', 'Pokemon', 'This Pokemon MCP server by grovesjosephn provides comprehensive Pokemon data access through a local SQLite database populated from PokeAPI, offering six core tools for Pokemon information retrieval, comparison, searching, and analysis. The implementation features a modular architecture with separate ingestion and server packages, flexible response formatting (Markdown and JSON), and robust database queries supporting complex searches by type, generation, stats, and other criteria. Built with TypeScript and better-sqlite3, it includes comprehensive test coverage, rate-limited data ingestion, and production-ready error handling, making it valuable for Pokemon enthusiasts, game developers, or educational applications that need reliable access to detailed Pokemon statistics, type effectiveness data, and comparative analysis without depending on external API availability.', '@grovesjosephn', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/grovesjosephn/pokemcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/grovesjosephn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980321+00:00'),
  ('growthbook', 'GrowthBook', 'GrowthBook MCP Server enables AI assistants to interact with GrowthBook, an open source feature flagging and experimentation platform. It provides tools for managing feature flags, experiments, environments, and SDK connections through a standardized interface. Built with TypeScript and the Model Context Protocol SDK, it includes capabilities for searching documentation, creating targeting rules, and generating implementation code for various programming languages. The server requires minimal configuration through environment variables and can be integrated with clients like Cursor, VS Code, and Claude Desktop, making it particularly valuable for developers who need to manage feature flags and A/B tests directly through natural language interactions.', '@growthbook', 'development', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/growthbook/growthbook-mcp', '@growthbook/mcp', 13365, 'https://github.com/growthbook.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980349+00:00'),
  ('grumpydev', 'GrumpyDev', 'GrumpyDev MCP is a server that lets AI assistants get code reviews from a simulated grumpy senior developer with 40+ years of experience. Created by Yohan Lasorsa, this tool provides thorough, sarcastic, and slightly condescending feedback on code quality, pointing out mistakes, inefficiencies, and bad practices. The implementation uses GenAIScript to define a review_code tool that accepts code input and returns detailed critiques in a distinctive grumpy tone, making it useful for developers seeking brutally honest feedback on their code.', '@sinedied', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/sinedied/grumpydev-mcp', 'grumpydev-mcp', 627, 'https://github.com/sinedied.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980423+00:00'),
  ('dsr', 'DSR', 'Enables interaction with DSR (Deep State Representation) graphs, a knowledge representation framework for robot perception and scene understanding. Provides 11 tools for querying, modifying, and exporting graph structures including nodes (robots, persons, rooms) and semantic edges (spatial relationships, ownership). Includes 4 read-only resources for efficient data access.', '@grupo-avispa', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/grupo-avispa/dsr_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/grupo-avispa.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980493+00:00'),
  ('swiss-ai-labor-market', 'Swiss AI Labor Market', 'Tracks AI''s impact on the Swiss labor market through automated data collection from BFS statistics, news sources, and research publications, providing semantic search and trend analysis for employment patterns, industry disruption, and AI adoption across Switzerland''s economic sectors.', '@gsalami', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gsalami/swiss-ai-labor-market', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gsalami.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980529+00:00'),
  ('nccn-guidelines', 'NCCN Guidelines', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with access to the National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN) clinical practice guidelines through automated web scraping, PDF downloading, and content extraction capabilities. Built using Python with httpx for async HTTP requests, BeautifulSoup for HTML parsing, and pdfplumber for PDF text extraction, the implementation automatically scrapes NCCN''s website to build a searchable index of guidelines, handles login authentication for PDF downloads with intelligent caching, and extracts specific pages from guideline PDFs while preserving layout and table structures. The server maintains a 7-day cache for both the guidelines index and downloaded PDFs to minimize server load, supports targeted page extraction for efficient content retrieval, and includes comprehensive logging for debugging, serving healthcare professionals and AI assistants requiring programmatic access to evidence-based cancer treatment protocols and clinical decision support without manual navigation of the NCCN website.', '@gscfwid', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/gscfwid/nccn_guidelines_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gscfwid.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980565+00:00'),
  ('nautobot-network-infrastructure', 'Nautobot Network Infrastructure', 'Nautobot MCP integrates the Model Context Protocol server with Nautobot, a network infrastructure management platform, enabling AI assistants to query and interact with network data through standardized tools. Developed by Geury Torres, this Django-based app provides tools for retrieving information about devices, interfaces, circuits, IP addresses, and locations stored in Nautobot. The server exposes these capabilities through a RESTful API that follows the MCP specification, making it ideal for network engineers and administrators who want to leverage AI to automate network documentation, troubleshooting, and management tasks.', '@gt732', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/gt732/nautobot-app-mcp', 'nautobot-mcp', 2068, 'https://github.com/gt732.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980614+00:00'),
  ('continuo-memory', 'Continuo Memory', 'A persistent memory system for MCP that implements hierarchical compression and semantic search using ChromaDB and sentence transformers. Built by D.D. and Gustavo Porto, it provides three-tier memory storage (N0 chunks, N1 micro-summaries, N2 meta-summaries) with automatic compression of older content to maintain efficiency while preserving context. The server offers tools for storing content, performing semantic searches, and retrieving memory statistics, supporting both local embeddings via sentence-transformers and cloud-based OpenAI embeddings. Useful for applications requiring long-term context retention, knowledge base management, and RAG-based retrieval where traditional context windows are insufficient.', '@gtokai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gtokai/continuo-memory-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gtokai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980664+00:00'),
  ('finance-market-data', 'Finance Market Data', 'FinanceMCP is a Model Context Protocol server that provides financial data and news tools for AI assistants. Built with TypeScript and the MCP SDK, it offers three main tools: stockData for retrieving stock market information, indexData for market indices tracking, and financeNews for gathering financial news updates. The implementation follows a modular structure with separate TypeScript files for each tool, making it easy to extend with additional financial data sources. This server is particularly valuable for users who need real-time financial information without leaving their AI conversation context.', '@guangxiangdebizi', 'development', 'Unknown', 478, 'https://github.com/guangxiangdebizi/financemcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guangxiangdebizi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980692+00:00'),
  ('news-api-aggregator', 'News API Aggregator', 'A smart news MCP server with automatic API switching for reliable news fetching, created by Xingyu Chen. The implementation integrates with five different news APIs (TheNewsAPI, NewsData.io, NewsAPI.org, GNews, and Twingly) and automatically switches between them based on priority and availability when rate limits are hit or APIs fail. Built with TypeScript and featuring intelligent fallback mechanisms, it''s designed for applications that need consistent access to news data without manual intervention when individual APIs become unavailable or exceed their quotas.', '@guangxiangdebizi', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/guangxiangdebizi/news-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guangxiangdebizi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980721+00:00'),
  ('io-github-expertvagabond-guardrails', 'io.github.ExpertVagabond/guardrails', 'AI Agent Guardrails MCP server - security layer', '@expertvagabond', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/expertvagabond/guardrails-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/expertvagabond.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980749+00:00'),
  ('neo4j-graphrag', 'Neo4j GraphRAG', 'Unified Neo4j GraphRAG server combining vector similarity search, fulltext search, and search-augmented Cypher queries into a single implementation. Solves the critical limitation where LLMs cannot directly use Neo4j search indexes in Cypher by generating embeddings server-side and injecting them as parameters. Includes production-ready safeguards with automatic data sanitization for large embeddings and text content, intelligent token-aware response truncation limiting outputs to 8,000 tokens, and property size warnings to optimize query performance.', '@neo4j-field', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/neo4j-field/mcp-neo4j-graphrag', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/neo4j-field.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980791+00:00'),
  ('lex', 'Lex', 'Lex enables AI agents to maintain persistent memory across work sessions. It provides tools for frame-based memory operations, policy validation, and architectural analysis using a SQLite backend with optional encryption.', '@guffawaffle', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/guffawaffle/lex', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guffawaffle.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980802+00:00'),
  ('brasil-api', 'Brasil API', 'Brasil API MCP server provides tools for querying various Brazilian data services through a standardized interface. Developed by Guilherme Lirio, it integrates with the Brasil API to offer capabilities for postal code (CEP) lookups, company (CNPJ) information retrieval, bank data access, area code (DDD) information, IBGE geographic data, currency exchange rates, and domain registration checks. The implementation is built with TypeScript and runs on Node.js, making it valuable for applications requiring Brazilian-specific data validation, address verification, financial information, or domain availability checking without leaving the conversation context.', '@guilhermelirio', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/guilhermelirio/brasil-api-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guilhermelirio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980828+00:00'),
  ('brazilian-cep', 'Brazilian CEP', 'Brazilian CEP MCP provides tools to query Brazilian postal code (CEP) information through the Model Context Protocol. Built by Guilherme Lirio, it uses Node.js with TypeScript and integrates with external CEP APIs via Axios to retrieve address details. The implementation is containerized with Docker for easy deployment and configured through Smithery.ai, making it ideal for applications requiring Brazilian address validation or location-based services within AI assistant workflows.', '@guilhermelirio', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/guilhermelirio/brazilian-cep-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guilhermelirio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980848+00:00'),
  ('mlb-stats-api', 'MLB Stats API', 'This MLB API MCP Server provides comprehensive access to Major League Baseball statistics and data through a FastMCP-based interface that bridges AI applications with MLB data sources. Built by James Guillochon, it exposes over 20 specialized tools for retrieving current standings, game schedules, player statistics including sabermetrics like WAR and wOBA, team rosters, live game data with boxscores and play-by-play, game highlights, and Statcast data for advanced baseball analytics. The server integrates both the official MLB Stats API and pybaseball for Statcast data, supports flexible team/player identification by name or ID, includes intelligent result size management to prevent overwhelming responses, and offers both HTTP and stdio transports with Docker deployment options, making it valuable for sports analytics, fantasy baseball applications, and AI-driven baseball research workflows.', '@guillochon', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 39, 'https://github.com/guillochon/mlb-api-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guillochon.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980936+00:00'),
  ('swagger-openapi-explorer', 'Swagger/OpenAPI Explorer', 'This Swagger/OpenAPI MCP server enables AI assistants to dynamically load and explore API specifications from URLs or files, providing comprehensive endpoint discovery and documentation access. Built with TypeScript using the @apidevtools/swagger-parser library, it offers four core tools for loading API specs, retrieving detailed endpoint information with optional natural language summaries, listing all loaded APIs, and searching endpoints by pattern matching. The implementation supports multiple concurrent API specifications through unique identifiers and provides both structured JSON responses and human-readable summaries, making it valuable for API integration workflows where assistants need to understand and interact with external services by first examining their OpenAPI documentation.', '@gulbaki', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/gulbaki/swagger-mcp-server', 'swagger-mcp-server', 1053, 'https://github.com/gulbaki.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.980999+00:00'),
  ('osmosis-apply', 'Osmosis Apply', 'This MCP server provides intelligent code merging capabilities through the Osmosis-Apply-1.7B model via Ollama, enabling AI assistants to apply targeted edits to existing code while preserving exact formatting and structure. Built using Python with comprehensive file operation support, it offers a single edit_snippet tool that accepts original code and edit instructions using ''// ... existing code ...'' markers to indicate preserved sections, with optional direct file modification capabilities that search for original code patterns and replace them in-place. The implementation features streaming response support for real-time feedback, robust error handling for file permissions and missing content, and extensive test coverage including edge cases like malformed responses and permission errors, making it valuable for automated code refactoring workflows, AI-assisted development environments, and building coding assistants that need precise code modification capabilities without breaking existing functionality.', '@osmosis-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 53, 'https://github.com/osmosis-ai/osmosis-apply-1.7b-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/osmosis-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981034+00:00'),
  ('gumlet', 'Gumlet', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to Gumlet''s video and image processing APIs along with documentation search capabilities. Hosted remotely at https://docs.gumlet.com/mcp, it enables AI development tools like Cursor, Windsurf, and Claude Desktop to interact with Gumlet functionality including video asset management, live streaming, DRM integration, image transformations, and analytics without manual API navigation. The implementation supports authentication via query parameters and is designed for developers building media processing workflows, video streaming applications, and AI assistants that need programmatic access to Gumlet''s content delivery and optimization services.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.gumlet.com/reference/mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981063+00:00'),
  ('guru', 'Guru', 'Integrates with Guru''s Knowledge Agents to provide AI assistants with access to verified, permission-aware company knowledge. Supports searching content, asking questions, retrieving research with citations, and creating or updating Guru Cards through natural language interactions. All queries respect existing permissions and are logged in the AI Agent Center for governance and auditability.', '@guruhq', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/guruhq/remote-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/guruhq.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981140+00:00');


