Get attraction wait times
Get show times', '@habuma', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/habuma/tpapi-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/habuma.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981770+00:00'),
  ('odoo-erp', 'Odoo ERP', 'This MCP server provides comprehensive Odoo ERP integration through XML-RPC, enabling AI assistants to interact with Odoo instances for business process automation across sales, purchasing, inventory, and accounting modules. Built by Yhasmani Valdes using Python with FastMCP, it offers tools for creating and managing sales orders, purchase orders, invoices, inventory operations, and financial records, along with resources for browsing Odoo models and fields. The implementation features Docker containerization, environment-based configuration, detailed logging, and modular tool organization by business domain, making it valuable for businesses wanting AI assistance in automating ERP workflows, generating reports, and managing complex business operations within their existing Odoo infrastructure.', '@hachecito', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 36, 'https://github.com/hachecito/odoo-mcp-improved', 'odoo-mcp-improved', 3588, 'https://github.com/hachecito.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981798+00:00'),
  ('unity-code', 'Unity Code', 'Unity Code MCP Server is a Rust-based MCP server built by Hackerzhuli that provides reliable AI-Unity Editor integration by addressing the core limitation of existing Unity MCP servers: their inability to survive Unity''s domain reload functionality that makes Editor components unavailable. The server exposes essential tools for refreshing Unity''s asset database with compilation error reporting and executing both EditMode and PlayMode tests with comprehensive results and logs, using a compilation-resilient architecture that maintains connection through Unity''s reload cycles. Designed as a component for the Unity Code Pro VS Code extension, it enables AI assistants to effectively assist with Unity development workflows by providing direct access to Unity''s compilation and testing systems without being disrupted by Unity''s internal state changes.', '@hackerzhuli', 'databases', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/hackerzhuli/unity_code_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hackerzhuli.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981844+00:00'),
  ('hackthebox', 'HackTheBox', 'The HTB MCP Server provides a bridge to the HackTheBox API, enabling AI assistants to interact with the cybersecurity learning platform through natural language commands. Built in Go with comprehensive tool coverage, it exposes 12 core tools including listing and filtering challenges/machines, starting instances, retrieving connection details, submitting flags, and accessing user progress data, all authenticated via JWT token. The server supports both active and retired content with advanced filtering by difficulty, category, and operating system, making it valuable for cybersecurity education workflows, automated lab management, and integrating hands-on hacking practice into AI-driven learning experiences.', '@noaslr', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/noaslr/htb-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/noaslr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981904+00:00'),
  ('mixamo', 'Mixamo', 'Integrates with Adobe Mixamo''s animation library to search, download, and automatically configure character animations for Unity projects. Provides batch download capabilities, smart keyword mapping for animation discovery, and automatic Humanoid rig setup for imported FBX files. Generates Animator Controllers from animation folders to streamline Unity animation workflow.', '@had0yun', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/had0yun/unity-mcp-mixamo', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/had0yun.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981937+00:00'),
  ('poly-pizza-unity-integration', 'Poly.Pizza Unity Integration', 'Integrates with Poly.Pizza''s library of 10,500+ low-poly 3D models to automatically download, import, and configure assets directly into Unity projects.', '@had0yun', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/had0yun/poly-pizza-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/had0yun.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.981959+00:00'),
  ('facebook-pages-manager', 'Facebook Pages Manager', 'The Facebook MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to Facebook Page management capabilities through the Graph API. This Python implementation offers tools for creating and managing posts, handling comments, monitoring engagement metrics, and analyzing post performance through detailed insights. The server exposes a comprehensive set of functions for content moderation, including the ability to filter negative comments based on keywords and delete problematic content. Built with FastMCP and structured around a clean API abstraction layer, it enables seamless interaction with Facebook Pages without context switching, making it particularly valuable for social media managers who need to monitor engagement, respond to comments, and analyze post performance metrics through natural language interactions.', '@hagaihen', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 117, 'https://github.com/hagaihen/facebook-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hagaihen.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982010+00:00'),
  ('starrocks', 'StarRocks', 'StarRocks MCP Server provides a standardized interface for AI models to interact with StarRocks databases, enabling querying, table management, and data manipulation through a set of predefined tools. Built with Python and supporting both read-only and write modes, the server allows AI assistants to execute SELECT queries, list tables, describe schemas, and perform write operations like INSERT and CREATE TABLE when not in read-only mode.', '@hagsmand', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/hagsmand/mcp-server-starrocks', 'mcp-server-starrocks', 10636, 'https://github.com/hagsmand.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982024+00:00'),
  ('gitlab-jira', 'GitLab & Jira', 'MCP server implementation by hainan.zhao that provides AI assistants with integrated access to both GitLab and Jira APIs through a unified interface, supporting comprehensive project management workflows including merge request reviews, pipeline management, issue tracking, and ticket operations. The implementation features GitLab tools for MR details with diff parsing, comment management, project/branch/issue operations, CI/CD pipeline control, and user management, alongside Jira tools for ticket CRUD operations, JQL searching with intelligent fuzzy matching, custom field updates, and project management. Built with TypeScript using official GitLab REST API and Jira.js SDK, it includes a unified search tool that replaces multiple individual search functions with smart fuzzy matching for priorities, statuses, and assignees, making it valuable for development teams managing code reviews, sprint planning, and cross-platform project coordination between GitLab repositories and Jira workflows.', '@hainanzhao', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/hainanzhao/mcp-gitlab-jira', 'mcp-gitlab-jira', 1100, 'https://github.com/hainanzhao.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982054+00:00'),
  ('obsidian-tasks', 'Obsidian Tasks', 'Reads Obsidian vault markdown files to query and filter tasks using a subset of the Obsidian Tasks plugin query syntax. Supports filtering by task status, due date comparisons, tag inclusion and exclusion, file path patterns, and description text matching. Returns structured task objects with metadata including file path, line number, tags, and due dates.', '@hairyhenderson', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/hairyhenderson/obsidian-tasks-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hairyhenderson.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982086+00:00'),
  ('popcorn', 'Popcorn', 'Provides comprehensive video analysis capabilities by extracting keyframes and generating transcripts from video files using FFmpeg and multiple Whisper backends. Features intelligent preset configurations optimized for different video types (screencasts, presentations, movies, interviews, surveillance footage, sports) and analysis objectives (summary, detailed analysis, transcription focus, visual-only). Supports scene detection for smart frame extraction, multiple transcription backends including MLX Whisper for Apple Silicon optimization, and returns both structured metadata and inline base64-encoded frames for direct consumption by clients.', '@haithamelmengad', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/haithamelmengad/popcorn', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/haithamelmengad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982112+00:00'),
  ('keycloak', 'Keycloak', 'Keycloak MCP server provides a standardized interface for managing Keycloak identity and access management through the Model Context Protocol. Developed by Haitham Oumerzoug, it leverages the official Keycloak Admin Client to enable AI assistants to perform user management operations including creating users, assigning roles, managing groups, and listing clients across different realms. The implementation is built with TypeScript and Node.js, packaged for easy installation via npm or Smithery, and requires minimal configuration with Keycloak server credentials. This server is particularly valuable for teams wanting to automate identity management tasks or integrate Keycloak administration into AI-assisted workflows.', '@haithamoumerzoug', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/haithamoumerzoug/keycloak-mcp', 'keycloak-mcp', 5507, 'https://github.com/haithamoumerzoug.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982144+00:00'),
  ('deep-research', 'Deep Research', 'Deep Research MCP is a server that provides web search and advanced research capabilities for AI assistants. Based on HuggingFace''s smolagents, it offers tools for web browsing, document analysis, image description, YouTube transcript retrieval, and archive site searching. The implementation includes specialized components for handling various file formats (PDF, DOCX, PPTX) and media types, making it particularly valuable for users who need to gather information from diverse sources without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@hajime-y', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 17, 'https://github.com/hajime-y/deep-research-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hajime-y.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982187+00:00'),
  ('things-app', 'Things App', 'This MCP server, developed by hald, integrates with the Things task management app to enable AI assistants to interact with users'' task data. It leverages the Things.py library and Things URL scheme to provide a wide range of operations including creating tasks, analyzing projects, managing priorities, and more. The implementation is built in Python 3.12+ and uses modern dependencies like httpx and pydantic. It''s designed for Things users who want to incorporate AI assistance into their productivity workflow, allowing for natural language queries and updates to their task lists, projects, and areas.', '@hald', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 347, 'https://github.com/hald/things-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hald.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982226+00:00'),
  ('domain-finder', 'Domain Finder', 'An intelligent domain name suggestion MCP server that combines AI-powered brainstorming with real-time availability checking through Namecheap and Domainr APIs. The implementation uses multiple creative strategies including word slicing, portmanteau combinations, and LLM-generated suggestions to find brandable domain names, with advanced scoring algorithms that evaluate factors like pronounceability, keyword relevance, and TLD appropriateness. Features include standard domain suggestions with smart retry logic, batch domain availability checking, and a unique deep TLD exploration tool that cycles through all 1,441+ available TLDs using AI analysis to discover standout combinations, making it particularly valuable for entrepreneurs, marketers, and developers who need creative, available domain options for new projects or brand development.', '@halfaipg', 'development', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/halfaipg/domain-finder-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/halfaipg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982257+00:00'),
  ('electron-desktop-automation', 'Electron Desktop Automation', 'The Electron MCP Server by Halil Ural provides automation and management capabilities for Electron desktop applications through Chrome DevTools Protocol integration. It connects to running Electron apps via remote debugging ports (typically 9222) to enable screenshot capture with base64 image data for AI analysis, JavaScript command execution for DOM interaction and button clicking, console log monitoring, and window information retrieval. The server automatically detects various Electron project types including Vite, Webpack, and React-based applications, intelligently launching them with appropriate debugging configurations, making it valuable for automated testing, desktop app debugging, and AI-assisted application interaction workflows.', '@halilural', 'development', 'Unknown', 59, 'https://github.com/halilural/electron-mcp-server', 'electron-mcp-server', 3712, 'https://github.com/halilural.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982289+00:00'),
  ('cimri-price-investigator', 'Cimri Price Investigator', 'Cimri-Price-Investigation is an MCP server that enables AI assistants to search for product prices on Cimri.com, a Turkish price comparison website. The implementation uses Puppeteer to scrape real-time pricing data from the site based on product name queries. When invoked, the server launches a headless browser, navigates to Cimri''s search results for the specified product, extracts price information, and returns it in a formatted text response. This tool is particularly useful for price comparison tasks, helping users find current market rates for products in Turkey without leaving their conversation interface.', '@halityurttas', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/halityurttas/cimri-mcp-investigate', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/halityurttas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982332+00:00'),
  ('meme-generator-imgflip', 'Meme Generator (ImgFlip)', 'Meme MCP Server enables AI models to generate meme images through the ImgFlip API. Developed by Vladimir Haltakov, it provides a single tool called ''generateMeme'' that accepts parameters for template ID and text placeholders. The server runs locally using Node.js and requires ImgFlip credentials, making it easy to integrate with Claude Desktop for creating custom memes directly within conversations without leaving the interface.', '@haltakov', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 47, 'https://github.com/haltakov/meme-mcp', 'meme-mcp', 5723, 'https://github.com/haltakov.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982371+00:00'),
  ('android-adb', 'Android ADB', 'Provides Android device automation through ADB (Android Debug Bridge) integration, enabling control of Android devices programmatically. Built with TypeScript and the @devicefarmer/adbkit library, it exposes tools for taking screenshots, dumping UI hierarchies, sending key events, tapping coordinates, inputting text, starting activities, and finding/tapping UI elements by text or content description. Supports multiple device management with automatic device selection for single-device setups, making it valuable for mobile app testing, UI automation, accessibility testing, and remote device control workflows.', '@hamen', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/hamen/android-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hamen.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982439+00:00'),
  ('imagen-3', 'Imagen 3', 'Imagen3-MCP is a Rust-based server that enables AI assistants to generate images using Google''s Imagen 3 API. It provides a simple interface for creating images from text prompts, handling the API communication, image storage, and serving the generated images through a local HTTP server. The implementation includes comprehensive prompt writing guidance to help users create effective prompts, supports various image aspect ratios, and requires a Google Gemini API key to function. Particularly valuable for AI assistants that need to enhance conversations with visual content based on textual descriptions.', '@hamflx', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 58, 'https://github.com/hamflx/imagen3-mcp', 'imagen3-mcp', 0, 'https://github.com/hamflx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982481+00:00'),
  ('kokoro-speech', 'Kokoro Speech', 'Koroko Speech MCP Server provides text-to-speech capabilities using the Kokoro TTS model, enabling AI assistants to generate and play audio from text input. The implementation offers multiple tools for basic speech synthesis, customizable playback speed, and voice selection from a curated list of high-quality voices. It features robust error handling with automatic retry mechanisms for model initialization failures and temporary file management for audio playback. The server runs on stdio transport for seamless integration with Claude Desktop, making it particularly valuable for adding natural-sounding voice output to AI assistant conversations without requiring external applications.', '@hammeiam', 'communication', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/hammeiam/koroko-speech-mcp', 'speech-mcp-server', 1038, 'https://github.com/hammeiam.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982522+00:00'),
  ('handrails', 'Handrails', 'This Replit MCP server adds a development banner notification when Replit projects are accessed outside their native environment. The implementation detects when a Replit-hosted application is being viewed in development mode from an external context and automatically injects a banner at the top of the page to inform users of the development status. This is particularly useful for developers working on Replit projects who need to provide clear visual indicators to users when they''re interacting with development versions of applications, helping distinguish between production and development environments and managing user expectations during the development process.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://handrails.dev', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982546+00:00'),
  ('java-class-analyzer', 'Java Class Analyzer', 'This MCP server provides Java class file analysis and decompilation capabilities, integrating with Maven repositories and Java decompilation tools to enable deep inspection of compiled Java bytecode. Built by handsomestWei with TypeScript and featuring CFR decompiler integration, dependency scanning, and Maven repository support, it offers tools for analyzing class file structure, decompiling bytecode to readable Java source, scanning JAR dependencies, and extracting metadata from compiled artifacts. The implementation includes environment configuration for Java and Maven paths, automatic class indexing with caching, and archive handling for JAR/ZIP files, making it valuable for reverse engineering Java applications, dependency analysis, security auditing, and understanding third-party library implementations where source code is unavailable.', '@handsomestwei', 'development', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/handsomestwei/java-class-analyzer-mcp-server', 'java-class-analyzer-mcp-server', 419, 'https://github.com/handsomestwei.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982575+00:00'),
  ('handwriting-ocr', 'Handwriting OCR', 'This Handwriting OCR MCP server enables AI assistants to extract text from handwritten documents through a TypeScript implementation. The server provides a bridge between Claude and other MCP-compatible clients and the Handwriting OCR API, allowing users to upload images containing handwritten content and receive digitized text in return. Built with TypeScript and requiring an API key for authentication, it supports various image formats and offers accurate text extraction from handwritten notes, making it valuable for digitizing physical documents, processing historical manuscripts, or converting handwritten notes into editable text.', '@handwriting-ocr', 'development', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/handwriting-ocr/handwriting-ocr-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/handwriting-ocr.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982600+00:00'),
  ('hangfire', 'Hangfire', 'Hangfire MCP enables AI assistants to enqueue background jobs in Hangfire, a popular .NET job scheduling library, through the Model Context Protocol. Developed by Oleksii Nikiforov, it provides a dynamic job scheduling system that discovers available jobs, handles method overloading, and supports complex parameter types through JSON deserialization. The implementation integrates with .NET Aspire for distributed application development and includes a comprehensive MCP server with tools for job management. This approach allows users to execute background tasks directly from any MCP client, including VS Code in Agent Mode, without writing additional code - making it particularly valuable for developers who need to trigger server-side processing from AI assistants.', '@nikiforovall', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/nikiforovall/hangfire-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/nikiforovall.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982627+00:00'),
  ('stata', 'Stata', 'The Stata MCP Extension provides seamless integration between Stata statistical software and code editors like VS Code and Cursor through the Model Context Protocol. It enables users to execute Stata commands directly from their editor, view real-time output, and benefit from AI-assisted coding with contextual understanding of Stata data and commands. Created by Lu Han and published by DeepEcon, this cross-platform extension automatically detects Stata installations, supports syntax highlighting for Stata file formats, and establishes a local MCP server that connects the editor to Stata - making it particularly valuable for data scientists and researchers who want enhanced productivity when working with statistical analyses.', '@hanlulong', 'development', 'Unknown', 194, 'https://github.com/hanlulong/stata-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hanlulong.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982692+00:00'),
  ('ant-design-components', 'Ant Design Components', 'MCP-Antd-Components provides a server that exposes Ant Design component documentation to Large Language Models like Claude. Developed by Hannes Junnila, it extracts and serves component information from the Ant Design repository, allowing AI assistants to explore available components, view detailed documentation, examine props and API definitions, and access code examples. The server offers six specialized tools for component discovery and understanding, making it valuable for developers who need AI assistance with implementing Ant Design components in their React applications without requiring the full Ant Design repository to be present.', '@hannesj', 'development', 'Unknown', 25, 'https://github.com/hannesj/mcp-antd-components', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hannesj.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982718+00:00'),
  ('graphql-schema', 'GraphQL Schema', 'The GraphQL Schema MCP server enables AI models to explore and understand GraphQL schemas through specialized tools. Built using the Model Context Protocol SDK, it loads any GraphQL schema file and provides tools for exploring query, mutation, and subscription fields, looking up detailed type definitions, searching for types and fields using pattern matching, and getting simplified field information. This implementation is particularly valuable for developers working with GraphQL APIs who need AI assistance in understanding schema structure, exploring available operations, or searching for specific functionality within complex GraphQL schemas.', '@hannesj', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 43, 'https://github.com/hannesj/mcp-graphql-schema', 'mcp-graphql-schema', 2046, 'https://github.com/hannesj.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982765+00:00'),
  ('openapi-schema', 'OpenAPI Schema', 'The OpenAPI Schema MCP server exposes OpenAPI specification information to Large Language Models through a set of specialized tools. Developed by Hannes Junnila, it loads any OpenAPI schema file (JSON or YAML) and provides tools for exploring API paths, operations, parameters, schemas, and security definitions. The server converts complex OpenAPI structures into YAML format for better LLM comprehension and includes features like endpoint listing, schema searching, and example retrieval. It''s particularly valuable for workflows requiring API exploration and understanding within AI assistant conversations, eliminating the need to manually parse OpenAPI documentation.', '@hannesj', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 47, 'https://github.com/hannesj/mcp-openapi-schema', 'mcp-openapi-schema', 2717, 'https://github.com/hannesj.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982812+00:00'),
  ('imessage-query', 'iMessage Query', 'This MCP server, developed by Hannes Rudolph, enables AI assistants to query and analyze iMessage conversations on macOS. Built with FastMCP and the imessagedb library, it provides read-only access to the iMessage database with robust safety features like phone number validation and attachment handling. The server exposes a ''get_chat_transcript'' tool that retrieves message history for specific contacts, including text, timestamps, and attachment info. By connecting AI capabilities with personal messaging data, this implementation allows AI systems to gain insights from conversation history while maintaining privacy and security. It is particularly useful for personal productivity use cases like summarizing past discussions, analyzing communication patterns, or extracting action items from chats.', '@hannesrudolph', 'databases', 'Unknown', 75, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph/imessage-query-fastmcp-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982825+00:00'),
  ('qdrant-docs-rag', 'Qdrant Docs Rag', 'This MCP server, developed by Hannes Rudolph, enables AI assistants to augment their responses with relevant documentation context through vector-based search and retrieval. Built as a fork of qpd-v''s original implementation, it integrates with OpenAI for embeddings generation and Qdrant for vector storage. The server provides tools for adding documentation from URLs, performing semantic searches, extracting links, and managing a processing queue. By connecting AI capabilities with efficient vector search of documentation, this implementation allows AI systems to enhance their knowledge with domain-specific information in real-time. It is particularly useful for building documentation-aware AI assistants, implementing semantic documentation search, and creating context-aware developer tools that require access to up-to-date technical information.', '@hannesrudolph', 'development', 'Unknown', 254, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph/mcp-ragdocs', '@hannesrudolph/mcp-ragdocs', 2136, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982866+00:00'),
  ('sqlite-explorer', 'SQLite Explorer', 'This MCP server, developed by Hannes Rudolph, provides safe read-only access to SQLite databases for AI assistants. Built with FastMCP, it exposes tools for executing validated SELECT queries, listing tables, and describing table schemas. The implementation stands out with its focus on security, featuring query sanitization, parameter binding, and row limit enforcement. By connecting AI capabilities with local SQLite data sources, this server enables AI systems to explore and analyze structured data while maintaining strict safety controls. It is particularly useful for scenarios requiring AI-assisted data exploration, report generation, or insights extraction from SQLite databases, without risking data integrity or exposing sensitive information.', '@hannesrudolph', 'databases', 'Unknown', 104, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph/sqlite-explorer-fastmcp-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hannesrudolph.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982879+00:00'),
  ('discord-full-api', 'Discord (Full API)', 'This Discord Raw API MCP server, developed by hanweg, provides a flexible interface for AI assistants to interact with Discord''s API. Built using Python and the discord.py library, it supports both REST API calls and slash command syntax, offering a unified approach to Discord bot development. The implementation stands out by abstracting Discord''s complex API structure into a more accessible format, allowing for easier integration with AI systems. By exposing Discord''s capabilities through standardized MCP endpoints, it enables AI assistants to perform a wide range of Discord operations, from message sending to role management. This server is particularly useful for scenarios requiring dynamic Discord bot behavior, such as moderation tools, custom command handlers, or AI-driven community management systems.', '@hanweg', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/hanweg/mcp-discord-raw', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hanweg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982938+00:00'),
  ('sql-server-express', 'SQL Server Express', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Microsoft SQL Server Express, enabling AI assistants to interact with SQL databases. Developed by hanweg, it offers tools for executing SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE queries, as well as creating tables and describing database schemas. The server supports both Windows and SQL Server authentication, with configurable database access restrictions. Built using Python and pyodbc, it''s designed for easy integration into Claude Desktop environments. The implementation focuses on secure database interactions and is particularly useful for AI applications requiring data analysis, reporting, or automated database management tasks within Microsoft SQL Server ecosystems.', '@hanweg', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/hanweg/mcp-sqlexpress', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hanweg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.982995+00:00'),
  ('tushare-chinese-financial-data', 'TuShare (Chinese Financial Data)', 'A Rust-based MCP server for TuShare financial data API, providing structured access to Chinese market data including stock listings, concept themes, money flow statistics, and minute-level price data. The implementation uses a custom derive macro system to handle API responses and includes models for various financial data types like limit-up stocks, concept lists, and trading statistics. The server supports multiple platforms through GitHub Actions workflows that build releases for macOS, Windows, and both x86_64 and ARM architectures.', '@hanxuanliang', 'development', 'Unknown', 28, 'https://github.com/hanxuanliang/tsrs-mcp-server', 'tsrs-mcp-server', 0, 'https://github.com/hanxuanliang.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.983020+00:00'),
  ('hanzo', 'Hanzo', 'Hanzo MCP enables AI assistants to interact with codebases through tools for file operations, command execution, project analysis, and Jupyter notebook management. Built with Python and FastMCP, it provides secure access to local files and commands through a permission system that validates paths and operations. The implementation is designed for developers who want to use Claude for code understanding, modification, and project management tasks while maintaining security through explicit path allowlisting and operation validation.', '@hanzoai', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/hanzoai/mcp', 'hanzo-mcp', 59545, 'https://github.com/hanzoai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.983043+00:00'),
  ('phone-control-android-adb', 'Phone Control (Android ADB)', 'Phone MCP is a Python-based server that enables AI assistants to control Android phones through ADB commands. Developed by hao, it provides tools for making calls, sending text messages, taking screenshots, recording screens, managing contacts, launching apps, and retrieving system information. The implementation includes specialized modules for different phone functionalities and supports map-related features when an API key is configured. It''s particularly useful for scenarios requiring remote phone control, automated testing, or accessibility assistance, allowing AI agents to interact with mobile devices without direct physical manipulation.', '@hao-cyber', 'development', 'Unknown', 211, 'https://github.com/hao-cyber/phone-mcp', 'phone-mcp', 12499, 'https://github.com/hao-cyber.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.983074+00:00'),
  ('latex-mathml', 'LaTeX MathML', 'A lightweight MCP server that converts LaTeX mathematical expressions to MathML using MathJax-node, providing both tool-based and resource-based conversion methods. Developed by happyan, this server enables easy integration of mathematical notation translation for developers and researchers working with scientific or technical documentation.', '@happyany', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/happyany/latex-mathml-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/happyany.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.983110+00:00');





By integrating with AI-powered IDEs through the MCP protocol, QA Sphere enhances the testing workflow by allowing developers and QA engineers to interact with their test cases using natural language. This integration bridges the gap between test management and development environments, enabling teams to work more efficiently and maintain better test coverage without switching contexts.
', '@hypersequent', 'development', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/hypersequent/qasphere-mcp', 'qasphere-mcp', 5225, 'https://github.com/hypersequent.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990780+00:00'),
  ('jina-web-search', 'Jina Web Search', 'Jina Web Search MCP server that provides web crawling and search capabilities through Jina AI''s API, offering two core tools: fetch_url_content for extracting clean text from any URL with JavaScript rendering and shadow DOM support, and web_search for performing semantic web searches optimized for AI consumption. Built by hypersniper05 using the official MCP Python SDK with FastMCP framework, the implementation features Docker deployment, streamable HTTP transport on port 5003, and integrates seamlessly with Claude Desktop through mcp install commands. Designed for AI applications that need reliable web content access and search functionality without handling complex crawling infrastructure, making it valuable for research workflows, content analysis, and knowledge gathering tasks that require both targeted URL extraction and broad web search capabilities.', '@hypersniper05', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/hypersniper05/jinawebsearchmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hypersniper05.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990808+00:00'),
  ('tauri', 'Tauri', 'Provides tools to interact with running Tauri desktop applications. Captures screenshots and inspects webview elements, executes JavaScript within the application, monitors console logs and IPC events, and runs Tauri CLI commands. Designed for development workflows to accelerate Tauri app development through AI-assisted debugging and automation.', '@hypothesi', 'development', 'Unknown', 98, 'https://github.com/hypothesi/mcp-server-tauri', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hypothesi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990827+00:00'),
  ('pdf-knowledge-base', 'PDF Knowledge Base', 'PDF RAG MCP Server is a knowledge base system that enables semantic search across PDF documents through vector storage and the Model Context Protocol. Built with FastAPI and React, it allows users to upload PDFs through a modern web interface where documents are automatically processed, chunked, and vectorized for intelligent querying. The system features real-time processing status updates via WebSockets, integration with AI tools like Cursor through MCP, and a responsive frontend built with Chakra UI. This implementation is particularly valuable for researchers, analysts, and developers who need to extract insights from multiple PDF documents without switching context from their AI assistant.', '@hyson666', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 40, 'https://github.com/hyson666/pdf-rag-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hyson666.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990889+00:00'),
  ('onecite', 'OneCite', 'OneCite automates academic citation management by parsing mixed-format references and outputting them in standard formats. It features fuzzy matching against multiple academic databases including CrossRef, Semantic Scholar, OpenAlex, PubMed, DBLP, arXiv, DataCite, Zenodo, and Google Books. The server provides tools for single and batch citation generation with automatic metadata completion and interactive disambiguation.', '@hzacode', 'databases', 'Unknown', 56, 'https://github.com/hzacode/onecite', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/hzacode.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990901+00:00'),
  ('flux-image-generator', 'Flux Image Generator', 'Flux-Cloudflare-MCP enables AI assistants to generate images through the Flux API running on Cloudflare Workers. Developed by Hzzy2O, this implementation provides a streamlined interface for text-to-image generation with customizable parameters including prompt, dimensions, aspect ratio, and inference steps. The server handles the entire workflow from API communication to image retrieval and optional local file saving, making it particularly valuable for creative workflows requiring image generation without leaving the conversation context.', '@duoduohe', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/duoduohe/flux-cloudfare-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/duoduohe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990923+00:00'),
  ('kali-linux', 'Kali Linux', 'This Kali Linux MCP server by Ethan Blair provides remote access to penetration testing and security assessment tools through a client-server architecture, with the server component running on a Kali Linux system and exposing security tools via Flask REST API endpoints. Built with Python and featuring a FastMCP client that communicates with the Kali server, it offers tools for network scanning (nmap), web directory enumeration (gobuster, dirb), vulnerability assessment (nikto, wpscan), SQL injection testing (sqlmap), password cracking (hydra, john), exploitation frameworks (metasploit), and system enumeration (enum4linux), plus arbitrary command execution capabilities. The implementation includes robust command execution with timeout handling, threading for real-time output capture, health monitoring for tool availability, and configurable request timeouts, making it valuable for security professionals conducting remote penetration tests, red team exercises, and security assessments where they need AI-assisted tool orchestration and centralized access to Kali Linux security utilities from non-Kali systems.', '@i3t4an', 'databases', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/i3t4an/kali_linux_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/i3t4an.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990936+00:00'),
  ('memento', 'Memento', 'This MCP server provides persistent memory capabilities for AI assistants through a SQLite-based knowledge graph that stores entities, observations, and relationships with both full-text search (FTS5) and semantic search (sqlite-vec) capabilities. Built using @xenova/transformers for embedding generation with the BGE-M3 model, it offers tools for creating and managing entities with typed relationships, adding text observations that are automatically indexed for search, and performing hybrid keyword/semantic queries across stored knowledge. The implementation uses SQLite''s vector extension for cosine similarity search, FTS5 for keyword matching, and provides CRUD operations for all graph components, making it valuable for AI assistants that need to maintain long-term memory of conversations, build knowledge bases from interactions, and retrieve relevant context through intelligent search across accumulated observations and entity relationships.', '@iachilles', 'databases', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/iachilles/memento', '@iachilles/memento', 2404, 'https://github.com/iachilles.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.990970+00:00'),
  ('readwise', 'Readwise', 'The Readwise MCP Server provides AI assistants with access to a user''s Readwise library, including saved articles, books, highlights, and documents. Built with Node.js using the Smithery framework, it implements a secure authentication flow for Readwise API tokens and offers endpoints for browsing books, accessing highlights, performing searches, and retrieving recent content. The implementation by Alexander Bastien features both npm package and Docker deployment options, making it ideal for users who want to reference their saved reading materials, analyze highlighted passages, or search across their knowledge collection during AI conversations.', '@iamalexander', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/iamalexander/readwise-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/iamalexander.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991020+00:00'),
  ('17track-package-tracking', '17TRACK Package Tracking', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with parcel tracking capabilities through the 17TRACK API, enabling package delivery monitoring across multiple carriers worldwide. Built by Cho Sungju using TypeScript with fuzzy search support via Fuse.js and CSV-based carrier data management, it offers two main tools: carrier search with typo tolerance for finding the correct shipping company by name, and delivery tracking that requires both tracking number and carrier ID for accurate results. The implementation includes a comprehensive carriers.csv database, automatic carrier name-to-ID mapping with multilingual support (English, Chinese, Hong Kong), and API integration that registers tracking numbers before retrieving delivery status, making it valuable for e-commerce workflows, customer service automation, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to global package tracking without manual lookup across different carrier websites.', '@iamfiro', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/iamfiro/parcel-tracking-mcp', 'parcel-mcp', 1411, 'https://github.com/iamfiro.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991036+00:00'),
  ('dida365-ticktick', 'Dida365 (TickTick)', 'Dida365 (TickTick) MCP Server provides tools for AI assistants to interact with the Dida365 task management API after user authorization. It enables managing tasks and projects through a set of MCP tools that handle authentication, project creation, and task operations (creating, updating, retrieving, and deleting tasks). The server is built with Node.js, packaged as a Docker container, and configured through Smithery.ai, making it ideal for workflows that require task management integration without leaving the conversation interface.', '@iamjzx', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/iamjzx/dida', 'my-mcp-server', 4459, 'https://github.com/iamjzx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991056+00:00'),
  ('cursor-rules', 'Cursor Rules', 'A server that enables AI assistants to interact with Playbooks Rules API, providing tools for listing, searching, and retrieving rules. The implementation handles API requests to fetch rules data, processes URL-based rule slugs, and formats responses into Cursor-compatible rule files with appropriate metadata and content. Built for integrating rule management capabilities into AI workflows, it''s particularly useful for developers who want to programmatically access and apply Playbooks rules through natural language interactions.', '@iannuttall', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/iannuttall/cursor-rules-mcp', 'cursor-rules-mcp', 7641, 'https://github.com/iannuttall.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991156+00:00'),
  ('iaptic', 'Iaptic', 'This MCP server for Iaptic, developed by Jean-Christophe Hoelt, provides a seamless interface for AI assistants to interact with Iaptic''s customer and transaction data. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for querying customers, purchases, transactions, and statistics. The implementation focuses on efficient data retrieval and pagination, making it easy for AI models to analyze customer behavior, track sales, and generate insights. It''s particularly useful for tasks like customer support automation, sales trend analysis, or integrating e-commerce data into AI-driven systems, allowing assistants to access Iaptic data without requiring deep knowledge of the underlying API complexities.', '@iaptic', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/iaptic/mcp-server-iaptic', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/iaptic.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991185+00:00'),
  ('io-github-sidneybissoli-ibge-br-mcp', 'io.github.SidneyBissoli/ibge-br-mcp', 'MCP Server for IBGE APIs - Localidades, SIDRA, Nomes, Malhas e Pesquisas', '@sidneybissoli', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/sidneybissoli/ibge-br-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/sidneybissoli.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991201+00:00'),
  ('io-github-expertvagabond-ibmcloud', 'io.github.ExpertVagabond/ibmcloud', 'IBM Cloud CLI MCP server', '@expertvagabond', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/expertvagabond/ibmcloud-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/expertvagabond.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991215+00:00'),
  ('ibm-content-services-filenet', 'IBM Content Services (FileNet)', 'Integrates with IBM FileNet Content Manager through the Content Services GraphQL API, providing comprehensive enterprise content management capabilities including document operations (create, update, delete, check-in/out), folder management and filing, metadata-driven search across repositories, class and property introspection, text extraction, and annotation handling. Features multiple authentication methods (basic auth, OAuth, ZenIAM), SSL/TLS configuration, metadata caching for performance optimization, and fuzzy matching algorithms for intelligent class discovery. Built with FastMCP using asyncio for concurrent operations, includes audit logging, connection pooling, and proper session management for enterprise-scale content repositories and automated filing workflows.', '@ibm-ecm', 'search', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/ibm-ecm/ibm-content-services-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ibm-ecm.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991283+00:00'),
  ('ibm-i', 'IBM i', 'IBM i MCP Server provides direct access to IBM i (AS/400) systems through SQL-based tools and database operations. Built by IBM using TypeScript and the MCP SDK, it offers both predefined YAML-configured tools for common system queries and dynamic SQL execution capabilities, with security validation to prevent destructive operations. The server supports multiple transport modes (stdio/HTTP), includes authentication strategies for IBM i token-based access, and provides specialized tools for system monitoring, performance analysis, and database exploration through Db2 for i services. Features include connection pooling, parameter validation, toolset organization for different operational contexts, and extensive logging with request tracing, making it valuable for system administrators, developers, and analysts who need to query and monitor IBM i systems through natural language interactions while maintaining enterprise-grade security and performance.', '@ibm', 'databases', 'Unknown', 43, 'https://github.com/ibm/ibmi-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ibm.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991295+00:00'),
  ('charly-memory-cache', 'Charly Memory Cache', 'This memory cache server, developed for the Model Context Protocol (MCP), optimizes token consumption in AI interactions by efficiently caching data between language model queries. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the MCP SDK, it provides an in-memory storage system with features like LRU eviction, TTL management, and memory usage tracking. The implementation stands out by offering automatic caching of file contents, computation results, and frequently accessed data, reducing the need for repeated token-heavy operations. By integrating seamlessly with any MCP client and language model, this server enables significant performance improvements and cost savings in scenarios involving repetitive data access or computations, making it particularly valuable for applications in data analysis, file processing, and AI-assisted development workflows.', '@ibproduct', 'development', 'Unknown', 22, 'https://github.com/ibproduct/ib-mcp-cache-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ibproduct.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991328+00:00'),
  ('ibrahim-s-calendar-google-calendar', 'Ibrahim''s Calendar (Google Calendar)', 'Ibrahim''s Calendar MCP server provides Google Calendar integration alongside basic utility tools for AI assistants. The server exposes three main capabilities: an addition tool for simple arithmetic, a dynamic greeting resource generator, and most notably a calendar tool that retrieves events from a specified Google Calendar by date using the Google Calendar API v3. Built as a personal project by Ibrahim Sajib, it demonstrates how to combine multiple tool types in a single MCP server, making it useful for calendar-aware AI workflows where assistants need to check scheduling availability or retrieve meeting information for specific dates.', '@ibrahim-sajib', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/ibrahim-sajib/my-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ibrahim-sajib.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.991371+00:00');

- portfolio_tools manages investment creation and updates
- stock_tools handles market data retrieval
- analysis_tools generates insights and recommendations
- visualization_tools creates graphical representations of portfolio allocations

The data layer uses JSON-based storage with a well-defined schema for portfolio data, while our transport layer implements robust error handling with automatic retry mechanisms and graceful shutdown procedures. We followed REST-like design principles for our resource URIs (e.g., "portfolio://{user_id}") and implemented asynchronous operations for external API calls to ensure responsive performance even during intensive operations like market data retrieval or report generation.', '@ikhyunan', 'communication', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/ikhyunan/mcp_investmentportfolio', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ikhyunan.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992610+00:00'),
  ('netbrain', 'NetBrain', 'NetBrain MCP is a network device management server that connects AI assistants to network infrastructure through SSH, Telnet, and SNMP protocols. Built by Koreyoshi using FastAPI and the FastMCP framework, it provides over 30 tools for network scanning, device discovery, topology mapping with CDP/LLDP, configuration management, and real-time monitoring. The implementation features a template-based command system for vendor-specific operations across Cisco, Huawei, and H3C equipment, along with credential management and device connection handling. It includes a web-based interface with XTerm.js terminal emulation and D3.js topology visualization, making it valuable for network automation, infrastructure monitoring, and AI-assisted network troubleshooting workflows.', '@ikoreyoshii', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/ikoreyoshii/netbrain_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ikoreyoshii.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992657+00:00'),
  ('redmine', 'Redmine', 'This MCP server implementation provides integration with Redmine, allowing AI assistants to interact with Redmine projects and issues. Developed by ilask, it offers tools for accessing project details and creating new issues through a custom API built on top of the node-redmine library. The server is designed to work with the Cline VS Code extension, making it particularly useful for developers who want to incorporate Redmine project management capabilities into their AI-assisted workflows.', '@ilask', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/ilask/redmine-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ilask.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992682+00:00'),
  ('ilert', 'ilert', 'Official ilert MCP server that provides AI assistants with direct access to alerting and incident management resources through the ilert platform. Built by ilert GmbH, the implementation uses a remote Streamable HTTP transport architecture hosted at mcp.ilert.com, requiring only an ilert API key for authentication rather than local installation. Designed for DevOps teams and incident responders who want conversational access to their alerting workflows, incident data, and on-call management through AI assistants like Claude, Cline, Cursor, and Windsurf.', '@ilert', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/ilert/mcp-ilert', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ilert.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992725+00:00'),
  ('groundng-qa-for-cursor', 'GroundNG (QA for Cursor)', 'Makes sure you only test finished products from cursor. This tool allows your AI coding assistant like cursor/roo code to:  Record new tests, test in regression and discover new test flows using natural interaction.', '@groundng', 'development', 'Unknown', 66, 'https://github.com/groundng/vibeshift', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/groundng.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992745+00:00'),
  ('clickfunnels', 'ClickFunnels', 'ClickFunnels MCP Framework provides a server implementation that integrates Claude Desktop with ClickFunnels marketing platform API. It offers tools for listing and retrieving funnels, managing contacts, and debugging API connections. Built with TypeScript and the mcp-framework package, it features a modular architecture where each API endpoint is implemented as a separate tool. The server handles environment configuration through dotenv, includes comprehensive error handling for API requests, and is designed to be easily deployed through Claude Desktop''s configuration system, making it valuable for marketers who need to access and analyze their ClickFunnels data directly within conversations.', '@illgatesmusic', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/illgatesmusic/click-funnels-mcp-shared', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/illgatesmusic.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992774+00:00'),
  ('llmbasedos', 'LLMBasedOS', 'LLMBasedOS is a minimal Arch Linux distribution that creates a secure bridge between LLMs and local system capabilities through a standardized protocol. Built around a central gateway that routes requests to specialized servers (file system, email, sync, and agent), it features a Python-based shell for interactive command execution. The architecture uses UNIX domain sockets for inter-component communication, implements robust path validation to prevent arbitrary file access, and provides tiered licensing with rate limiting and capability restrictions. This implementation is particularly valuable for users who need controlled, secure access to their personal data and tools from various LLM frontends without exposing sensitive information directly to the models.', '@iluxu', 'communication', 'Unknown', 283, 'https://github.com/iluxu/llmbasedos', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/iluxu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992869+00:00'),
  ('gradle', 'Gradle', 'Gradle MCP server enables AI tools to interact with Gradle projects through a standardized interface built on the Gradle Tooling API. It exposes tools for retrieving project metadata and executing Gradle tasks remotely, with support for both stdio and SSE transport modes. Particularly valuable for developers who want to automate Gradle project management and builds through conversational AI without manual configuration.', '@ilyagulya', 'development', 'Unknown', 44, 'https://github.com/ilyagulya/gradle-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ilyagulya.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992892+00:00'),
  ('academia', 'Academia', 'Academia MCP is a research-focused server built by Ilya Gusev that provides comprehensive tools for scientific literature discovery, analysis, and reporting. It integrates with ArXiv, ACL Anthology, Semantic Scholar, Hugging Face datasets, and multiple web search providers (Exa, Brave, Tavily) to enable paper search, citation analysis, and reference tracking. The server includes LaTeX compilation capabilities, PDF processing, and optional LLM-powered features for document Q&A, paper review generation, and research proposal workflows using the "bitflip" methodology. It supports both HTTP and stdio transports with configurable tool availability based on API keys, making it useful for literature reviews, academic research workflows, citation analysis, and automated paper evaluation tasks.', '@ilyagusev', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 67, 'https://github.com/ilyagusev/academia_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/ilyagusev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992943+00:00'),
  ('serpapi-google-search', 'SerpApi Google Search', 'This MCP server implementation integrates with the SerpApi Google Search API, enabling access to structured search results data. It is designed to be used with the MCP CLI tool and requires a SerpApi API key for authentication. The server can be useful for applications that need to programmatically access and analyze Google search results, such as SEO tools, market research platforms, or data aggregation services.', '@serpapi', 'search', 'Unknown', 108, 'https://github.com/serpapi/serpapi-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/serpapi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.992985+00:00'),
  ('feishu-project', 'Feishu Project', 'Feishu Project MCP Service provides a bridge between AI assistants and Feishu (ByteDance''s project management platform), enabling automated requirement management and development workflows. The server exposes tools for retrieving projects, requirements, and bugs from Feishu, as well as creating and managing tasks based on these items. Built with TypeScript and Express, it features a robust task management system, health monitoring endpoints, and Docker support for easy deployment. Particularly valuable for development teams using Feishu who want to automate analysis of requirements, bug tracking, and code implementation tasks without switching contexts.', '@im47cn', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/im47cn/feishu-project-mcp', 'feishu-project-mcp', 701, 'https://github.com/im47cn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993009+00:00'),
  ('io-github-oguntolaibrahim-image-viewer', 'io.github.OguntolaIbrahim/image-viewer', 'InChat Image Viewer MCP - View images inline in AI chat by just providing the file path', '@oguntolaibrahim', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/oguntolaibrahim/inchat-image-viewer-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/oguntolaibrahim.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993024+00:00'),
  ('dynamodb', 'DynamoDB', 'This DynamoDB MCP server, developed by Iman Kamyabi, provides a comprehensive interface for managing Amazon DynamoDB resources through the Model Context Protocol. It offers tools for table management, capacity adjustment, and data operations, enabling AI assistants to interact with DynamoDB using natural language commands. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the AWS SDK, this implementation stands out by offering a wide range of DynamoDB-specific operations while maintaining safeguards against accidental data deletion. It''s particularly useful for developers and database administrators who want to streamline their DynamoDB workflows, automate routine tasks, or integrate AI-assisted database management into their existing tools.', '@imankamyabi', 'databases', 'Unknown', 15, 'https://github.com/imankamyabi/dynamodb-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/imankamyabi.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993035+00:00'),
  ('io-github-cyberpapiii-imessage-max', 'io.github.cyberpapiii/imessage-max', 'AI-optimized MCP server for iMessage on macOS. Read, search, and send messages.', '@cyberpapiii', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/cyberpapiii/imessage-max', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/cyberpapiii.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993060+00:00'),
  ('strands-agents', 'Strands Agents', 'Strands Agent MCP is a server that enables the execution of Strands agents through a plugin architecture. Developed by Nacho Garay, it provides a bridge between the Strands agent framework and MCP-compatible systems like Amazon Q. The server automatically discovers and registers plugins that follow a specific naming convention, allowing users to add new agents without modifying core code. It features tools for executing agents with custom prompts and listing available agents, making it particularly valuable for organizations looking to integrate AI agents with their existing workflows while maintaining a clean separation between agent implementation and execution.', '@imgaray', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/imgaray/strands-agents-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/imgaray.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993088+00:00'),
  ('azure-devops-project-creator', 'Azure DevOps Project Creator', 'This Azure DevOps MCP server enables AI assistants to programmatically manage Azure DevOps projects through a FastAPI implementation. Built with the FastMCP framework, it provides a tool for creating new projects in Azure DevOps organizations by authenticating with personal access tokens stored in environment variables. The implementation handles checking if projects already exist, creates projects with default Git version control settings, and monitors operation status until completion. It''s particularly useful for automating DevOps infrastructure setup directly from AI assistant conversations without requiring manual Azure portal interaction.', '@taslim1743', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/taslim1743/mcp-server-sandbox', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/taslim1743.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993110+00:00'),
  ('imgmcp', 'ImgMCP', 'ImgMCP provides a unified MCP server for accessing diverse multimedia AI models from providers like OpenAI, Stability AI, and Replicate through a single interface, enabling seamless creation of images, audio, and video content. Built with a pay-as-you-use credit system and supporting both hosted API access and bring-your-own-key (BYOK) configurations, it includes curated ''Styles'' (expert prompts), workflow automation features like background removal, and concurrent processing with intelligent retry mechanisms. The platform is designed for creators, developers, and teams who need streamlined access to multiple AI model providers without managing separate integrations, making it valuable for creative workflows, content generation pipelines, and AI-assisted multimedia production.', '@imgmcp', 'communication', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/imgmcp/imgmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/imgmcp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.993151+00:00');





The core concepts in foreverVM are machines and instructions.

Machines represent a stateful Python process. You interact with a machine by running instructions (Python statements and expressions) on it, and receiving the results. A machine processes one instruction at a time.', '@jamsocket', 'development', 'Unknown', 228, 'https://github.com/jamsocket/forevervm/tree/HEAD/javascript/mcp-server', 'forevervm-mcp', 1936, 'https://github.com/jamsocket.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999346+00:00'),
  ('trainingpeaks', 'TrainingPeaks', 'Provides secure access to TrainingPeaks training data through cookie-based authentication. Offers tools for retrieving workout details, personal records, fitness metrics (CTL/ATL/TSB), and athlete profiles. Implements dual credential storage using system keyring with encrypted file fallback for cross-application authentication. Focuses on endurance sports analytics including training load analysis, performance tracking, and workout planning for cyclists, runners, and triathletes.', '@jamsusmaximus', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/jamsusmaximus/trainingpeaks-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jamsusmaximus.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999387+00:00'),
  ('skill-vision-control', 'Skill Vision Control', 'Provides safe version management for MCP skills, enabling automatic update detection, intelligent three-way merging of custom changes with official updates, and parallel testing environments to maintain current skills without losing modifications.', '@jane-xiaoer', 'development', 'Unknown', 61, 'https://github.com/jane-xiaoer/skill-vision-control', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jane-xiaoer.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999440+00:00'),
  ('fibaro-home-center-3', 'Fibaro Home Center 3', 'VS Code extension and MCP server implementation by jangabrielsson that provides AI assistants with complete access to Fibaro Home Center 3 smart home systems through 66+ REST API tools covering device control, scene management, energy monitoring, climate zones, alarm systems, and QuickApp development. The implementation includes both a VS Code extension for configuration management and a standalone MCP server that communicates via stdio, supporting comprehensive HC3 operations from basic device control (lights, sensors, dimmers) to advanced features like sprinkler systems, backup management, and plugin lifecycle control. Built with TypeScript and designed for smart home automation enthusiasts, the server includes intelligent context tools for automation suggestions, device relationship analysis, and built-in HC3 programming documentation, making it valuable for users who want conversational control over their Fibaro systems and developers building HC3 QuickApps with AI assistance.', '@jangabrielsson', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/jangabrielsson/hc3_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jangabrielsson.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999475+00:00'),
  ('needle', 'Needle', 'This Needle MCP integration, developed by Jan Heimes, provides a bridge between the Needle AI platform and MCP (Machine Comprehension Protocol) servers. Built using Python, it leverages the needle-python and mcp libraries to enable seamless communication between Needle''s AI capabilities and standardized MCP endpoints. The integration supports environment variable configuration via python-dotenv for flexible deployment. By abstracting the complexities of API interactions, it allows developers to easily incorporate Needle''s AI functionalities into MCP-compatible systems. This implementation is particularly useful for projects requiring advanced natural language processing, machine learning, or AI-driven decision making within an MCP framework, enabling use cases such as intelligent chatbots, automated content generation, or AI-assisted data analysis.', '@needle-ai', 'communication', 'Unknown', 96, 'https://github.com/needle-ai/needle-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/needle-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999543+00:00'),
  ('tigerbeetle', 'TigerBeetle', 'A Model Context Protocol server providing TigerBeetle account management capabilities for AI assistants. Built with Spring Boot, it enables creating and configuring TigerBeetle accounts with detailed parameters through a simple interface. The server integrates directly with Claude desktop through a stdio-based connection, making it valuable for financial applications that need to interact with TigerBeetle''s high-performance accounting database without leaving the conversation interface.', '@jantoniucci', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/jantoniucci/mcp-tiggerbeetle', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jantoniucci.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999554+00:00'),
  ('vsegpt-image-generator', 'VseGPT Image Generator', 'This MCP server implementation provides image generation capabilities through the VseGPT API. It offers a single tool function that accepts English-language prompts and returns local file paths to the generated images. The server handles API authentication, makes requests to the VseGPT image generation endpoint, processes the base64-encoded response, and saves the resulting image to a local directory with a timestamp-based filename. Environment variables control the API key, model ID, and image size settings, making it flexible for different deployment scenarios. Ideal for applications needing AI-generated imagery with local storage of results.', '@janvarev', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/janvarev/mcp-vsepgt-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/janvarev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999583+00:00'),
  ('image-generation-cloudflare', 'Image Generation (Cloudflare)', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Cloudflare''s AI image generation capabilities. Developed by Jan Wilmake, it leverages Cloudflare Workers for serverless deployment and utilizes the workers-mcp package for MCP compatibility. The implementation is designed to be lightweight and efficient, focusing on image generation tasks. It''s particularly useful for AI applications that require on-demand image creation, such as content generation tools or visual design assistants. The server uses TypeScript and is configured for easy deployment and development using Wrangler, Cloudflare''s command-line tool for Workers.', '@janwilmake', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/janwilmake/image-generation-mcp-cloudflare', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/janwilmake.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999604+00:00'),
  ('uithub', 'UIThub', 'UIThub MCP Server enables Claude to fetch and analyze GitHub repositories through the UIThub API. It provides a tool for retrieving repository contents with flexible filtering options by file extension, directory, size limits, and token constraints. The implementation handles GitHub authentication via personal access tokens and integrates seamlessly with Claude Desktop through a simple configuration process, making it particularly useful for code analysis, repository exploration, and development assistance tasks.', '@janwilmake', 'development', 'Unknown', 20, 'https://github.com/janwilmake/uithub-mcp', 'uithub-mcp', 1062, 'https://github.com/janwilmake.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999629+00:00'),
  ('japanese-text-analyzer', 'Japanese Text Analyzer', 'A server that provides Japanese text analysis capabilities through morphological parsing using the Kuromoji library. It enables AI assistants to break down Japanese sentences into their component parts, identifying words, their grammatical functions, readings, and base forms. This implementation makes it possible to analyze complex Japanese text structures programmatically through the MCP protocol, making it valuable for language learning applications, translation tools, and natural language processing tasks that require detailed understanding of Japanese grammar and vocabulary.', '@mistizz', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mistizz/mcp-japanesetextanalyzer', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mistizz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999711+00:00'),
  ('vibe-worldbuilding', 'Vibe Worldbuilding', 'Vibe Worldbuilding MCP provides a structured approach to creating detailed fictional worlds with Claude, complete with automatic image generation capabilities. The implementation guides users through a systematic worldbuilding process—from establishing core concepts to developing taxonomies and detailed entries—while maintaining consistency throughout. Built with Python and integrating Google''s Imagen API, it enables users to generate visual representations of their world elements directly from markdown files. The server includes specialized prompts for different worldbuilding stages and offers tools for consistency management, making it ideal for writers, game designers, and worldbuilding enthusiasts who want to develop rich, cohesive fictional universes.', '@jasnonaz', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/jasnonaz/vibe-worldbuilding-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasnonaz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999781+00:00'),
  ('campus-assistant', 'Campus Assistant', 'Campus Assistant is a comprehensive educational management MCP server built with Python and FastAPI that provides AI agents with direct access to school administration systems including student enrollment, grade management, messaging, and scheduling. The implementation integrates with MySQL databases to manage multi-school environments with class instances, parent-student relationships, memo reminders, notice broadcasting, and real-time messaging queues. It features role-based access control for students, teachers, parents, and administrators, automated daily quote delivery, open window scheduling for communication availability, and outgoing message queuing with priority handling.', '@jason76789', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/jason76789/campus-assistant', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jason76789.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999793+00:00'),
  ('connectwise-manage-api', 'ConnectWise Manage API', 'ConnectWise API Gateway MCP Server provides a bridge between Claude and the ConnectWise Manage API, enabling efficient API discovery and execution through a SQLite database built from the ConnectWise API definition. Developed by Jason Smith, it features natural language search capabilities, categorized API navigation, and a Fast Memory system that saves frequently used queries for quick retrieval. The server supports both simplified parameter handling and raw API access, making it valuable for IT professionals who need to interact with ConnectWise Manage for service ticket management, company information retrieval, and other ConnectWise operations directly within Claude conversations.', '@jasondsmith72', 'databases', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/jasondsmith72/cwm-api-gateway-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasondsmith72.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999804+00:00'),
  ('vscode-debugger', 'VSCode Debugger', 'This MCP server and VS Code extension, created by Jason McGhee during a 2-hour hackathon, enables AI models like Claude to interactively debug code and evaluate expressions. Built as a language-agnostic tool, it integrates with VS Code''s debugging capabilities and launch configurations. The implementation allows AI assistants to set breakpoints, step through code, and inspect variables in real-time, providing a unique approach to AI-assisted debugging. It''s particularly useful for developers seeking AI guidance in troubleshooting complex code issues, understanding program flow, or learning debugging techniques, without requiring the AI to have direct access to the development environment.', '@jasonjmcghee', 'development', 'Unknown', 492, 'https://github.com/jasonjmcghee/claude-debugs-for-you', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasonjmcghee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999830+00:00'),
  ('webmcp', 'WebMCP', 'WebMCP is a browser extension that implements the Model Context Protocol (MCP) to enable web browsing capabilities for AI assistants. It allows AI models to browse the web, take screenshots, and interact with web content through a secure interface.', '@jasonjmcghee', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 558, 'https://github.com/jasonjmcghee/webmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasonjmcghee.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999867+00:00'),
  ('cloudera-ai-agent-studio', 'Cloudera AI Agent Studio', 'Cloudera AI Agent Studio MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and Cloudera''s Agent Studio platform, enabling programmatic creation and management of AI workflows and agents. Built with Python using the FastMCP framework, it exposes tools for listing, creating, and configuring workflows, adding manager and specialized agents to workflows, and enabling conversational capabilities. The server communicates with the Agent Studio API using environment-configured credentials, handling the complex backend interactions required to set up multi-agent systems with hierarchical management structures. It''s particularly valuable for developers who want to automate the creation of sophisticated agent-based workflows in Cloudera environments without navigating the underlying API complexity.', '@jasonmeverett', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/jasonmeverett/cloudera-ai-agent-studio-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasonmeverett.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999919+00:00'),
  ('albacore', 'Albacore', 'A lightweight MCP server built with TypeScript and Ollama, providing a flexible framework for AI-powered tools, resources, and prompts. Integrates local text generation and embedding services, with optional Supabase database support, enabling developers to quickly prototype and deploy context-aware AI assistants with modular, extensible components for tasks like search, retrieval, and generative interactions.', '@jsmiff', 'databases', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/jsmiff/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jsmiff.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999936+00:00'),
  ('railway', 'Railway', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Railway.app, enabling AI assistants to interact with Railway''s platform services. Developed by Jason Tan, it utilizes TypeScript and integrates with the Model Context Protocol SDK. The server is designed for use cases requiring Railway.app integration, such as managing deployments, monitoring application performance, or automating DevOps workflows within the Railway ecosystem.', '@jason-tan-swe', 'development', 'Unknown', 70, 'https://github.com/jason-tan-swe/railway-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jason-tan-swe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:01.999983+00:00'),
  ('cloud-regions', 'Cloud Regions', 'An MCP server providing comprehensive cloud region data across 14 major providers including AWS, Azure, GCP, Oracle Cloud, DigitalOcean, Linode, Vultr, and specialized providers like Crusoe, CoreWeave, and Lambda Labs. Covers 267 regions with tools for discovery and filtering by provider, country, compliance certifications (HIPAA, GDPR), GPU availability, and carbon neutrality. Includes geospatial capabilities for finding nearby regions by coordinates, listing countries and cities with cloud presence, and distance-based optimization. Enables multi-provider coverage comparison for infrastructure planning.', '@jasonwilbur', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/jasonwilbur/mcp-server-cloud-regions', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasonwilbur.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02+00:00'),
  ('anki-cards-clanki', 'Anki Cards (Clanki)', 'Integrates with Anki flashcards to provide card creation and deck management capabilities.', '@jasperket', 'development', 'Unknown', 27, 'https://github.com/jasperket/clanki', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jasperket.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000037+00:00'),
  ('meigen-ai-design', 'MeiGen AI Design', 'Provides tools for AI-powered image generation that route across local ComfyUI installations, OpenAI-compatible APIs, and MeiGen Cloud. Includes a curated library of prompt templates, prompt enhancement capabilities, reference image uploading, and multi-direction parallel generation workflows. Supports gallery search for creative inspiration and ComfyUI workflow management.', '@jau123', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 315, 'https://github.com/jau123/meigen-ai-design-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jau123.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000071+00:00'),
  ('java-debug-adapter-protocol', 'Java Debug Adapter Protocol', 'MCP server that bridges AI assistants with Java debugging capabilities through the Debug Adapter Protocol (DAP), enabling remote debugging of Java applications by providing tools to attach to debug sessions, inspect thread states, examine stack traces and variable scopes, evaluate expressions in debugging contexts, and control execution flow. Built with Quarkus and Java 21, the implementation acts as a protocol translator between MCP''s tool-based interface and DAP''s debugging commands, allowing AI assistants to perform interactive debugging tasks like analyzing application state, inspecting variables, and stepping through code execution. Designed for developers who want AI assistance with debugging Java applications, troubleshooting runtime issues, and performing automated debugging workflows where programmatic access to debugging capabilities enhances the development process.', '@igorrhamon', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/igorrhamon/mcp_debugger', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/igorrhamon.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000105+00:00'),
  ('zoom', 'Zoom', 'A Zoom MCP server that enables AI assistants to create and manage Zoom meetings. Developed by Bill Lau, this TypeScript implementation authenticates with the Zoom API using server-to-server OAuth and provides tools for creating meetings with customizable settings and listing scheduled meetings. The server requires Zoom account credentials (Account ID, Client ID, and Client Secret) and can be deployed as a standalone application or within a Docker container. Ideal for use cases where AI assistants need to schedule video conferences or manage meeting calendars on behalf of users.', '@javaprogrammerlb', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 14, 'https://github.com/javaprogrammerlb/zoom-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/javaprogrammerlb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000196+00:00'),
  ('tidymodels', 'Tidymodels', 'The Tidymodels MCP Server provides tools for working with the tidymodels ecosystem in R, enabling AI assistants to access GitHub repositories under the tidymodels organization. Built by Javier Orraca-Deatcu, it offers five key tools: listing packages, retrieving package details, searching R functions, generating template code for common tasks, and searching issues in repositories. The server integrates with GitHub''s API to fetch real-time data while implementing caching for performance, and is designed to work with Cline.bot and Claude Desktop as a local MCP server for data science and machine learning workflows in R.', '@javorraca', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/javorraca/tidymodels-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/javorraca.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000242+00:00'),
  ('optimizely-dxp', 'Optimizely DXP', 'Jaxon Digital''s MCP server for Optimizely DXP deployment operations, built by an Optimizely Gold Partner using PowerShell integration and the official MCP SDK. The implementation provides comprehensive deployment management including environment-to-environment deployments with smart defaults (upward deployments default to code, downward to content), database export/import operations, storage container management, package deployment workflows, and edge log retrieval. Features intelligent deployment validation that prevents invalid deployment paths, supports both Commerce and CMS projects with configurable source apps, and includes detailed status monitoring with user-friendly formatting and actionable next steps, making it valuable for DevOps teams managing Optimizely DXP environments who need AI-assisted deployment workflows with proper guardrails and enterprise-grade functionality.', '@jaxondigital', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/jaxondigital/optimizely-dxp-mcp', 'jaxon-optimizely-dxp-mcp', 9520, 'https://github.com/jaxondigital.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000298+00:00'),
  ('goose-extensions', 'Goose Extensions', 'Goose MCP is a collection of MCP servers designed to extend the capabilities of the Goose AI assistant. It includes five specialized servers: mcp_plex for interacting with Plex Media Server, mcp_rt for scraping movie information from Rotten Tomatoes, mcp_sales_history for fetching eBay sales data, mcp_searxng_search for web searches via SearxNG instances, and mcp_taskwarrior for task management. Each server is built using FastMCP, requires Python 3.10+ with UV package management, and is designed to be easily integrated into Goose through its extension system, enabling users to access external services and data sources directly within their AI assistant conversations.', '@jay4242', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 13, 'https://github.com/jay4242/goose_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jay4242.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000345+00:00'),
  ('searxng-search', 'SearxNG Search', 'MCP SearxNG Search provides a server that enables AI assistants to perform web searches through a SearxNG instance. Built with FastMCP, it exposes a single tool that queries a user-specified SearxNG server and returns structured search results containing titles, URLs, and content snippets. The implementation requires only setting a SearxNG base URL environment variable and is designed for easy integration with Goose via StandardIO extensions, making it valuable for workflows requiring private or customized web search capabilities without leaving the conversation interface.', '@jay4242', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/jay4242/mcp_searxng_search', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jay4242.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000388+00:00'),
  ('osrs-wiki', 'OSRS Wiki', 'MCP OSRS Server provides tools for interacting with the Old School RuneScape Wiki API and game data files. Built with TypeScript by JayArrowz, it exposes 19 different tools including wiki search capabilities and specialized methods for querying various game definition files like items, NPCs, locations, and player variables. The server handles both API requests to the OSRS Wiki and local file searches with pagination support, making it valuable for players and developers who need to access structured game information without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@jayarrowz', 'development', 'Unknown', 19, 'https://github.com/jayarrowz/mcp-osrs', '@jayarrowz/mcp-osrs', 4242, 'https://github.com/jayarrowz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000462+00:00'),
  ('xpath', 'XPath', 'XPath MCP Server enables Claude to execute XPath queries on XML and HTML content, supporting both direct content parsing and web scraping capabilities. Built by JayArrowz, it provides two main tools: ''xpath'' for querying XML strings directly and ''xpathwithurl'' for fetching and querying content from URLs using Puppeteer. The implementation handles various node types and error cases gracefully, making it valuable for data extraction workflows that require structured information from XML documents or web pages without leaving the conversation interface.', '@thirdstrandstudio', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/thirdstrandstudio/mcp-xpath', '@jayarrowz/mcp-xpath', 3803, 'https://github.com/thirdstrandstudio.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000505+00:00'),
  ('api2mcptools', 'API2MCPTools', 'API2MCPTools is a Node.js-based server that converts JSON API definitions into Model Context Protocol tools, enabling AI assistants to interact with external APIs through a standardized interface. Developed by JayLi52, this implementation uses TypeScript and the MCP SDK to dynamically load and manage tool definitions from a tools.json file, making it easy to add new API integrations without modifying the core codebase. The server includes a setup script for Claude desktop integration and supports both direct execution and containerized deployment via Docker, making it ideal for developers who want to quickly expose existing APIs to AI assistants without building custom MCP servers for each one.', '@jayli52', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/jayli52/api2mcptools', '@terryliyongjie/api2mcptools', 418, 'https://github.com/jayli52.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000527+00:00'),
  ('outscraper', 'Outscraper', 'This MCP server provides access to Outscraper''s data extraction services for Google Maps, Google Search, Google News, Google Play Store, and domain contact information through eight specialized tools. Created by Jay Ozer and built with Python using the FastMCP framework, it requires an Outscraper API key and offers capabilities including business search with enrichment data, review extraction with filtering options, photo retrieval, directions planning, web and news search, app store review analysis, and email/contact discovery from domains. The implementation formats all responses for readability and supports various parameters like language selection, result limits, sorting options, and regional filtering, making it valuable for market research, competitor analysis, lead generation, and business intelligence workflows.', '@jayozer', 'communication', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/jayozer/outscraper-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jayozer.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000592+00:00'),
  ('ghidramcp', 'GhidraMCP', 'Bridges Ghidra reverse engineering platform with natural language queries through socket-based architecture, enabling function decompilation, memory mapping, string extraction, import/export analysis, and security-focused identification of cryptographic patterns and vulnerabilities for malware analysis and binary research', '@jayvps', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/jayvps/ghidramcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jayvps.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000625+00:00'),
  ('next-js-api-scanner', 'Next.js API Scanner', 'Next.js MCP server enables AI assistants to analyze and understand Next.js applications by extracting API route information, validation schemas, and type definitions. Built by jazelly, it scans project directories to discover route handlers, parameters, status codes and response types, providing structured insights about the application''s API surface. Particularly valuable for developers who want AI assistants to help with Next.js API development, documentation, and testing without manually documenting endpoint details.', '@vertile-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 99, 'https://github.com/vertile-ai/next-mcp-server', 'next-mcp-server', 3068, 'https://github.com/vertile-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000674+00:00'),
  ('document-reader', 'Document Reader', 'MCP Document Reader is a server that enables AI assistants to interact with PDF and EPUB documents. Developed by Jerome Boisvert-Chouinard, this implementation provides a solution for users of Windsurf IDE by Codeium, which only supports MCP tools rather than resources. The server allows for reading and analyzing document content, making it useful for research tasks, content extraction, and document analysis workflows where AI assistants need direct access to document files.', '@jbchouinard', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/jbchouinard/mcp-document-reader', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jbchouinard.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000696+00:00'),
  ('cursor-db-explorer', 'Cursor DB Explorer', 'The Cursor DB MCP server provides AI assistants with access to Cursor IDE''s SQLite databases, enabling exploration of project data, chat history, and composer information. It automatically detects Cursor installations across operating systems, scans for project databases, and exposes them through a structured API of resources and tools. The implementation includes features for listing projects, retrieving chat history, accessing composer data, and executing custom queries against database tables, making it valuable for users who want to analyze their Cursor usage patterns or extract information from their development environment.', '@jbdamask', 'databases', 'Unknown', 24, 'https://github.com/jbdamask/cursor-db-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jbdamask.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000707+00:00'),
  ('the-guardian', 'The Guardian', 'This MCP server provides comprehensive access to The Guardian newspaper''s content through their Open Platform API, enabling AI assistants to search articles, retrieve full content, browse sections, and perform advanced analytical operations like author profiling and topic trend analysis. Built by Joshua Benton using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK and Zod for validation, it offers 17 specialized tools including Long Read discovery, related article finding through tag similarity, content timeline analysis, and intelligent story ranking by editorial prioritization. The implementation features flexible search capabilities with date ranges and section filtering, full article content retrieval with URL parsing, performance optimization through configurable detail levels, and robust error handling with rate limiting awareness, making it valuable for journalism research, content analysis workflows, news monitoring applications, and building AI assistants that need programmatic access to high-quality news content without manual Guardian website navigation.', '@jbenton', 'development', 'Unknown', 19, 'https://github.com/jbenton/guardian-mcp-server', 'guardian-mcp-server', 3857, 'https://github.com/jbenton.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000746+00:00'),
  ('pure-storage-flashblade', 'Pure Storage FlashBlade', 'This Pure Storage MCP server, developed by JB Thomas, enables AI assistants to interact with Pure Storage FlashBlade arrays. Built using Python and the Model Context Protocol, it provides a modular tool for retrieving real-time information about array components, volumes, and hosts. The implementation focuses on simplifying complex storage management tasks by offering a natural language interface to FlashBlade operations. It''s particularly useful for storage administrators and DevOps teams who want to streamline Pure Storage FlashBlade management, enabling efficient monitoring, troubleshooting, and resource allocation through AI-assisted workflows without requiring deep knowledge of Pure Storage APIs or command structures.', '@jboothomas', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/jboothomas/pure-model-context-protocol', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jboothomas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000791+00:00'),
  ('image-generator-openai', 'Image Generator (OpenAI)', 'The mcp-asset-gen server enables AI assistants to generate images through OpenAI''s image generation API. Built by jbrower95, this TypeScript implementation exposes a single tool that accepts a text prompt, quality setting, and image size parameters, then returns the generated image saved to a specified file path. The server requires an OpenAI API key set as an environment variable and uses the Model Context Protocol to provide a standardized interface for image generation requests. It''s particularly useful for workflows that need to create visual assets on demand without requiring users to switch contexts or manually interact with image generation services.', '@jbrower95', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/jbrower95/mcp-asset-gen', 'mcp-asset-gen', 282, 'https://github.com/jbrower95.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000864+00:00'),
  ('mcp-skill-server', 'MCP Skill Server', 'An MCP server that mounts your skill directory and adds deterministic entry for deployment.', '@jcc-ne', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/jcc-ne/mcp-skill-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jcc-ne.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000906+00:00'),
  ('bruno', 'Bruno', 'A Bruno CLI integration server that provides API testing capabilities through the Bruno CLI tool, featuring request execution, collection management, environment handling, and test result analysis. Built with TypeScript and featuring robust configuration management, caching for performance optimization, security validation for path traversal protection, logging with rotation, and retry mechanisms with exponential backoff. The implementation includes tools for discovering Bruno collections, listing and executing individual requests or entire collections, managing environments and variables, validating collection integrity, and generating detailed test reports in multiple formats, making it useful for automated API testing workflows, CI/CD integration, and development teams managing large API test suites.', '@jcr82', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/jcr82/bruno-mcp-server', 'bruno-mcp-server', 1286, 'https://github.com/jcr82.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000936+00:00'),
  ('sherlock', 'Sherlock', 'Enables deep introspection of .NET assemblies through reflection-based analysis. Provides 28+ specialized tools for analyzing types, members, signatures, and metadata, with XML documentation extraction, project/solution analysis, and dependency resolution. Built on .NET 9.0 with stable JSON APIs and advanced filtering capabilities.', '@jcucci', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/jcucci/dotnet-sherlock-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jcucci.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.000964+00:00'),
  ('ccxt-cryptocurrency-exchange', 'CCXT Cryptocurrency Exchange', 'The CCXT MCP Server provides Large Language Models with direct access to cryptocurrency exchange operations through the CCXT library. Developed by Chanwoong Joo, this asynchronous server implementation exposes both public market data tools (like fetching OHLCV data and tickers) and private account operations (such as balance retrieval, order creation, and position management) across multiple exchanges. Built with FastMCP, the server handles authentication, provides clear parameter definitions using Pydantic, and supports specialized operations for spot, futures, and options markets, making it valuable for AI assistants that need to analyze crypto markets or execute trading strategies without context switching.', '@jcwleo', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/jcwleo/ccxt-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jcwleo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.001012+00:00'),
  ('tenets', 'Tenets', 'Intelligently discovers and ranks the most relevant code files using multi-factor analysis including BM25, TF-IDF, import graphs, and git signals. Processes everything locally with no external API requirements. Supports three ranking modes from fast keyword matching to thorough ML-powered semantic search. Automatically injects project-specific coding principles into every prompt to maintain consistency across conversations.', '@jddunn', 'development', 'Unknown', 7, 'https://github.com/jddunn/tenets', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jddunn.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.001033+00:00'),
  ('claude-ipc', 'Claude IPC', 'This MCP server enables secure inter-process communication between multiple AI instances (Claude, Gemini, etc.) running on the same machine, particularly designed for WSL environments. Built with Python using TCP sockets and session-based authentication, it provides a message broker that handles registration, message queuing, broadcasting, file sharing, and command output sharing between AI instances, with features like automatic message forwarding during instance renames, large message file storage, and rate limiting. The implementation includes both MCP tools for Claude integration and standalone Python scripts for other AI models, making it valuable for coordinating multi-AI workflows, collaborative problem-solving scenarios, and building AI systems that need to communicate and share data across different instances without manual intervention.', '@jdez427', 'development', 'Unknown', 125, 'https://github.com/jdez427/claude-ipc-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jdez427.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.001065+00:00'),
  ('markdownify', 'Markdownify', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge for converting various document formats to Markdown. Developed by quasimodo-XY based on work by @zcaceres, it supports UTF-8 encoding and integrates with the markitdown library. The server offers functionality for handling multiple input formats including PDF, Word documents, and HTML, making it suitable for use cases requiring document conversion and standardization to Markdown format.', '@jdjr2024', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/jdjr2024/markdownify-mcp-utf8', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jdjr2024.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.001100+00:00'),
  ('sql-server-schema-explorer', 'SQL Server Schema Explorer', 'MsSqlMCP is a Model Context Protocol server that enables AI assistants to query SQL Server database schemas, providing tools to retrieve tables, columns, and relationships. Built with .NET 9, it offers three main functions: getting all tables in a database, retrieving columns for a specific table, and identifying relationships between tables. The implementation connects to SQL Server databases using connection strings configured in appsettings.json, making it particularly valuable for developers who need to understand database structures or generate database-related code without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@jdlemes', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/jdlemes/mssqlmcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/jdlemes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.001115+00:00');








ex: "Hotels near the F subway line in West Village">
Compare hotel prices for any date range.

Find out more at makekismet.com or kismet.travel', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://kismet.travel/mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015444+00:00'),
  ('database-operations', 'Database Operations', 'A Java Spring Boot database server that provides secure SQL execution capabilities across multiple database types including MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, SQL Server, and KingBase. Features connection pooling via HikariCP, SQL security checking to prevent dangerous operations, audit logging for all database interactions, and a write confirmation system that previews changes before execution. Includes comprehensive database metadata retrieval and Docker deployment support.', '@kiss-gg', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/kiss-gg/db_mcp_server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kiss-gg.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015454+00:00'),
  ('kiteworks', 'Kiteworks', 'Enables secure integration between LLM applications and Kiteworks enterprise file sharing platforms through OAuth 2.0 authentication and enterprise-grade security controls. Built by Kiteworks as a cross-platform STDIO server, it provides file and folder management capabilities including upload/download operations, metadata retrieval, and user information access while storing credentials securely in the OS keychain and validating TLS certificates to prevent man-in-the-middle attacks. The implementation includes configurable security features like relative path restrictions by default, rate limiting, and refresh token support, making it suitable for enterprise environments that need AI assistants to interact with sensitive file repositories while maintaining strict security boundaries.', '@kiteworks', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/kiteworks/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kiteworks.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015526+00:00'),
  ('zoo', 'Zoo', 'Integrates with Zoo''s Design API (formerly KittyCAD) to enable CAD modeling capabilities through natural language. Features text-to-CAD generation that converts prompts into parametric CAD models, along with tools for accessing Zoo''s GPU-accelerated geometry engine and design utilities. Requires a Zoo API key for authentication.', '@kittycad', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/kittycad/zoo-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kittycad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015556+00:00'),
  ('code-analyzer', 'Code Analyzer', 'This MCP server, developed by kivo360, analyzes open source projects and assists with codebase integration. Built using Node.js and leveraging the Anthropic AI SDK, it provides repository analysis, code pattern detection, and intelligent merge strategy generation. The implementation focuses on using Claude to analyze code structures, dependencies, and documentation to provide context-aware integration recommendations. It''s particularly useful for development teams working on large-scale integrations, enabling use cases such as automated code analysis, conflict detection, and AI-assisted refactoring suggestions without manual code review.', '@kivo360', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/kivo360/anthropic-mcp-code-analyzer', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kivo360.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015585+00:00'),
  ('kiwi-flight-search', 'Kiwi Flight Search', 'The Kiwi.com MCP server allow you to search and book for flights using the Kiwi.com flights search engine.
The MCP server exposes a single tool: search-flight. This allows you to get instant access to a curated list of the best flights for your trip based on: 
- Round-trip or one-way flight
- Origin / destination (city or airport)
- Travel dates
- Flexibility up to +/- 3 days
- Number and types of passengers (adult, child, infant)
- Cabin class (economy, premium economy, business, first class)

Simply ask your AI assistant something like: 
- “Can you help me book a first-class ticket from Paris to Rome tomorrow?” 
- “Find me the best options for our family vacation. I need a round-trip flight for my husband, me and our two children from Vienna to London, August 3 to 10.”

You can also narrow your query by choosing your preferred airport, or enlarge it by specifying that your dates are flexible. 
Each result includes a booking link directly to the flight chosen.', '@alpic-ai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/alpic-ai/kiwi-mcp-server-public', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/alpic-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015679+00:00'),
  ('kkj-public-procurement-search', 'KKJ Public Procurement Search', 'Provides search access to Japan''s KKJ (kkj.go.jp) government procurement information portal, operated by the Small and Medium Enterprise Agency. Enables querying public tender notices, bidding information, and procurement data from national agencies, independent administrative agencies, and local government bodies across Japan. Targets businesses seeking government contract opportunities in the Japanese market.', '@unknown', 'search', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://n-3.ai/apps/reinfo-agent', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015847+00:00'),
  ('trinity', 'Trinity', 'Trinity-MCP is a Go-based server implementation that provides a bridge between AI assistants and the Trinity API. Built using the mark3labs/mcp-go library, it enables AI assistants to access Trinity''s formula-based tools through a standardized JSON-RPC interface. The server mounts Trinity tools to an MCP server, supports configuration options for app ID and host customization, and handles communication through standard I/O, making it suitable for integration with AI platforms that need to leverage Trinity''s capabilities.', '@kklab-com', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/kklab-com/trinity-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kklab-com.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.015898+00:00'),
  ('strata', 'Strata', 'Klavis AI provides a comprehensive MCP ecosystem including hosted MCP servers, client implementations, and development tools for integrating AI applications with external services. The platform offers over 35 pre-built MCP servers for popular services like Gmail, Salesforce, GitHub, and Slack with OAuth authentication, plus Strata - an open-source MCP router that aggregates multiple servers into a single endpoint. The implementation includes client bots for Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, and web interfaces, along with extensive examples for integrating with frameworks like CrewAI, LangChain, LlamaIndex, and OpenAI, making it valuable for developers building AI agents that need reliable access to external APIs and services without managing individual server deployments.', '@klavis-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 5653, 'https://github.com/klavis-ai/klavis', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/klavis-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016028+00:00'),
  ('klaviyo', 'Klaviyo', 'Klaviyo''s official MCP server enables AI assistants to interact with Klaviyo''s marketing automation platform through both remote-hosted and local server configurations. Built by Klaviyo, it provides comprehensive tools for managing campaigns, flows, profiles, events, catalogs, and reporting data, supporting major MCP clients including Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor, and VS Code. The server offers configurable security options including read-only mode and user-generated content filtering, with OAuth authentication for the remote server and private API keys for local deployment. This implementation is particularly valuable for marketers and developers seeking to automate campaign creation, analyze performance metrics, manage customer data, and generate marketing insights directly within AI-powered workflows.', '@klaviyo', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/klaviyo/klaviyo-mcp-server', 'klaviyo-mcp-server', 18740, 'https://github.com/klaviyo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016060+00:00'),
  ('awesome-cursor', 'Awesome Cursor', 'This MCP server, developed by kleneway, provides three Cursor Tools: Screenshot, Architect, and Code Review. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, OpenAI, and Puppeteer, it enables AI assistants to capture screenshots, analyze web page structures, and review code. The implementation focuses on automating visual and code-related tasks, making it easier to incorporate these capabilities into AI workflows. It''s particularly useful for developers and QA teams who want to streamline web testing, UI analysis, and code review processes, enabling use cases such as automated UI testing, web scraping, and AI-assisted code quality checks without manual intervention.', '@kleneway', 'development', 'Unknown', 337, 'https://github.com/kleneway/awesome-cursor-mpc-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kleneway.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016086+00:00'),
  ('kleros-court', 'Kleros Court', 'Kleros Court MCP server that retrieves comprehensive dispute data from the Kleros decentralized arbitration platform across Ethereum Mainnet and Gnosis Chain networks. The implementation integrates with Kleros APIs, The Graph subgraphs, and IPFS gateways to fetch meta-evidence, evidence submissions, and dispute details, handling various IPFS URI formats and providing robust error handling for failed content retrieval. Built with TypeScript and deployed on Fly.io, it uses modern Streamable HTTP transport and supports both successful evidence parsing and detailed error reporting, making it valuable for legal researchers, dispute participants, and developers building applications that need access to decentralized court proceedings and arbitration data.', '@gmkung', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/gmkung/kleros-court-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/gmkung.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016118+00:00'),
  ('kling-ai', 'Kling AI', 'Provides integration with Kling AI''s video and image generation APIs, enabling AI assistants to create high-quality videos from text prompts, convert images to videos, apply special effects, generate lip-sync videos, and perform virtual try-on operations. Built by the 199 Longevity team, it supports Kling''s latest v2 models with advanced features like camera controls, video extension, and professional quality modes, while handling file uploads through Supabase for seamless media processing. The server is particularly useful for content creators, marketers, and developers who need to generate dynamic visual content, create social media videos, or build applications requiring AI-powered video synthesis without directly managing the Kling API complexity.', '@199-mcp', 'databases', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/199-mcp/mcp-kling', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/199-mcp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016135+00:00'),
  ('paybysquare', 'PayBySquare', 'Generates and decodes PayBySquare QR codes following the Slovak national payment standard adopted by the Slovak Banking Association. Provides tools for creating QR codes from payment data, decoding existing QR codes from images, validating payment data against banking standards with detailed error reporting, and verifying round-trip encoding integrity. Built on the bysquare library with IBAN validation support.', '@klokain', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/klokain/pbsq-sk', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/klokain.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016155+00:00'),
  ('sparql', 'SPARQL', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to query SPARQL servers, enabling AI assistants to interact with RDF data sources. Developed by Kludge Works, it integrates Spring Boot, Spring AI, and Apache Jena to facilitate SPARQL queries and RDF data manipulation. The server is designed for use cases requiring semantic web integration, such as knowledge graph exploration, linked data analysis, or ontology-based information retrieval.', '@kludgeworks', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/kludgeworks/mcp-server-rdf', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kludgeworks.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016191+00:00'),
  ('excel-to-pdf-converter', 'Excel to PDF Converter', 'An MCP server that converts Excel (.xls/.xlsx) and Apple Numbers (.numbers) files to PDF format, enabling AI assistants like Claude to perform file conversions directly through conversations. Built with TypeScript and Node.js, it leverages LibreOffice for the actual conversion process and implements the Model Context Protocol to expose two primary tools: convert_excel_to_pdf and convert_numbers_to_pdf. The server handles file validation, secure path resolution, and temporary file management while providing detailed error messages. It''s particularly useful for users who need to share spreadsheets with stakeholders who may not have access to the original applications.', '@kmexnx', 'development', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/kmexnx/excel-to-pdf-mcp', 'excel-to-pdf-mcp', 3916, 'https://github.com/kmexnx.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016224+00:00'),
  ('co2-sensor', 'CO2 Sensor', 'This MCP Server simulates a CO2 sensor device, providing a JSON-RPC interface to interact with either a simulated sensor or a real Raspberry Pi Pico connected via USB. Built with Node.js and the SerialPort library, it offers resources for device information, sensor data, and network status, along with tools to publish data to MQTT, reconnect WiFi, and manage MQTT connections. The implementation includes both simulation mode with randomized CO2 levels and real mode that reads actual sensor data, making it ideal for testing IoT applications or integrating CO2 monitoring into AI assistant workflows.', '@kmwebnet', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/kmwebnet/mcp-server-for-sensor-device', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kmwebnet.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016252+00:00'),
  ('knit', 'Knit', 'Knit''s MCP Server is a cloud-hosted, SSE-based solution that bridges AI models with external tools and data across 10,000+ tools from popular business applications. It enables packaging APIs from different applications (HRIS, ATS, CRM, Accounting, etc.) into a single server with robust authorization support via Bearer tokens. The server follows a simple 4-step setup process: finding tools, creating a package, configuring the server with necessary integrations, and connecting it to AI models—making it particularly valuable for production-grade B2B workloads requiring secure, scalable API access.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://developers.getknit.dev/docs/knit-mcp-server-getting-started', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016315+00:00'),
  ('glide-api', 'Glide API', 'This Glide API MCP server, developed by an unnamed creator, provides a bridge between the Model Context Protocol and Glide''s API (versions 1 and 2). Built with TypeScript and leveraging the MCP SDK and Axios, it offers tools for interacting with Glide apps, including retrieving app information, managing tables, and manipulating data rows. The server implements secure API key handling through environment variables and runtime configuration. By abstracting Glide API operations into a standardized MCP format, it enables AI systems to easily interact with and manage Glide applications. This implementation is particularly valuable for automating Glide app management and data operations, facilitating use cases such as dynamic data updates, automated reporting, and integration of Glide apps with other systems or workflows.', '@knmurphy', 'development', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/knmurphy/glide-api-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/knmurphy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016345+00:00'),
  ('neo4j-agent-memory', 'Neo4j Agent Memory', 'A Neo4j-based memory system for AI agents that stores entities as nodes and relationships as edges in a graph database, enabling semantic memory management through word-tokenized search and temporal filtering. Built by KnowAll AI with contributions from Daichi Okazaki, it provides 10 specialized tools for creating memories (people, places, organizations), building connections between them, and querying the knowledge graph with configurable depth traversal. The implementation emphasizes an LLM-driven approach where the AI handles all intelligence while the server provides simple graph operations, automatic integer conversion, and comprehensive guidance tools, making it useful for conversational AI systems, voice assistants, and any AI agent requiring persistent contextual memory with relationship awareness.', '@knowall-ai', 'databases', 'Unknown', 64, 'https://github.com/knowall-ai/mcp-neo4j-agent-memory', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/knowall-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016357+00:00'),
  ('knowsync', 'KnowSync', 'KnowSync''s MCP server enables AI agents to access organizational knowledge bases in real-time through two unified tools: universal query for intelligent search with AI-powered reranking and session-aware context preservation, and document management for web crawling, discovery, and content operations. Built with enterprise security features including API key authentication, granular permissions, rate limiting, and team member attribution, it provides 60-85% faster responses through intelligent caching and supports integration with Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code, and other AI tools via standardized JSON-RPC 2.0 API. The implementation transforms traditional documentation workflows by enabling AI agents to automatically access relevant information contextually rather than requiring manual searches, making it valuable for development teams, customer support, product management, and sales enablement use cases.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.knowsync.ai/docs/mcp-integration', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016385+00:00'),
  ('consul', 'Consul', 'Consul MCP Server provides a bridge to HashiCorp Consul, enabling AI assistants to interact with this service discovery and configuration management tool. Developed by Erik Koci, this TypeScript implementation offers tools for service management, health checks, key-value store operations, session handling, and event management. The server connects to a Consul instance (configurable via environment variables) and exposes its functionality through a standardized MCP interface, making it valuable for infrastructure monitoring, service registration, configuration management, and distributed systems coordination without leaving the AI assistant environment.', '@kocierik', 'development', 'Unknown', 16, 'https://github.com/kocierik/consul-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kocierik.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016412+00:00'),
  ('nomad', 'Nomad', 'Nomad MCP Server provides a bridge to HashiCorp Nomad''s cluster management capabilities, enabling AI assistants to interact with Nomad infrastructure through a comprehensive set of tools. Built in Go, this implementation supports job management (create, run, stop, scale), deployment tracking, namespace administration, node operations, and ACL management. The server exposes both static and dynamic resources for accessing job specifications, node statuses, and allocation logs, while supporting multiple transport methods (stdio and SSE). Particularly valuable for DevOps teams managing containerized workloads who need AI assistance with infrastructure operations without leaving their assistant interface.', '@kocierik', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 46, 'https://github.com/kocierik/mcp-nomad', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kocierik.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016458+00:00'),
  ('discord-extended', 'Discord Extended', 'Provides extensive Discord server management capabilities including role creation and assignment, channel operations, permission controls, message handling with bulk operations, member management, reactions, forum support, webhooks, and batch command execution. Built on Discord.js with Zod schema validation for robust error handling.', '@kogollones', 'communication', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/kogollones/mcp-discord', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kogollones.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016481+00:00'),
  ('exia-voiceroid', 'Exia Voiceroid', 'Exia-MCP is a server implementation for generating Voiceroid explanation scenarios, designed to work with the Exia application. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the OpenAI API, it provides a bridge between AI assistants and the Voiceroid text-to-speech system. The server processes scenario requests through the Model Context Protocol SDK, transforming them into structured explanations suitable for Voiceroid narration. It''s particularly useful for creators who need to automate the generation of explanatory content with the natural-sounding voice synthesis that Voiceroid offers.', '@kokushin', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/kokushin/exia-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kokushin.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016549+00:00'),
  ('kollektiv-document-management', 'Kollektiv Document Management', 'The Kollektiv MCP server enables AI assistants to access document management capabilities through a secure OAuth authentication flow. Built with Cloudflare Workers and Supabase for authentication, this implementation provides tools for querying and listing documents that users have previously uploaded to Kollektiv. The server features a robust authentication system with support for GitHub, Google, and magic link login methods, along with comprehensive consent management for authorization requests. Deployed as a Durable Object with KV storage for OAuth tokens, it''s particularly valuable for users who need to search and analyze their document collections through natural language without leaving their conversation context.', '@alexander-zuev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 61, 'https://github.com/alexander-zuev/kollektiv-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/alexander-zuev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.016597+00:00');



Demonstrative example can be seen here: https://blog.kuzudb.com/post/2025-03-23-kuzu-mcp-server/
', '@kuzudb', 'databases', 'Unknown', 40, 'https://github.com/kuzudb/kuzu-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kuzudb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020514+00:00'),
  ('speech-interface-faster-whisper', 'Speech Interface (Faster Whisper)', 'This MCP server implementation provides voice interaction capabilities for AI assistants, enabling speech-to-text and text-to-speech functionality. It uses faster-whisper for improved speech recognition performance and integrates with PyAudio for audio processing. The server offers a simplified API for starting conversations and replying to user input, making it suitable for applications requiring natural language voice interfaces with AI models.', '@kvadratni', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 81, 'https://github.com/kvadratni/speech-mcp', 'speech-mcp', 15210, 'https://github.com/kvadratni.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020640+00:00'),
  ('square', 'Square', 'This MCP server implementation provides access to Square API functionality, enabling AI assistants to interact with Square''s payment and business management services. Developed by Max Novich, it offers a streamlined interface for Square API operations, supporting both sandbox and production environments. The server is built using Python and leverages the squareup library for API interactions. It''s particularly useful for AI applications requiring e-commerce capabilities, point-of-sale integrations, or business analytics based on Square data. The implementation focuses on secure API token management through environment variables and efficient request handling, making it suitable for various business-oriented AI use cases.', '@block', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/block/square-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/block.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020687+00:00'),
  ('kvm-control', 'KVM Control', 'KVM MCP server that provides JSON-RPC control over KVM virtual machines through libvirt, featuring VM lifecycle management (create, start, stop, reboot), VNC display access, and Fedora CoreOS support with Ignition configuration. Built by steveydevey, the implementation includes performance optimizations like connection pooling, VM information caching, and asynchronous processing to reduce latency and improve resource efficiency when managing multiple VMs. Designed for developers and system administrators who need programmatic VM control without manually using virsh and virt-install commands, enabling automated infrastructure management and remote VM operations through a standardized API interface.', '@steveydevey', 'development', 'Unknown', 10, 'https://github.com/steveydevey/kvm-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/steveydevey.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020826+00:00'),
  ('nltk', 'NLTK', 'A lightweight MCP server that provides a word-finding tool for word games, specifically designed to read from a local corpus file and return the longest valid word matching given letter constraints. The implementation filters words efficiently, excluding previously used words and ensuring all letters are within the allowed set, making it useful for games like Spelling Bee where players need strategic word selection.', '@kwen1510', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/kwen1510/mcp-nltk', 'ntlk-mcp-002', 1305, 'https://github.com/kwen1510.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020875+00:00'),
  ('web-fetch', 'Web Fetch', 'Web content fetching MCP server built by kwp-lab that retrieves and processes web pages into markdown format with automatic image extraction and proxy support. Forked from @smithery/mcp-fetch, this implementation replaces node-fetch with node-fetch-native to enable HTTP/HTTPS proxy routing through environment variables (http_proxy, https_proxy) or custom MCP_HTTP_PROXY configuration. The server uses Mozilla Readability for content extraction, JSDOM for HTML parsing, and Turndown for markdown conversion, automatically identifying and listing image URLs found within article content, making it valuable for AI assistants that need to access web content through corporate proxies or restricted network environments while maintaining clean markdown output with embedded media references.', '@kwp-lab', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/kwp-lab/mcp-fetch', '@kwp-lab/mcp-fetch', 2478, 'https://github.com/kwp-lab.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.020925+00:00');











- Security
WebAssembly (Wasm) provides sandboxed execution, ensuring code runs safely and securely in any environment without compromising your system.

-  Portability
Write once, run anywhere. Wasm code works across platforms, languages, and environments such as your laptop, the cloud, the edge, the browser, your mobile device, and more!

-  User Experience
Users (or agents) don''t need to install and configure a node or python service. They can search, install, and configure tools without leaving their client.
', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://mcp.run', '@dylibso/mcpx', 12760, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038204+00:00'),
  ('swarm-at', 'Swarm.at', 'Swarm.at provides a settlement protocol for autonomous AI agent workflows across organizational boundaries. It offers a hash-chained, tamper-evident ledger for recording verified agent settlements, trust scoring for agents, revenue-generating blueprint publishing, and framework adapters for LangGraph, CrewAI, and AutoGen. Supports both local stdio transport and a hosted SSE remote endpoint.', '@mediaeater', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/mediaeater/swarm-at-ledger', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mediaeater.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038372+00:00'),
  ('screenpipe', 'Screenpipe', 'This screenpipe MCP server, developed by Mediar AI, provides a standardized interface for searching and retrieving screen recordings and associated data. Built with Python and leveraging libraries like httpx and nest-asyncio, it offers tools to query recordings based on content type, time range, and application context. The server integrates with a local screenpipe API, abstracting the complexities of data retrieval and formatting into a consistent MCP interface. By enabling AI systems to access and analyze screen capture data, this implementation facilitates use cases such as productivity tracking, user behavior analysis, and automated documentation of digital workflows.', '@screenpipe', 'development', 'Unknown', 17151, 'https://github.com/screenpipe/screenpipe/tree/HEAD/screenpipe-integrations/screenpipe-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/screenpipe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038398+00:00'),
  ('io-github-sidneybissoli-medical-terminologies-mcp', 'io.github.SidneyBissoli/medical-terminologies-mcp', 'Unified access to global medical terminologies: ICD-11, SNOMED CT, LOINC, RxNorm, MeSH', '@sidneybissoli', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/sidneybissoli/medical-terminologies-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/sidneybissoli.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038419+00:00'),
  ('medium-accelerator', 'Medium Accelerator', 'This MCP server accelerates Medium article research by providing tools to extract article links from Medium archive pages, scrape full article content for summarization, and persistently store summaries with metadata using TinyDB. Built by Daniele Carta, it streamlines the workflow of discovering, processing, and organizing Medium articles by automating the extraction process and maintaining a local database of summaries with titles, URLs, tags, and timestamps. The implementation is particularly useful for content researchers, writers, and analysts who need to efficiently process and catalog multiple Medium articles for reference or analysis.', '@crtdaniele', 'databases', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/crtdaniele/mcp-medium-accelerator', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/crtdaniele.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038430+00:00'),
  ('medrecpro-drug-label', 'MedRecPro Drug Label', 'MedRecPro Drug Label provides access to FDA Structured Product Labeling (SPL) data through a hosted MCP server. Users can search drug labels by brand name, generic ingredient, or UNII code, and export structured pharmaceutical data. The platform parses and normalizes SPL XML documents according to FDA specifications and HL7 standards, supporting regulatory and clinical research workflows.', '@chriserikbarnes', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/chriserikbarnes/medrecpro/tree/HEAD/MedRecProMCP', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/chriserikbarnes.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038453+00:00'),
  ('mysql-mariadb-database-navigator', 'MySQL/MariaDB Database Navigator', 'The MySQL Navigator MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to MySQL/MariaDB databases through a secure, feature-rich interface. Developed by Ahmed S. Said-ahmed, this implementation offers tools for connecting to databases, switching between them, loading schema information, and executing parameterized queries with comprehensive security measures including input sanitization, rate limiting, and SSL/TLS support. The server implements connection pooling for optimal performance, detailed metrics tracking, and robust error handling while maintaining a structured logging system. It''s particularly valuable for users who need to explore and query relational databases directly from their AI assistant without switching contexts.', '@medsaad', 'databases', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/medsaad/mcp-db-navigator', 'mcp-db-navigator', 3745, 'https://github.com/medsaad.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038465+00:00'),
  ('medusa', 'Medusa', 'Access information from the Medusa documentation to assist with e-commerce development. Query the docs for accurate answers, code snippets, and explanations about Medusa''s commerce modules, API routes, data models, workflows, and framework features without leaving your development environment.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.medusajs.com/learn/introduction/build-with-llms-ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038483+00:00'),
  ('meeting-baas', 'Meeting BaaS', 'Meeting BaaS MCP Server provides tools for managing meeting recordings, transcripts, and calendar data across Zoom, Google Meet, and Microsoft Teams. Built by Meeting-Baas, this TypeScript implementation enables AI assistants to create meeting bots that automatically record and transcribe meetings, search through meeting content, manage calendar integrations, and share meeting segments with teammates. The server includes robust authentication handling, environment selection capabilities, and QR code generation for bot avatars, making it ideal for teams who need to capture, access, and share meeting knowledge without manual note-taking.', '@meeting-baas', 'development', 'Unknown', 25, 'https://github.com/meeting-baas/meeting-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/meeting-baas.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038508+00:00'),
  ('meetlark', 'MeetLark', 'MeetLark is an agent-first meeting scheduling poll service designed as a Doodle alternative for the age of AI agents. It enables AI assistants to autonomously create scheduling polls, share participation links, collect votes from participants, and determine optimal meeting times. Supports both human and agent-driven scheduling workflows.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://meetlark.ai', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038538+00:00'),
  ('sql-database', 'SQL Database', 'Provides SQL database connectivity for PostgreSQL, SQLite, and MySQL databases with read-only safety by default and optional write operations. Features comprehensive database introspection including table listing, schema description with foreign key relationships, sample data preview, query execution with automatic LIMIT injection, and query plan analysis. Implements robust security measures including SQL injection prevention, transaction-level read-only enforcement, query timeouts, and identifier sanitization.', '@mehdig-dev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mehdig-dev/mcp-sql', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mehdig-dev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038613+00:00'),
  ('shaderc-vkrunner-gpu-shader-sandbox', 'Shaderc-VkRunner (GPU Shader Sandbox)', 'shaderc-vkrunner-mcp is a Model Context Protocol server that provides AI agents with a secure sandbox for developing, compiling, and visualizing GPU shaders using Vulkan. It runs entirely locally in a Docker container using Mesa''s software Vulkan implementation, eliminating risks of GPU crashes while supporting advanced features like subgroups, atomic operations, and raytracing without physical GPU hardware. The implementation leverages Rust''s type safety, integrates with tools like Shaderc for compilation and VkRunner for execution, and is designed to work with VS Code Copilot and other MCP-capable AI tools for shader development workflows.', '@mehmetoguzderin', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/mehmetoguzderin/shaderc-vkrunner-mcp', 'shaderc-vkrunner-mcp', 0, 'https://github.com/mehmetoguzderin.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038639+00:00'),
  ('data-gov', 'Data.gov', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to Data.gov, enabling AI assistants to interact with government datasets. Developed by Joao Bondan, it offers tools for searching packages, retrieving dataset details, listing groups and tags, and accessing specific resources. The server is designed to facilitate data-driven analysis and research using public government information, making it valuable for projects requiring access to official U.S. datasets.', '@melaodoidao', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 19, 'https://github.com/melaodoidao/datagov-mcp-server', '@melaodoidao/datagov-mcp-server', 4303, 'https://github.com/melaodoidao.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038772+00:00'),
  ('docs2prompt', 'Docs2Prompt', 'docs2prompt-mcp is an MCP server that wraps the docs2prompt library, allowing AI assistants to convert documentation from GitHub repositories or websites into LLM-friendly prompts. Developed by Andrew Melbourne, it builds on Reza Tabrizi''s original library and exposes two main tools: one for fetching documentation from GitHub repos and another for retrieving documentation from URLs. The server handles authentication with GitHub via tokens and includes safeguards against oversized responses, making it particularly useful for developers who need to quickly reference or understand external codebases and documentation without leaving their conversation interface.', '@melbourneandrew', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/melbourneandrew/docs2prompt-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/melbourneandrew.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038796+00:00'),
  ('chromadb-remote', 'ChromaDB Remote', 'Provides remote access to ChromaDB vector databases for AI assistants. Enables semantic search and vector operations across multiple Claude clients (Desktop, Mobile, Code) with a shared, persistent database. Supports deployment via Tailscale VPN, Cloudflare Tunnel, or traditional reverse proxy with authentication.', '@meloncafe', 'databases', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/meloncafe/chromadb-remote-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/meloncafe.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038816+00:00'),
  ('mem0', 'Mem0', 'Mem0-MCP provides a structured approach for managing coding preferences through an MCP server that integrates with mem0.ai. Built with Python using the FastMCP framework, it offers three main tools: adding coding preferences with comprehensive context, retrieving all stored preferences, and semantically searching through preferences to find relevant code implementations, solutions, and documentation. The server runs as a persistent process that agents can connect to via SSE, making it ideal for cloud-native environments where server and clients operate as decoupled processes. This implementation is particularly valuable for developers using Cursor who need efficient storage and retrieval of code snippets and programming knowledge.', '@mem0ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 618, 'https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mem0ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038844+00:00'),
  ('mem0-for-project-management', 'Mem0 for Project Management', 'Brings AI power into your Project management methods.
Stop manage your project by your own experience based instincting black boxed knowledge that leads you into hell fired project !!
Enpower your management by AI capablity, they are obviously sperior to you !!😇', '@kunihiros', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 6, 'https://github.com/kunihiros/mem0-mcp-for-pm', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/kunihiros.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038894+00:00'),
  ('memara-memory', 'Memara Memory', 'This MCP server implementation provides a minimal foundation structure with only a README.md file, serving as a basic template or starting point for developers to build their own MCP server integrations. The bare-bones repository structure suggests this is either a placeholder project, an early-stage implementation, or a template repository designed to be forked and extended with specific functionality, making it useful for developers who want to bootstrap new MCP server projects without starting from scratch.', '@memara-memory', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/memara-memory/mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/memara-memory.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038924+00:00'),
  ('member-berries-apple-productivity', 'Member Berries (Apple Productivity)', 'This MCP server provides seamless integration with Apple''s native productivity apps (Notes, Reminders, and Calendar) on macOS, enabling AI assistants to create, search, and manage personal information directly within the user''s existing Apple ecosystem. Built by M-Pineapple using TypeScript with JXA (JavaScript for Automation) for native macOS app control, it offers tools for note creation and search in Apple Notes, reminder management with list organization and due dates, calendar event operations including search and creation, and a unique "Member Berries" memory system that tracks conversation starters and recent activities to make AI interactions more natural and contextual. The implementation leverages AppleScript automation for deep system integration, automatic folder organization with fallback handling, and persistent memory storage to maintain conversational context across sessions, making it valuable for users who want AI assistance that works natively with their existing Apple productivity workflow while maintaining personal context and relationship continuity.', '@m-pineapple', 'development', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/m-pineapple/member-berries-apple-mcp/tree/HEAD/member-berries', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/m-pineapple.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038966+00:00'),
  ('io-github-thelabvenice-memdata', 'io.github.thelabvenice/memdata', 'Persistent memory for AI agents. Store context, retrieve it semantically.', '@thelabvenice', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/thelabvenice/memdata-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/thelabvenice.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.038981+00:00'),
  ('meminal', 'Meminal', 'Meminal maintains conversation context across multiple AI tools and applications. The service enables continuity in AI conversations by automatically capturing and retrieving context as users switch between different assistants and development environments. Features include cross-platform memory, unlimited storage, and industry-standard security with full user data ownership.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://meminal.ai/mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039009+00:00'),
  ('memobase', 'MemoBase', 'MomeDB-MCP server provides a bridge between AI assistants and the MemoBase API for managing conversation context and personal knowledge. It implements tools for user management, blob storage (for conversation data), and knowledge base operations including querying, adding, updating, and relating knowledge items. The server uses a JSON-RPC interface over stdio, making it compatible with any MCP client while enabling AI assistants to maintain persistent user data and retrieve relevant contextual information during conversations.', '@wuyunmei', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/wuyunmei/momedb-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/wuyunmei.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039051+00:00'),
  ('memory-graph', 'Memory Graph', 'This memory server implementation provides persistent knowledge graph storage for AI assistants through entity-relationship modeling with observations. Built with TypeScript and Hono.js, it offers both standard MCP protocol support and HTTP streaming capabilities, storing data in a configurable JSON file format with JSONL serialization. The implementation includes comprehensive CRUD operations for entities, relations, and observations, plus search and filtering capabilities, making it suitable for AI applications requiring long-term memory persistence, knowledge base management, and contextual information retrieval across conversation sessions.', '@songlairui', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/songlairui/mcp-memory-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/songlairui.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039127+00:00'),
  ('memory-libsql', 'Memory LibSQL', 'An MCP server implementation that uses LibSQL as a memory store for the Model Context Protocol.', '@joleyline', 'databases', 'Unknown', 23, 'https://github.com/joleyline/mcp-memory-libsql', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/joleyline.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039137+00:00'),
  ('memory-plugin-sqlite', 'Memory Plugin (SQLite)', 'This Memory Plugin is a Python-based SQLite implementation for persistent storage in AI conversations. It provides tools for storing, retrieving, and searching memories, allowing AI assistants to maintain context across sessions. The plugin uses a simple database structure to categorize and timestamp memories, with features like access counting and category-based filtering. It''s designed to integrate seamlessly with the Model Context Protocol (MCP) ecosystem, making it ideal for enhancing AI assistants with long-term memory capabilities in applications ranging from personal assistants to complex knowledge management systems.', '@mekanixms', 'databases', 'Unknown', 5, 'https://github.com/mekanixms/mcp_memory_plugin', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mekanixms.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039149+00:00'),
  ('memphora', 'Memphora', 'Enables AI assistants to store and recall information across conversations through a persistent memory layer. Provides semantic search, graph-based memory relationships, and multi-agent support for maintaining context and user preferences over time.', '@memphora', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/memphora/memphora-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/memphora.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039175+00:00'),
  ('mender-iot', 'Mender IoT', 'MCP server for Mender IoT device management platform that provides AI assistants with comprehensive access to device fleets, deployments, artifacts, releases, and audit logs through Personal Access Token authentication. The implementation features robust security controls including automatic credential masking, input validation with Pydantic models, error sanitization to prevent information leakage, and comprehensive logging with sensitive data filtering. Built with Python and httpx for API communication, it supports both read-only operations (device status, inventory attributes, deployment logs) and monitoring capabilities (audit trails, group management) with fallback mechanisms for different Mender API versions. Designed for DevOps teams managing IoT deployments who need AI-assisted device fleet monitoring, deployment tracking, and troubleshooting workflows while maintaining security best practices for production environments.', '@pasinskim', 'communication', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/pasinskim/mender-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/pasinskim.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039247+00:00'),
  ('jira-xray', 'Jira Xray', 'Built by mendezangelleo, this server automates test case generation and synchronization for Jira/Xray integration using Google''s Vertex AI. It analyzes Jira user stories and comments to generate Gherkin-formatted test scenarios, then intelligently syncs them with existing linked test issues by comparing content signatures to determine which tests need creation, updates, or are obsolete. The implementation supports ADF (Atlassian Document Format) parsing, handles Spanish/English copy validation scenarios, includes deduplication logic, and provides Jira API integration for test case management, making it useful for QA teams looking to automate test case creation from requirements and maintain synchronized test suites.', '@mendezangelleo', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mendezangelleo/mcp-xray-python', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mendezangelleo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039278+00:00'),
  ('mercado-libre', 'Mercado Libre', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with direct access to Mercado Libre''s comprehensive API documentation and resources, built by the Mercado Libre team to streamline developer integration workflows. The implementation offers two core tools: search_documentation for finding specific terms across all technical documentation with language and country filtering, and get_documentation_page for retrieving complete content from specific documentation pages including detailed specifications and use cases. Built with natural language querying capabilities and multi-language support (English, Spanish, Portuguese), it serves developers building e-commerce integrations who need contextual API guidance, development teams requiring automated documentation lookup during coding sessions, and AI-powered IDEs that can generate integration code by accessing real-time API specifications and examples directly from Mercado Libre''s official documentation.', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://mcp.mercadolibre.com/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039380+00:00'),
  ('mercadopago', 'MercadoPago', 'Demo MercadoPago MCP server built by MercadoLibre that provides AI assistants with access to MercadoPago''s developer documentation through a search tool that queries their documentation API. The implementation uses OAuth client credentials authentication and supports searching across multiple Latin American markets (Argentina, Brazil, Mexico, Uruguay, Chile, Colombia, Peru) with language-specific results in Spanish or Portuguese. Built with TypeScript and featuring comprehensive error handling, request logging, and automatic token refresh, the server formats search results as markdown with direct links to the relevant documentation pages, making it useful for developers integrating MercadoPago payment solutions who need conversational access to API documentation and implementation guides.', '@mercadolibre', 'development', 'Unknown', 8, 'https://github.com/mercadolibre/demo-mercadopago-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mercadolibre.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039411+00:00'),
  ('mercado-pago', 'Mercado Pago', 'Tools to enhance developer experience in integrating Mercado Pago solutions, the Latin American payment platform.', '@unknown', 'finance', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://mcp.mercadopago.com/', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039437+00:00'),
  ('counsel', 'Counsel', 'Integrates with the Counsel strategic reasoning platform for multi-perspective analysis. Provides tools for starting strategic consultations that analyze complex questions from multiple stakeholder perspectives, refining questions through an enhancement engine, and running interactive advisor sessions for brainstorming. Supports both STDIO and HTTP transport modes with OAuth 2.0 authentication.', '@mercurialsolo', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mercurialsolo/counsel-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mercurialsolo.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039474+00:00'),
  ('mercury', 'Mercury', 'Provides AI assistants with secure read-only access to Mercury business banking accounts. Enables analysis of spending patterns, monitoring account balances, downloading statements, and accessing card and recipient information. Requires OAuth authentication and offers one-click setup for supported AI tools.', '@unknown', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://docs.mercury.com/docs/what-is-mercury-mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039501+00:00'),
  ('mercury-spec-ops', 'Mercury Spec Ops', 'Programmatic prompt engineering server that dynamically generates technology-specific prompts and templates. Provides tools for PRD generation, codebase analysis, and bug analysis across 31 technology stacks including 11 languages, 10 frameworks, 4 databases, and 3 cloud platforms. Constructs contextually relevant guidance by combining base templates with technology-specific modules.', '@n0zer0d4y', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/n0zer0d4y/mercury-spec-ops', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/n0zer0d4y.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039514+00:00'),
  ('merge-request-summarizer', 'Merge Request Summarizer', 'This MCP merge request summarizer, developed by Joe Luo, provides automated analysis and summary generation for git commits between branches using GitPython and rich text formatting. The implementation offers both asynchronous MCP server tools and synchronous CLI commands for analyzing commit history, categorizing changes by type (features, bug fixes, refactoring), estimating review time, and generating structured markdown or JSON summaries of merge requests. Built with comprehensive error handling, timeout protection, and modern Python async patterns, it integrates with development workflows through editor configurations for VSCode, Cursor, Claude Desktop, and Gemini, making it useful for development teams needing automated code review preparation and commit analysis across git repositories.', '@sonicjoy', 'development', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/sonicjoy/mcp_merge_request_summarizer', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/sonicjoy.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039541+00:00'),
  ('lokka-microsoft-graph', 'Lokka (Microsoft Graph)', 'Lokka is an MCP server that provides a bridge between AI assistants and Microsoft Graph API, enabling natural language interaction with Microsoft 365 tenants. Developed by Merill Fernando, it allows users to query and manage their Microsoft environment through simple conversational prompts rather than complex API calls. The server authenticates with Microsoft Entra using client credentials, translates natural language requests into appropriate Graph API calls, and returns formatted results. Particularly valuable for administrators who need to perform tasks like creating security groups, reviewing conditional access policies, or managing Intune configurations without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@merill', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 226, 'https://github.com/merill/lokka/tree/HEAD/src/mcp', '@merill/lokka', 8948, 'https://github.com/merill.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039588+00:00'),
  ('mermaid-chart', 'Mermaid Chart', 'Provides validation and rendering capabilities for Mermaid diagrams through hosted remote endpoints. Supports both streamable-http and SSE transport methods for diagram generation and validation. Built by Mermaid Chart, a commercial platform founded by the creator of the open-source Mermaid project.', '@mermaid-chart', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/mermaid-chart/mermaid-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mermaid-chart.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039646+00:00'),
  ('ida-pro-multi-instance', 'IDA Pro Multi-Instance', 'A multi-instance orchestration layer for IDA Pro that enables simultaneous reverse engineering of multiple binaries through a single MCP endpoint. Provides a centralized registry system that tracks active IDA instances, automatically generates unique instance IDs, and routes tool calls to the appropriate instance based on context or explicit targeting. Includes health monitoring for stale instance detection, response caching for large outputs, and management tools for switching between active instances. Built on top of the ida-pro-mcp project for reverse engineers and security researchers who need to analyze multiple binaries concurrently.', '@merozemory', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 42, 'https://github.com/merozemory/ida-multi-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/merozemory.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039692+00:00'),
  ('adeo-mozaic-design-system', 'ADEO Mozaic Design System', 'Provides programmatic access to ADEO''s Mozaic Design System through an indexed SQLite database of Vue components, design tokens, and MDX documentation. Offers tools for listing components with detailed props and examples, retrieving design tokens in multiple formats (JSON, SCSS, CSS, JS), generating framework-specific code (Vue, React, HTML), and searching documentation with full-text search. Particularly valuable for developers working with ADEO brands (Leroy Merlin, Bricoman, Weldom) who need consistent component usage and automated code generation across projects.', '@merzoukemansouri', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/merzoukemansouri/adeo-mozaic-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/merzoukemansouri.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039828+00:00'),
  ('imap', 'IMAP', 'A Go-based IMAP adapter that bridges email accounts to MCP. Built using the emersion IMAP library, it provides read-only access to email summaries, headers, and message bodies through a resource-based interface. Supports standard IMAP servers including Gmail (with app passwords) and exposes emails from the last 24 hours via structured URIs for discovery, metadata retrieval, and content access. Distributed as both a container image and downloadable binary releases.', '@meschbach', 'communication', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/meschbach/mcp-imap', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/meschbach.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039868+00:00'),
  ('meshseeks', 'MeshSeeks', 'MeshSeeks is a multi-agent mesh network coordination system inspired by Rick and Morty''s Mr. Meeseeks, enabling parallel task execution across specialized Claude Code agents for complex coding problems. Built by Peter Steinberger using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK, it provides problem analysis and decomposition into parallel tasks, agent mesh execution with dependency management and result aggregation, end-to-end problem solving with configurable approaches (analysis-first, parallel exploration, iterative refinement), and real-time status monitoring with agent lifecycle tracking. The implementation features specialized agent roles (analysis, implementation, testing, documentation, debugging), intelligent task coordination with dependency resolution, boomerang-style task orchestration for complex workflows, and comprehensive performance testing with scalability metrics, making it valuable for large-scale refactoring projects, complex feature development requiring multiple specialized perspectives, and automated code analysis workflows that benefit from parallel agent collaboration.', '@twalichiewicz', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/twalichiewicz/meshseeks', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/twalichiewicz.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039905+00:00'),
  ('medical-sql-mysql-hospital-database', 'Medical SQL (MySQL Hospital Database)', 'Integrates with MySQL hospital databases to enable natural language querying in Chinese, converting questions into SQL queries through intelligent schema mapping and organizing tables into semantic categories for medical data analysis and healthcare information system integration.', '@metalxiaoxiao', 'databases', 'Unknown', 1, 'https://github.com/metalxiaoxiao/medical-sql-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/metalxiaoxiao.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039918+00:00'),
  ('metamcp', 'MetaMCP', 'This MCP server implementation manages multiple MCPs through a centralized interface, streamlining AI assistant interactions across various platforms. Developed by James Zhang, it utilizes TypeScript and integrates with the Model Context Protocol SDK. The server focuses on secure API key management and provides a unified access point for multiple MCP services. It''s designed for scalability and easy configuration, making it particularly useful for applications that need to coordinate multiple AI assistants or integrate diverse AI services. The implementation supports Docker deployment and is optimized for production environments, offering a robust solution for complex AI orchestration scenarios.', '@metatool-ai', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 152, 'https://github.com/metatool-ai/mcp-server-metamcp', '@metamcp/mcp-server-metamcp', 18989, 'https://github.com/metatool-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.039941+00:00');


This is an early work-in-progress, has limited testing, and requires access to API''s that will be replaced in the near future. For now, the following API keys are required to be set in the environment or in a .env file (see .env.example):

OpenAI API Key: https://platform.openai.com/
HuggingFace API Key: https://huggingface.co/
SERP API Key: https://serpapi.com/', '@microsoft', 'development', 'Unknown', 389, 'https://github.com/microsoft/semanticworkbench/tree/HEAD/mcp-servers/mcp-server-open-deep-research', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/microsoft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.040974+00:00'),
  ('playwright-browser-automation', 'Playwright Browser Automation', 'Playwright MCP is a server implementation that enables AI assistants to control web browsers through the Model Context Protocol. It provides tools for navigating websites, capturing page snapshots, interacting with elements, and taking screenshots - all accessible via standardized MCP interfaces. The server offers two modes: a snapshot-based approach that uses accessibility trees for better semantic understanding of web pages, and a vision-based mode that works with screenshots for visual interactions. Built by Microsoft, this implementation leverages Playwright''s automation capabilities to allow AI assistants to perform complex web tasks like form filling, clicking elements, and extracting information from websites.', '@microsoft', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 28403, 'https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp', '@playwright/mcp', 27611856, 'https://github.com/microsoft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041021+00:00'),
  ('vscode', 'VSCode', 'The VSCode MCP Server is a VSCode extension that acts as a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server integrated directly within VSCode. Its primary purpose is to expose a coding diagnostic tool—namely, the code_checker—which aggregates diagnostic messages (similar to those displayed in VSCode’s Problems panel) and makes them accessible to an external AI assistant via Server-Sent Events (SSE). This allows your assistant to invoke MCP methods and retrieve timely diagnostic information from your workspace.', '@microsoft', 'development', 'Unknown', 389, 'https://github.com/microsoft/semanticworkbench/tree/HEAD/mcp-servers/mcp-server-vscode', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/microsoft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041077+00:00'),
  ('microsoft-word', 'Microsoft Word', 'MCP Server for Interaction with Office Apps
This is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server project.

Warning: Be VERY careful with open Word or PowerPoint apps. Your content may be unexpectedly modified or deleted.

', '@microsoft', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 389, 'https://github.com/microsoft/semanticworkbench/tree/HEAD/mcp-servers/mcp-server-word', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/microsoft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041101+00:00'),
  ('chatvolt', 'Chatvolt', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with complete access to the Chatvolt API for managing conversational AI agents, datastores, and CRM workflows, built using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK. The implementation offers tools for creating and managing agents with various LLM models (GPT, Claude, Gemini, etc.), handling datastores and datasources for knowledge management, querying agents for conversational interactions, and managing CRM scenarios and steps for automated customer workflows. Built with comprehensive API coverage including agent integrations for WhatsApp/Telegram, datastore management with vector search capabilities, and CRM automation with step-based workflows, it serves developers building AI-powered customer service platforms, teams requiring programmatic access to conversational AI infrastructure, and organizations needing automated CRM workflows that leverage Chatvolt''s agent-based architecture for customer engagement and knowledge management.', '@miguelmartinezcv', 'development', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/miguelmartinezcv/chatvolt-mcp', 'chatvolt-mcp', 574, 'https://github.com/miguelmartinezcv.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041185+00:00'),
  ('cupertino', 'Cupertino', 'Cupertino crawls and indexes Apple Developer documentation, Swift.org, Swift Evolution proposals, and Apple Archive legacy guides into a fast SQLite FTS5 database. It provides offline access to 138,000+ documentation pages with deterministic search using BM25 ranking. The server integrates with AI assistants to provide accurate, up-to-date Apple API documentation without hallucinations.', '@mihaelamj', 'databases', 'Unknown', 611, 'https://github.com/mihaelamj/cupertino', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mihaelamj.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041216+00:00'),
  ('meilisearch-hybrid-search', 'Meilisearch Hybrid Search', 'Meilisearch Hybrid Search MCP Server provides a bridge between AI assistants and Meilisearch''s hybrid search capabilities, enabling semantic and keyword-based document searches with adjustable weighting. Built in Go, it allows users to fine-tune search results by setting a semantic ratio (from pure keyword to pure semantic search) and supports filtering by document attributes. The server includes helpful prompts for guiding users on parameter adjustment and offers detailed documentation on search optimization, making it particularly valuable for applications requiring nuanced document retrieval from Meilisearch indexes.', '@miiton', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 11, 'https://github.com/miiton/meilisearch-hybrid-search-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/miiton.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041262+00:00'),
  ('adobe-creative-suite', 'Adobe Creative Suite', 'This MCP server provides AI-driven automation for Adobe Creative Suite applications including Photoshop, Premiere Pro, and InDesign through a multi-component architecture consisting of Python MCP servers, a Node.js proxy server, and UXP plugins that communicate via WebSocket connections. Built by Mike Chambers using Python with FastMCP, Socket.IO for real-time communication, and Adobe''s UXP framework for plugin development, it enables AI assistants to perform complex creative workflows including layer manipulation, filter application, selection tools, adjustment layers, video editing with transitions and effects, and document creation across Adobe applications. The implementation bridges the gap between AI language models and professional creative software by translating natural language commands into Adobe API calls, making it valuable for automated design workflows, AI-assisted content creation, tutorial generation, and scenarios where creative professionals need conversational interfaces to complex Adobe functionality.', '@mikechambers', 'development', 'Unknown', 495, 'https://github.com/mikechambers/adb-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikechambers.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041341+00:00'),
  ('starbucks', 'Starbucks', 'Starbucks MCP server provides programmatic access to Starbucks menu and ordering data through a set of tools for retrieving menu categories, menu items, and potentially store locations. Built using TypeScript and the MCP SDK, it leverages Playwright for web interactions and Zod for type validation, enabling developers to programmatically explore and interact with Starbucks menu data without direct web scraping.', '@mike-pete', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/mike-pete/starbucks-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mike-pete.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041400+00:00'),
  ('reminders', 'Reminders', 'This MCP server provides AI assistants with a simple reminder system that functions like ''Alexa, remind me...'' but for AI conversations, built by MikeyBeez using TypeScript with persistent JSON storage in the user''s home directory. The implementation offers priority-based reminder management (high/normal/low), automatic sorting by priority and creation time, and integration with Obsidian for moving important reminders to permanent notes in a structured markdown format. Built with comprehensive reminder lifecycle management including creation, completion, deletion, and automatic cleanup of old items, it serves users needing persistent memory across AI sessions, teams requiring shared reminder systems with priority handling, and individuals wanting to seamlessly transition important reminders into their personal knowledge management workflows through Obsidian integration.', '@mikeybeez', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/mikeybeez/mcp-reminders', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikeybeez.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041434+00:00'),
  ('image-generation-flux-schnell', 'Image Generation (Flux-Schnell)', 'This MCP server, developed by an unspecified author, enables image generation using Replicate''s flux-schnell model. Built with TypeScript and leveraging the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers configurable image parameters such as resolution, aspect ratio, and quality. The implementation focuses on providing a standardized interface for text-to-image generation, including features like saving generated images to specified directories and full error handling. It''s particularly useful for applications requiring on-demand image creation, enabling use cases such as content illustration, design prototyping, and AI-assisted art generation without complex API integrations or local model deployments.', '@mikeyny', 'development', 'Unknown', 127, 'https://github.com/mikeyny/ai-image-gen-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikeyny.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041465+00:00'),
  ('kubeview', 'KubeView', 'KubeView enables read-only inspection and diagnostics of Kubernetes clusters. Provides tools for examining pods, services, deployments, namespaces, and other resources. Includes deep inspection of Helm releases with manifests, values, and history. Integrates with Argo Workflows and ArgoCD applications for workflow management visibility.', '@mikhae1', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/mikhae1/kubeview-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikhae1.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041482+00:00'),
  ('azure-revisor', 'Azure Revisor', 'An Azure DevOps pull request review assistant that enables automated code review workflows through MCP. Provides tools for retrieving pull request diffs and creating inline comments programmatically using Azure Personal Access Tokens. Designed to streamline code review processes by allowing AI-powered review and annotation of code changes directly within Azure DevOps pull requests.', '@mikhael-abdallah', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/mikhael-abdallah/mcp-revisor-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikhael-abdallah.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041498+00:00'),
  ('magi-code-review', 'MAGI Code Review', 'MAGI MCP Server provides a code review orchestration system that connects AI assistants to a distributed review framework with three specialized agents (Melchior, Balthasar, and Casper). The server establishes WebSocket connections to the MAGI Gateway, submits code for evaluation, and aggregates agent decisions into a final verdict based on majority rule. Built with FastMCP and supporting both SSE and WebSocket transports, it features authentication token generation, detailed logging, and containerization via Docker. This implementation is particularly valuable for developers seeking automated, multi-perspective code quality assessment without leaving their AI assistant interface.', '@miki-hoshizaki', 'cloud', 'Unknown', 2, 'https://github.com/miki-hoshizaki/mcp-magi', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/miki-hoshizaki.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041521+00:00'),
  ('biodiversity', 'Biodiversity', 'This MCP server implementation provides a simple interface for adding numbers and generating personalized greetings. It utilizes the FastMCP framework and includes custom helper functions for string capitalization. The server exposes an addition tool and a dynamic greeting resource, making it suitable for basic arithmetic operations and customized user interactions in MCP-based applications.', '@mikkohei13', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/mikkohei13/mcp-biodiversity', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mikkohei13.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041602+00:00'),
  ('milemaker', 'MileMaker', 'MileMaker provides commercial truck routing and mileage services for the transportation industry. It calculates optimized routes based on vehicle specifications, weight restrictions, vertical clearances, toll costs, and hazmat regulations across the United States, Mexico, and Canada. The server supports route customization for shippers, brokers, carriers, and 3PL providers, offering features such as traffic-influenced routing, fuel cost analysis, and IFTA compliance reporting.', '@unknown', 'maps-location', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://www.milemaker.com', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041711+00:00'),
  ('binance-bitcoin-market-data', 'Binance Bitcoin Market Data', 'Binance-mcp is a TypeScript-based MCP server that provides real-time and historical Bitcoin market data from Binance. Built by MilesCool, this implementation offers five specialized tools for accessing Bitcoin ticker data, order book information, recent trades, historical price charts, and real-time price streams. The server leverages WebSocket connections for live data and REST API calls for historical information, formatting responses with detailed market metrics including price trends, trading volumes, and buy/sell pressure indicators. It''s particularly valuable for financial analysis workflows, market research, and educational use cases where AI assistants need access to cryptocurrency market data without requiring direct API integration.', '@milescool', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/milescool/binance-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/milescool.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041742+00:00'),
  ('java-conferences', 'Java Conferences', 'JavaConf MCP Server provides access to Java conference information by parsing data from a GitHub-hosted markdown file. Built with Spring Boot and CommonMark, it extracts structured conference details including names, locations, dates, and CFP statuses from markdown tables organized by year. The server exposes a single tool that allows filtering conferences by year, making it particularly valuable for developers looking to discover upcoming Java events, track call for papers deadlines, or find conferences in specific locations without manually parsing the source repository.', '@miliariadnane', 'development', 'Unknown', 3, 'https://github.com/miliariadnane/javaconf-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/miliariadnane.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041767+00:00'),
  ('pulsar', 'Pulsar', 'Pulsar is a semantic router for MCP ecosystems that enables AI agents to discover and execute tools across multiple MCP servers without context bloat. Built with FastMCP, it uses embeddings and vector search to provide natural language tool discovery, progressive exploration with minimal token usage, and background task execution with inter-process communication. The implementation features content management for large results, server lifecycle management, access controls, and a unified semantic router interface that consolidates all operations across distributed services.', '@milkymap', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 21, 'https://github.com/milkymap/omnimcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/milkymap.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041847+00:00');


​
Key Features
Unified Data Gateway
MindsDB acts as a unified data gateway that handles complex data operations, freeing AI apps and agents from the need to manage individual data sources or write complex logic. MindsDB enables “one-step” querying across multiple sources with full auditability.

Superior User Experience
MindsDB delivers a polished, secure, and user-friendly experience on top of MCP integrations. Our turnkey solution includes robust security controls, monitoring, governance, and native integrations to ensure compatibility with non-MCP solutions and applications.

Advanced AI Workflows
MindsDB orchestrates complex AI workflows, such as joining data from multiple sources and coordinating across various models and data systems in a single query. These composite workflows are challenging to implement using MCP alone.', '@mindsdb', 'databases', 'Unknown', 38651, 'https://github.com/mindsdb/mindsdb', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mindsdb.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.041992+00:00'),
  ('doubao', 'Doubao', 'This server provides access to ByteDance''s Doubao AI model (doubao-seedream-4-0-250828) for text-to-image generation through the Ark SDK. Built by mingforpc, it can generate up to 3 images per request in various sizes (1K, 2K, 4K) with customizable watermarking options. The implementation includes automatic image downloading, batch processing capabilities, and Pillow-based image compression tools for resizing and format conversion. It features comprehensive error handling and is designed for content creation workflows, social media automation, and applications requiring AI-generated visual assets with post-processing optimization.', '@mingforpc', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/mingforpc/seedream_mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mingforpc.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042082+00:00'),
  ('godot-4-runtime', 'Godot 4 Runtime', 'Provides runtime debugging and development capabilities for Godot 4 C# projects through a bridge between the Godot engine and external development tools. The implementation features a C# MCP server that communicates with a Godot plugin via HTTP API, exposing tools for scene manipulation, script management, property inspection, signal handling, resource operations, and real-time debugging during game development. Built with strongly-typed architecture using Refit for HTTP client generation and comprehensive tool categories including SceneTools, ScriptTools, PropertyTools, SignalTools, and ResourceTools, it enables game development workflows like dynamic scene modification, script debugging, and asset management directly within running Godot projects.', '@minghuiliu', 'development', 'Unknown', 9, 'https://github.com/minghuiliu/godot4-runtime-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/minghuiliu.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042112+00:00'),
  ('todoist-taskmaster', 'Todoist TaskMaster', 'TaskMaster-Todoist-MCP is a server implementation that provides AI assistants with access to Todoist task management capabilities through the Todoist REST API. The server exposes a tool for retrieving tasks with flexible filtering options, allowing users to query tasks by date, priority, status, and other criteria using Todoist''s native filtering syntax. Built with FastMCP, it handles authentication via environment variables and formats task data for optimal display. This implementation is particularly valuable for users who want to manage their tasks and productivity workflows directly through AI assistants without switching contexts.', '@mingolladaniele', 'productivity', 'Unknown', 42, 'https://github.com/mingolladaniele/taskmaster-todoist-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mingolladaniele.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042153+00:00'),
  ('android-debug-bridge', 'Android Debug Bridge', 'This MCP server implementation provides a bridge to control and interact with Android devices using ADB (Android Debug Bridge). It offers tools for retrieving installed packages, executing ADB commands, capturing screenshots, and analyzing UI layouts. Developed as an open-source project, it integrates with the MCP CLI and uses libraries like adb-shell and Pillow for device communication and image processing. The server is designed for use cases requiring automated Android device testing, app analysis, or remote device management.', '@minhalvp', 'development', 'Unknown', 687, 'https://github.com/minhalvp/android-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/minhalvp.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042180+00:00'),
  ('minimax-coding-plan', 'MiniMax Coding Plan', 'Official MiniMax implementation that provides web search and image understanding capabilities specifically designed for coding workflows. Built with FastAPI and Python, it integrates with MiniMax''s API to deliver web search results with titles, links, and related queries, plus AI-powered image analysis supporting JPEG, PNG, GIF, and WebP formats. The server includes authentication via API keys, comprehensive error handling with specific status codes, and supports both HTTP/HTTPS URLs and local file paths with automatic base64 conversion. Designed for integration with Claude Desktop, Cursor, Windsurf, and other MCP-compatible clients to enhance AI-assisted development workflows.', '@minimax-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 31, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai/minimax-coding-plan-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042210+00:00'),
  ('minimax-multimodal', 'MiniMax Multimodal', 'MiniMax-MCP-JS is an official JavaScript implementation of the Model Context Protocol that provides seamless integration with MiniMax''s AI capabilities including image generation, video generation, text-to-speech, and voice cloning APIs. The server supports multiple transport modes (stdio, REST, and SSE), handles file processing and resource management, and includes comprehensive error handling. It''s particularly useful for developers building applications that need to leverage MiniMax''s multimodal AI features through a standardized protocol interface.', '@minimax-ai', 'development', 'Unknown', 106, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai/minimax-mcp-js', 'minimax-mcp-js', 12331, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042236+00:00'),
  ('minimax', 'MiniMax', 'MiniMax MCP is a server implementation that provides AI assistants with access to MiniMax''s text-to-speech, voice cloning, and video generation capabilities. Developed by Roy Wu at MiniMax, this Python-based server handles authentication with the MiniMax API, manages file operations, and provides tools for audio playback and file conversion. The implementation includes robust error handling, fuzzy filename matching, and environment variable configuration, making it particularly useful for applications requiring high-quality voice synthesis and media generation from AI interactions.', '@minimax-ai', 'ai-ml', 'Unknown', 1298, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai/minimax-mcp', 'minimax-mcp', 384961, 'https://github.com/minimax-ai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042279+00:00'),
  ('wordpress-code-review', 'WordPress Code Review', 'This MCP server provides WordPress-focused code review capabilities by fetching coding guidelines, validation rules, and security patterns from configurable web-hosted markdown files. Built by miniOrange''s internal development team using TypeScript with the Model Context Protocol SDK, it offers tools for validating PHP and JavaScript code against WordPress best practices, performing security vulnerability scans for common issues like SQL injection and XSS, and accessing customizable coding standards through a flexible URL-based guideline system. The implementation uses a factory pattern designed for extensibility to future sources like Confluence or GitHub, parses markdown-formatted rules with configurable severity levels, and includes comprehensive security checks for dangerous functions, input validation, and WordPress-specific vulnerabilities, making it valuable for development teams maintaining WordPress plugins or themes who need automated code quality enforcement and security validation integrated into their AI-assisted development workflow.', '@miniorangedev', 'databases', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/miniorangedev/wp-code-review-mcp-server', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/miniorangedev.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042292+00:00'),
  ('claude-prompts', 'Claude Prompts', 'Claude Custom Prompts MCP Server provides a flexible, template-based prompt system for Claude AI models. Built with TypeScript and Node.js, it allows users to define and manage custom prompts in markdown format organized by categories, with support for both simple prompts and multi-step prompt chains. The server includes a comprehensive API for prompt management, execution via STDIO or SSE transports, and features like conversation history tracking and error handling. Particularly valuable for users who need to standardize interactions with Claude across different use cases, it enables complex reasoning workflows through its chain execution capabilities while maintaining a modular, extensible architecture.', '@minipuft', 'development', 'Unknown', 141, 'https://github.com/minipuft/claude-prompts', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/minipuft.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042323+00:00'),
  ('io-github-tk26-minoa', 'io.github.tk26/minoa', 'Automate business cases, articulate customer outcomes & analyze your value-selling motion with Minoa', '@unknown', 'development', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://us-central1-minoa-roi-firebase.cloudfunctions.net/endpoints-mcp', NULL, 0, NULL, '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042338+00:00'),
  ('io-github-h1-hunt-mintclub', 'io.github.h1-hunt/mintclub', 'Trade bonding curve tokens on Base via Mint Club V2 — buy, sell, swap, create', '@steemhunt', 'development', 'Unknown', 4, 'https://github.com/steemhunt/mint.club-v2-ai', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/steemhunt.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042354+00:00'),
  ('mintline', 'Mintline', 'Provides access to Mintline''s receipt and transaction management platform. Enables searching and viewing receipts, reviewing and confirming transaction-receipt matches, analyzing spending by vendor and time period, and automating expense management workflows. Tools are loaded dynamically from the Mintline API.', '@mintlineai', 'search', 'Unknown', 0, 'https://github.com/mintlineai/mintline-mcp', NULL, 0, 'https://github.com/mintlineai.png?size=128', '2026-03-09T05:21:02.042387+00:00');
